@1000313 = ~I do not want to die... please have mercy!~ []
@1000318 = ~It's so bright!~ []
@1000337 = ~I have stated my wishes, now get lost!~ []
@1000338 = ~Very well. He said roughly thirty trolls and snake creatures, and that Lord de'Arnise was alive.~ []
@1000341 = ~He is alive? Wonderful! Lord de'Arnise is my father, and much preferable to Aunty. Quickly, we must rout these creatures while father is still there to save!~ []
@1000343 = ~I fear he said very little. Daleson is... dead. A tragic, tragic casualty.~
@1000353 = ~He was... a traitor. Yeah, that's it. He conspired... with the trolls and caused all this carnage. Yeah.~
@1000354 = ~It was... dreadful. He was a traitor. He did say Lord de'Arnise was alive, but can we trust his word? He was but a poor peasant, pity him.~ []
@1000356 = ~You... are worse than any noble! He was not worthless! He was pitiable, but he had every right to exist! Get out! I will not have you in my home! Get out!~
@1000358 = ~I see. I suppose... he could not refuse. I... pity his weakness. There... is much left to do. You must still find my father. He will have defended this place to the last.~
@1000375 = ~I killed him, plain and simple.~ []
@1000376 = ~He was... a traitor. Yeah, he had conspired with... the trolls. He did say Lord de'Arnise was still alive, but maybe he was lying. Yeah.~ []
@1000377 = ~He conspired to help the trolls. He did say Lord de'Arnise was still alive, but I don't know if I trust his word. He was but a poor peasant. Pity him.~
@1000380 = ~Trolls are large, so bigger rooms may be full. Be careful. Strange... trolls are destructive, but much has been left intact. Maybe I'm wrong. I've been wrong before.~ []
@1000385 = ~I... I don't know what to say. I think you are lying. You do not have the presence to lie well. Get away from me. I will die on my own rather than have you in my home.~
@1000386 = ~I will honor him, I swear! Help me avenge him and rescue my father, Lord de'Arnise. He will give you the reward you deserve for your actions.~
@1000426 = ~Aerie, dear, I see that you begin to become more confident in this world... which is undoubtedly quite strange to you.  You are learning what it's like to live and thrive here.~ [MAZZY51]
@1000468 = ~Are you interested in purchasing a bit o' merchandise, my friend?~ [JANJAN01]
@1000471 = ~What I'm getting at, o-so-friendly one, is that I've items to sell you that are especially created, by yours truly, to aid one on the dangerous path to heroism. They're known as Jan Jansen's (that's me) Flasher Master Bruiser Mates.~
@1000472 = ~Argh, not again. That bottom-feeding, turnip-hating, scum-sucking brigand! Nothing better to do than stop an honest businessman from selling high quality illegal Flashers for a reasonable price. Here he comes, cover for me.~
@1000524 = ~Curses! The gnome has gotten to you, too! Jansen, you can no longer peddle in Athkatla. As for you, <CHARNAME>, you have made a dangerous enemy.~
@1000572 = ~You associate with this... stable boy? What can he offer a woman of your standing?~
@1000573 = ~Go to the stables often, do you? I take it you prefer the company of... common men?~
@1000614 = ~M-my apologies, Miss Nalia, I... I meant nothing.~ []
@1000619 = ~Magical slings are the hallmark of stout halfling warriors.  Usually their mothers or a talented aunt will create such a sling for the halfling lad or lass who is about to embark on their second great adventure.  The reason that the sling is given on the second adventure and not the first is that many halflings decide not to pursue the life of an adventurer after getting a taste of it.

