@1002348 = ~Consisting of a cleaver-like axe blade mounted on a staff averaging six feet in length, the halberd is the oldest and most often used polearm. It is best described as a cross between a spear and an axe. Magic has been used to forge this particular weapon, gifting it with enhanced abilities to slaughter foes.

