@1002497 = ~The Underdark I left a lifetime ago. Ye blackskins are all the same; good fer three things... owning, hunting and killing.~ []
@1002498 = ~I hate Amn. I hate the heat, the squalor, the desperation. Everyone has the silver-tongue here. I hate the stagnant, lant-tepid brew... Oh! Friends! Ye'd hear me tale then?~ [KORGAN73]
@1002502 = ~We'll join you on one condition... you pay us.~ []
@1002509 = ~I were sorely mistaken to think I'd find heroes amongst yer sorry lot. No pay, only rewards. I'll be herein should ye change that greedhead mind.~ []
@1002524 = ~Reconsider! I will rage as never before, and those in my path will fall left, right and 'round the back! Dynaheir is... she is dead, and I will not rest...~ []
@1002536 = ~We've grown weary of this escapade. We've decided not to go to the tomb.~ []
@1002541 = ~Hold on, Korgan. Wait a moment. Let's go to the tomb right now.~ []
@1002544 = ~My Tabitha... loyal to the end. Your death I shall avenge, on that I swear.~ []
@1002545 = ~Ahh, I see you still have that... rodent. Dare I ask how you have kept it hidden from our captors?~ []
@1002546 = ~Are you talking to a... hamster? What kind of a warrior are you?~ []
@1002548 = ~Ahh, I see you still have that... rodent. Dare I ask how you have kept it hidden from our captors?~ []
@1002549 = ~Are you talking to a... hamster? What kind of a warrior are you?~ []
@1002551 = ~Stop your pitiful whining, dwarf, and waddle aside.~ []
@1002554 = ~Good company, great risk, and... treasure. Perhaps more than you could imagine.~ []
@1002555 = ~Whoa, I've changed my mind. Why don't you go on ahead without me and I'll, uh... catch up with you later. Yeah...~ []
@1002558 = ~Why don't you just head off on your own and we'll meet up again... later. Yeah.~ []
@1002571 = ~Speak of the undersized broadarse and what should waddle in? I was just remarkin' ta Crazyface and Scrooloose that shame it all no dwarf tossin' til next moonsday. Shame it is.~ []
@1002580 = ~Uncle Quayle! Haer'Dalis and I thought it would be nice to come back and visit you. He--He's giving me acting lessons.~ []
@1002581 = ~Haer'Dalis, is it? And acting lessons? Oh, my little Aerie, you have surrounded yourself with such wonderful friends... or is he more than a friend?~ []
@1002593 = ~Time passes, the people walk by... but at least I've been able to stay here at the circus. Take care, <GABBER>...~ []
@1002595 = ~I--I never should have let you take me from the circus! You're all heartless, every last one of you!~ [AERIEC4]
@1002618 = ~Alright, Aerie... but be careful out there.~ []
@1002626 = ~Love... justice... the rights of people to choose their own destiny in this world.~ []
@1002638 = ~Look, Anomen, the sun is rising...~ [AERIE49]
@1002643 = ~Ha, I do not have the time to be frightened. And besides... the Order cannot turn me aside forever.~ []
@1002655 = ~Anomen... I... I've been watching you since you failed your Test, and... you... you're starting to scare me a little, I think...~ [AERIE50]
@1002657 = ~Just because you failed your Test doesn't mean you have to abandon everything good about the Order, does it? I mean... you were almost a paladin!~ []
@1002658 = ~That's just it, isn't it? I was almost a paladin, I was almost strong enough. Well, almost isn't good enough, Aerie... so no, it doesn't mean a thing. Not anymore.~ []
@1002681 = ~Ahh, what the hell. Right-o, Minsc! Our deeds will ring in the evil ears we box and label 'Do not open 'til mid-winter fest'!~ []
@1002684 = ~These acts will place our names in the songs of skalds and bards from here to my home, there can be no doubt!~ [MINSC80]
@1002689 = ~When making a glorious egg-dish of goodness I understand some eggs must be broken, but actions such as this are... simply deplorable!~ [MINSC82]
@1002696 = ~I, uh... I could use a bit of a lie down, lest I drop Boo on the battlefield. Have we a healer near?~ [MINSC83]
@1002716 = ~So there is sanity in all this madness. If you are not in league with the evil that dwells in this unholy place, Yoshimo begs your assistance.~ [YOSHIM01]
@1002726 = ~I had four husbands during my life in the Underdark... before the fall of House DeVir. I killed each one. Three for sport and one for infidelity with my sister.~ []
@1002734 = ~I do not know how long I was there before awakening.~ []
@1002760 = ~My faith is my home and... and by the will of Torm, I take it with me where I go...~ []
@1002778 = ~Follow me closely inside as well. I fancy there no be a more dangerous a building in all o' Baldur's Gate. Can you think o' anywhere better equipped against thieves, than the thieves' guild itself? Could teach Durlag's Tower a thing or three, I dare say.~ []
@1002783 = ~The barkeep's name is Bernard. He will sell you high quality equipment at a reasonable price. If you have the time, though, I would suggest the Adventure Mart in the promenade.~ []
@1002872 = ~You see those tiny mushrooms hidden away, there... and how they glow? They are of the foxfire family and are the material component for the 'faerie fire' spell.~ [CERND50]
@1002900 = ~Move carefully now... do you see that large red flower? It is a Dead Man's Lotus and shall put you right to sleep should you disturb its pollen.~ [CERND52]
@1002908 = ~I cannot understand it, Aerie. Why this magic... why from you, of all people? You are too innocent and good to practice such things.~ [VALYGA46]
@1002911 = ~... I hope you're right, Aerie. For your sake and mine...~ []
@1002917 = ~Quit yer whinin', wench. So you be tired, we care not. Sleep when death takes hold o' ye, which would be a welcome respite for the rest of us... god knows!~ [KORGAN61]
@1002921 = ~Ha ha! Looka' the sky, missy. Yer day's up and I'm still 'ere. Ol' <CHARNAME> didn't e'en break it to ya gently. Take the hint and head back to yer little circus, girlie.~ [KORGAN62]
@1002941 = ~You mustn't let yourself get so wounded, Aerie. I won't always be here to bandage you, you know.~ [JAHEIR44]
@1002953 = ~I--I don't know what you're after, drow. Just--just stay away from me.~ [AERIE44]
@1002957 = ~Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills

A forest spirit named Mairyn has implored me to aid her against humans who are tearing down her forest in the west, in the area where the Shadow altar once was. She says the humans will not listen to her and I have agreed to go and do what I can to help.~ []
@1002972 = ~Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills

Delon of Imnesvale came and told me of a group of orcs that seems to have come down from the hills and attacked the village. I have other things to do, so the boy left. If I change my mind, I should go to the village within three days or it will be too late.~ []
@1002973 = ~Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills

I managed to fight off the orcs and rescue Madulf the ogre, who had taken shelter in the nearby cave after his fellows were driven off.~ []
@1002974 = ~Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills

I cam to the village and saved it from attack by a clan of orcs that had come down from the mountains. Madulf the ogre, it seems, protected the village despite not having an alliance. The mayor was surprised and is going to speak to the ogre about the possibility, now.~ []
@1002991 = ~Ahhh, Mazzy, the sweetest flowers always resist the plucking. The fire doth burn most brightly in ye fer ol' Korgan... I can see that plain as day.~ []
@1003012 = ~Only if it will cease your fawning. Stand still and I'll work that kink from your neck... but if you breach the rules of chivalry I'll wring it while I'm there.~ []
@1003014 = ~Aye... carved this one on the wall of the lav at the Red Sheaf Inn, reckon it still causes an uproar each time a bowler uncoils his business.~ []
@1003023 = ~This wand was created for you by your apprentices, and will randomly cast a variety of three spells, each from a separate elemental source. It apparently has 50 charges.

Requires: 9 Intelligence
Usable By:
 Mage
 Bard~ []
@1003024 = ~Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills

The mayor of Imnesvale told me that Umar, or whoever is claiming to be her, has set up in the Shadow Portal dungeon to the west and threatens to destroy the village unless the inhabitants leave.~ []
@1003031 = ~Ruling the de'Arnise Keep and Lands

A runner has come to me, stating that I must return to the de'Arnise keep as soon as possible... no more than a week... as Lord Farthington Roenall, the head of the family that wished to take Nalia's family's keep, desires to see me.~ []
@1003043 = ~This short sword was forged by hands both magical and highly skilled. Neither nick nor stain mar the flawless blade. When used in battle, the blade radiates magic and gifts the wielder with increased skill.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2 bonus
Damage: 1D6 + 2
Damage type: piercing
Speed Factor: 1
Weight: 2
Proficiency Type: Short Sword
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 5 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Cleric 
 Mage
 Beast Master~ []
@1003058 = ~Longlimbs! Look at them! Like grubworms scurryin' away from the light o' day. All avoidin' pain, on the prowl fer pleasure. Nay facin' uncertain futures. Best all dead, I reckon.~ [KORGAN63]
@1003059 = ~I did nay know ye were within earshot, girl. 'Twas a wee pondering, nothin' more. I enjoy making fun of the big folk.~ []
@1003068 = ~If there be more of ye out skulking in the shadows, then show yerselves! I have to have some fun... I cannae go about tough and unfeeling all the time!~ []
@1003109 = ~True... there are not so many buildings to obstruct the view.~ []
@1003151 = ~Minsc has had the pleasure of standing next to many a warrior in battle, but I swear I have never been as impressed as I am with you, Mazzy.~ [MINSC51]
@1003159 = ~I could not be more so! Don't look for subtle messages, I keep nothing hidden. I help the weak and leave evil in my boot print. You are similar... Boo can tell.~ []
@1003171 = ~NOOOOO!!! Such a vile act will not go unpunished! Minsc will see this paladin's heart avenged! And Boo shall burrow through your black little souls!~ [MINSC54]
@1003172 = ~Mazzy! You walk with the living once more! Minsc was so scar... uh... well... Boo! Boo was so scared you were lost to us, but miracles have brought you back!~ []
@1003173 = ~Stand easy, Minsc, all is well. Though I am a bit... woozy. Praise The Defender, I have been brought back.~ []
@1003175 = ~Of course, brave little one. See, Boo, she is well and as she was. You were foolish to have been worried. Yes... you were.~ []
@1003179 = ~Ahh... this land is fine, but I wish I could show Boo the fields of Rashemen. We could run free through the snow, though Boo would look some kind of funny in a drift, I tell you this... ha ha!~ [MINSC66]
@1003188 = ~My sword, my soul, my hamster... all of these I pledge to... to Aerie, my witch... HEAR THAT, EVIL?! MINSC HAS A NEW WITCH!! WOE IS YOU!!~ []
@1003190 = ~You are okay, Aerie? ... Boo tried his best to save you.~ [MINSC55]
@1003196 = ~All will fall before the might of Minsc and Boo! Evil all about! All will FFWRRAAAGHHHGHG!!!~ [MINSC56]
@1003202 = ~I will... I... Keldorn?~ []
@1003207 = ~Raaagh! Ra... Minsc... Minsc is... better now. Boo calms as we speak. Thank you, paladin.~ []
@1003212 = ~Who wants a piece of Minsc?! Who!? Evil will die here! Enemies everywhere!~ [MINSC58]
@1003214 = ~Friends... my friends...~ []
@1003215 = ~You don't have to trade a city for it... I want to smile and--and you make it so easy, Haer'Dalis.~ []
@1003217 = ~Minsc calms... you are right... Thank you, Keldorn. You are... an inspiration to me.~ []
@1003220 = ~Please... it is so dark and late, and I am so tired... Is there no chance that we might stop and rest for a while?~ [AERIEB4]
@1003226 = ~It's just a little dark, Aerie... there's nothing to be afraid of.~ []
@1003230 = ~I--I'm not scared... I'm only tired, and maybe a little unused to traveling so late at night. N-never mind... I'll be fine...~ []
@1003231 = ~Alright but don't take long... You may think me silly, but I... I am just unused to traveling so late at night...~ []
@1003232 = ~Thank you... I... I'll try not to be such a bother. I'm just... unused to traveling in such darkness...~ []
@1003233 = ~I--I'm sorry, I just have a... a bad feeling...~ []
@1003235 = ~Yet more scars that show Minsc's prowess in battle! All great warriors wear such marks. Keldorn, you must have a great many scars that are your medals of combat! Do you wear them proudly, as Minsc does?~ [MINSC60]
@1003241 = ~Oh, your legacy did not die! You are with us again! Oh, Boo is positively vibrating with happiness! Minsc will not let such evil claim you again!~ [MINSC62]
@1003246 = ~Flame of the North +2~
@1003247 = ~Minsc... Minsc breathes! Boo, where is Boo? Oh... there you are, you did not leave me. A miracle is this!~ [MINSC63]
@1003251 = ~Oh... it-it's so hard to describe. It's the ultimate freedom, to soar above the clouds and become part of the wind, itself.~ []
@1003255 = ~I remember I used to be so happy. The clouds are a special place up there, <CHARNAME>... it's like a land of billowing white beauty that you can almost walk upon.~ []
@1003256 = ~Harbinger +3~ []
@1003257 = ~But I suppose that place is forever denied to me, now. It... it just feels so slow and mundane to walk everywhere. I don't know how you can stand it.~ []
@1003258 = ~You get used to it... there's plenty of beauty on the ground, as well.~ []
@1003262 = ~Oh, y-yes, I know... I meant no offense to you. I just remember what it was like... to effortlessly soar through the clouds like the birds overhead. To be truly free.~ []
@1003266 = ~I-I'm sorry, <CHARNAME>... I didn't mean to bother you. I'll talk to somebody else, instead.~ []
@1003268 = ~Is there? All I can think of is how majestic something might look from up high. I'm sorry... you would think by now I would know better than to dwell upon it. Excuse me.~ []
@1003271 = ~Maybe not for you, but for me it is very different. I was born to fly. But I should not dwell on it so... you would think after all this time I had learned better. Excuse me, please...~ []
@1003272 = ~I... I have been trying for many years to get used to it, <CHARNAME>. It is not an easy thing, for one born to the skies. But... but you are right, of course. Excuse me.~ []
@1003273 = ~Have you... have you ever heard of my people? The Avariel?~ [AERIE89]
@1003278 = ~My own people live high in the mountains to the far south, in a place called Faenya-Dail, separated from contact with others. It is... was... a grand and majestic place.~ []
@1003284 = ~Oh... of course, <CHARNAME>. I didn't mean to bother you.~ []
@1003285 = ~Our... our homes were open places of marble pillars and vistas from which you could watch the entire mountain range below. There was no place you could not spread your wings...~ []
@1003286 = ~We cherished the wind and the rains... we breathed in life, <CHARNAME>, and lived in peace with each other.~ []
@1003288 = ~There were distinct societies among us, as I remember. There were... great aerial warriors who defended us, possessing glass weapons that radiated in the sunlight...~ []
@1003289 = ~And my own class pursued art and knowledge, building the great buildings and filling them with glorious wonders. It... it was...~ []
@1003290 = ~... I am sorry, <CHARNAME>, I can speak of it no longer. I think of my lost home and I am reminded of my poor uncle Quayle. It... it simply wrenches my heart...~ []
@1003291 = ~... I am sorry, <CHARNAME>, I can speak of it no longer. I am suddenly homesick, as silly as that seems. I miss... so much, it makes me ache. I suppose I must seem very foolish to you.~ []
@1003292 = ~I... I must seem very foolish to you, I suppose. I will not bother you again, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1003293 = ~I... everyone here seems too unhappy and severe... I am so unused to living this way. In the circus, we always were cheerful. Or, at least, Uncle Quayle was determined to be.~ [AERIE90]
@1003298 = ~You are not as serious as many Druids I have met, Cernd. Some even disapprove of me because I am... I am... I'd... hmm... I don't really know why. Boo will not tell me either.~ [MINSC69]
@1003309 = ~To play with a party entirely created by you simply start a multiplayer session and assign control of all characters to yourself.~ []
@1003310 = ~Under the Gameplay section of the Options page, you can turn on the option to rest until healed.~ []
@1003311 = ~You now have the ability to customize your Biography. Go to the Records Page and choose Customize, then Biography.~ []
@1003312 = ~If you prefer to play the game in Turn-Based Style, go to the Auto-pause section of the Gameplay Options.~ []
@1003313 = ~I... I have been looking at the scars... on my back. The stumps that were... that were once my wings. They do not... they do not make me truly homely, do they? Am I... am I ugly to you?~ [AERIE91]
@1003321 = ~R-really? You are... very kind to say so, <CHARNAME>. I... I suppose I am too proud, that I miss my white wings so.~ []
@1003323 = ~When I was first enslaved, I was kept in a small cage and put on display. I had no room to stand, much less stretch my wings. I... I tried to warn my captor, I pleaded to him...~ []
@1003324 = ~... But my wings withered and became bloody and diseased. Until, finally, he was forced to... to... saw them off. It was... it was so painful and horrid!~ []
@1003325 = ~I've felt like a great part of me has been missing ever since. I am incomplete. I... do not feel beautiful, <CHARNAME>. Not anymore.~ []
@1003327 = ~Vanity? I... I suppose it is. That and my silly pride. I... I'll not bother you with such nonsense again, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1003328 = ~Don't be so hard on yourself, Aerie... like I said, you're still a beautiful elf.~ []
@1003331 = ~You... you make me blush with such comments. It makes me wonder if you are sincere, <CHARNAME>... but I thank you nonetheless.~ []
@1003332 = ~It is... very hard for me. But I shall try to think as you say... and I thank you for your kind words.~ []
@1003337 = ~No... but I have no time to hear the story now.~ []
@1003338 = ~It was... my fault, really. I was away from Faenya-Dail, flying just for the glory of it. I... spotted a large group of armed men assaulting some humans on the ground below.~ []
@1003340 = ~I was distraught. My mother had always warned me to be wary of outsiders... but I did not heed her warnings this time. I flew down to aid the child, swooping to carry him away.~ []
@1003341 = ~The child was surprised and frightened, and his struggles slowed me... enough so that a slaver struck me with an arrow. I plummeted to the ground and was knocked unconscious.~ []
@1003342 = ~When I awoke... I was in my cage. I was the prize of the slavers... to be sold to the highest bidder. They were pleased to sell me to the circus for a great amount of gold...~ []
@1003343 = ~I... I suppose... I suppose I was glad to learn that the child escaped, after all. He ran away after my fall. Hopefully, he survived...~ []
@1003347 = ~Yes... I suppose now is not the time for talk. Forgive me.~ []
@1003348 = ~It is, though... it was foolish of me to disregard my teachings. And I have paid for it dearly. I was bereft of my home... and then my wings, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1003352 = ~Doom (Alteration) 
Level: 1
Sphere: Charm
Range: Visual range of caster
Duration: 1 turn 
Casting Time: 1 round 
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None 

This spell causes a feeling of doom to overwhelm the target. For the duration of the spell, the target receives a -2 penalty to all dice rolls, including THAC0 and saving throws. There is no saving throw for this spell. Multiple castings of Doom are not cumulative.~ []
@1003419 = ~My comrades... fallen... my last breaths are of rage.~ []
@1003475 = ~Why must we emulate the ways of the dwarven folk by crawling about these warrens?~ [KIVAN14]
@1003487 = ~Blessed Bolt +1~
@1003491 = ~This is a crossbow bolt that has been permanently enchanted with the spell 'Bless'. The enchantment will remain until it is fired out of a crossbow, at which time the magic will fade. Legend has it that if a Rakshasa is struck with this bolt, it will die instantly.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1D8 + 1
THAC0: +1 bonus
Damage type: missile (piercing)
Weight: 0
Launcher: Crossbow~ []
@1003537 = ~ You are a man of honor. I respect your integrity.~ [AJANT36]
@1003586 = ~There is nothing to calm my anger now... my business is ruined. My failure ends with my death.~ []
@1003622 = ~ No... it cannot end like this... I shall not allow it!~ [VICONI15]
@1003623 = ~ I am still unused to all this green and fragrant brightness... part of me yet looks for the hidden spider's web amongst all this.~ [VICONI16]
@1003624 = ~ Ahhh, this light... still it burns me!~ [VICONI19]
@1003630 = ~ Trust is for the foolish... and the dead.~ [VICONI27]
@1003643 = ~ I am... flattered, thank you.~ [VICON33]
@1003853 = ~ You have the most beautiful... er... eyes.~ [CORAN37]
@1003910 = ~ Let's go shopping!~ [SKIEE25]
@1003971 = ~ No, I do not feel this is working out. You waste opportunity after opportunity. I will stand no more.~ [EDWIN06]
@1003977 = ~ What is it now?!~ [EDWIN22]
@1004013 = ~ I... I cannot believe the change in this group! For the greater balance I must... I must oppose you!~ [JAHEIR06]
@1004040 = ~ You are amusing, in a "what the hell is wrong with you" kind of way.~ [JAHER35]
@1004071 = ~ Please J-Jaheira, you needn't be so... s-so...~ [KHALD27]
@1004083 = ~ Jah... Jaheira. No. NO!~ [KHALD41]
@1004110 = ~ Lay a finger on what I protect and forevermore ye will answer nature's call with a hook!~ []
@1004177 = ~ I am so smart!  S  M  R  T!  I mean S  M  A  R  T!~ [QUAYL23]
@1004251 = ~ The trees... move. Do you not see it?!~ [XZARR12]
@1004329 = ~ Please sirs, I'm sorry for what I've done, but a girl's gotta eat you know.~ []
@1004401 = ~This is the cloak that Bodhi has asked you to plant, along with a dagger, in Vulova's home to frame the Shadow Thieves for his murder.

Not Usable By:
