@1014868 = ~Well, I have no doubt in my mind that the wizard is a criminal to begin with. Do you know who he is?~ []
@1014888 = ~We are here to do no harm. That wizard who was taken away... do you know who he is?~ []
@1014905 = ~Candlekeep~ []
@1014924 = ~Nalia Abducted By Isaea Roenall

I brought the evidence I had before Isaea's commander, Corgeig, but it is not enough to warrant an investigation in the man's eyes. I will need to collect more before he will listen to me.~ []
@1014961 = ~(sniffle)  I... I... I just want my momma...~ []
@1014980 = ~Such a... lovely specimen of the elven race you have there. Might she be available, hm?~ []
@1014996 = ~Let me see. You are one of that troupe I was brought to recently. Quite good... for local entertainment, anyway.~ []
@1015008 = ~Why, hello there. My, that's quite the rugged friend you have, there. I could always use a new, um... gardener, mmmm?~ []
@1015014 = ~Errr... ahem! I am, uh... sorry my Lady. Gardening is... not my specialty.~ []
@1015040 = ~(grrr)  I am a virtuous follower of Arvoreen. He will reward me for my patience. (sigh)~ []
@1015044 = ~Be giving me a few minutes, longlimb wench, and this rockrunt'll ravish ye til ye're visited by furoles and 'ave a baker's leg!~ []
@1015050 = ~Ah, good day to you. I am Lord Dermod Ophal, and this is my wife, Lady Shareen. We... we have... we... hmmm. (What do you think, my dear?)~ []
@1015063 = ~I am a relative of one of the great families. You are obviously too common for me to address, much less converse with.~ []
@1015099 = ~I've heard that people have seen strange things around here... people being led about in chains. What can you tell me about that?~ []
@1015107 = ~It's none of yer business. Be off with ye.~ []
@1015108 = ~Ye should pay no heed to th' queer minds o' others, an' pay more heed to yer business... an' yer health, fer that matter.~ []
@1015114 = ~I've heard that people have seen strange things around here... people being led about in chains. What can you tell me about that?~ []
@1015129 = ~I've heard that people have seen strange things around here... people being led about in chains. What can you tell me about that?~ []
@1015170 = ~Aye, now, friend... does I knows ye?~ []
@1015173 = ~Ah... er... pardon me for a moment whilst my head implodes.~ []
@1015181 = ~Conjure Earth Elemental (Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 7
Sphere: Elemental, Summoning 
Range: Visual sight of caster 
Duration: 1 turn/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

Upon casting a conjure earth elemental spell, the caster opens a special gate to the elemental plane of Earth, and an earth elemental is summoned to the vicinity of the spellcaster. It is 60% likely that a 12 hit dice elemental appears, 35% likely that a 16 hit dice elemental appears, and 5% likely that a 24 hit dice elemental appears. All of the commands given to the elemental are done telepathically, so there is no time lost due to miscommunication, and it is not necessary to know the language of the summoned creature. Priests do not have to engage in a battle of the wits to control their summoned elemental (unlike mages). The elemental will remain under the caster's control until slain or until the spell duration expires.~
