Sphere: Elemental, Summoning 
Range: Visual sight of caster 
Duration: 1 turn/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

Upon casting a conjure fire elemental spell, the caster opens a special gate to the elemental plane of Fire, and a fire elemental is summoned to the vicinity of the spellcaster. It is 60% likely that a 12 hit dice elemental appears, 35% likely that a 16 hit dice elemental appears, and 5% likely that a 24 hit dice elemental appears. The elemental will do the bidding of the caster until it is slain, or the duration of the spell runs out. All of the commands given to the elemental are done telepathically so there is no time lost due to miscommunication, and no need to know the language of the summoned creature. Unlike the mage elemental conjuring spells, priests do not have to engage in a battle of the minds to control their elemental.~
@1015220 = ~ These trees and glades hide horrors of all manner... watch your backs!~ [ANOMEN17]
@1015225 = ~Ah... 'tis a fine enough day to travel. Many a battle has been fought on a day just such as this.~ [ANOMEN20]
@1015242 = ~~ [ANOMEN29]
@1015264 = ~Ah, yer a cheapshkate if I ever sheen one. (burp) Gah.~
@1015284 = ~Err, oh, aye. Mayhapsh ye should be ashkin' Lehtinan for yourshelf, if 'at's whatsh ye be wantin'. (burp) I 'ave little enough coin, myshelf, to 'ave ever indulged.~
@1015319 = ~Mmmm, I saw you playing the other day. Perhaps you would... like to sit down for a while with me?~ []
@1015322 = ~A... tempting offer, my dear. Perhaps another time.~ []
@1015390 = ~I truly hope you will be able to. The beastmaster has the key to our cells... he stays in the pit, in an area across from this hall. With the key, we can escape!~ []
@1015401 = ~(YAWN)... I'm... I live to see the earth mother's dawn once more? Then... then you have succeeded. Excellent. And Ployer? What of him?~ []
@1015406 = ~Dead and gone.~ []
@1015408 = ~I have you to thank, I assume. Of course I do. You have proven quite the friend. Shall we... continue our adventures? I believe I am fit for travel.~ []
@1015421 = ~Good. We shall leave immediately.~ []
@1015424 = ~Let's go then. There is much left to see.~ []
@1015461 = ~I am not impressed by fighting slaves. But I would CRUSH any true opponent who dared to face me!~ []
@1015463 = ~Ah, you're an entertainer, are you not? Are you here to provide music for the fights?~ []
@1015464 = ~I am not, sire. Rather, I am hear to witness the depravity and baselessness of your society as it inevitably leads itself to decay and destruction. Please... do continue.~ []
@1015480 = ~Ha ha ha! You amuse me, little mortal. Bluster as you wish, I shall not allow you to pass until you have solved my puzzle.~ []
@1015497 = ~Wrong! Ha ha! The prince, I am afraid, is 30 years old. The princess is most assuredly 40. Being a benevolent sort I shall give you one more riddle!~ []
@1015508 = ~There you are! I... I missed you while I was gone. I mean... well, I am glad to see you. I must tell you, however, that we must go to the Harper Hold in Athkatla.~ [JAHEIRE2]
@1015544 = ~You are an adventurer, my <LADYLORD>, no? You might find others of your ilk at the Copper Coronet in the slums.~ []
@1015546 = ~The Shadow Thieves? I know little <LADYLORD>, and consider myself up a pearl for the lack. All the crime in the city can be attributed to them.~ []
@1015693 = ~The hunt for Valygar is over.

I tried to tell the Cowled Wizard Tolgerias where Valygar could be found, but the wizard obviously had expected me to bring his body only. He has stormed off to look into the matter, refusing to reward me... I suspect I shall face repercussions from the Cowled Wizards, as well. I doubt I shall see Valygar again.~ []
@1015714 = ~The hunt for Valygar is over.

I have informed Tolgerias, a Cowled Wizard, of the location of Valygar here in the city. Despite the fact that I did not bring them the ranger's body, it was good enough for the wizard and I received my reward. He left immediately... likely to capture the ranger and use him for whatever purposes he had intended.~ []
@1015723 = ~Investigate the deaths in the Umar Hills.

I have encountered Madulf and his band. They have had their own string of deaths, and Madulf is almost as worried as the villagers are. He doesn't seem to present a threat, and even wanted me to arrange a peace between the village and his band... which, of course, I'm not going to do. He is still an ogre and cannot be trusted, but it is unlikely that his group is causing the deaths. Perhaps I should tell the mayor this.~ []
@1015731 = ~Helping Tiris in Trademeet

I spoke to Tiris and found out something startling... Rejiek, the murderer from the Bridge District in Athkatla whom I drove off, is now in Trademeet and apparently working with a strange, skinless creature. Tiris and his girlfriend, Raissa, were kidnapped and brought to the woods by the southwest gate, where Tiris was just barely able to escape. He begs that I find Raissa, and suggests that I look in the woods for any clues.~ []
@1015735 = ~Valygar's family quest is over.

Valygar's quest is finally done. Lavok was not what he expected, and has caused the normally judgmental ranger to think deeply about what he has experienced. With the necromancer dead and the Cowled Wizards no longer hunting him, Valygar has asked to continue traveling with me. I have accepted him back into the group.~ []
@1015739 = ~Valygar's family quest is over.

Valygar's quest is finally done. Lavok was not what he expected, and has caused the normally judgmental ranger to think deeply about what he has experienced. With the necromancer dead and the Cowled Wizards no longer hunting him, Valygar has asked to continue traveling with me. I have declined, and the ranger told me that he could be found at his home in the Docks District should I have need of him in the future.~ []
@1015743 = ~Idle hands in Imnesvale.

Well, I bought the three kids in Imnesvale what I promised them, and they've run off to enjoy it. Hopefully, they don't get into too much trouble... and here's to hoping their parents don't get wind of this.~ []
@1015760 = ~Getting Inside the Asylum

Captain Golin told me that I could get inside Spellhold by convincing a pirate named Desharik that I was insane... he could send me within Spellhold as a patient if he was cared to do so. Desharik can be found on the far west of the island... if I go there, Golin said to tell the doorman that he sent me.~ []
@1015783 = ~Getting Inside the Asylum

We have arrived on the island safely, and Bodhi has informed me that Saemon will be aiding as a guide of sorts, bringing me to someone who will help me get inside the asylum. As for Bodhi herself, she has left and said she will meet up with me afterwards.~ []
@1015803 = ~Helping Tiris in Trademeet

I went to the place Tiris described, but met only a man named Darsidian Moor who claimed to be hunting the skinless creature who is with Rejiek. He calls it a 'Skin Dancer' and believes the creature to be at a walled-off area of the town just north of the east gate, in an orange pavilion... and has left to confront it. He asks that I meet him there as soon as possible.~ []
@1015805 = ~Helping Tiris in Trademeet

The man I met at the woods, Darsidian Moor, inferred that the skinless creature may have captured Raissa to remove her skin and create another like himself... else it would have consumed her flesh on the spot. What the creature's connection to Rejiek might be, I have no idea.~ []
@1015809 = ~The prophecy of Sekolah

I have defeated the King's monster and he has ordered the opposing priestess sacrificed to Sekolah. I am now the 'chosen one', the King intends to have me kill the leader of a group of rebels outside of the city and return with his heart... for which he will reward me with great riches. I am to see High Priestess Senityili in her temple to get more information on how to reach the rebel encampment. Until then, I have the run of the city.~ []
@1015828 = ~Ziose is the name given by sages to a particular facet-grade variety of ziosite; a rare mineral that yields cut stones that flash three vivid hues depending on how the light catches them; purple, blue, and red, or purple, green, and red. Very large (fist- or foot-sized) gems are found and are prized for use in pendants and brooches.~ []
@1015854 = ~Gah! Must Arnolinus being disturbed at every opportunity?! What is it you being wanting?~ []
@1015865 = ~Ar, why ye nay be saying so when ye first coming?! Everyone always being wasting Arnolinus' time!~ []
@1015882 = ~You wanted to be an adventurer for as long as you can remember. Even as a small child , you knew there was a vast world beyond the simple life you witnessed around you every day. Traveling bards fanned the flames of your determination to escape your mundane existence with tales of dragons and monsters, wizards and knights, legendary heroes and infamous villains. And you knew then that one day your deeds.. your name.. would be known throughout the Realms.~ []
@1015917 = ~Party AI Off~ []
@1015943 = ~Ahhh, Maheer has all kinds to offer... scimitars, swords, even iron weapons from the Storm Horn Mountains!  Look at my wares for yourself!~ []
@1015959 = ~You are coming from Rashemen? I remember it fondly and hope to take Boo to see it once I have completed my dajemma.~ []
@1015962 = ~Oh... I, I see. I -- where was I? Ah, yes, my <LADYLORD>! You are, uh, still interested in examining my wares, yes?~ []
@1016000 = ~Giant spiders
'Spiders are aggressive predators, dwelling both above and below ground. Most are poisonous and bite prey first, because unconscious victims are easier to carry to a lair. 
'Spiders have eight legs and eight eyes. They usually fit into two categories: web-spinners, which have bulbous abdomens and thin, sleek legs; and hunting spiders, which have smaller bodies, larger heads and fangs, and hairy bodies and legs. 
'Most giant spiders are simply much bigger versions of the web-spinning large spiders.~ []
@1016003 = ~Errr... alright. Show me what you have in stock.~ []
@1016008 = ~Ah, gut! Ve be havink much fruit, yes? But you no be wantink fruit, I be sure! I show you vat else I be havink! Come! I show!~ []
@1016009 = ~Very well, show me everythink... er, I mean, show me what you have.~ []
@1016020 = ~I am renowned for my quality fletching, and as a fair bowyer as well. Dost thou care to peruse my inventory of fine missile weapons?~ []
@1016025 = ~This is not a spell but rather a druid's innate ability. It enables the druid to polymorph into a bear.~ []
@1016028 = ~Nalia's Father's Funeral

At the funeral, Nalia ran into the son of Lord Roenall, Isaea, who seems determined that Nalia live up to the betrothal that her father made for her... and quite angry at her continued refusal. There is more to his demands than meet the eye. No doubt this is not the last we've seen of him.~ []
@1016040 = ~Hail there! I said I would return, and I have. Sorry to have kept you waiting, but there were things I had to take care of. Now that we have met once again there is something I must ask of you. We must go... we must go to the Harper hold in Athkatla.~ [JAHEIRE3]
@1016095 = ~I... Yes, I see. If you would give me a moment I will do what needs be done.~ []
@1016097 = ~Relax, <CHARNAME>, I will not be gone long. Please, I will explain when I return. I... I do not wish to be apart from you too long. I will return when I can.~ []
@1016101 = ~Who is this wench, and why does she think she can split us up so easily? We've not the time for this.~ []
@1016121 = ~It is an odd time. (hurrrm)  Strangers can be... dangerous. If one is not careful. (hurrrm)  You wish something?~ []
@1016122 = ~(Hurmm). Coin is... always... welcome. You will find the Copper Coronet able to fulfill your needs, whether drink, rest, or other sorts... of entertainment. (hurrrm)~ []
@1016123 = ~You do not have to leave, stranger. (hurrm) Not yet. But if you wish to purchase something you must speak to Bernard. He... handles my transactions. (hurrm)~ []
@1016124 = ~Of course. (hurrm)  I would expect... nothing less.~ []
@1016138 = ~Ohh...(hurrm)... one is always able to provide entertainment. (hurrm) Things like companionship, perhaps, or gambling on battles, and other things.~ [LEHTIN08]
@1016142 = ~People come and go from the Coronet all the time. (hurrm) I have no need to acquire slaves. (hurrm) I trust that will be all, I have... other things to attend to.~ []
@1016145 = ~What sorts of... other things are you referring to? I'm interested.~ []
@1016148 = ~What sorts of... other things are you referring to? I'm interested.~ []
@1016150 = ~No one is disputing that, but I do have obligations outside the group. I will return when I am able.~ []
@1016152 = ~Go over to the fellow by the door on the far wall and tell him I said to let you in. Talk to Frankie or perhaps Madame Nin if you wish to... partake. And enjoy. (hurrm)~ []
@1016165 = ~Monster Summoning IV
(Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 6
Range: 40 yards 
Duration: 5 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None 
This spell is much like its 3rd level counterpart Monster Summoning I, except that this spell summons 6 HD monsters. There is a 60% chance of receiving one monster, and a 40% chance of receiving two monsters. These monster(s) appear within spell range and attack the caster's opponents until the spell duration expires, or until they are slain.~ []
@1016168 = ~(hurrrmm... hurrm)  Nay. I do not believe you. You stink of trouble. Begone.~ []
