@1016287 = ~A crossbow is a bow mounted crosswise on a wooden or metal shaft called a tiller. The bow is usually made of ash or yew. The crossbow fires a type of projectile known as a quarrel or bolt. Light crossbows not only weigh less than their heavier counterparts, but they fire faster as well. This light crossbow has been enchanted.

