This spell allows the caster to summon forth and control one or two massive mountain bears. The bears will respond to the caster's every whim for the duration of the spell. The bears' attacks are considered to be of +1 enchantment, and cause crushing damage.~ []
@1016373 = ~Yes, that's right. An adventurer and traveler. Now, be off with you. I've better things to attend to.~ []
@1016380 = ~Zircon is a brownish crystal found in igneous (volcanic) rocks. Zircon attains its pale blue shade with heating and cutting (usually facet-cut).~ []
@1016395 = ~Bah! There's no need to yell so loud, idjit! Fine, fine, I'll have th' bleedin' pit set up for ye... once I sees your gold, that is.~ []
@1016432 = ~Welcome! Restrict all fighting to the pits in the main bar. To my right is the entrance to the rooms of Madame Nin and the courtesans. To my left is the challenge pits... watch and gamble, as you wish.~ []
@1016434 = ~We should make our way to the Harper Hold in Athkatla as soon as we are able. I do not look forward to the trip any more than you do, but we must.~ []
@1016437 = ~If you are so eager to take me there, why have you not left my company?~ []
@1016438 = ~Why have you not left without me? Perhaps you value my company more than others?~ []
@1016446 = ~Um... perhaps I had best be on my way. Please excuse me.~ []
