@1016789 = ~We know of your treachery, Irenicus! Where have you taken our brethren?!~ [GAELEN36]
@1016802 = ~Child, you escape? I did not foresee this! I am not done with you! You.. you have angered me! Do you know what that takes!?~ [IRENIC08]
@1016841 = ~People have been saying lots of things. Some say it's creatures made by magic... others say it's just a big wolf pack huntin' in the hills.~ []
@1016896 = ~Fool! You'll never escape here alive! Come, Tabitha! Come... open the cages! Aid your master!~ []
@1016903 = ~Bah! I have had enough of your insolence! It is time to feed my Tabitha anyway! Come... open the cages... attack!!~ []
@1016907 = ~Insolent! Did I not tell you to leave?! Bah! It is time to feed my Tabitha, now, anyway. Come... open the cages... attack!~ []
@1016911 = ~That big ball appeared out o' nowhere a few weeks back! Me gramma's house used t' be there... I wonder if it's still inside.~ []
@1016912 = ~They should be burnin' up that big ball, they should! It's evil, I just knows it!~ []
@1016917 = ~It is meant to be a planar traveling device of some sort, or at least that's what Lavok's apprentice is reported to have said.~ []
@1016945 = ~Lavok was a wizard and merchant of great wealth. He built this planar sphere, but it disappeared three years after construction began, along with all his confidantes.~ []
@1016951 = ~Would that I could help you... may the Gods grant you speed and strength to aid your task!~ []
@1016954 = ~These people are being kept here against their will... forced to fight daily. Would you leave us here to die, knowing you could have done something?~ []
@1016955 = ~I myself have nothing to offer but gratitude, but when I take this inn, my gratitude may be worth more to you. I ask you again, then... will you free us?~ []
@1016983 = ~Music to me ears! There's a customer born every minute, and a rube soon after. What'll it be for ye today?~ []
@1016989 = ~Oh, hullo, can I help you? Actually... hmmmn... perhaps you can help me.~ []
@1017057 = ~Excellent news. Then I can stay and enjoy the ale of this marvelous place.~ []
@1017061 = ~No coaching, my dear, he will answer as he must. On to the next question then.~ []
@1017063 = ~As a child of Bhaal, have you... violent thoughts?~ []
@1017065 = ~Hey, bosses! Ye've th' look of peoples wit discrom... discrimer... uh, good tastes. Lookin' fer a bit o' dandies, undies, and exotic stuffs? Eh? Jayes ain't got all day, peoples.~ []
@1017067 = ~Tell me, Jayes, what would one be doing selling 'exotic' items in an alley? Would you, perchance, be dealing in less-than-legal merchandise?~ []
@1017073 = ~I'm having several right now. Really good ones too. You'd laugh if you could see them. Well, no, maybe YOU wouldn't.~ []
@1017075 = ~Hmm... must use violence. To be expected from one with such a despicable heritage.~ []
@1017088 = ~Wadda you want here? Ain't nothing here for public to see. We just take care of cleanin' the sewers and such.~ []
@1017092 = ~Never what? You are clouded by personal feelings. He may not think like us at all. Can you understand an illithid? Or a beholder? He is akin to these.~ []
@1017101 = ~Hmm... finds that violence is unavoidable. Certainly to be expected in a creature such as you.~ []
@1017169 = ~Wallag
  We travel this day to search out the wolf lair.  My own scouting of the region has confirmed Merella's suspicions that there is a large pack of wolves acting in this area.  On the map included I have indicated where I believe the wolf den to be located.  Follow us if you can, but be cautious. We can ill-afford another mysterious disappearance.  Until we meet again. 

Mazzy

(on the same sheet is drawn a crude but effective map which indicates the path to a forested area several hours west of the Imnesvale region.)~
@1017172 = ~You... who have so much power... would raise no hand to aid us? Damn you! May the abyss swallow your soul for what you do!~ []
@1017192 = ~~ []
@1017230 = ~The cursed girdle of gender, a rare yet oft-discussed magical item, is wrought with a most powerful magic. Anyone unfortunate enough to secure it around their waist instantly finds their gender to be transformed. It is said that, not fifty years past, a nameless court jester was beheaded for presenting the girdle as a gift to Duke Lobelahn's lover.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017240 = ~This simple cloak has been imbued with some small magical properties to help protect its wearer. It does so by augmenting its wearer's saving throws and armor class. It is ideal for mages and others who cannot wear bulkier or more restrictive types of armor.

