@1017659 = ~The body shield, also known as the kite or tower shield, is a massive wooden or metal shield extending from the chin to the toe of the user. It must be firmly fastened to the forearm, and the shield hand must firmly grip it at all times. Naturally, this precludes the use of the shield hand for anything but holding the body shield in place.

