@1017692 = ~Oh... oh! (sob!)  I'm free? Oh, thank you, <SIRMAAM>, thank you!~ []
@1017693 = ~(gasp)  My... my thanks to you, kind <SIRMAAM> for saving our lives. That monster surely would have killed us!~ []
@1017697 = ~Here, child. Here is 100 gold pieces... see if that can't get you and some of these other children back to where you came from.~ []
@1017700 = ~I'm, I'm not sure. I think one of them said that the merchant in Calimport didn't want us anymore. We were worthless, they said. I... I think they would have killed us all if you hadn't saved us!~ []
@1017705 = ~Indeed. You are free, now... go, while you can!~ []
@1017709 = ~When used, this wand emits a vapor bubble that travels towards the target area and then explodes into a deadly cloud of noxious gas that expands to fill an area roughly 15 feet in radius. The cloud will instantly kill any creature with 4 HD or less, with no saving throw allowed. Any creature having 5 to 6 HD must make a saving throw or be slain. Creatures with greater than 6 HD take 1-10 damage for every round that they remain within the cloud. The cloud will dissipate after 1 turn.

STATISTICS:

Effects: 1-10 damage per round
  1-4 HD: Instant death, no save allowed
  5-6 HD: Save vs. poison at -4 or instant death
Range: 60 ft.
Area: 15-foot radius
Duration: 1 turn
Requires: 9 Intelligence
Usable by:
 Mage
 Bard~ []
@1017713 = ~Good and done. We should make all speed to our destination.~ []
@1017714 = ~You have returned to my company, but I no longer know you. Tales of your deeds have spread before you... and the Harpers have kept certain tabs on you at all times. You will find no quarter here! Justice will take you!~ [JAHEIRE5]
@1017715 = ~I... I had hoped to see you again. I... that is, it is good to see you well. I have heard good things... for the most part at least. Shall we team once more? You and I both have much left to do.~ [JAHEIRH9]
@1017716 = ~I am glad to see you, Jaheira. I was hoping that you would... would consider traveling with me again.~ []
@1017725 = ~So it goes the sacred grimoire ne'er made it to our benefactor's hand. And now he awaits its arrival with a zeal reserved for a grog-blossom in an alekeg.~ []
@1017729 = ~Upon hearin' of a curious map, chart or book 'e's traveled countless leagues to obtain it, fearful of entrusting his commission to anyone else. This were his first outside hire.~ []
@1017733 = ~O bold warriors all... the sundial be turnin' on me appointed task, and I prevail upon ye all to hasten it.~ [KORGAN79]
@1017736 = ~Be wary of intruders... there may be a few of the lowlifes lingerin' about inside, stinkin' up the place.~ []
@1017737 = ~For... yes, for the sake of the group. We have friends to avenge and should get too it. Other... other things will wait. Yes, I will come with you.~ []
@1017749 = ~You must get our acorns back from Ilyich, the clan leader of Irenicus' duergar slaves. He is somewhere within the dungeon. Return to us when you have the acorns and we will tell you how to escape.~ []
@1017750 = ~It is about time you followed. Please, we should not keep them waiting any longer. The Harpers bid to me bring you here and expect me to do so. I will join the group once more and we will go inside.~ [JAHEIRE6]
@1017756 = ~At least I am no hypocrite, Anomen. There nay be a heart so holy that evil nay make a nest of black twigs in it.~ [KORGAN65]
@1017763 = ~Ye deserve the full wrath of my ire, weakling! Ye deserve it because ye're a coddled, privileged imbecile, a sad, little nobleman's offspring!~ []
@1017768 = ~Me mam were murdered. Nay by troll or giant, but by kindred, by one of me own. Pa had ta cut me from her while she heaved her death rattle.~ []
@1017770 = ~You must get our acorns back from Ilyich, the clan leader of Irenicus' duergar slaves. He is somewhere within the dungeon. Return to us when you have the acorns and we will tell you how to escape.~ []
@1017780 = ~Then I will not see them.~ []
@1017791 = ~Studded Leather of Missile Attraction +2~
@1017792 = ~As you wish. If you change your mind, I would still like to travel with you... I still think I have much to see in this world. I will return to my cabin in the hills, for now.~ [VALYGA88]
@1017794 = ~I see. I cannot defeat Lavok on my own. I do not know how I am to get home, but look for me there if you wish to have me back. I will be at my cabin in the hills.~ [VALYGA89]
@1017795 = ~What is this?! Reviane! What are you doing here? It is I, Jaheira!~ [JAHEIR96]
@1017809 = ~This seems far-fetched, Jaheira. You are well known to have hated Galvarey... and why should this <PRO_MANWOMAN> command such value?~ []
@1017815 = ~This armor was the property of the famous rogue, Telbar. How or why it left his possession is not known.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class: 5
Weight: 8
Not Usable By:
 Mage
 Kensai
 Monk
 Avenger
 Shapeshifter~ []
@1017830 = ~ It shall be done... and done well.~ [ANOMEN34]
@1017832 = ~I will stand by you in this, Jaheira. We should attack and get the upper hand.~ []
@1017833 = ~Stand down your weapons, Jaheira. We need not shed any blood here today.~ []
@1017835 = ~ Long live the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart, for I draw from the pool of right and strike in their name!~ [ANOMEN36]
@1017845 = ~This potion is imbued with a powerful enchantment, which will simulate a temporary increase in level. The effect lasts for 10 turns. This potion may only be used by warriors.

STATISTICS:

Hit Points: +10% (base only)
THAC0: Set to 90% of current base
Duration: 10 turns
Only usable by:
 Warriors and warrior subclasses (multi and dual also) other than Wizard Slayers~ []
@1017850 = ~I know you to be truthful, Jaheira, and I have heard good things of <CHARNAME>. I will try to sway the others, but passions run high in this matter.~ []
@1017852 = ~This potion confers invisibility similar to the second level wizard spell of the same name. Any actions other than movement cause termination of the invisible state. Barring such action, the effects will last for 12 hours.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017853 = ~This potion can be used only by warriors. When a giant strength potion is consumed, the individual gains great strength, and the consequent bonuses to hit and damage while using any hand-held or thrown weapon. The effect lasts for 10 turns.

STATISTICS:

Strength: 20 (Stone Giant Strength)
Not Usable By:
 Non-warrior classes
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017854 = ~This potion confers upon the user enhanced protection against attack, and provides bonuses to all saving throws. The effects of the elixir last for 5 turns, and can only be used by warriors.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class: set to 0
Saving Throws: +5 bonus
Not Usable By:
 Non-warrior classes
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017855 = ~Once exposed to air, this oil will immediately burst into flame, inflicting 6d6 points of damage to all within the area surrounding the point of impact, with a save vs. breath allowed in order to reduce the damage by half. The potion can be hurled up to 40 feet, at which point it hits the ground and immediately explodes into a ball of fire.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017856 = ~This oil increases the movement rate and combat capabilities of the imbiber. Movement rate is doubled, and the user gains one extra attack per round. Thus, a movement rate of 9 becomes 18, and a character normally able to attack once in a round may attack twice. The potion's effects do not reduce spellcasting time, however. The duration of the effects is 5 turns.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017857 = ~The Elixir of Health is a powerful healing mixture designed to cleanse the body of all impurities. First it cures the user of all poisons, and then heals him or her by 10 hit points to speed the recovery process.

Usable By:
 All~ []
@1017858 = ~This potion will cushion the user against blunt attacks made against him or her, so that only the strongest get through. The potion also confers 100% immunity to electricity for the duration of the effect, which is 10 turns.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class: +10 bonus vs. crushing attacks
Electrical Resistance: +100%
Duration: 10 turns

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017859 = ~This potion will raise the dexterity of the imbiber to 18, affecting armor class and missile attack adjustment for the duration of the effect, which is 15 turns.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017860 = ~As the name implies, this potion will neutralize any poison currently affecting the user. The cleansing is instant and the potion may only be used once.

Usable By:
 All~ []
@1017861 = ~This potion will allow its user to maintain clarity and order in the face of encroaching chaos and insanity. After drinking this potion, the imbiber will feel an overwhelming feeling of calm and purpose, such that he or she will be unaffected by harmful mental influences such as feeblemind, confusion and charm. This feeling will last for the duration of the enchantment or until dispelled.

STATISTICS:

Special: Prevents feeblemind, confusion, fear, and charm
Duration: 5 turns

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017862 = ~This potion will confer upon the imbiber 50% resistance to cold for the duration of the enchantment, which is 10 turns.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017863 = ~This potion improves the armor class of the imbiber. The effect lasts for 10 turns.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class: set to 0
Duration: 10 turns

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017864 = ~As the name implies, this potion will increase the intelligence of the imbiber by 4 points, up to a maximum of 25. The effect will last for 15 turns, or until dispelled.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017865 = ~This potion will bestow the ability of infravision upon its user. The effect will last for 20 turns or until dispelled.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017866 = ~This potion will confer upon the imbiber 50% resistance to electricity for the duration of the enchantment, which is 10 turns.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017867 = ~This powerful elixir imbues the drinker with immunity to all spells up to and including the 5th level. At the same time, all spell effects of 5th level and lower are removed from the imbiber. The effect will only last for 5 rounds, however, so careful timing is necessary.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017868 = ~This powerful elixir imbues the drinker with 50% resistance to all forms of magical damage. The effect lasts for 3 turns.

STATISTICS:

Damage: +50% resistance to all forms of magical damage
Special: All saving throws are made automatically
Duration: 3 turns

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017869 = ~This potion will imbue the drinker with 50% resistance to all magic, which can be a blessing or a curse. The effect will last for 10 turns or until dispelled.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017870 = ~This potion will temporarily transform the drinker into a master thief, significantly increasing his or her ability to pick locks and pick pockets. The effect will last for 3 hours.

STATISTICS:

Lock Picking: +40
Pick Pockets: +40
Duration: 3 hours

Usable By:
 Thief
 Bard~ []
@1017871 = ~This potion will imbue the drinker with the ability to focus his or her mind unerringly towards any task that needs to be performed.

STATISTICS:

Intelligence: +3 bonus
Dexterity: +3 bonus
Duration: 12 hours

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017872 = ~This potion heightens the sensory perception of the drinker, allowing delicate tasks to be performed better. The effect is to make certain thieving skills more likely to succeed.

STATISTICS:

Find/Remove traps: +20
Pick pockets: +20
Pick locks: +20
Hide in shadows: +20
Duration: 6 hours
Usable By:
 Thief
 Monk~ []
@1017873 = ~This powerful elixir imbues the drinker with the regenerative ability of a troll; any wounds that are sustained when under its effect will literally close over and heal as you watch. The user will regenerate 2 hit points per round for the duration of the effect, which is 3 turns.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017874 = ~When consumed, this potion will raise the wisdom of its user to 18 for 6 hours, or until dispelled.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017875 = ~When consumed, this potion will give the drinker a surge of energy such that his or her muscles will seem to ripple and bulge, coursing with magical energy. The effect is to raise the strength of the imbiber to 18 for approximately 20 turns, or until dispelled.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1020884 = ~Werebane +1~
@1017886 = ~Is it not enough that you have driven Jaheira from you? Must you continue this pointless exercise?~ []
@1017901 = ~Is Jaheira the only one among you that can see clearly? Even she was stunned by the actions of those I killed.~ []
@1017902 = ~And such a threat demands an equal response!~ []
@1017906 = ~A planar sphere appeared in the slums of Athkatla weeks ago. My ancestor, the necromancer Lavok, built that sphere as some sort of planar traveling device.~ []
@1017907 = ~I have no desire to meet my ancestor, and even less desire to help the Cowled Wizards, who seem certain that my body is the only key to the sphere... alive or not.~ []
@1017937 = ~Ha! You'll find little wealth or treasure of any kind, here. If it's treasure you value, however, I've a thought that might interest you... if you'd care to listen, that is.~ []
@1017942 = ~Aye, I did. 'Twas no murder, however... they attacked me first. I refused to co-operate with their 'request', and fled as soon as I was able to withdraw.~ []
@1017944 = ~I care not. The Cowled Wizards have hired me and I will do as I am bid.~ []
@1017951 = ~When consumed, this potion confers upon the drinker effects like those of the spell Free Action. The drinker becomes completely immune to any effects which hinder action or movement, whether magical in origin or not. The duration of the potion is 10 turns.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017952 = ~The potion of firebreath magically transforms the throat of the user so that it is capable of breathing fire. Hence, the user does not drink this potion so much as he or she uses it on an enemy. The resulting firebreath does 6d10 damage to the target, with a save vs. breath allowed to reduce the damage by half.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017953 = ~Once consumed, this potion will cause a surge of energy to travel through the body, raising the drinker's constitution to 18. The user then enjoys all the bonuses of having a high constitution, such as increased hit points, for the duration of the effect, which is 15 turns.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017955 = ~It seems unlikely that Lavok survived these five hundred years. How could he be alive?~ []
@1017977 = ~This potion will protect the drinker from all forms of petrification, including gaze attacks. The effect will last for 10 rounds or until dispelled.

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017984 = ~Close examination reveals this liquid to be very peculiar in nature. It could be a sorcerer's dream, but that would depend entirely on whom you asked. After ingesting the mixture, the drinker becomes the weakest, most unwise, yet incredibly intelligent person to have ever lived, with an innate 50% resistance to magic damage as well. The effects remain for an entire 24 hours, so think carefully before unplugging the cork.

STATISTICS:

Intelligence: set to 25
Wisdom: set to 3
Strength: set to 3
Special: +50% resistance to magic damage
Duration: 24 hours

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1017991 = ~This is one of the oddest potions you have ever examined. Once consumed, this mixture causes one's muscles to bulge to completely inhuman proportions, while dexterity and constitution are both reduced to that of a slug. The effect lasts for a full 24 hours, so think carefully before quaffing this suspect drink.

STATISTICS:

Strength: set to 25
Dexterity: set to 3
Constitution: set to 3
Duration: 24 hours

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1018020 = ~This slider controls the difficulty level of the game. The settings are as follows:  INSANE (far right):  all enemies do double damage. HARD (middle right):  All enemies do 50% more damage  CORE RULES (middle):  Baldur's Gate 1 rules apply  NORMAL (middle left):  All hit point rolls are maximum, characters cannot permanently die, all spells learned automatically, enemies only do three-quarters damage  NOVICE (far left):  Same as Normal mode and the enemies only do half damage.~ []
@1018076 = ~There is no talking to you, is there? Very well, do your worst. I will no longer dignify your actions with attempts at reason.~ []
@1018095 = ~A crossbow is a bow mounted crosswise on a wooden or metal shaft called a tiller. The bow is usually made of ash or yew. The crossbow fires a type of projectile known as a quarrel or bolt.

STATISTICS:

Damage: +2 (missile)
Weight: 14
Speed Factor: 10
Proficiency Type: Crossbow
Type: 2-handed
Requires: 12 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Cleric
 Mage
 Thief
 Monk
 Kensai
 Cavalier~ []
@1018098 = ~A Protection From Poison scroll will protect the target from all forms of common poison, be they of a natural or magical nature. The effect is not permanent, however, and will wear off after 6 hours.

STATISTICS:

Poison: Will not affect the target
Special: Removes poison already in the target's system
Range: 30 ft
Area: 1 creature
Duration: 6 hours
Requires: 9 Intelligence
Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1018139 = ~It has been a long time, but for all I know time may work differently when traveling the planes. As for his immortality... well, my ancestor has extended his life, before... but that is a different story.~ []
@1018142 = ~It has been a long time, but for all I know time may work differently when traveling the planes. As for his immortality... well, my ancestor has extended his life, before... but that is a different story.~ []
@1018150 = ~Imprisonment (Abjuration) 
Level: 9
Range: Touch 
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None 

When the Imprisonment spell is cast and the victim is touched, he or she is entombed in a state of suspended animation in a small sphere far beneath the surface of the earth. The victim remains there unless the reverse of the spell, Freedom, is cast. Otherwise, the victim will remain there as long as the earth exists. If a Freedom spell is cast in the area where the creature was imprisoned, then the victim will reappear exactly where he or she was last standing. Dispel magic will not free creatures trapped in this manner. There is no saving throw, and the target's magic resistance is ignored.~ []
@1018168 = ~I've a terrific elf-knot near strangling me... right here. Can ye help me with those nimble fingers and delicate manner?~ []
@1018173 = ~"Hold fast to dreams, for if dreams die, life be a broken bird that cannae fly."~ []
@1018187 = ~Good fight! We're in an age of murder, child. Killing is our business, and business be good.~ [KORGAN70]
@1018189 = ~  I... I am surely close to death.~ [PC2MA11]
@1018201 = ~Ye know, though ye all be gutless, clumsy and nay too bright, this party is a sight better than me former crew of delvers and ne'er-do-wells.~ [KORGAN71]
@1018203 = ~And I had to stop him flailing about while he struggled with his melting armor, so I hit him. And killed him. Accident, really, but he rankled me nerves.~ []
@1018205 = ~There can be no rhyme or reason for this crime. Justice will be served on the end of my blade! There can be no talking with the killer of Harpers!~ []
@1018233 = ~And Cutter went and got infected with plague so I up and broke his neck, to save him the agony.~ []
@1018236 = ~Indeed. It has been a very long time.~ [DERMIN02]
@1018240 = ~Of... of course, you were the one that introduced me to the Harpers.~ []
@1018242 = ~What... what are you getting at, Dermin?~ []
@1018244 = ~Oh... oh yes, here is the stone.~ []
@1018261 = ~The reward for the task is known only to the one I represent. But he is eager to meet with you, and as a Cowled Wizard possesses resources to offer great rewards.~ []
@1018269 = ~He will be most pleased. Master Tolgerias can be found in the government building behind me... you may go within. Do not tarry overlong, my friend.~ []
@1018278 = ~On ramparts across the Faerun are heads on pikes of the radiant who've been eulogized to the myth and allure of your vaunted brotherhood.~ [EDWIN56]
@1018294 = ~Leaving so soon? How... unfortunate. You realize the reward the Cowled Wizards can offer for completing this task is considerable. Can I change your mind, hm?~ []
@1018298 = ~Yes, it is a lot for even I to ask, eh?  You are more than capable of performing this task and it will conflict with none of your current loyalties.~ []
@1018299 = ~And you would garner the goodwill of the Cowled Wizards... not to mention a substantial reward. But if you are determined to refuse, I certainly cannot stop you.~ []
@1018305 = ~Excellent. Your agreement means that the Cowled Wizards shall hold you to your word. This matter must be handled with discretion and expediency.~ []
@1018314 = ~We have been unable to do so, much to our frustration. Cowled Wizards cannot be assaulted without repercussions or it will lead to... serious problems.~ []
@1018339 = ~And once I have found this fellow... what am I to do with him?~ []
@1018343 = ~Hmph. Such a declaration is dangerous, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. The Cowled Wizards will not treat treachery lightly.  Return to your task, or things will get... unpleasant.~ []
@1018370 = ~I warn you, however, not to lie to me. I will know the truth of your words. So, then... where is the fool?~ []
@1018386 = ~Mae'Var has been courting the Night Masks in order to bolster his own strategic position and betray Renal. Masterfully planned, but I have seen through it.~ []
@1018389 = ~The Masks are a cutthroat guild of footpads, brigands and highwaymen based in the congested cesspool of Westgate. Obviously they wish to expand.~ []
@1018391 = ~Very good. Do not make us wait overlong, my <PRO_LADYLORD>, or we shall get very upset. After that, things would become... dangerous. Begone.~ []
@1018394 = ~The eye dangles along the cheek, watching the rest of the body being eviscerated. You can't look away, and you can't blink.~ []
@1018401 = ~That was the best that you could do?? The stories of your prowess are greatly exaggerated! Bah! Tell me where the body is, you ineffective fool.~ []
@1018405 = ~A heartfelt round of congratulations to all! Justice has been dispensed this day. To other matters, however.~ [EDWIN73]
@1018414 = ~Fool! I shall not be deterred by the likes of you! We shall have a reckoning... elsewhere. And then I shall take the ranger from your dead hands if need be!~ []
@1018425 = ~ So... it has come, my raven. I'll leave this foul partnership and it shall be as if we've never been acquainted. Try not to trip over yourself as you continue your dreary way, aye?~ [HAERDA07]
@1018426 = ~Woman or not, my spellthrowing is unparalleled and will bring the wrath of cleansing hellfire upon you should the mood move me!~ []
@1018427 = ~ So! My part in this little play has changed, has it? 'Tis a role I'll relish... follow me, then! We charge on!~ [HAERDA08]
@1018431 = ~My name is... Celisa of Waterdeep. Yes, daughter of... Kur..Kurdall Al... Ale... Kurdall Aleconnor, a wealthy mead-maker and owner of a chain of festhalls.~ []
@1018435 = ~ Ah!~ [HAERDA14]
@1018436 = ~ At last... oblivion...~ [HAERDA15]
@1018438 = ~Would that I knew where this place was. I've no quarrel with you duergar.~ []
@1018439 = ~Edwin is a self-serving nerveless worm. He's gone rogue. He tithes nothing and has vilified the masters of the order and sullied their good names.~ []
@1018443 = ~ Beneath the earth our fates await us... and, just think, we shan't need go far to lie in our graves!~ [HAERDA19]
@1018446 = ~ Hmmn... the sky, 'tis a brilliant azure shade. Pity you Primes have only the one sun.~ [HAERDA20]
@1018448 = ~ Ahhh, night has laid her shroud upon us. A perfect time for a warm fire and a story to regale you all... were you not so distracted by pressing quests, that is.~ [HAERDA21]
@1018453 = ~ This sparrow is ready to fly... at your command, of course.~ [HAERDA22]
@1018462 = ~ Thy will be done... and not a moment too soon!~ [HAERDA31]
@1018465 = ~ I shall be glad to dance to your tune... if you but learn to play.~ [HAERDA33]
@1018480 = ~ I don't think I like your attitude much. You have all the makings of a nasty griffon... which reminds me, you need a bath.~ [JANJAN05]
@1018481 = ~ That's it... time to move on, places to go and all that. The way you're going, you're just going to end up like Golodon the Unmanned. And I didn't want to see that the first time.~ [JANJAN06]
@1018482 = ~ Well, now, this is a fine turn of events. I haven't led a party since... well, since Uncle Scratchy turned sick with the pox and put me in charge. He just didn't trust the dwarf, you see. Hmmn... hopefully, this time works out better than the last...~ [JANJAN07]
@1018483 = ~ It's long past time for turnip tea. A little rest will shake the stew from our eyes and the ache from our legs.~ [JANJAN08]
@1018487 = ~Who...? Jaheira, you travel with a killer of Harpers. I do not wish to think you had any complicity in those acts, but here <PRO_HESHE> is and <PRO_HESHE> is still alive.~ []
@1018488 = ~I have washed my hands of the incident in the Harper Hold. Galvarey was in the wrong and brought his fate upon himself.~ []
@1018489 = ~We know nothing of this. There is only the fact that you... you and your friend were the cause of many deaths. This cannot be ignored.~ []
@1018492 = ~It is not seen that way, Jaheira. Exact the necessary justice. That is the only route to redemption for you. The others... will not accept you otherwise.~ []
@1018498 = ~Do not concern yourself. This was the only course open, even if... I... I wish to not talk of this. This matter is... is behind me. Onward, we have much to do.~ []
@1018499 = ~I thank you, <CHARNAME>, but part of me is gone. I... I will speak no more of this. This is behind me. I must go forward. Come, we have friends to avenge.~ []
@1018500 = ~Dermin... I...~ []
@1018504 = ~What are you saying, Jaheira?~ []
@1018505 = ~If this is the justice you represent then I... I renounce you. I renounce... I renounce my life as a Harper.~ []
@1018506 = ~Jaheira, you cannot mean... Think this through.~ []
@1018507 = ~It would seem I am the only one that has thought any of this through. You do not, Galvarey did not, and now the Harpers out for blood do not.~ []
@1018510 = ~... don't forget to raise me...~ [JANJAN14]
@1018511 = ~ Er... don't mean to startle you, or anything, but all this blood spurting about is actually mine!~ [JANJAN15]
@1018513 = ~... hmmn... I'd wager the turnip market's making a killing today...~ [JANJAN17]
@1018514 = ~ Ahhh, this reminds me of the turnip cellars... except Uncle Gerhardt isn't passed out by the turnip still in the corner...~ [JANJAN18]
@1018518 = ~It is their... it is my duty to 'meddle,' <CHARNAME>. It is only this instance where they are wrong. I cannot go along with this.~ []
@1018520 = ~ (burp!) Pardon. Turnip reflex.~ [JANJAN23]
@1018528 = ~ It shall be done with skill and care... if not brevity.~ [JANJAN30]
@1018530 = ~ I'll do it... for a turnip.~ [JANJAN32]
@1018532 = ~No... no... I do not think it is. You are advocating revenge without thought. You are not giving the balance its due. I... I have little choice here I think.~ []
@1018533 = ~ You know, this reminds of that time... way back...~ [JANJAN33]
@1018534 = ~Dermin... Dermin, I renounce my life as a Harper.~ []
@1018536 = ~You are right, of course, and <PRO_HISHER> has proven it. No, I think it best if I return to tending the balance with my druidic brethren.~ []
@1018537 = ~This is perhaps worse than if you actually were. I... I have no more desire to pursue this matter. Goodbye Jaheira. This... this is a sad day.~ []
@1018548 = ~You have a place here, Jaheira, regardless of this mess.~ []
@1018551 = ~Garbage!? Do you comprehend the magnitude of what I have done?! Do you see... what... no, I will not cheapen this moment by arguing with you.~ []
@1018554 = ~You have a place here, Jaheira, regardless of this mess.~ []
@1018556 = ~Come, enough sadness for the day. We have much to do and... and together we will not fail.~ []
@1018557 = ~I take strength from the group, but... more so in your company. I have friends to avenge, but life is also for the living. Life is worth pursuing. I... I hope you agree.~ []
@1018560 = ~ I think we make a fine partnership! Like Drizzt and Wulfgar! Elminster and Volo! Hah! We should go into the mobile vegetable peddling business together!~ [JANJAN35]
@1018569 = ~ I've nicked a bit from our friend here.~ [JANJAN40]
@1018593 = ~Selfishness~
@1018595 = ~ The spirit is willing, my friend... but this old and battered body demands rest.~ [KELDOR08]
@1018605 = ~ A pleasant enough setting... although I have had little time, in my life, to pay proper homage to beauty.~ [KELDOR16]
@1018608 = ~ Keep a wary eye about... one never knows the form that danger can take in a place such as this.~ [KELDOR18]
@1018637 = ~But... what?~ []
@1018638 = ~But I'm on good terms with Harpers and I don't want that to change. Word's got around about what happened. Jaheira... it ain't true, is it?~ []
@1018645 = ~He's in the lower... Gods, no! He comes! He's here!~ [CSCOW302]
@1018646 = ~I cannot be caged.~ [DPJON147]
@1018659 = ~You understand nothing, mortal! I am not who you seek... this be merely the body! And your intrusion has caused the sphere to leap back to my own dimension!!~ [LAVOK08]
@1018660 = ~Wh-where am I? The... force that possessed me is... is gone?~ [LAVOK10]
@1018664 = ~Who might you be? I... I can barely see you...~ []
@1018666 = ~Corthala... yes, I remember this now. My family. Oh, I am dying, Valygar Corthala, of that you can be certain. Nothing would bring me greater relief.~ []
@1018678 = ~If I could call it all back... Ah... if I could go back and convince the man I once was that the sphere was a mission of pride doomed to failure.~ []
@1018682 = ~I... I don't... what would you ask of me?~ []
@1018684 = ~This... this is not a trick?~ []
@1018686 = ~You are not the man I expected, Lavok. I... I shall do as you ask.~ []
@1018701 = ~Hm. A side to you I hadn't noticed. Very well... I'll find my own way and likely be the better for it. I wish you well, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1018702 = ~Wh-where am I? The... the force that possessed me is... is gone?~ [LAVOK10]
@1018713 = ~It took all my power to keep him from prying the knowledge of the sphere from what remained of my soul... and it has been so long I can barely remember when it all began.~ []
@1018715 = ~You seem to be trying to sound almost noble... are you not the terrible necromancer Lavok?~ []
@1018720 = ~I was the scourge of the living before I left this plane... I terrorized my own blood and tampered with the laws of life and death. Evil and arrogant was I, indeed.~ []
@1018721 = ~... Ah... if I could go back and convince the man I once was that the sphere was a mission of pride doomed to failure.~ []
@1018723 = ~I... I can feel my last breaths coming upon me, but I have some time yet. Time enough for one last bargain. You... you, there, <PRO_RACE>... might I bargain with you?~ []
@1018725 = ~I would rather maintain my distance and wait for your death to come. I trust no necromancer... especially not one that I have just fought and lost friends battling.~ []
@1018726 = ~This... is all I ask, no tricks or subterfuge. I... beg it of you, stranger.~ []
@1018731 = ~I do not trust you... who knows what you might attempt to pull? I will find another way.~ []
@1018737 = ~Ah, it is the sky, after all. I had forgotten how it looked after so long. I thank you... I... I wish...~ [LAVOK17]
@1018738 = ~Ah, it is the sky, after all. I had forgotten how it looked after so long. I thank you... and I wish to repay you for your kindness...~ [LAVOK18]
@1018739 = ~... I sense within you a power and ability similar to my own, yes? You are a mage. Yes, I am correct.~ []
@1018740 = ~Take the planar sphere, mage. I grant it to you, in payment for my release. Use it... use it far more wisely than I ever did...~ []
@1018742 = ~ I have buried many fallen comrades... let us endeavour to remain hale this day.~ [KELDOR34]
@1018745 = ~Er... why, yes I am. He said I could look around if I wished.~ []
@1018758 = ~Don't hurt me! Those horrible... peasants... have done enough!
~ []
@1018762 = ~NO! (cough)  This isn't what was supposed to happen! This isn't what was promised to me!~ [KALAH11]
@1018772 = ~This... this is unexpected. I had thought we were closer than simple group comrades. Not that I doubt you, but should I leave the group I doubt things will be the same between us.~ [JAHEIRF1]
@1018779 = ~Of course, Jaheira, please stay. I do not wish you to leave, it was just a word misspoken.~ []
@1018783 = ~I am glad of this. I have... I have high hopes for what we will accomplish in the future.~ []
@1018791 = ~The ordeal with the Cowled Wizards was just awful. They came here two weeks ago, demanding to see Master Corthala. I was just shaking in my shoes.~ []
@1018793 = ~This is not wise. We should be making all haste to the Harper hold in Athkatla. I... I do not look forward to the trip so I will not force you to go, but it would be best if you complied.~ [JAHEIRF2]
@1018794 = ~There was a loud crash... fighting. I was terrified when the wizards came back down the stairs alone. They said Valygar had committed murder and must pay.~ []
@1018796 = ~(cough)  You... you've killed me... destroyed Kalah with your misplaced morals and beastly greed for adventure...~ [KALAH13]
@1018798 = ~I fear that the actions of my fellow Harpers may have colored your view of me. I assure you I wish to be in no other place than by your side.~ [JAHEIRF3]
@1018805 = ~It is none of your concern. If you answer my questions, no harm will come to you.~ []
@1018809 = ~You are done talking, gnome. You'll be dead in moments.~ []
@1018810 = ~In Amn... a mage is a criminal and a gnome is a spectacle. In this tent... in my world... Kalah was the master, where none would dare to laugh...~ []
@1018812 = ~I... I see. What did you wish to know?~ []
@1018814 = ~Tell me about Valygar... does he have any friends?~ []
@1018818 = ~You are done talking, gnome. You'll be dead in moments.~ []
@1018826 = ~I... I beg your pardon? I may have misheard your decision; you... you wish me to leave? But... I wish to be no other place than here, with... with you. I could not come back if I am wrong. Tell me you have misspoken.~ [JAHEIRF4]
@1018829 = ~That is good to know. I have few others to turn to now and I... I value our time together.~ []
@1018830 = ~Curse me for a fool then. Why I thought... I will not show such weakness again. So be it, I will venture off on my own.~ []
@1018831 = ~I am not sure where I will go. Goodbye, <CHARNAME>. I do not think we will meet again.~ []
@1018832 = ~What? You cannot mean... I stood by you through a very difficult time; I have turned my back on many of my own brethren! Am I to be cast aside like any other member of the group? I'm not sure I could return after something like this.~ [JAHEIRF5]
@1018836 = ~I see. Well, I will not waste my breath arguing. I will go... I cannot go to the Harpers, here. I will go... where? Goodbye, <CHARNAME>, I doubt we shall meet again.~ []
@1018837 = ~A medium shield is carried in the same manner as a small shield. Unlike the small shield, however, a medium shield's weight prevents the bearer from using his or her shield hand for anything other than carrying the medium shield. Medium shields are usually made of metal, range from 3 to 4 feet in diameter, and can be of any shape, from round to square to resembling a dragon's spread wings. A typical medieval shield resembles a triangle with one point facing downward. This shield is magical, granting additional protection to its wearer.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class Bonus: 2
Weight: 6
Requires: 12 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Bard
 Druid
 Mage
 Thief
 Monk
 Kensai~ []
@1018838 = ~That is rather odd, but I would like to know if the master is alright. The master was paranoid about thieves, so when you look around be careful.~ []
@1018839 = ~A small shield is usually round, carried on the forearm, and gripped with the shield hand. Its light weight compared to a medium shield permits the user to carry other items in the shield hand, although he or she cannot wield or carry another weapon. This magical shield grants the user some extra protection.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class Bonus: 2
Special: No Missile Weapon Protection
Weight: 3
Requires: 4 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Bard
 Druid
 Mage 
 Thief
 Monk
 Kensai~ []
@1018844 = ~Very well, then... I'll be leaving.~ []
@1018849 = ~Hm. It truly puzzles me. I remember the family used to own some land in the Umar Hills. Perhaps the master has gone there. Is this helpful?~ []
@1018851 = ~Not really... do you know of any friends that Valygar has?~ []
@1018853 = ~Well, the master has friends amongst the woodsmen and rangers. He was in the scouts, you see, up until a couple of years ago. Very skilled.~ []
@1018858 = ~No. I have no idea. I really think this is enough questions... I shall inform the master of your search when he returns, yes? Have a good day, my <LADYLORD>.~ []
@1018865 = ~Indifference killed those fools from the circus. I treat them in death as they were to me in life. A gnome gets no respect... I just wanted people to look up... to me. All that I have done...~ []
@1018867 = ~You don't understand, do you? You take my life, but worse, you take my dignity. I just wanted... I wanted to be the king instead of... instead of...~ []
@1018868 = ~You don't know... denied respect my entire life. A clown, a fool... it does not matter... I die as I... as I...~ []
@1018872 = ~I was attacked by Cowled Wizards here... what do you know about that?~ []
@1018876 = ~I am Kalah the grand... but an illusionist in Amn is a criminal, and a gnome is a spectacle... I was a clown... I was promised a world where Kalah was master, where none would dare...~ []
@1018881 = ~I... I suppose so. What do you wish to know?~ []
@1018890 = ~Yes... Valygar told me that you would know how to get ahold of him.~ []
@1018891 = ~Yes... Valygar told me that you would know how to get ahold of him.~ []
@1018892 = ~Yes, actually. Valygar said he would be here... do you know where he is?~ []
@1018896 = ~When wholly consumed, this potion restores 27 hit points to the user. The effect is instantaneous and the potion is destroyed in the process.

Usable By:
 All~ []
@1018897 = ~Er... yes. You are the <LADYLORD> <CHARNAME>, is it? The master is... expecting you. He is upstairs, for the moment.~ []
@1018909 = ~It is very sad, with Master Corthala dead now. He has no family left, I understand... oh, I just don't know what I am to do!~ []
@1018910 = ~I... I don't think that you should be here, however. Please leave at once!~ []
@1018912 = ~As well as can be expected, Hervo. Thank you and... um... carry on.~ []
@1018919 = ~Oh... pardon me. I'll be going.~ []
@1018923 = ~Slings have existed since the beginning of recorded history. The basic sling consists of a leather or fabric strap with a pouch for holding the missile. The weapon is held by both ends of the strap and twirled around the wielder's head. When top speed is attained, the missile is launched by releasing one of the strap's ends. This particular sling is enchanted.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +1 bonus
Damage: +1 (missile damage)
Weight: 0
Speed Factor: 5
Proficiency Type: Sling
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 3 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Kensai
 Cavalier~ []
@1018932 = ~Among mankind's earliest weapons, dating back to the most primitive of times, the first spears were simply wooden poles or sticks that had been sharpened at one end. Upon mastering the use of metals, weaponsmiths forged spear heads from iron and steel, and began experimenting with different types of spear heads, thus leading to the development of certain types of polearms. This spear is special, however, as it has been imbued with certain magical properties.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +1 bonus
Damage: 1D6 + 1
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 5
Speed Factor: 5
Proficiency Type: Spear 
Type: 2-handed
Requires: 5 Strength
Not Usable By:
