@1019364 = ~Getting Inside the Asylum

I found where the so-called 'Pirate Lord', Desharik, is staying... and managed to get inside by mentioning Golin's name. It appears the Captain is respected, here.~ []
@1019373 = ~Actually, no... I am just curious.~ []
@1019379 = ~I... I see. We are more than a little interested in finding this murderer. Perhaps you might be amenable to assisting us in this endeavour?~ []
@1019384 = ~Still, the man is a murderer. The Cowled Wizards cannot allow one such as he to run free or all in this city will think it permissible to stand against us.~ []
@1019390 = ~I see. Hm. I notice that you have something in your hand... some form of letter. Hand it over to me at once.~ []
@1019401 = ~No, I've no interest in hunting this man for you. Find someone else to perform this task.~ []
@1019402 = ~Ah, the reward. Adventurers have much use for items the Cowled Wizards possess. It is sad that magic is so despised in Athkatla, for it has many uses.~ []
@1019403 = ~We will offer you an item of substantial magical power as well as a good deal of gold coin. What say you, then... will you find this man for us?~ []
@1019415 = ~Very good. Now... it is my belief that you know too much of Cowled Wizard business. It is time to be rid of you, as well as our friend Valygar. My apologies.~ []
@1019417 = ~Very well... here you go.~ []
@1019420 = ~Once you have Valygar in custody, bring him to me. I shall wait here in this building, as I doubt you could locate the Cowled Wizards' headquarters.~ []
@1019426 = ~This machine buzzes with electrical energy.~ []
@1019427 = ~Hmph. Such a declaration is dangerous, my <LADYLORD>.  The Cowled Wizards will not treat treachery lightly. Perform your task,  or things will get... unpleasant.~ []
@1019434 = ~Perhaps we have met. We traveled in much the same circles, though not at the same time. Terminsel is the... ahh... name, and I should like to ask ye a question.~ []
@1019435 = ~Do... I know you? I... your voice is familiar, but I cannot place your face.~ [JAHEIRC2]
@1019461 = ~Be thee not of impure heart or thou wilt surely destroy thyself. Kalah is the one Ruler, the One True Being.~ []
@1019463 = ~Thank you for your welcome and I shall most certainly beware.~ []
@1019464 = ~I've come to see the circus, not some half-dressed tart spouting dire warnings!~ []
@1019465 = ~Kalah is beyond thy ken, mortal! He is the Beginning. He is the End. He is our God and our King. Tremble before him and he may take pity on thee.~ []
@1019468 = ~Algernon's cloak is imbued with magical properties such that the wearer will seem to shine with an inner glow.

STATISTICS:

