@1020365 = ~The hunt for Valygar Corthala.

Hervo mentioned that Valygar had numerous friends in the Amnish military, as he was a scout for them at one point. He remembered one friend in particular... a woman by the name of Suna Seni... but he has no idea where she might be found, as she works as a mercenary.~ []
@1020372 = ~Wherever the trail of gold leads us. I lost much in my capture, and I will not leave poor.~ []
@1020391 = ~Moral, most definitely. I must watch the overall balance of things, and you may figure largely in the tipping. It is because of... what you are.~ []
@1020393 = ~Who will judge what path is right for me?~ []
@1020400 = ~I enjoy matching wits with cretins like these.~ []
@1020402 = ~Perhaps not here as such, but you are still a valuable commodity. There are those that know of the Children of Bhaal, and they may desire... services from you.~ []
@1020406 = ~How the hell should I know?~ []
@1020408 = ~Perhaps an inn. I guess it doesn't really matter, does it?~ []
@1020419 = ~I'm... I'm sorry, <CHARNAME>. I do not wish to cause undue strain in our party. I am merely a bit stressed, and no doubt you are as well.~ []
@1020422 = ~Stow it, Jaheira.~ []
@1020423 = ~Yes, but not acceptable. We are friends, and should act as such. I... I apologize.~ []
@1020424 = ~Agreed, though we have all suffered much and the mood may change. I will try to be civil by your side.~ []
@1020426 = ~Mmmph... no... no... NO!! Wh-what... what?~ [JAHEIR76]
@1020427 = ~Nnn... no... NO!! wh... wh... what?~ []
@1020429 = ~Jaheira, you scared the hell out of me. I thought we were under attack.~ []
@1020431 = ~No, there is something very wrong. I... I have been having nightmares, and when I wake, it is still there. Khalid... I thought I was stronger than this.~ []
@1020439 = ~None of us can affect the past, Jaheira.~ []
@1020443 = ~You are harsh and cruel, but it seems to serve you well. Perhaps that is the answer. I... I don't know. I will not bother you again with this.~ []
@1020447 = ~Yes, well, we should be going. I am fine now. Thank you.~ []
@1020456 = ~Hmm... seems I cannot help but speak of the dead lately. I did not wish to cause you any distress if I have.~ []
@1020464 = ~I... I see. That attitude will not make you popular among the living that do remember. The dead leave their tendrils behind, for good or bad.~ []
@1020465 = ~This I know all too well.~ []
@1020468 = ~I think you are right. It is a shame when the dead take the living with them.~ []
@1020470 = ~Yes. His story became yours, and you took it with you. You are not of his blood, but there is much of him in you.~ []
@1020472 = ~True... true enough. You are wise to see as such.~ []
@1020473 = ~Well... enough of this for now. Talk such as this can get maudlin if indulged too often. I have a... a good feeling from this though.~ []
@1020474 = ~Yes, he sheltered you carefully from those that would harm you. Khalid was the same way, always taking the cautious path.~ []
@1020476 = ~Yes, and they are missed.~ []
@1020496 = ~Thank you for that grasp of the obvious.~ []
@1020499 = ~Nothing of the sort, but I am interested in how you fare against your own instincts.~ []
@1020500 = ~Do you think my struggle different than any other person's?~ []
@1020505 = ~'The present will pass by if you live in the past. Neither should you wait too long for the future to find you.'   Who said this? It was... Khalid.~ []
@1020506 = ~Now look, foolish things in my head. Still, these talks always make me feel... better.~ []
@1020508 = ~Mmmph... Khal... No... Khal.. NO! I...~ [JAHEIR78]
@1020512 = ~I... I am not so bad. This one was not so cruel as the others. Khalid was in the distance, but he would not come closer, and I could not see the way to him.~ []
@1020514 = ~He walked with us, from a distance. He smiled that I was content. I guess... I guess I was.~ []
@1020517 = ~Then we can finally be rid of his specter then? I was getting tired of you constantly depressing me.~ []
@1020518 = ~It... it was not a group. Just... it was just you and I... and I think you are right.~ []
@1020521 = ~Well... um... shall we be off. It is already late in the day. Plenty to do.~ []
@1020522 = ~This is quite cruel of you. So be it, I will not endeavor to speak to you of such things again. It is a waste of... of... Let's just get out of here.~ []
@1020524 = ~Pssst... psssst. Hey. Hey there.~ []
@1020525 = ~RISE AND SHINE! Oh, I hope I didn't disturb ye. My, but yer a bunch of sound sleepers. Did'nay hear the approach of us wee little bandits and now look at the mess yer in.~ []
@1020526 = ~Uh uhh, stay right where ye are. Wipe the sleep from yer eyes and ye'll see me little friend, a sharp little number right at this here lassie's throat. I would'nay want to... SLIP.~ []
@1020532 = ~An honorable what? Bandit? Do ye have a clue what will be happening here, buddy boy? We're here to steal ye blind, and ye wish me to do that 'honorably?' Fine. Hand over yer valuables... SIR!~ []
@1020533 = ~Yes, lets do just that. I'll start. Ye'll be handing over what valuables ye have -and we've heard ye have a lot- and then we'll be going on our way.~ []
@1020534 = ~We get what we want and ye get... well, perhaps we just get what we want. That's good enough for me.~ []
@1020542 = ~Riddle of the Imps

There was some kind of specter in the chest that held the drow treasure, which killed the opener rather viciously before fleeing. Perhaps I should have played the imps' game when they offered it.~ []
@1020549 = ~Well, yer certainly being reasonable about all of this. Mind you, I'll just keep a grip on the lassie here until my boys have finished their work. Stand still, will you?~ []
@1020552 = ~Hush now, lassie. Yes, I stand before ye a liar. Go figure. Now we'll just finish ye and... hold still ye... OW!! Me hand!~ []
@1020554 = ~Oh, for shame. That was simply a mistake, especially for the little lassie. Oops, there goes my shaky wrist. Aw, that has got to sting.~ []
@1020560 = ~Eughh, should I let ye polish me boots while you're down on your knees? Ye have the spine of a noble, that is for certain. What the... hold still, lassie!~ []
@1020564 = ~You... you...~ [JAHEIR86]
@1020565 = ~You... you were pretty quick to give up your equipment.~ [JAHEIR87]
@1020566 = ~Are... are you alright?~ [JAHEIR88]
@1020579 = ~This potion is a vial of pain, as it will explode into a burning ball of fire upon impact. Keep it in a safe place lest ye meet an untimely end.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 6D6 (save vs. spell for half)
Area: 15-foot radius

Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1020584 = ~I... I think so. Rather a close call there.~ []
@1020587 = ~I... I suppose. I didn't think about it at the time. I just wanted you safe.~ []
@1020589 = ~Don't you EVER do something that stupid again, you hear me? Not in a thousand seasons! I lost... I lost...~ []
@1020590 = ~*ahem*... I lost Khalid... to a pointless death, I'm not going... to lose you too.~ []
@1020592 = ~Oh, shut up and let's get out of here. We'll... we'll talk later.~ []
@1020596 = ~Ahh, it's all just baggage. I couldn't carry it all without you anyway.~ []
@1020598 = ~Regardless, I really appreciate what you did... what you tried to do. I was worried that I was... I mean, I've already lost... um...~ []
@1020613 = ~We like to think so, but it does not always work out that way. I believe it began a century ago, with what seems a curse in retrospect.~ []
@1020649 = ~The door to this house is rotting off its hinges. You assume the house has been abandoned for years.~ []
@1020669 = ~'Tis but a flesh wound, Mistress Mazzy.~ [VALYGA60]
@1020671 = ~The return to Harper Hold.

Jaheira's tutor, Dermin, returned once again... this time with a warning: the Harpers have ordered Jaheira executed. The attacks from them will continue in severity unless Jaheira turns herself in to them. Jaheira told him that she would think on it, and he left.~ []
@1020672 = ~Ahhh... nothing. Nothing at all...~ []
@1020694 = ~Bodhi keeps her side of the bargain.

Bodhi agreed to fulfill our bargain, though there were some additional concerns she revealed.
According to Bodhi, Irenicus captured me because he had discovered my nature as a child of Bhaal, and he was attempting to 'aid' my development, though his methods were indistinguishable from torture. The Shadow Thieves attacked Irenicus before I could be told any of this, and I escaped as he was incarcerated.

Bodhi also told me that she is essentially Irenicus' sister, and that her reason for helping me is that she wishes to free the wizard from the same place that Imoen has been sent to, a dread asylum for magic-users called Spellhold. Bodhi does this not out of any familial attachment, but rather because she requires Irenicus for her own purposes. As added incentive she offers to reveal whatever Irenicus learned about me. 

The asylum is on an island under its own rule, and Bodhi used the gold I gave her to book passage for me. There I will try to find a way into Spellhold to free Imoen... and, Bodhi hopes, free Irenicus at the same time.~ []
@1020707 = ~You keep mentioning your eyes... did you put your own eyes out?~ []
@1020708 = ~Errr... I'll be on my way.~ []
@1020715 = ~Please Insert Baldur's Gate CD~ []
@1020729 = ~This potion confers very high resistance to all attacks, and gives bonuses to all saving throws. The effects of the elixir last for 5 turns, but can only be used by warriors. The liquid in the potion has a strange, murky quality to it that you haven't noticed in other potions.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class: set to 0
Saving Throws: +5 bonus
Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1020739 = ~I have been shown the way, faithless one! Lathander is nothing before the presence of the Unseeing Eye! Bow down... bow down and put out your vile eyes!~ []
@1020741 = ~You... put out your own eyes, then?~ []
@1020742 = ~Er... actually, I'll be going.~ []
@1020748 = ~He is everywhere! Everywhere!! The master calls the name out to us and we respond! See me now, oh great one... see your servant humbling herself before you!~ []
@1020755 = ~Okay... where might one find this Unseeing Eye?~ []
@1020771 = ~... the Master has called on us to spread the word of He who shall cause the false gods to cry out in their folly before his sightless gaze!~ []
@1020787 = ~Er... why would having eyes make me foolish?~ []
@1020793 = ~You have no eyes... who did this to you?~ []
@1020797 = ~The Eye! He is beautiful... sooo beautiful! Worship him! Kneel and worship him, I tell you, before he casts you down! Throw aside your gods and bow, bow, boooowwww!!~ []
@1020808 = ~I... sense something most disturbing and unnatural about this.~ []
@1020813 = ~This is... most disturbing, <CHARNAME>. Nature itself curls back from this vileness. Something must be done!~ []
@1020815 = ~Listen to me, my brothers and sisters... heed my words. We have been chosen as the recipients of a most holy miracle, one that should neither be dismissed nor ignored!~ [GAAL07]
@1020816 = ~I, Gaal... I, who have been stripped of my eyes most mercifully, have been shown the truth that has eluded the sighted! The gods that you worship are false gods, icons that serve to increase the wealth of churches and heathens! Listen to them not!~ [GAAL08]
@1020817 = ~Hold! You speak of blasphemy! The Morninglord Lathander has always shown His benevolence and power. His presence among us is unquestionable!~ [CSCLER01]
@1020833 = ~What... what does that mean? Shall we tear our own eyes out, then? Don't be foolish!~ [CSHEC301]
@1020834 = ~What shall we do, then? Who shall we turn to if there's no gods?~ [CSSUP201]
@1020838 = ~Bah! What has your god ever done for me, eh? Eh!? I'm poorer and no better off than I ever was!~ [CSSUP102]
@1020842 = ~No, my friends... you do not wish to 'see'. Forget what the years of lies have taught your eyes! You wish to 'know'. You wish to 'learn'. These are the truths that the Unseeing Eye can offer to you.~ [GAAL19]
@1020847 = ~Come, then! Those of you who wish to become the truly faithful, to witness the magnificence of the Unseeing Eye and the truth he brings, come with me!~ [GAAL21]
@1020858 = ~That so? I was thinkin' me sources of information infallible. Well, I suppose ye won't be wantin' any information on the young woman arrested by the Cowled Wizards when ye first came to Athkatla, huh?~ [GAELEN08]
@1020863 = ~But they can be doing far better than the tellin', my friend. They can also affect the rescue of your lass to boot.~ [GAELEN28]
@1020876 = ~Well then, so be it. The wizard who was arrested with her, though... ye were kept in his dungeon like a rat, aye? Maybe ye's have a question or two. Maybe ye wants to find 'im?~ [GAELEN13]
