@1021417 = ~Hello, pretty one! My... the people here are rather friendly, aren't they? Cheshire smiles from strangers.~ []
@1021418 = ~She has watched you for a time, though she is not the only one. Those that you are asked to trust spy as openly or more so, and she offers a solution to your problems of privacy... among others.~ [VALENX09]
@1021421 = ~She is worthy of your trust. If you feel worthy of hers, come to the Graveyard District in the near future and she will speak her offer. Make your visit after the sky has darkened; she will not be there before then.~ [VALENX10]
@1021431 = ~That is foolish and premature. Should you not hear the offer first? Granted her meeting conditions are less than ideal, but so is your current circumstance. She will wait... for a time.~ [VALENX14]
@1021433 = ~More important... such as joining one of the Royal Orders. Or perhaps earning a career in the military. Serving your lord or your god, as it were.~ []
@1021446 = ~You have fulfilled your family's oath. A vow lived up to is a rare thing, my friend. Even rarer a vow that stretches back five hundred years.~ []
@1021447 = ~Yes, I see. My family's vow to kill Lavok. It... does not feel as I think it should.~ []
@1021453 = ~Minsc... something about you concerns me...~ [VALYGA49]
@1021468 = ~I have asked you here because we are unlikely to be overheard, and so you can see the benefits of working with me. Follow, please, and stay exactly in my step. You would... regret doing other.~ [BODHIX11]
@1021476 = ~Have you... considered seeing a priest, Minsc? Someone who might try to heal your... uh... head wound?~ []
@1021477 = ~I have been seen by the best and by the worst, and all have learned that Minsc is Minsc is Minsc. I do good things for those that need them; why is there a problem?~ []
@1021486 = ~Well... no, of course not. But that has--~ []
@1021488 = ~I... I suppose...~ []
@1021491 = ~So joyful, ranger? You find some happiness, perhaps, in the slaughter of a relative?~ [VICONI58]
@1021493 = ~Ah. I thought perhaps it was the murder of your uncle... or whatever he was. We have similarities in drow culture to such a thing.~ []
@1021496 = ~I... I still know evil when I see it, Viconia. I am just... just...~ []
@1021499 = ~I have been thinking ranger... and I have decided that I do feel sorry for you.~ [VICONI57]
@1021510 = ~You are... employed of course, and do errands occasionally. No doubt you have questioned the intent of your employer on occasion? If you haven't, then you should.~ [BODHIX13]
@1021512 = ~I would offer an alternative. I would help you find your friend for... oh... 15,000 gold? It is a sizeable amount less than the Shadow Thieves have asked and, coincidentally, it is what you have now.~ []
@1021558 = ~That's terrible... all of your family is gone?~ []
@1021562 = ~Soon one can challenge the boundaries of life and death. The unnatural becomes commonplace, and before you realize, you are on a path that only leads to ruin.~ []
@1021563 = ~I have seen every facet of magic's dark side with my mother before... before she died. Try as I might, I cannot twist and turn it enough to find its light side.~ []
@1021566 = ~Every Corthala: adventurer, sage, necromancer, all would have been better served staying home to take care of their family and living natural lives.~ []
@1021573 = ~I... I suppose so. You have traveled more than I. Perhaps if I see these miracles I would be more easily convinced. I shall have to think on that.~ []
@1021577 = ~But... perhaps, <CHARNAME>. Perhaps I would consider it. Somewhere else, who knows?~ []
@1021578 = ~They either killed each other in their pursuits or have been... dealt with. It was not a large family anyway... few sorcerers see the need for a family life.~ []
@1021579 = ~And those that do are rarely happy with it. No, no... it is very likely best that I am the last of us. A sad thing, but true enough.~ []
@1021580 = ~Yes. Yes, it is. I... never mind. Let us be going.~ []
@1021581 = ~Tell me... what kind of family did you have?~ [VALYGA68]
@1021583 = ~My family is... best not discussed.~ []
@1021587 = ~A very good man. He died, though... killed by Sarevok while protecting me many months ago.~ []
@1021597 = ~My lineage is... best not discussed, actually.~ []
@1021609 = ~You are... the child of a god? How is that possible?~ []
@1021615 = ~But I must sound like a mewling child. Enough, <CHARNAME>... let us continue on our travels.~ []
@1021628 = ~I have thought of his death much, and it raises a question to me. I had thought that evil... true evil... was absolute. Now I am unsure if such a thing exists.~ []
@1021630 = ~It does exist. Evil is evil and it must be punished.~ []
@1021631 = ~It may. I think it depends on the person... and the deeds.~ []
@1021635 = ~That is, more or less, how I used to feel. It troubles my mind, though... and the more I see, the less I think it is true.~ []
@1021649 = ~Drow: Hurry up, slaves!~ []
@1021657 = ~Move them NOW, male!~ []
@1021659 = ~Where?~ []
@1021661 = ~Enough of this insolence!~ []
@1021669 = ~Get and talk to Renal... he's the only one around here who wants anything to do with you.~ []
@1021670 = ~Nothing can withstand the wrath of the Shadow Thieves... just mind that.~ []
@1021673 = ~Aha... do come in, come in. Take a look around, if you wish. I am Gorch, the humble proprietor of this modest establishment.~ []
@1021685 = ~Oh? That door? Just the entry to my own humble abode. Let me show you a fine piece of Sembian jewelry, imparted to me by an unfortunate merchant.~ []
@1021689 = ~Ah... why did you not simply say so earlier? You have something written for me, yes, hm?~ []
@1021690 = ~Hm... um-hmmn... yes. Everything appears to be in order. You can see Mae'Var... through the door in the back. So nice to meet you, my good friend.~ []
@1021704 = ~Well, I didn't miss ya before you talked to me, did I? Or did I? Terrible thing, losin' your memory. My medicine's gotta be here... I just had it, I'm sure...~ []
@1021721 = ~He's downstairs, doing what he loves best, of course. Heh... it's what he always does to unnerve newcomers. You'll be expected to go down there and speak to him while he does it, naturally.~ []
@1021724 = ~I'm Zyntris. And let's just get this straight, now, so there's no mistaking it later, alright? I'm the senior cutpurse. Me... not nobody else. Try to slide in on me and I'll stick ya. Got it?~ []
@1021725 = ~Er... sure. Can you tell me where I might find Mae'Var?~ []
@1021729 = ~Er... no, no. Of course not. Just tryin' to inform ya of the ranks, is all.~ []
@1021732 = ~I'm Zyntris. Just so you're aware, I'm the senior cutpurse around here, right? Get too big for yer britches and I stick ya... got it?~ []
@1021737 = ~I hear ya killed a Cowled Wizard. Yeah, I killed a few of 'em in my time, too. (sniff)~ []
@1021744 = ~My name is <CHARNAME>... pleased to meet you.~ []
@1021751 = ~Well, just go down those stairs over there and you'll find Mae'Var engaged in the business of information extraction. Forcible extraction, that is.~ []
@1021754 = ~Er... thanks. I'll be on my way.~ []
@1021756 = ~<CHARNAME>... how utterly delicious. I shall recite it over and over to myself in between each of our meetings. Which, I do hope, will not be too far between, hm?~ []
@1021757 = ~Uh... could you direct me to Mae'Var?~ []
@1021760 = ~Er... could you direct me to Mae'Var, perhaps?~ []
@1021762 = ~Well, I am very pleased to meet you, <CHARNAME>. There truly aren't enough fellow sisters in the Shadow Thieves... although we are amongst the very best, aren't we?~ []
@1021768 = ~Mae'Var says that you are to be our newest member. How delightful to see a new face for one... Lin's did tire me so dreadfully. I am Anishai, and I am most pleased to meet you.~ []
@1021770 = ~I truly believe that Mae'Var has become a bit too big for himself. How very sad... I suppose it is only a matter of time, now.~ []
@1021775 = ~I wouldn't be crossing Edwin, if I were ye... I've heard some pretty nasty things about him since he arrived from the north.~ []
@1021776 = ~Everyone has been pretty nervous, here... I think Mae'Var's gone mad, he has.~ []
@1021781 = ~That is because I am not a thief! I... I am here merely to assist <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1021789 = ~The One God has demanded that his disciples achieve a higher state of wisdom... you must remove that which is limiting and offensive.~ []
@1021800 = ~Sadly, there are those who lack the stamina to serve the One God... their lack of faith betrays them. The bodies of these unfortunates are offered to the Pit of the Faithless.~ []
@1021809 = ~Alright... so how does one become a servant?~ []
@1021820 = ~I say yes. I never liked serving those fools anyway. I will enjoy their destruction..~ []
@1021821 = ~What is this item you speak of... and where would I locate it?~ []
@1021822 = ~You have... changed your mind, faithless one? Have you decided to enter the holy fold of the Unseeing Eye?~ [GAAL25]
@1021825 = ~The item is a rod... or part of a rod, rather, that you will find atop a holy altar. I cannot tell you more than that. You must let your faith guide you.~ []
@1021832 = ~And you will help me find Imoen for 15,000? I still wonder why you would do this.~ []
@1021837 = ~I have a key I can give you... this will allow you entrance to the inner chambers through a door a short distance back the way you came, at the sewer passages.~ []
@1021840 = ~What is this item you speak of... and where would I locate it?~ []
@1021846 = ~Somewhat.  You are certainly braver than the cattle inside. You leave the safety of the palisade with a confident stride and a dangerous look about you. Those fools within are frightened of their own shadows.~
@1021849 = ~Uhhhh... okay...~ []
@1021857 = ~No... but I have decided to end your worthless life!~ []
@1021865 = ~There is no such thing as 'safe risk.' Are your tasks for the thieves full of 'safe risk?' I doubt it very much so. I offer an alternative risk, nothing more.~ []
@1021866 = ~Perhaps they would, but they are not here. I am not without my defenses. I would not ask you here if I thought you were a threat.~ []
@1021868 = ~Such confidence is admirable. Very well, this place is now open to you. It is a safe haven, and below there are friends of mine that will tend to your trading needs.~ [BODHIX16]
@1021870 = ~I will side with you, Mistress, and may the gods have mercy on our enemies.~ []
@1021874 = ~That is... unfortunate. Very well, you may go.~ []
@1021876 = ~Hmm... be wary, my friends! Someone has come before us, I can sense it!~ [SASSAR02]
@1021884 = ~I wish a campaign of disruption, and you will begin it. There is a shipment of supplies arriving by boat. You are to... confiscate it.~ [BODHIX18]
@1021905 = ~But how am I to be of use if I am revealed as an enemy?~ []
@1021907 = ~There will be other things for you to do in time. These little chores are only the preliminary. I will speak of others later.~ []
@1021920 = ~Valen said something about a business opportunity?~ []
@1021921 = ~What would you have of me in this place?~ []
@1021923 = ~Reasons don't matter to the dead.~ []
@1021926 = ~Yes, I was to offer a... relationship... to oppose your current employers, but I do not think it will be available to you after all..~ []
@1021944 = ~By the gods! Haven't we paid off enough of the council to not have you idiot Amnish soldiers barge in here every time you feel like filling your arrest quotas?~ []
@1021948 = ~This is the buckler of Kiel the Legion-Killer, first-born son of Durlag Trollkiller and Clan-prince of his father's ill-fated tower. Its light weight and excellent craftsmanship increase the dexterity of all who bear it by a single point.

