@1022156 = ~The beholder has failed to acquire the rod because the gods have cursed the item. This lets you determine the artifact's true worth... or threat.~ []
@1022157 = ~Would you... would you be willing to go below and retrieve the artifact, my <PRO_LADYLORD>?~ []
@1022159 = ~Very well... I will go below and see if I can locate this rod.~ []
@1022162 = ~Very well... I shall return as soon as I am able.~ []
@1022164 = ~I am most grateful, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. We have tried, but our blindness limits us. This chamber we are in is safe... so long as the sarcophagus is not opened.~ []
@1022166 = ~Please do not hurt us, noble one!~ [SASSAR11]
@1022167 = ~You have no eyes... are you members of the Unseeing Eye's flock, then?~ []
@1022171 = ~Is... is that you? Have you returned successful?~ [SASSAR12]
@1022175 = ~Yes... I have half of the rod here with me.~ []
@1022176 = ~Ah... that is sad news, indeed. I urge you to return to the levels below, my <LADYLORD>, as soon as you are able! The beholder must be stopped!~ []
@1022180 = ~Otiluke's Resilient Sphere (Alteration) 
Level: 4
Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: Target creature
Saving Throw: Neg.

When this spell is cast, the result is a globe of shimmering force that encloses the subject creature if it fails to successfully save vs. spell. The resilient sphere will contain its subject for the duration of the spell. The sphere is completely immune to all damage. Actually, the only method of removing the sphere is a successful dispel magic. Hence the creature caught inside the globe is completely safe from all attacks, but at the same time is completely unable to affect the outside world.~
@1022181 = ~Remove Curse (Abjuration)
Level: 4
Range: Touch 
Duration: Permanent 
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: Special 

Upon casting this spell, the wizard is usually able to remove a curse affecting the target of the spell. The Remove Curse spell does not remove the curse from a cursed object, although the spell typically enables the person afflicted with any such cursed item to get rid of it. Certain special curses may not be countered by this spell, or may be countered only by a caster of a certain level.~ []
@1022183 = ~The Unseeing Eye is in a great pit in the center of the cult compound. You cannot enter the pit by the stairs: the beholder's minions would slay you.~ []
@1022184 = ~But you must get into the pit. There is a niche where the beholder stores his treasures... including the rod. There is a safe way to get to that niche.~ []
@1022186 = ~Greater Malison (Enchantment/Charm)
Level: 4
Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: 2 rounds/level 
Casting Time: 4 
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None

The spell allows the caster to adversely affect the saving throws of enemies. The effect is applied to all hostile creatures within the area of effect. Opponents under the influence of this spell make all saving throws at a penalty of -4. Multiple castings of Greater Malison are not cumulative.~ []
@1022195 = ~You will find him by the Pit of the Faithless... do hurry, my <LADYLORD>! The beholder continues to mesmerize and murder the innocent even as we speak!~ []
@1022200 = ~Please, my <LADYLORD>... reconsider! The creature must be stopped, and with the piece of the rod, you are the only one who can do it!~ []
@1022203 = ~So... you're the leader of this lot? Perhaps you can tell me how to get to the beholder lair above, then.~ []
@1022205 = ~You... you're here to kill me, aren't you?! Please! Tell Mae'Var it was all a misunderstanding!~ []
@1022206 = ~It is good to see you again! Have you need of my services, because I am ready to travel if you do. This place is dulling to the senses.~ [YOSHIM63]
@1022207 = ~Sorry... business is business, Embarl. Time to die.~ []
@1022234 = ~De'Tranion's Baalor Ale, brewed with pimentos for that extra little kick.~ []
@1022256 = ~Corpse of Evalt's brother Renfeld, retrieved from the Sirine.~ []
