@1023942 = ~  Leave here and do not return until your world ends.~ []
@1023944 = ~  You are... different.~ []
@1023945 = ~  I smell... outsider?~ []
@1023948 = ~  Some will not trust you... some like me.~ []
@1023954 = ~  I don't know you. You are... stranger.~ []
@1023965 = ~Seek out the befoulers!~ []
@1024001 = ~You! Are you for hire? As a mercenary, I mean? You look capable and hearty, like you've had formal training.~ []
@1024006 = ~Your grace, I am Mazzy Fentan, a valiant servant of justice and righteousness. As you can see, I could use your assistance.~ [MAZZY76]
@1024008 = ~Obviously you're not to be trusted. Even if you speak the truth, you deserve your fate.~ []
@1024022 = ~Contemptuous oaf! Have you no honor? If this is to be my fate, then don't envenom it further with your presence.~ []
@1024029 = ~It is here to dominate and to conquer. This Shade Lord seems to feed on the corruption of souls. If it is not stopped it will continue to build its army of shadows.~ []
@1024050 = ~You've a spiteful soul, <CHARNAME>. I'll go no further in this group. Leave me be. I have important work to accomplish and I'll not have it soiled with your presence.~ []
@1024051 = ~They died with honor regardless of what the Shade Lord did to them afterwards.~ []
@1024091 = ~Why don't you return when you've made some money? Perhaps you could pit-fight for the funds. Surly pays a bit to the winners of the dog fights.~ []
@1024098 = ~Yes, but we need to negotiate the price.~ []
@1024114 = ~Thanks... wait... you don't really mean it.~ []
@1024138 = ~You there! You look like you've... killed... before. Are you mercenaries? Capable mercenaries? No offense, but I need some help and it requires a harsh touch. 

~ []
@1024147 = ~Perhaps I can be of assistance, but my time is a valuable commodity.~ []
@1024152 = ~At present I am on sabbatical. I find myself missing the road and I long again for adventure. Does your party require another sword arm?~ []
@1024173 = ~My lost companions, my boon friends. May your souls rest in peace. I shall always carry your courage and your honor with me. I shall strike down evil in your name!~ [MAZZY78]
@1024184 = ~But... no, there is no point in arguing. Very well, but I hope you reconsider. Who knows what horrors are being visited upon my poor family even as we speak.~ []
@1024185 = ~You are very cruel. My family will be paupers... think of the servants we employ. We are kind, and I have given more than my share to those less fortunate.~ []
@1024192 = ~I would not have thought you so snobbish, but you certainly act it. I... I guess I cannot be choosy. I need help wherever I can get it. Will you help me?~ []
@1024195 = ~I risk my neck for a favor, save you from some kind of enchanted slavery... and the first thing you think of is bad poetry?!~ []
@1024202 = ~Some secrets are for keeping, Haer'Dalis.~ []
@1024203 = ~It should be on Mekrath's altar... should you retrieve it, I will be with my mistress at the playhouse under the Five Flagons, waiting anxiously for its return. May we meet again...~ []
@1024204 = ~A bard to sing my praises? My dear Haer'Dalis, how could I refuse?~ []
@1024213 = ~And tear you from your troupe, Haer'Dalis? The critics would drag me through the coals for stealing such a fine talent.~ []
@1024225 = ~Now... in the altar of this wizard's lair is a very important gem. Our dear friend Mekrath took it from me and I must have it back. Come, let us look for it and return to Raelis as soon as possible.~ []
@1024231 = ~I fear I cannot. You will have to get someone else.~ []
@1024234 = ~I must return to Raelis, but please... find that gem and bring it to me there. Both she and I shall be greatly in your debt.~ []
@1024238 = ~You are with Raelis? Well, well, well... my hide may yet be saved. Come, let me join with you and we shall be done with the foul humors of this place.~ []
@1024245 = ~There you are! I've been waiting positively AGES for you. I did a little scouting around and the outer walls have been breached. That means they are inside, and we'll have a tough time getting them out.~ [NALIA60]
@1024246 = ~I've practiced! I'm going to be someone that gives to the poor and takes from the rich, I am. We've got lots to spare... and it's fun, too.~ []
@1024247 = ~Whatever the reason, they are here. I am sorry, but I don't know numbers or tactics; I only know that we must get rid of them... we must rescue my family, that is all.~ []
@1024248 = ~You'll have to sneak in and rescue someone. Perhaps... oh, what's his name... Daleson, the servant that tended the stables. He might be in there. Will you find him?~ []
@1024251 = ~I had no interest in you before, and I have no interest in you now.~ []
@1024258 = ~We need more information. If we march through the front door it will be a slaughter.~ []
@1024259 = ~We don't know how many they have, how smart they are, or even if there is anyone left alive to rescue.~ []
@1024261 = ~Perhaps... oh, what's his name... Daleson! He worked in the stables. They may have left him to tend the animals for food. He would know! He might be inside.~ []
@1024269 = ~But you have come all this way... No, if you do not wish to help then I will not ingratiate myself further. I see quite enough of that from the nobles around here.~ []
@1024270 = ~Is it cowardly to live through the day? You can certainly storm the front gates if you like, but what happens to my family when the trolls realize you are there?~ []
@1024286 = ~Enter north of the palisade, though a secret door along the wall of the keep. I used it to sneak out at night. Aunty never approved, but I didn't care.~ []
@1024288 = ~Is it cowardly to live through the day? We can storm the front gates if you like, but what happens when the trolls realize we are there?~ []
@1024292 = ~I can't go another step without knowing who we face. I will not go blind into this.~ []
@1024293 = ~We need more information. A frontal assault would be a slaughter.~ []
@1024294 = ~We don't know how many they have, or even if there is anyone left alive to rescue.~ []
@1024331 = ~Yes, my friend. I thank you again for your support. I suggest that we seek out the Temple Superior, Overgold Renwellyn. We've no proof of Barl's guilt other than Wallace's word and my suspicions.~ []
@1024339 = ~Why no, I've seen them just this week. I expect wedding bells'll be comin' for the two of them.~ []
@1024347 = ~Shut up and listen, old man. We know your buddy Barl's been poisoning people and we're gonna kill him. Where is he?~ []
@1024350 = ~I assure you this is true. Barl supplies Wallace, a local merchant, with potions... and one of those potions poisoned Mazzy's sister.~ []
@1024360 = ~What? But I just joined... oh, very well. I can't wait around for you though. I have to go to my family's land and help them. If you still want to help then that's where you should go. I'll meet you there and we can plan the attack.~ [NALIA97]
@1024364 = ~I have no intention of helping you. Get someone else.~ []
@1024375 = ~But... but we've been together such a short while. Please, do you still intend to help me defend my family's keep?~ [NALIA93]
@1024376 = ~Please, you did promise. We need to go to my family's land and join the defense. If you have changed your mind, please tell me.~ [NALIA69]
@1024387 = ~You could have said earlier! I need to be there! They may already be... Goodbye and thanks for nothing!~ []
@1024389 = ~We must get to Daleson soon. They may kill him, and then we'll have no idea what we're up against! He should be inside next to the secret door.~ [NALIA71]
@1024390 = ~Now, there be a vital gem nestled within the stench of this place... in an altar, I believe. Mekrath took it from me and I must have it back. Come, let us retrieve it before we venture further.~ []
@1024392 = ~Mekrath has stolen an important gem from my keeping and locked it away within an altar in this lair. Find it and I shall stand guard over ye mewling babes 'til we return to Raelis.~ []
@1024409 = ~You want fight Gorf? Hah, hah, hah!~ []
@1024414 = ~Ugh, that much good. Gorf ready to fight, pit man!~ []
@1024423 = ~How dishonorable! The boorishness of the large people never ceases to amaze me.~ [MAZZY84]
@1024425 = ~You told him, Mazzy!~ []
@1024435 = ~We need comrades, not servants, Haer'Dalis. What skills do you bring with you?~ []
@1024447 = ~It'll do... Welcome to the group, Haer'Dalis.~ []
@1024450 = ~More than enough, Haer'Dalis, more than enough. My apologies for doubting you.~ []
@1024452 = ~It is mine and I was on my way to deliver it to Raelis Shai of the Sigil theater troupe when he captured me. Come, let us find it that Ms. Shai may reward us both for its safe delivery.~ []
@1024453 = ~I don't believe that it's any of your business, hound. Now may I join you or is this meeting over?~ []
@1024455 = ~You're right: This meeting's over.~ []
@1024456 = ~Of that, you have my word... Come, my late but unmourned captor has hidden a gem in an altar, here. It is imperative that I return it to Raelis Shai of the Sigil theater troupe and soon. You have my assurance that her reward shall be generous.~ []
@1024458 = ~A word to the wise, however: it is best you come to her with gifts. I had a gem that would have served the purpose nicely but the late Mekrath saw fit to steal it from my hands. It is in an altar in this place... I strongly recommend you take it with you.~ []
@1024468 = ~Very well, Haer'Dalis. Friendship... Welcome aboard.~ []
@1024473 = ~I believe the jewel lies within an altar, here... If we can find the jewel and complete the delivery, then I shall place myself at your every command.~ []
@1024476 = ~If you find it, I ask that you deliver it to the playhouse of the Sigil theater troupe where I will be waiting. I will see to it that my mistress rewards you greatly. Now fare thee well, my hounds of rescue, for time is short.~ []
@1024484 = ~This is the second half of the Rift Device Rod. The completed Rod may be used for the destruction of the Unseeing Eye.~ []
@1024485 = ~The mysterious Rift Device. 
This rod is said to be so destructive that it was cursed by the gods and buried deep within the Earth. The ancient god Amaunator and his worshippers were charged with the task of guarding it. Amaunator's fading Avatar has allowed you to use it with the expressed purpose of destroying the Unseeing Eye. The Avatar asked that you return it when your task is done, as it would be exceptionally dangerous to bring this device above ground.~ []
@1024487 = ~If we can find it, a certain Raelis Shai of the Sigil theater troupe shall reward us greatly for its return. Come, let us search for it and be done with these wretched airs.~ []
@1024491 = ~Should you find it, I ask that you deliver it to me at the playhouse of the Sigil theater troupe. I will see to it that my mistress rewards you greatly.~ []
@1024494 = ~You wound me... 'twas a simple verse. You think, mayhap, that my brain has been addled too long by arcane spells? Oh, what tragedy!~ []
@1024498 = ~ You can... feel the wrongness in such a place. It has seeped into the very rocks, themselves.~ [MAZZY18]
@1024515 = ~Mekrath has given you to me fairly... your only other choice would have been to remain a mindless slave.~ []
@1024516 = ~I'm from Imnesvale in the Umar Hills. People h-have been disappearing. Some of them have t-t-turned up, but they're all turned inside-out and mad.~ []
@1024526 = ~I suppose such actions are the only means of raising your status, but I still want your tromping about in these halls kept to a minimum. Delousing will interfere with my social schedule.~ []
@1024528 = ~Obviously those filthy creatures have swung the doors wide to any common traveler. You do look somewhat different than the fiends that entrapped me.~ []
@1024529 = ~Nalia sent you, didn't she? Only she would know where to get such ruffians. Consorting with servants will leave her dead like her softhearted mother, earning a virulent fever for her charitable excesses.~ []
@1024530 = ~I have a hazy recollection of it being in an altar, here... but should you ever find it, I know an actress of the Sigil theater troupe, Raelis Shai, who would pay a fine reward to any who might bring it to her.~ []
@1024534 = ~I must find it again so it may be returned to its rightful owner, Miss Raelis Shai of the Sigil theater troupe... Your help in this would mean a million worlds to me.~ []
@1024535 = ~Your friend Mekrath stole from me a certain gem that I must have back. If you can find it in this place... in an altar, if I remember right... please bring it to me at the playhouse. You will not go unrewarded.~ []
@1024540 = ~The gem is in an altar, here... so let's return it and reap a good reward. So put aside your illusions of grandeur for a while and help me find the blasted thing before Mekrath comes back.~ []
@1024541 = ~I suppose I should expect nothing less. Your lack of breeding is apparent in your close-set eyes. Loot as you will, but you will not get the satisfaction of a fearful response from me.~ []
@1024543 = ~I think you should be afraid. I do not keep baggage for no purpose. Prepare to die.~ []
@1024544 = ~Do, as you will. I will not lose my dignity just because you threaten my life. Indeed, I would rather die than lose respect for myself. Frankly, I don't know how you peasants stand it.~ []
@1024548 = ~... until yon mage cast me into bondage, of course. Miss Shai will reward you greatly for the jewel, of that I have no doubt. So come, I believe it lays in an altar here... let us find it 'ere the wizard returns.~ []
@1024550 = ~'Twas mine before my capture and I was delivering it to Raelis Shai, the Mistress of the Sigil theater troupe. I do not doubt that she would still reward us greatly for its delivery. Come, let us find it and be gone from here before the wizard fool returns.~ []
@1024554 = ~Do you now? Perhaps you are unsure where your place is? Below mine, and while your current actions may place my life in your hands, they certainly do not elevate you above your true station.~ []
@1024561 = ~Alright, then... just join with me and we'll figure it out as we go along.~ []
@1024563 = ~I don't have time for this... if you really want to go, then go. I don't need a companion who babbles so much.~ []
@1024567 = ~It is in an altar, here, and we must bring it to Raelis Shai, mistress of the Sigil theater troupe. I assure you, she shall be more than pleased to see it. Come, let us find it before more unpleasantness occurs.~ []
@1024573 = ~Haer'Dalis, there is always room for one such as you within my company.~ []
@1024576 = ~I doubt he will say a word. He's as soft as Nalia at times, but he does not lower himself to dealing with his lessers. Do rescue him, will you? It is your duty, I believe.~ []
@1024577 = ~In an altar, here, if I remember right. Once this gem was mine, you see, and it must be mine once more that I might deliver it to Raelis Shai of the Sigil theater troupe for she has need of it. Come, let us search this place and then make this long-delayed delivery.~ []
@1024582 = ~Oh, 'tis like a nightmare! Yet more hooligans tracking their filth through the halls! We shall have to vacation for a tenday while the whole building is deloused.~ [DELCIA02]
@1024583 = ~You are angry, my friend. This I understand implicitly. Injustice and indifference have always been the banes of our society. I often suspect that these sins pose more of a danger to us than any dragon ever could.~ [MAZZY67]
@1024591 = ~When Kalos heard Dana was gone, he and his friends took up what arms they could. They stormed the Baron's manor unthinking, like men gone berserk.~ []
@1024595 = ~If you could only find it and bring it to my quarters at the playhouse beneath the Five Flagons Inn, I promise you Miss Shai would be most grateful.~ []
@1024601 = ~It bears repeating my dear. She would slum as you do, offering charity to those beneath her, and her reward was a pestilence that took her life.~ []
@1024605 = ~Milady, we should save such discussion for another TIME. Let's move on. NOW.~ []
@1024610 = ~What am I saying? You will NEVER need to worry about being in a position such as I hold. Simply don't have the blood for it.~ []
@1024612 = ~Nalia, I think we should let your aunt get to safety while we MOVE ON. Now. Please.~ []
@1024621 = ~I would like that, Haer'Dalis.~ []
@1024624 = ~Return to your playhouse, Haer'Dalis. I shall look for this jewel you speak of and bring it to you there.~ []
@1024631 = ~Raelis Shai, Mistress of the Sigil theater troupe, beneath the Five Flagons Inn, would be more than pleased to have it in her possession. Come, let us retrieve it and make haste unto the playhouse.~ []
@1024632 = ~I believe the gem to be in an altar, here... if you could retrieve it and return it to me at the playhouse, Mistress Shai would be most pleased. It would be advisable that you hurry, too, as Mekrath will no doubt be returning shortly. Now I must go.~ []
@1024634 = ~Before my capture at Mekrath's hands, I carried with me a certain gem. I believe it to be in an altar, here... deliver it to me at the playhouse below the Five Flagons and Miss Shai will be more than grateful.~ []
@1024643 = ~Hmm? Oh! Yes, we should... really get moving. You will be safe back the way we came, Aunty, but I cannot go with you yet.~ []
@1024645 = ~You needn't whisper, dear, but do try to refrain from talking behind my back with the help, will you? It does not do them good to see their betters maligned.~ []
@1024648 = ~Rather an amusing bit of restraint on your part, and I appreciate that. She's decent enough, but very set in her ways and hard to deal with. Come, we must rescue my father.~ [NALIA72]
@1024649 = ~What? And who be you then? Come 'round the back way did ye? I suppose ye must have. Nothin' but trolls and snakes the front way. What are ye doin' here then?~ []
@1024650 = ~Fear not, I have come to rescue you.~ []
@1024654 = ~You? Rescue me? I ain't nobody, even the trolls know that, so they left me to tend the animals cuz I ain't no threat. Did Miss Nalia send you?~ []
@1024656 = ~Now why would you want to go and do something like that? Sure don't sound like you care much for the likes of me. It were Miss Nalia what sent you, wasn't it?~ []
@1024658 = ~Will you now? And why do you care about this place? Could only be two reasons. Either you heard this place ain't as poor as you say, or... or Miss Nalia sent you.~ []
@1024664 = ~Nalia did send me, and I just meant that I would stop the trolls from taking over.~ []
@1024670 = ~It's not like that at all. I'm just more interested in the combat and reward.~ []
@1024672 = ~Nothin' personal, but thrillseekers like you get us little guys hurt. I guess you're better than nothing, and probably better than Nalia. She means well, I suppose, but she's still a noble.~ []
@1024686 = ~Maybe thirty. There was a big troll that seemed to be in charge. I've kept out of sight, but I also heard him bossing something called a "yuan-ti". I don't know how many of those there are.~ []
@1024687 = ~Probably took him down to the dungeon. Lord de'Arnise had his dungeon boarded up, but I think them trolls sniffed it out. Don't know why they didn't just kill everyone.~ []
@1024701 = ~I'll just be staying right here, thanks all the same. They ain't bothered to come get me yet, and if you go out there making trouble, I think this is the safest place for me.~ []
@1024703 = ~Of course not, just having a little fun with you.~ []
@1024706 = ~You... you 're no better than the monsters out there. Have it your way, but make no mistake you will pay for this in the long run, I just knows it!~ []
@1024707 = ~This place isn't open to your kind anymore. This estate and all its possessions are now in the care of Family Roenall. Move along, rabble.~ []
@1024708 = ~He is well. He told me their strengths, and that a Lord de'Arnise was still alive.~ []
@1024709 = ~Storm Ring

This ring is worn by followers of the Storm Lord Talos, whose disciples await their god's wrath and welcome it eagerly. The ability to wreak havoc and ruin are the principal ideals that Talos desires in his subjects.~ []
@1024711 = ~Sniff... SNIFFFFFF... I smell you... I do... you gradunk no be hiding on TorGal!~ [TOGAL03]
@1024717 = ~I rain 'cross many places, what think you gradunk leave here dry? I TorGal, and I trgank lead Rocksmash pack! We serve Stronger, so who traag you to say no?!~ []
@1024718 = ~You grrranktal no tell me what be done! None but Stronger tell TorGal what fregRrrrt be done! Who you to say to Rocksmash pack? GweRrl?~ []
@1024720 = ~Who ask grgath like you what should die? Rocksmash pack think all die, now have what stronger grrreth want. TorGal do good job, now you rrrthag die for fun!~ []
@1024722 = ~Mekrath stole it from me and has hidden it in an altar within this place. Come, let us rescue it from its unjust confinement and reap our reward at the playhouse.~ []
@1024723 = ~I believe it to be in an altar, here... return it to me at the playhouse of the Sigil theater troupe. I assure you that my mistress, Raelis Shai, would be more than grateful. With your leave, my hounds of chaos, I must make my exit. I pray we meet again.~ []
@1024724 = ~Goodman Valygar! I tire. Would you please prepare my bedroll and fetch extra wood for the fire. There seems to be a chill in the air.~ [MAZZY50]
@1024728 = ~Perhaps I should have made a formal request, but... I am new to this as well... There is none other more fit to be my squire. You are a gentleman... a friend.~ []
@1024732 = ~It is a large building... a large orange building to the southwest of the Docks District. There will be a man guarding the door... his name is Rylock. Please, take me to him...~ []
@1024739 = ~It is... no use, I am afraid. I have already attempted to neutralize the poison inside me. I... do not know... what has been done to me. Please... I must go to my friends...~ []
@1024742 = ~Very well... I will take you now.~ []
@1024744 = ~Reward? (groan)  I... I have nothing to offer you... aside from my gratitude and those of my friends. Please... I do not have much time...~ []
@1024747 = ~Very well... I'll take you there.~ []
@1024749 = ~Th-thank you. I... do not have long to live. You must take me there quickly... (groan) ... take me to Rylock...~ []
@1024750 = ~H-have... have you no compassion? I... I am dying. Nobody will aid me... please, I am begging you...~ []
@1024754 = ~You? P-please... I ask you again... please help me...~ []
@1024764 = ~He has been poisoned, somehow... but he said magic was not able to cure it. He seemed desperate to find you.~ []
@1024765 = ~He is... sick? I shall bring him inside immediately. Thank you, friend, for doing this. We are most grateful. Here is a small reward for you troubles.~ []
@1024766 = ~A reward? Er... yes, I suppose so. For you trouble. Renfeld appears ill... I must take him inside immediately. Thank you.~ []
@1024767 = ~This is a private residence. Thank you for bringing Renfeld to me. He appears ill, so I must bring him inside immediately. Some coin... for your trouble.~ []
@1024768 = ~Poisoned? By the gods! Thank you... I must bring him inside immediately! Here is some coin, for your trouble. I thank you again, friend.~ []
@1024769 = ~Yes? Is there someth... Renfeld? He is dead? What has happened to him?~ []
@1024773 = ~Poisoned? It is a sad thing, then, that he did not arrive to us soon enough. Thank you for bringing his body... we are most appreciative.~ []
@1024781 = ~Hm. Alright... for your trouble, I suppose. I thank you again for bringing the body to us. Good day to you.~ []
@1024782 = ~None of those questions are your concern. Here... some money to cover your trouble. I must take him inside, now... thank you and good day.~ []
@1024784 = ~We maintain the balance, fool... and every Harper goes more out of his or her way for the common good than anyone else ever cares to. (sigh)~ []
@1024787 = ~You have one of our brethren with you!  We must resurrect her immediately and... what is wrong? I feel great ugliness around her... a foul curse!~ []
@1024793 = ~Good. This will make things easier for every one.~ []
@1024795 = ~ I am yours to command.~ [MAZZY22]
@1024797 = ~Conjure Lesser Earth Elemental 
(Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 5
Range: 15 yards
Duration: 1 turn + 1 round/level
Casting Time: Special
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

When cast, this spell summons a lesser earth elemental to do the caster's bidding. The elemental has 8 hit dice, and will serve the caster's every whim until the spell duration expires or the elemental dies. However, every time this spell is cast, there is a 15% chance that the elemental will escape the caster's control and attack the being who dared summon it. For this reason, the spell requires rigid concentration after the casting in order to gain full control of the elemental. This mental contest with the elemental lasts for three rounds after the summoning. At the end of this time, if the caster has prevailed, he or she has control of the elemental; otherwise, the elemental becomes an enemy.~ []
@1024799 = ~Conjure Lesser Fire Elemental 
(Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 5
Range: 15 yards
Duration: 1 turn + 1 round/level
Casting Time: Special
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

When cast, this spell summons a lesser fire elemental to do the caster's bidding. The elemental has 8 hit dice, and will serve the caster's every whim until the spell duration expires or the elemental dies. However, every time this spell is cast, there is a 15% chance that the elemental will escape the caster's control and attack the being who dared summon it. For this reason, the spell requires rigid concentration after the casting in order to gain full control of the elemental. This mental contest with the elemental lasts for three rounds after the summoning. At the end of this time, if the caster has prevailed, he or she has control of the elemental; otherwise, the elemental becomes an enemy.~ []
@1024800 = ~Conjure Lesser Air Elemental 
(Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 5
Range: 15 yards
Duration: 1 turn +1 round/level
Casting Time: Special
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

When cast, this spell summons a lesser air elemental to do the caster's bidding. The elemental has 8 hit dice, and will serve the caster's every whim until the spell duration expires or the elemental dies. However, every time this spell is cast, there is a 15% chance that the elemental will escape the caster's control and attack the being who dared summon it. For this reason, the spell requires rigid concentration after the casting in order to gain full control of the elemental. This mental contest with the elemental lasts for three rounds after the summoning. At the end of this time, if the caster has prevailed, he or she has control of the elemental; otherwise, the elemental becomes an enemy.~ []
@1024801 = ~Ah, such passion! You set me on fire with your words... and with your lovely body, as well...~ []
@1024803 = ~Well... er, no, not really...~ []
@1024806 = ~By Arvoreen, not you! And stop calling me your little chestnut... that is a ridiculous name.~ []
@1024809 = ~But Salvanas aches to hear your every word, my sweet... even if they are cruel and punishing...~ []
@1024811 = ~Hello, my pretty dove. I am Salvanas... and I am so pleased that my gaze has chanced to fall upon you...~ []
@1024813 = ~But of course I am talking to you... your skin is so pale, your gaze so innocent and your hips so rounded... I burn with sudden, aching desire!~ []
@1024817 = ~Ahhh... I have not seen you here, before, lovely creature. How do you do?~ []
@1024820 = ~Why... I'm just fine, you -- (aargh! hold your tongue, fool!)  Begone, you slithering eel!~ []
@1024821 = ~Ah, yes... the eel... I slither about your loveliness because you draw me to you. You... with your dark lashes and your come-hither eyes...~ []
@1024823 = ~Salvanas understands you. He hears your words and he feels your passion. Your fire ignites my own, my sweet... come to me...~ []
@1024824 = ~My, but you are a flatterer! (Gah!)  I mean... stop it, get lost! A fireball in your gullet would dampen your mood, lizard!!~ []
@1024825 = ~Nothing could keep me away from your exotic grace... those hands... those lips... that throat... that, er, adam's apple?~ []
@1024834 = ~We shall build a temple around the sphere! Yes... yes, a temple! The faithful shall come from miles around to see it!~ []
@1024835 = ~And we shall... shall... charge admission! Yes! Admission! Oooo! Now that IS a good idea...~ []
@1024841 = ~Jaheira, our meeting here was no accident. I have waited for this moment, for this time when I would reward your filthy libelous ways.~ []
@1024847 = ~No, I don't think... oh, yes. I reckon someone did do just that a couple o' weeks ago. Zapped into a pile o' ashes quicker than ye could blink.~ []
@1024856 = ~Children throwing apples, merchants loosing the hounds, hunters with their arrows... and for what? Tales around a dinner table, a few guffaws at a watering hole?~ []
@1024857 = ~Oh, er... the l'il fella says all that, does he?~ []
@1024868 = ~You... er... you think so? Too cheap?~ []
@1024870 = ~Say... you are right, sir! From now on, the asking price is 10,000 gold pieces!~ []
@1024878 = ~Yes, well... er...200 gold pieces?~ []
@1024882 = ~Well, in some places that wouldn't narrow things down, much. I take it, however, that you are bellowing at me, good sir.~ []
@1024884 = ~I'd say you remind me of my cousin Rintin. Grew the largest turnip one summer, larger than a house, almost. Well... larger than his house, at any rate.~ []
@1024888 = ~All six of them arrived one day and poor Rintin couldn't even pull it out of the ground. Went purple from exhaustion... which actually disguised him rather well in front of the turnip.~ []
@1024891 = ~Er... ummm... You! You over there! No, not the gnome... you!~ []
@1024899 = ~Er... me?~ []
@1024905 = ~Excellent doing business with you! I'll just... leave you alone with your new purchase.~ []
@1024909 = ~This is wrong... you can't go selling something like that!~ []
@1024910 = ~Besides, your coins are nothing compared to sweet revenge! Your deaths will complete my victory! Meet my assassins! They will make short work of the lot of you!~ []
@1024912 = ~Jiscanan, the younger son, left to use the outhouse. I jammed a stake in the door, trapping him inside. Then I set the building aflame.~ []
@1024913 = ~You... open it with a magic word. Yes... a magic word. Which I will sell to you for the 500 gold pieces.~ []
@1024921 = ~Rats! Hmm... You! Hey you! You over there!~ []
@1024930 = ~Er... who, might I ask, is your husband?~ []
@1024936 = ~Rumar's around here somewhere! No one will tell me where he is! But I'll get him... and his cheap slattern, too!~ []
@1024939 = ~Mmmm... now?~ [SSWORD05]
@1024947 = ~Er... ah... yes, ma'am. Right away, ma'am...~ []
@1024950 = ~You must be Rumar. Oh, yeah... she's still looking for you, alright.~ []
@1024955 = ~I thought I heard her bellow, earlier. If so... well... I'll just have to take my time with my little dalliance, here. Bwahaha!~ []
@1024956 = ~Er... I think she must have left, already, then.~ []
@1024957 = ~Well, if you're talking about Lady Tiana... no, she's out there, alright.~ []
@1024960 = ~Really? Well, be a sport and don't mention my whereabouts to her. I'm rather... tied up with my little pumpkin, here. Isn't that right, pumpkin?~ []
@1024967 = ~(chuckle) Oh, do not glare at me so, <CHARNAME>. I am only teasing. This girl was raised with you, I understand... so, yes, naturally you will spring to her rescue.~ []
@1024968 = ~(eek!) Uh... darling?~ [RUMAR01]
@1024970 = ~Yes, dear...~ [RUMAR02]
@1024976 = ~In this one instance, however, my men are limited. I need someone of skill who is not one of the Shadow Thieves... someone more or less unknown to us.~ []
@1024977 = ~G-g-girls... ladies... d-don't fight!~ []
@1024981 = ~I don't have time to hear you prattle on, Viconia... leave me be.~ []
@1024984 = ~I... I'm alright, Rumie. The witch didn't hurt me too bad.~ []
@1024986 = ~Sorry, nothing. We're getting married, Rumie... NOW.~ []
@1024987 = ~Don't talk of Sarevok like you know anything about it. Believe me, you haven't a clue... so remain quiet.~ []
@1024993 = ~Everyone must endure hardships Viconia. Come... let's continue our journey.~ []
@1024997 = ~Legs and hands, I have hands again! I am free of this horrible place! Thank you so much! I must... Giran! I hope my son hasn't gone far. Momma's on her way!~ []
@1025000 = ~You fool! You... you truly know nothing... I am Kalah, an illusionist. I was made a clown-mage for the pleasure of the tall folk... but I bided my time... and I was... promised a world I could rule...~ []
@1025009 = ~Nobody cheats Minsc! If somebody dares to cheat me they are in for a boot-stomping adjustment to their moral value systems!~ []
@1025014 = ~Of course I have been cheated. And I have cheated others. Cheated death, cheated life... it is all the same thing, and the inevitable process of social decay.~ []
@1025015 = ~Your grasp of the obvious rubs salt in my wounds... my world, my triumph... all gone...~ []
@1025017 = ~Enough of your morbid story, Viconia... I can hear no more.~ []
@1025019 = ~Er... no, I don't.~ []
@1025021 = ~He dropped to his knees in shock, which afforded me a height advantage as I caved his head with a miner's mallet.~ []
@1025024 = ~I am... glad that you had your revenge.~ []
@1025029 = ~Hmmm... you're not a Cowled Wizard, are you? Hmmm... mmm... it's for soup. Yes, that's it. Salamander soup. For my, er, children... and things. (grumble)  Do you see it or not?~ []
@1025033 = ~Oh... what do you need salamander dust for?~ []
@1025034 = ~Sorry... I have to go.~ []
@1025040 = ~Er... no, I don't see anything here.~ []
@1025041 = ~Why... hmmm... yes. Yes I do. Waaaaay over at the other side of the store there.~ []
@1025045 = ~I've known Ribald here since... hmm... since that l'il adventure there in Shadowdale. Isn't that right, Ribald?~ []
@1025052 = ~Watch fer thieves in the slums and docks, me friend. Me... I be not worried. Killed three last week, I did.~ []
@1025054 = ~Ye should be wary of the Cowled Wizards, if ye e'er cross paths with them. They be a frightenin' lot... the only ones in Athkatla who may practice magic.~ []
@1025058 = ~So, what do you think of Amn so far? It is certainly not without its charms, or its hardships lately.~ [JAHEIR92]
@1025063 = ~There does not seem to be a healthy balance between the two.~ []
@1025071 = ~I do not know either. The bars have no lock at all, they are smithed together. I am proud that they feared me enough to imprison me permanently!~ []
@1025092 = ~I know you will do it! I only travel with heroes!~ []
@1025097 = ~You return! And with the means to rescue me, no doubt! Haha... I see hope in your face! Dirt mostly, but hope is there too.~ [MINSC75]
@1025106 = ~The bars! They bend and twist with my berserker strength! Minsc and Boo are free! Now you will... nuh... now...~ [MINSC76]
@1025107 = ~Ooooh! Ohhh hoho... you are a smart one. I understand now! You said what you did just to get me mad! Mad enough to break free! Haha! You are as smart as Boo sometimes!~ [MINSC77]
@1025111 = ~Um... yeah. I think perhaps we should... split up.~ []
@1025117 = ~Now... now, I say, just what kind o' friend are ye, anyway to say such things about me?~ []
@1025121 = ~Aye, I did. Last week. Huge thing, it is, larger than life an' twice as grim. No one knows how t' get inside... and no one's come out.~ []
@1025131 = ~Well... well, I does some cobblin' NOW, sure. But BEFORE that I were an adventurer!~ []
@1025133 = ~I... well, if ye must be knowin', I was well known in Scornubel for a time.~ []
@1025135 = ~Er... well, I... no. (grumble)  Sometimes, I really does hate ye, Ribald.~ []
@1025139 = ~I'm warning ye, Ribald... ye keep that wyvern away from me, now...~ []
@1025142 = ~Ahhh... hello, my dear lady. You do look so... delicious... that the mere thought of wrapping my tongue around you enflames my mind with feelings of desire...~ []
@1025145 = ~Really? Hmmm... I am having thoughts very much along those lines, myself...~ []
@1025149 = ~My, that is quite the line... I feel myself getting warm and tingly all over...~ []
@1025167 = ~Oh? That doesn't sound like such a bad idea... I'm thinking I wouldn't mind that, myself...~ []
@1025172 = ~You are? I mean... your enthusiasm makes my head simply swim with giddy relief, I am awash in the ocean of your eyes, drowning in your field of dreams...~ []
@1025175 = ~Oooo, alright, then... just let me go and rent one of the inn's rooms. Prepare yourself for a night of pure passion that you'll not soon forget!~ []
@1025183 = ~Prepare...? Really? You... um... want to get a room, here? Well, I... I... I think I hear my captain calling! Yes, my captain! COMING, CAPTAIN!!~ []
@1025186 = ~archer~ []
@1025201 = ~BERSERKER: Berserkers are warriors in tune with their animalistic side and, during combat, can achieve an ecstatic state of mind that will enable them to fight longer, harder and more savagely than any humanoid has a right to. Berserkers tend to be barbarian-like in nature, but not always. Sometimes it is a conscious choice that a warrior in training makes. Regardless, opponents on the battlefield will be unsettled when they see the savage elements of the berserker's personality. This class is common amongst dwarves, known to them as 'battleragers'.

Berserkers may not be of any Lawful alignments.

Advantages:
-  May use 'enrage' ability once per day per 4 levels. The enraged state lasts for 60 seconds.
-  While enraged: +2 to hit, +2 damage, -2 AC
-  While enraged: immune to charm, hold, fear, maze, imprisonment, stun, confusion, level drain, feeblemind, and sleep
-  While enraged: gains 15 hit points. These hit points are temporary, and are taken away at the end of the berserk spree, possibly killing the berserker.

Disadvantages:
-  Becomes winded after berserking. While winded receives penalties of -2 to hit, -2 to damage and +2 to armor class.
-  Cannot specialize (two proficiency points) in ranged weapons (bows, crossbows, slings, or darts)~ []
@1025202 = ~Will none of you people listen? Anyone? I've helped your kind, now why won't you help me?~ [NALIA63]
@1025203 = ~WIZARD SLAYER: These warriors have been specially trained by their sect to excel in hunting and attacking spellcasters of all kinds.

Advantages:
-  For each successful melee hit on an opponent, 10% cumulative spell failure penalty is applied
-  2% magic resistance per level

Disadvantages:
-  May not use ANY magic items (potions other than healing potions, scrolls, rings, amulets, cloaks, etc.) except for weapons and armor~ []
@1025204 = ~KENSAI: Kensai are also known as 'Sword Saints', warriors who have been specially trained to be one with their swords. They are deadly and fast and trained to fight without encumbrance.

Kensai may not be of any Chaotic alignments.

Advantages:
-  Bonus +1 to hit and +1 damage for every 3 levels
-  Bonus -2 to AC
-  Bonus -1 to speed factor for every 4 levels
-  May use 'kai' ability one time per day for every 4 levels (starts at 1st level with one use): this ability lasts 10 seconds and makes all attacks do maximum damage.

Disadvantages:
-  May not use missile weapons (slings, bows and crossbows, darts) unless they also have a melee component (such as magic axes and daggers that can be both used in melee and hurled)
-  May not wear any armor
-  May not wear gauntlets or bracers~ []
@1025206 = ~CAVALIER: This class represents the most common picture of the knight: the gentleman warrior who epitomizes honor, courage and loyalty. He is specialized in battling 'classical' evil monsters such as demons and dragons.

Advantages:
-  Bonus +3 to hit and +3 to damage against all demonic and draconic creatures. 
-  May cast 'remove fear' 1 time per day per level
-  Immune to fear and morale failure
-  Immune to charm
-  Immune to poison
-  20% resistance to fire
-  20% resistance to acid

Disadvantages:
-  May not use missile weapons (slings, bows and crossbows, darts) unless they also have a melee component (such as magic axes and daggers that can be both used in melee and hurled)~ []
@1025207 = ~INQUISITOR: The Inquisitor's life has been dedicated to finding and eliminating practitioners of evil magic and defeating the forces of darkness, and the Inquisitor's god has provided special abilities towards that end.

Advantages:
-  May use 'Dispel Magic' ability once per day per 4 levels (starts at 1st level with one use): ability is used at speed factor 1 and acts at twice the Inquisitor's actual level.
-  May cast 'True Sight' once per day per 4 levels (starts at 1st level with one use)
-  Immune to Hold and Charm spells

Disadvantages:
-  May not use 'lay on hands' ability
-  May not cast priest spells
-  May not turn undead
~ []
@1025208 = ~UNDEAD HUNTER: This holy avenger's abilities have been honed towards the destruction of the undead and other unnatural creatures, and the Undead Hunter is immune to many of their more devastating abilities.

Advantages:
-  +3 to hit and +3 damage vs. undead
-  Immune to Hold
-  Immune to level drain

Disadvantages:
-  May not use 'lay on hands' ability~ []
@1025209 = ~ARCHER: The archer is the epitome of skill with the bow, the ultimate in accuracy, able to make almost any shot no matter how difficult. To become so skilled with the bow, the archer has had to sacrifice some proficiency with melee weapons and armor.

Advantages:
-  Can achieve grandmastery (five points) in bow missile weapons (bows and crossbows)
-  +1 to hit, and +1 to damage with any missile weapon for every 3 levels of experience.
-  Every 4 levels, gains the ability to make a called shot once per day. When this ability is activated, any shot made within the next 10 seconds is augmented in the following manner (according to the level of the archer):
4th level:  -1 to THAC0 of target
8th level:  -1 to save vs magic of target
12th level:  -1 to strength of target
16th level:  +2 bonus to damage

Disadvantages:
-  Can only become proficient (one point) in melee weapons (including those that can also be used as missile weapons.)
-  Can only become specialized (two points) in non-bow missile weapons (ie darts and slings.)
-  Cannot wear any metal armor.
-  No Charm Animal ability~ []
@1025211 = ~STALKER: Stalkers serve as covert intelligence-gatherers, comfortable in both wilderness and urban settings. They are the spies, informants, and interrogators, and their mastery of stealth makes them deadly opponents.

Advantages:
-  +20% to stealth ability
-  Has access to three mage spells at 12th level. They are Haste, Protection from Normal Missiles and Minor Spell Deflection.
-  May backstab for a lesser amount than the thief class (double damage at levels 1-8, triple damage at levels 9-16, quadruple damage at levels 17 and above)

Disadvantages:
-  May not wear armor greater than studded leather~ []
@1025212 = ~BEAST MASTER: This ranger is a wanderer, and is not comfortable in civilized lands, maintaining a natural affinity for animals; they are the Beast Master's friends and comrades-in-arms, and the Beast Master has a limited form of telepathic communication with them.

Advantages:
-  +15% to stealth ability
-  Enhanced spell ability with regard to the following spells:
-  May cast the 1st level wizard spell Find Familiar.
-  May cast the 4th level druid spell Animal Summoning 1 at 8th level.
-  May cast Animal Summoning 2 at 10th level.
-  May cast Animal Summoning 3 at 12th level.

Disadvantages:
-  Cannot use any metal weapons (such as swords, halberds, hammers or morning stars)
-  Cannot wear armor heavier than studded leather~ []
@1025213 = ~ASSASSIN: This is a killer trained in discreet and efficient murder, relying on anonymity and surprise to perform his task.

Advantages:
-  Weapon may be coated with poison once per day per 4 levels. Any weapon may be poisoned for five rounds when this ability is used. Successful hits will inject the poison into the target, dealing out 1 damage per second for 24 seconds (3 damage for the first 6 seconds). A saving throw vs. poison limits damage to 12 total. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative.
-  Bonus +1 to hit and +1 damage
-  Backstab reaches x7 instead of x5

Disadvantages:
-  Only 15 points per level to distribute on thief abilities~ []
@1025215 = ~BOUNTY HUNTER: This is a hunter of men, skilled in tracking quarry and bringing them back alive... whether for lawful authorities or underworld masters. Bounty Hunters are specially trained at their task and make fearsome opponents. They have honed their trap making abilities well beyond that of the average thief.

Advantages:
-  +15% to trap setting
-  Can lay special traps (other than the ones that all thieves receive). The traps are more powerful than the typical thief trap, and the effect varies according to level. The effects are listed below:
1st: the trap deals out damage and slows the target (if save is failed)
11th:  The trap holds the target if a save is failed
16th:  The trap erects an Otiluke's resilient sphere around the target if save is failed
21st:  The trap mazes the target (no save given)

Disadvantages:
-  Gets only 20 points to distribute between thief abilities each level~ []
@1025216 = ~SWASHBUCKLER: This rogue is part acrobat, part expert swordfighter and part wit: the epitome of charm and grace.

Advantages:
-  Bonus +1 to AC.
-  Gains another +1 bonus to Armor Class every 5 levels.
-  Gains +1 to hit and damage every 5 levels.
-  Can specialize in any melee weapon that a thief can use.
-  May place 3 slots into the proficiency 'Two Weapon Style'

Disadvantages:
-  No backstab multiplier~ []
@1025217 = ~BLADE: The Blade is an expert fighter and adventurer whose bardic acting abilities make this bard appear more intimidating and fearsome. The Blade's fighting style is flashy and entertaining, but is also quite deadly.

Advantages:
-  May use 'Offensive Spin' and 'Defensive Spin' abilities once per day per 4 levels
-  Offensive Spin: lasts 24 seconds, granting the Blade +2 to hit, +2 to damage, and an extra attack. As well, all attacks do maximum damage for the duration. Offensive spin cannot be used in conjunction with haste or improved haste.
-  Defensive Spin: lasts 24 seconds, roots him to the spot but gives -1 AC per level of experience. This armor class bonus does not go over -10.
-  May place 3 slots into two weapon fighting style

Disadvantages:
-  Only has one-half normal Lore value
-  Only has one-half Pick Pockets percentage.~ []
@1025218 = ~Nothing formal, usually... the normal rite is an act with which you and I are recently familiar with. But it does vary with some cultures.~ []
@1025219 = ~JESTER: This bard is well versed in the arts of ridicule and hilarity, whose abilities distract and confuse enemies as the Jester cavorts madly during combat. Do not mistake the Jester for a true fool, however, as this bard can also be quite deadly.

Advantages:
-  Unlike the typical bard's song, the Jester's does not help allies. Instead, it affects every opponent within 30 feet and varies with level:
1st:   Enemies must Save vs. Spells with a +2 bonus or be confused  
15th:  Enemies must Save vs. Spells with a +2 bonus or be confused, and must Save vs. Spells or be slowed
20th:  Enemies must Save vs. Spells with a +2 bonus or be confused and knocked unconscious, and must Save vs. Spells or be slowed.

Disadvantages:
-  None~ []
@1025220 = ~SKALD: A Nordic bard who is also a warrior of great strength, skill and virtue. The Skald's songs are inspiring sagas of battle and valor, and the Skald's life is devoted to those pursuits.

Advantages:
-  +1 to hit and +1 damage with all weapons
-  The Skald's song is different from the typical bard and varies with level:
1st:   Gives allies +2 to hit, +2 to damage and -2 to AC
15th:  Gives allies +4 to hit, +4 to damage, -4 to AC, and immunity to Fear
20th:  Gives allies +4 to hit, +4 to damage, -4 to AC, immunity to Fear, Stun and Confusion.

Disadvantages:
-  Pick pockets ability one-quarter normal~ []
@1025221 = ~PRIEST OF TALOS: Talos is the evil god of storms, destruction and rebellion. Clerics of the Stormlord warn that Talos must be appeased or he will rain destruction upon the land.

Advantages:
-  May cast 'Lightning bolt' once per day per 5 levels of the caster (starts at 1st level with one use).
-  May cast 'Storm Shield' once per day per 10 levels of the caster (starts at 1st level with one use), as detailed below. 

STORM SHIELD:  This spell lasts 6 seconds per level of the caster. It protects the caster from lightning, fire, cold and normal missiles.

Disadvantages:
-  None~ []
@1025222 = ~PRIEST OF HELM: Followers of the neutral God of Watchers and Protectors are warriors in their own right and are often seen as defenders of the innocent.

Advantages:
-  May cast 'True Sight' once per day per 5 levels (starts at 1st level with one use)
-  May cast 'Seeking Sword' once per day per 10 levels (starts at 1st level with one use), as detailed below.

SEEKING SWORD:  This spell creates a sword in the player's hand (that cannot be dropped or unequipped). The sword is +4 for purposes of determining what it can hit (but this bonus does not apply to damage), and it deals out 2-8 damage to any target it hits. The weapon sets the number of attacks of the cleric to 3. It lasts for 1 round per level of the caster. When equipped the wielder cannot cast further spells.

Disadvantages:
-  None
~ []
@1025223 = ~PRIEST OF LATHANDER: Lathander is the good god of renewal, creativity and youth, and is celebrated nearly everywhere. His followers are very popular throughout the Realms, and there are numerous wealthy temples devoted to Him.

Advantages:
-  May cast 'Hold Undead' once per day for every 5 levels of the caster (starts at 1st level with one use).
-  May cast 'Boon of Lathander' for every 10 levels of the caster, as detailed below (starts at 1st level with one use). 

BOON OF LATHANDER:  This spell lasts for 6 seconds per level of the caster. It gives the caster +1 to hit, +1 to damage, +1 to all saving throws and gives the caster 1 extra attack per round. It also protects the recipient from level drain.

Disadvantages:
-  None~ []
@1025224 = ~TOTEMIC DRUID: This druid closely identifies with a particular animal, an animal that is felt to represent the druid's spirit. This grants a special connection to the animal kingdom, and the ability to call upon their spirits to aid them.

Advantages:
-  May summon a special 'spirit' animal once per day per 5 levels of experience. Spirit animal is randomly selected from 'Spirit Bear', 'Spirit Wolf', 'Spirit Lion' and 'Spirit Snake'.

Disadvantages:
-  Cannot shapeshift~ []
@1025225 = ~SHAPESHIFTER: This druid is not called Shapeshifter because of access to a great variety of forms, rather because of the complete dedication to a single alternate form. This druid has willingly allowed infection with Lycanthropy, but due to intense study and training, has the ability to control the affliction. The creature shapeshifted to is that of the Werewolf, the most famous of the lycanthrope shape changers.

Advantages:
-  May shapeshift into the form of a werewolf once per day for every 2 levels (starts at 1st level with one use).
-  At 13th level gains the ability to change into a greater werewolf once per day.

Disadvantages:
-  No other shapeshifting abilities due to the effort required maintaining balance in primary forms
-  Cannot wear ANY armor~ []
@1025227 = ~AVENGER: A member of a special sect within the Druidic order, a druid of this type is dedicated to fighting those who would defile nature. Avengers have powers the average druid does not; additional abilities that have been earned through extensive rituals, a process that is very physically draining.

Advantages:
-  May shapechange into normal forms, as well as those of sword spider, baby wyvern and fire salamander
-  6 mage spells are added to spell repertoire, all the way up to 6th level. These are listed below:
1st:  Chromatic Orb
2nd:  Web
3rd:  Lightning Bolt
4th:  Improved Invisibility
5th:  Chaos
6th:  Chain lightning

Disadvantages:
-  May not wear better than leather (non-studded) armor.
-  On character creation, receives a -2 penalty to strength and constitution.~ []
@1025236 = ~I would see it be made a proper inn, and ensure that it never return to the hands of slavers. Please... I, who have never begged before, I beg this of you now...~ []
@1025253 = ~(sigh)  Very well... I will do what I can.~ []
@1025254 = ~(sigh)  Very well... I will do what I can.~ []
@1025255 = ~Perhaps later... I must go now.~ []
@1025278 = ~Willing or unwilling, it makes little difference. The gladiators fight to amuse our clientele... I'm sure you'll agree they put on an excellent show!~ []
@1025282 = ~The legalities are such a technicality... the amusements are here for your enjoyment. Let Lehtinan and his staff worry about such matters as legality.~ []
@1025283 = ~So... you're saying that there are fighters willing to risk their lives for the sake of entertainment?~ []
@1025287 = ~So... you're saying that there are fighters willing to risk their lives for the sake of entertainment?~ []
@1025291 = ~Slavery is such a harsh word, my <LADYLORD>. Here, we think of them as purchased employees... and an excellent source of entertainment! Go on in and witness it for yourself!~ []
@1025300 = ~Tell me, how did you come to be trapped here?~ []
@1025306 = ~The second last to die by my hand was Riklaunim, a devious controlling snake whose head leapt from his shoulders with a look of surprise I found most humorous.~ []
@1025307 = ~Everything that has gone wrong these days is because of those vile elves... they are the plague of the world, I tell you!~ []
@1025309 = ~Have you ever looked closely at an elf, aye? Narrow little eyes... narrow little faces... that can't be trusted!~ []
@1025315 = ~Never! The elven race should be seared from the face of Faerun, but you... you Drow... with your evil, blighted, cancerous hearts...!~ []
@1025322 = ~I lead no one to evil, human. And we elves have reason to be proud... we are an old race, far older than you.~ []
@1025325 = ~Oh, look... the moody <CHARNAME> does not feel like talking. What a surprise.~ []
@1025328 = ~B-but I... I have done nothing against you! Why do you rail at me so?~ []
@1025330 = ~I... I do not understand why you do this, sir, but I have done nothing to deserve it. I will not stand to have you cast such insults at me.~ []
@1025331 = ~'Will not stand'? 'Will not'?! Yet more elven pride! You elves are like ants... mindless and alien as you crawl about us!~ []
@1025337 = ~Don't worry... I'll be here to protect you.~ []
@1025342 = ~You had best watch your tongue, human... you are beginning to make me angry.~ []
@1025343 = ~I don't believe you, Viconia. You opened up to me... and now you snap shut again. Why?~ []
@1025345 = ~I am Belmin Gergas, elf... my son and daughter, both dead at the hands of your evil race! I shall see your kind wiped from the face of Faerun, I will!~ []
@1025352 = ~Very well, then, fool... you asked for it!~ []
@1025355 = ~Elven demon! Foul purveyor of evil seed! One day humanity shall recognize you for the evil you are! And then you shall die! ALL OF YOU SHALL DIE!!~ []
@1025356 = ~Do not deny your salivating male desires, fool. I found the thought of your touch pleasing, but now I know better... you are nothing more than a boy in man's clothing!~ []
@1025360 = ~I do so be missing my homeland... one day I am swearing to Calimshan I shall return. Yes, one day.~ []
@1025362 = ~Eh? Please be excusing me... this common tongue of yours is being very difficult for me.~ []
@1025370 = ~I am always willing to help those in need! I will give your troubles the one-two boot-stomp of goodness!~ []
@1025380 = ~Boo doesn't like rats either. Something about their tails makes him... edgy, and you don't know creepy until you've seen an edgy hamster!~ []
@1025383 = ~I am Sir Mardus, Guardian of Torm. Take your carcass out of my sight, foul one! By Torm's hand shall your ilk be taken from the earth.~ []
@1025391 = ~The young thieves these days, they not be knowin' what they're doin'. All vicious and murderin'... in my day we were respected. None was as smooth as me.~ []
@1025395 = ~It gained me respect in a society ruled by cruelty and ambition. I had lain with a male long before... many times, in fact. That is no measure of a Drow.~ []
@1025396 = ~I must say, some days I do surely miss me adventurin' and thievin' days... the Way were good to me, then. The best pickpocket ever is retired.~ []
@1025397 = ~Hello there, young feller... I knows ye, don't I? Yoshimo, isn't it?~ []
@1025399 = ~Eh... I find meself several days behind schedule on me sleep and several weeks ahead on me ales. All in all, it could be worse.~ []
@1025404 = ~That's what all the youngun' think. We'll see.~ []
@1025405 = ~And the act pleased Lolth. Pleasing the Spider Queen was our ethos and our mantra... girding ourselves to conquer the other races.~ []
@1025411 = ~Oh, sure, make fun of an old man. But I tells ye, I was good enough, surely. Once ye spend yer life thievin', what do you do next when ye loses yer speed an' yer agility?~ []
@1025413 = ~Well, I intend to do some good with my abilities. There are a lot of poor people who I can help... and I can help <CHARNAME> in <PRO_HISHER> quest, too.~ []
@1025415 = ~Ye think I had nary a dream, girlie? Ahhh, of course ye doesn't. Go on, then. Go and do yer adventurin'.~ []
@1025420 = ~Ye talks high an' mighty enough... is ye a thief?~ []
@1025423 = ~As I said, I am fully aware of the natural way of things... decay is the ultimate process.~ []
@1025424 = ~One thing t' say it, my friend... another thing entirely t' live it.~ []
@1025425 = ~Yes... well, I must admit I do not look forward to my own decay. I imagine myself being full of memories of a life well-lived by then, however... those, I think, shall comfort me.~ []
@1025426 = ~No! It's not like that at all! I just... I do what I can, and try to be a good person. Those foppish snobs that hold themselves above everyone make me ill.~ []
@1025428 = ~(sniff!)  I... I'm lost. I can't find me mommy...~ []
@1025433 = ~We... we don't live anywhere. (sniff!)  Mommy doesn't have any money.~ []
@1025434 = ~I see. Maybe tell me about your mother... maybe I can find her for you.~ []
@1025436 = ~Here, child... here's a gold piece for you. Buy yourself some food... and give the rest to your mother when you see her.~ []
@1025437 = ~Me mommy is... is... she's my mommy... (sniff!)  I just want my mommy! Please, please, I just want my mommy!~ []
@1025440 = ~There is no time! I only hope that the attackers have not made it inside. If they have... if they have breached the inner courtyard they will be hard to rout.~ []
@1025441 = ~I will tell you what secrets I can. Perhaps you will be able to sneak in and attack from a more vulnerable spot. I hope Father is all right. He... would not leave.~ []
@1025442 = ~B-b-b-but... I... I... (sniff!)  WwaaAAAAHHHH!!~ []
@1025446 = ~You're back! Have you reconsidered? The offer still stands. If we do not go soon my family's keep will be overrun, and not all the swordsmen in Calimshan will make a bit of difference then.~ [NALIA64]
@1025447 = ~Yes, I... I should have told you previously, but others refused to help when they found out. We are... beset by trolls. A vast number of them.~ []
@1025448 = ~"There once was a warrior true,
With the sense knocked out of him, too.
But in a hamster he found,
Some wisdom profound,
And now where goes he goes his Boo!"~ []
@1025449 = ~The main assault began just a few nights ago. I think they were driven from the north by the elves, or perhaps the new settlements south of Tethyr.~ []
@1025450 = ~Please! There is no one else! Think of my family! Think of the servants and their families! The servants! That's it! The trolls may not have killed all the servants because they pose little threat.~ []
@1025451 = ~The guards may be dead, but the servants will have seen the attack, and will know how many strong the invaders are. Please, if you stay we may have a chance.~ []
@1025454 = ~"There once was an elf proud and fair,
Men withered once under her stare.
But she loved one man true,
And he died... as men do,
And now there is naught but grief there."~ []
@1025455 = ~I know, I know. Wait! The servants wouldn't have posed much threat to the trolls. Some of them may be alive inside, and they would know numbers and strengths.~ []
@1025456 = ~I... I use it to occasionally sneak out while my parents aren't looking. They don't much like me interacting with the local peasants, but I can do so much for them.~ []
@1025458 = ~Are... are you speaking of me? And Khalid? How do you know of this, answer me!~ []
@1025459 = ~"There once was a man full of woes,
Strong and mighty he smote all his foes.
Soon he'll take his Test,
To him it's no jest,
If he'll pass not even he knows."~ []
@1025461 = ~I... I used it to occasionally sneak out while my parents weren't looking. They don't much like me interacting with the local peasants, but I can do so much for them.~ []
@1025463 = ~"There once was an elf of the Dark,
Whose bite was far worse than her bark.
Left without a home,
On the surface she'll roam,
In the sun she might just make her mark."~ []
@1025466 = ~"There once was an elf who could fly,
Without wings she was sure she would die.
But soon she'll have found
That it is on the ground
That her true destiny does lie."~ []
@1025468 = ~You... you know of me? What do you know of my destiny?~ []
@1025469 = ~"There once was a knight pure of heart,
From his wife he is always apart.
Has his heart grown colder
As his deeds grew bolder?
What is finished can never restart."~ []
@1025471 = ~"There once was a halfling so pure,
She's a paladin, as sure as she's sure.
If she's lucky one day
Her god will smile and say
That the lack of one she'll no longer endure."~ []
@1025472 = ~How... how do you know all of this?~ []
@1025473 = ~"There once was a man so afraid
That his soul was to be soon waylaid,
See, the wizard's returned
In his sphere, he has learned,
But has he learned if a soul can be weighed?"~ []
@1025480 = ~"There once was a child of... of...~ []
@1025486 = ~I..I.. (giggle!)  ..the gods speak! They speak and speak and speak and speak! To ME!! Hee hee...~ []
@1025504 = ~Whose estate is this?~ []
@1025515 = ~I see at last the serpent slithers out of hiding to reveal himself! Come, then, fiend and prepare to be dealt righteous vengeance!~ []
@1025516 = ~What is this? Ah... I see that old lizard Cor has finally sent his whelp to deal with me, eh?~ []
@1025530 = ~And here you give me the opportunity to strike at him again! His son... thundering into my home... it would only be right to defend ourselves, no?~ []
@1025533 = ~You spit upon her memory?! Very well, demon... I shall teach you the pain of losing one so dear!~ []
@1025536 = ~No! Stop! V-very well, Delryn... you have made your point! I... I beg you not to harm this innocent flower of my house!~ []
@1025545 = ~Wh...? Oh, by my stars and garters... HEEELLLP!! THIEEEEVES!!~ []
@1025549 = ~Ah... you must be the son of Lord Cor. Anomen, is it? I am afraid that there is very little I can tell you regarding your sister's death.~ []
@1025552 = ~Yes, my father... cannot afford additional guards and servants, it seems. But... is there nothing you can do? Surely you know that Saerk is responsible!~ []
@1025553 = ~I know of your family's feud with the merchant, but a motive is not enough without witnesses or evidence. The rule of law must prevail... surely you understand.~ []
@1025556 = ~I... I do not know.~ []
@1025558 = ~This Saerk may be innocent, Anomen. You cannot take vengeance on one who might be innocent... you are a knight, after all, first and foremost.~ []
@1025559 = ~Yes... yes! It is as you say, <CHARNAME>! Come... let us go to Saerk's demesne and I shall find justice for my sister!~ []
@1025572 = ~But I warn you to stay off the streets at night in that District until this is solved. Now... if you will excuse me, I have other things to attend to.~ []
@1025573 = ~We are still investigating the matter... there is nothing else I can say. Excuse me... I have other things I must attend to.~ []
@1025574 = ~Please excuse me, then... I must attend to other matters.~ []
@1025575 = ~Well, now, I don't know why that inspector fellow keeps lookin' odd at me... I ain't done nothin'. At least, I ain't done nothin' with those murders, that is.~ []
@1025576 = ~Aye, now... we'll rest easy now that that business is all over with.~ []
@1025577 = ~I'm just waitin' for someone to come by, here... and I don't be thinkin' that's you, neither.~ []
@1025578 = ~You're blockin' my view... why don't you go an' see the play downstairs? They're still doin' one, I think.~ []
@1025579 = ~Look... I don't be wantin' to buy nothin' and I ain't sellin' nothing. Leave me be.~ []
@1025580 = ~Aye, now... ye're back are ye?~ []
@1025581 = ~Yes, well... I was rather tied up there for a while, my friend.~ []
@1025582 = ~Wait, now... aren't ye the one I'm waitin' for, missy?~ []
@1025583 = ~The name is Mazzy. And no, I truly doubt that I am here to meet common rubbish such as yourself.~ []
@1025584 = ~Well, ye're a halfling... they all looks alikes t' me.~ []
@1025588 = ~Er... excuse me, sir... that painting on your head... are you one of the actors?~ []
@1025590 = ~I cannot stand this! This flagon has a speck of dirt on it... how am I expected to drink this?~ []
@1025591 = ~I'll tells ye how. (gulpgulpgulp)  Ah! That be how! Tastes like ale, it does... did they charge ye extra for the speck?~ []
@1025594 = ~All day spent cookin' and cleanin'... I expect to come here t' relax, I does.~ []
@1025595 = ~I be scared to go out into th' streets at night... me husband says there be ghouls on the loose to eat yer flesh.~ []
@1025598 = ~I must always strive to look my best and represent the Order, my lady.~ []
@1025600 = ~You should be careful, woman... you might miss him more than you think should your wish come true.~ []
@1025603 = ~Armor of Faith (Abjuration) 
Level: 1
Sphere: Protection
Range: 0
Duration: 3 rounds + 1 round/level 
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None 

Armor of Faith confers upon the caster significant protection against melee and magical attacks. This magical armor is a force of energy that absorbs a portion of the damage intended for the caster. At first level, the armor absorbs 5% of all damage, with an additional 5% absorbed for  every five levels of the caster, to a maximum of 25% for a 20th level priest. Armor or Faith is not cumulative with any other protections, physical or magical, including itself.~ []
@1025606 = ~Circle of Protection (Abjuration) 
Level: 1
Sphere: Protection
Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn/level
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: ??
Saving Throw: None~ []
@1025616 = ~Call Woodland Beings (Conjuration, Summoning) 
Level: 4
Sphere: Animal, Summoning 
Range: Visual Range of Caster 
Duration: 3 turns
Casting Time: 7 
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

This spell summons forth a nymph to assist the party. The nymph has several priest spells at her disposal and will use them in the best interests of the party. She will remain under the caster's control until slain, or until the spell duration expires.~ []
@1025622 = ~But of course! Take a look at the shelves... we have Tethyrian brandy, Sembian mead, Theskan dark ale... even a bit o' dwarven grog, if that tickles your fancy!~ []
@1025626 = ~You said something about having 'all' types of drinks... that isn't true, is it?~ []
@1025641 = ~Have a seat, if you wish... I've got three customers to serve before I can get to you.~ []
@1025646 = ~Surely enough... although it was difficult to drag my Samuel away. Sorry, dear... one of the drunks is hollering. Take care!~ []
@1025650 = ~I do so adore this tavern... it is the only place I have been able to locate a single glass of Damaaran white!~ []
@1025651 = ~This part of the city is so unsafe at night... it makes my flesh crawl to think of the murders, here!~ []
@1025655 = ~Oh... you... you are that Corthala man, are you not? The one with the... er... mansion down the way?~ []
@1025661 = ~(sniff)  If it weren't for the fine elven wines which that horridly cheerful little halfling sells, I wouldn't deign to come here at all.~ []
@1025662 = ~(sniff)  They really should do something about that murderer fellow in these parts... or at least force him not to flay his victims. How ghastly!~ []
@1025663 = ~(sniff)  I tried going to that theater they have in the cellar, here, but it is so dusty and drab. That, and the plays are horribly melodramatic.~ []
@1025664 = ~You haven't seen my signet ring, have you? It's a family heirloom... it must have fallen off my finger, I suppose...~ []
@1025666 = ~Ah... Lord Keldorn. Good to see you. (sniff)  I trust the Lady Maria is well?~ []
@1025667 = ~My wife is... well enough, Lord Sterk. Good day.~ []
@1025669 = ~I have honed my battle skills aboard the ships that ply the Sword Coast... many a pirate has fallen before my blade.~ []
@1025670 = ~I'm not interested in conversation... I am only here to wet my throat before I must go back to my ship.~ []
@1025671 = ~You, there... I've heard you can fight like a caged tiger. I tip my sword to you, you're a credit to women and to halflings both.~ []
@1025674 = ~Is... is this a compliment? It seems I can no longer tell among your kind.~ []
@1025675 = ~Mmmm... grog...~ []
@1025677 = ~Hey, now... ye weren't eyein' me grog, were you? You can't have it, it's MY grog!~ []
@1025680 = ~Halflings sure are as annoying as a rough patch o' hair on yer rump, but a tavern they knows how to run, aye!~ []
@1025681 = ~I know what you're thinking... halflings aren't anything but thieves, right? Well, bully on you!~ []
@1025688 = ~And I could shave your feet with my dagger faster than you could belch, little halfling. But I mean no harm... so relax.~ []
@1025691 = ~'Uda, you is good cook!'  'Uda, you is wonderful cook!'  But all halfling talks about is all his drink, all his drink from all over... not Uda's food! Uda quit one day, then see what halfling does!~ []
@1025693 = ~And if you haven't already, do take a look at the theater established downstairs! I'm told the plays are a marvel! Ooo, but I prattle... let me get you a menu...~ []
@1025697 = ~This item cannot be removed.~ []
@1025701 = ~You wouldn't be lookin' to spend time with a sailor lad, would ye?~ []
@1025704 = ~A tempting offer, my friend... but currently I have other more pressing plans.~ []
@1025705 = ~I am told that the use of magic is outlawed here in Athkatla... how very odd I find that.~ []
@1025706 = ~I am almost tempted to seek out the fabled elven city of Suldanessellar... I'm told it is fair to the eye. But the sea calls, of course...~ []
@1025710 = ~I wonder if there be a black market about. I truly need to get a few... things... for the next outing to Lantan.~ []
@1025711 = ~You there, gnome! You gnomes sell things... might you have a selection of wares I could look at?~ []
@1025713 = ~A... a drow elf? Here? Er... might you be... willing to, er...~ []
@1025718 = ~You there... you seem like a rugged and handsome enough sort. This sailor gal needs a break... care to join me for an eve?~ []
@1025719 = ~Er... certainly not. Somehow I think I'd rather pull a squid through my nostrils, thank you.~ []
@1025721 = ~No... that's not it. I was just wondering if you actually intended fish guts to be part of your outfit.~ []
@1025725 = ~Watch yer step there... ach, 'tis too late. Can't blame the horse, neither, aye? He's long gone, surely.~ []
@1025731 = ~Me wife keeps naggin' me to go to the promenade and do some shoppin' for her. Ach, but 'tis such a far walk... maybe I'll go the tavern and just say I was robbed, aye?~ []
@1025732 = ~There's a murderer on the loose, there is... yer a stranger, mayhap it's you!~ []
@1025736 = ~And he has ended your employment? I am sorry... there is nothing I can do to help you.~ []
@1025737 = ~Ye should be careful, miss... I understand even elven lasses aren't safe at night here, with that murderer on th' loose, an' all.~ []
@1025740 = ~Aerial Servant (Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 6
Sphere: Summoning 
Range: 15 yards
Duration: 1 turn/level
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

The caster of this spell summons an Aerial Servant to do the caster's bidding for the duration of the spell. The servant will attack any enemies that the caster decides, staying until the duration of the spell ends or he is slain.~
@1025741 = ~Have no fear for me, my friend. I am well capable of defending myself... and punishing those who commit such acts on others!~ []
@1025742 = ~The Council keeps raisin' the taxes on us poor folk, an' the District gets worse an' worse... it has t' stop, it does!~ []
@1025743 = ~Blade Barrier (Evocation)
Level: 6 
Sphere: Guardian/ Creation 
Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Special

When cast, Blade Barrier creates a wall of circling, razor-sharp blades which whirl and flash around the caster, forming an impenetrable barrier. Any creature attempting to pass through the blade barrier suffers 8D8 points of damage. Creatures within the area of the barrier when it is invoked are entitled to a saving throw vs. spells. If they save successfully, the blades are avoided and no damage is suffered.~ []
@1025744 = ~Have ye been by the Five Flagons? 'Tis a grand place t' drink... and I hears that the playhouse in the basement is worth the price t' get in.~ []
@1025745 = ~I used t' know one of the lasses who were murdered... an awful, awful tragedy, this is. Monsters ye almost can't blame, but what about monsters right amongst us?~ []
@1025751 = ~Creeping Doom (Conjuration/Summoning)
Level: 7
Sphere: Animal, Summoning 
Range: 80 yards
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Special

When the caster utters the spell Creeping Doom, he calls forth a mass of venomous, biting and stinging arachnids, insects, and myriapods. This carpetlike mass swarms over a large area spreading to all the creatures within 30 feet of the target. Those trapped by the insects suffer 2 points of damage each second, and a spell failure rate of 100%. For each round the victim remains inside the cloud he must make a save vs. spells at -2 or run away in fear for one round. The advantage of Creeping Doom over its fifth level counterpart Insect Plague is that it does twice as much damage in half the amount of time.~
@1025763 = ~I am a faithful servant to Arvoreen and His most valiant warrior, as well. We as a people should not limit our scope of vision, brother.~ []
@1025764 = ~Holy Word (Conjuration/Summoning)
Level: 7
Sphere: Combat
Range: 0
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None

Uttering a Holy Word channels magic of tremendous power. The priest acts as a bridge between his god and the prime material plane, causing a small explosion centered on the priest and reaching out to a radius of 15 feet. The spell affects creatures of any evil alignment that are caught in the area of effect. The effects experienced differ according to the hit dice of the target, as follows:

Hit Dice
1 to 4: Death
4 to 7: Stunned for 1 turn
8 to 11: Slowed for 1 turn with 75% chance of spell failure
12 and up: Deafened for 1 turn with 50% chance of spell failure

There is no saving throw vs. this spell, and the effects are instantaneous. Holy Word may not be cast by priests of evil alignment.~ []
@1025766 = ~Resurrection (Necromantic)
Level: 7
Sphere: Necromantic
Range: Touch
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Creature Touched
Saving Throw: None

Like the 5th level spell Raise Dead, Resurrection will return a character back to life. However, Resurrection also heals the character so that they are ready for the adventuring life once more.~ []
@1025779 = ~I'm so relieved that the murders are over with... who would have thought that little tanner fellow would be responsible? He always seemed so friendly and quiet.~ []
@1025780 = ~My children keep bothering me to go to the circus in the Waukeen's Promenade. I don't know... I've heard the most awful rumors.~ []
@1025783 = ~It is not the magic that is evil, but the purpose behind it, and the purpose of many magic users is good... something I am sure even you have benefited from somehow.~ []
@1025784 = ~I think it is such a shame that they just do not search all the houses and round up all the sorcerers and just... do away with them all!~ []
@1025786 = ~I hope me husband gets back soon from Trademeet... I hear that there's been trouble there as o' late.~ []
@1025787 = ~Have ye ever traveled much out by the Umar Hills? Me husband says there be good minin' there... if they could ever makes it safe, that is.~ []
@1025790 = ~I don't know why the guards don't take a harsher stance against th' thieves in this city... hang them all, I says.~ []
@1025792 = ~They should round up all the thieves, here... especially them Shadow Thieves... and just kick 'em out o' the city, I thinks!~ []
@1025793 = ~Hah! There are many reasons that thieves have survived as long as they have... none of which I am sure you would even be slightly aware of, madam.~ []
@1025794 = ~'Tis hard to feed a family o' wee folk in this city with all the robberies an' such... and me man cannot find work the law allows, as well.~ []
@1025795 = ~Get on, get on... don't bother a poor halfling woman who's runnin' the hair off her feet, almost.~ []
@1025796 = ~I haven't got anything to say to ye... ye're as likely to rob me as skin me, methinks.~ []
@1025798 = ~Calm yourself, little one, and restore your senses to some form of order. I am no murderer. A killer, perhaps, when I must... although I doubt you would detect the difference.~ []
@1025799 = ~(shudder)  You... you look like you could be a murderer, to me!~ []
@1025801 = ~Not bad intuition, halfling. Flawed and incorrect... but overall quite respectable. (The insult deserves a fireball, but it would only prove her right! Bah!)~ []
@1025803 = ~I got your nose! No, really, <SIRMAAM>... it's here, in this bag...~ []
@1025806 = ~Gosh, you're so big an' tall... when I grow up I want to be just like you!~ []
@1025808 = ~Gee, mister... your robe is so colorful... can I be like you when I grow up? Pleeeeaaaasssse?~ []
@1025812 = ~A commendable statement child, but... no, no! Back, back! (Somebody get this... thing... off of me! It's... hugging... me...)~ []
@1025823 = ~Er... I think someone needs to sit down and have a long talk with your mother...~ []
@1025824 = ~Legs and hands, I have hands again! I am free of this horrible place! Thank you so much! I must... Giran! I hope my son hasn't gone far. Momma's on her way!~ []
@1025825 = ~'Allo, darling. Is there something that ye cares t' sample... such as my affordable an' delightful little charms, mmm?~ []
@1025826 = ~Are ye sure ye wouldn't like a... souvenir, me sweetie?~ []
@1025827 = ~Don't mind me, honey... I be jus' mindin' me business and tryin' to keep me skin on me bones. If ye takes me meanin', that is.~ []
@1025829 = ~Hoy, there, honey... yer sweet enough, ye could makes quite a livin' on the streets. The men sure would take a shinin' to ye...~ []
@1025831 = ~Um... no, thank you. Somehow I just don't think it's for me.~ []
@1025832 = ~Hmmm... aren't you one of those actors from the Flagons? How about I give you my... special actor's discount?~ []
@1025833 = ~We actors are always destitute enough to appreciate a good offer, my dear... but this one time I am afraid I shall have to pass, alas.~ []
@1025835 = ~This is almost worse than when I worked the Docks... here, 'tis nothing but poor sailors and poorer husbands. Bleh!~ []
@1025836 = ~I had a child, once... but I was forced t' give her up right after she was born. I think she's in an orphanage or the like, now.~ []
@1025840 = ~Hmmm... ever think about joining the life, my dear? That dress looks simply stunning on ye...~ []
@1025842 = ~Ahhh... perhaps you might have an interest in perusing some stolen goods, hm? Perfectly good items... cheap prices...'win-win' situation?~ []
@1025845 = ~Alright, then... let's just move a few steps, here, so we can't be easily overseen...~ []
@1025846 = ~Your loss, my <LADYLORD>... if you decide to say anything about me, though, there will be trouble...~ []
@1025848 = ~Heh... more than I want to... but less than some. Apparently, the creature eats the skin from his victims and then leaves them for dead... but that's all I know.~ []
@1025849 = ~Very well, then... let me see your wares...~ []
@1025851 = ~Hallo to you, my <LADYLORD>. I have a small amount of goods that I sell out of my cart, here... some of which you might be interested in.~ []
@1025853 = ~Sure... let me see what you have.~ []
@1025856 = ~Not at all. I assure you that my goods are quite legitimate... unlike many other things in the area of the docks, more than likely.~ []
@1025857 = ~Alright, then... let me see what you have.~ []
@1025861 = ~So... these items of yours... are they stolen?~ []
@1025865 = ~A farewell to you, then, my <LADYLORD>... perhaps another time.~ []
@1025867 = ~Reflected Image (Illusion/Phantasm) 
Level: 1
Range: 0 
Duration: 3 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None 

When this spell is cast, a duplicate image of the caster is created. This image will mirror the actions of the caster such that any enemies will not know which image to attack. When a successful attack is launched against the caster, there is a 50% chance that it will land harmlessly upon the reflection, causing no damage to the caster, and dispelling the duplicate image.~ []
@1025868 = ~Circle of Protection (Abjuration) 
Level: 1
Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn/level
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: ??
Saving Throw: None~ []
@1025870 = ~Reveal Magic (Divination) 
Level: 1
Range: 0
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: ??
Saving Throw: None~ []
@1025872 = ~Detect Illusion (Divination)
Level: 3
Range: 0
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None 

This spell will cancel all illusion/phantasm spells of 3rd level and lower in the area, including: Reflected Image, Invisibility, Mirror Image, and Non-Detection. The targets' magic resistance, if any, does not affect the operation of this spell.~ []
@1025876 = ~Stoneskin (Alteration) 
Level: 4
Range: 0
Duration: 12 hours
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None 

Upon casting this powerful spell, an outer skin of stone will move up from the ground and completely cover the wizard. This skin is magical, will not hinder the movements of the wizard, and will protect the wizard from physical attacks. For every 2 levels of the caster an additional skin is gained upon casting (a 10th level wizard would receive 5 skins, while a 20th level wizard would receive 10). Each skin the wizard possesses will stop one attack (and be destroyed in the process). The skins will remain on the wizard until dispelled, until all of the skins are destroyed from absorbing attacks, or until the spell duration expires.~ []
@1025900 = ~Next time buy some fish!~ []
@1025913 = ~Spell Immunity (Abjuration)
Level: 5
Range: Self
Duration: 1 round / level
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Self
Saving Throw: None

Casting this spell grants the wizard protection from one spell school of her choice. After the spell is cast, the wizard must choose the school she wishes to be protected from. All spells of this school will not be able to harm the caster for the duration of this spell.~
@1025915 = ~Breach (Abjuration) 
Level: 5
Range: Visual sight of caster 
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Target Creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast at a creature, it breaches and dispels any and all of the following protections:

Chaotic Commands, Resist Fear, Protection From Fire/Cold, Resist Fire/Cold, Death Ward, Fireshield, Free Action, Protection From Acid, Protection From Electricity, Protection From Evil, Protection From Evil 10' Radius, Protection From Lightning, Protection From Magic Energy, Protection From The Elements, Protection From Energy, Blade Barrier, Physical Mirror, Shield, Protection From Normal Missiles, Protection From Normal Weapons, Protection From Magic Weapons, Barkskin, Stoneskin, Defensive Harmony, Armor, Armor Of Faith, Ghost Armor, Spirit Armor, Absolute Immunity, Mantle, and Improved Mantle.

The target's magic resistance, if any, does not affect the operation of this spell. Breach will not dispel Iron Skins.~ []
@1025935 = ~Pierce Magic (Abjuration) 
Level: 6
Range: Visual sight of caster 
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: Target Creature 
Saving Throw: Special

When this spell is cast upon a target creature, that creature's magic resistance will be lowered by 1% for every level of the caster, and one spell protection of 8th level or lower will be removed from the target creature. The list of protections that can be removed includes: Minor Spell Deflection, Minor Spell Turning, Spell Deflection, Spell Turning, Minor Globe Of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, and Globe Of Invulnerability. The target's magic resistance does not affect the operation of this spell.~ []
@1025936 = ~True Sight (Divination) 
Level: 6
Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: 120-foot radius
Saving Throw: None 

When True Sight is cast, all hostile illusion/phantasm spells in the area of effect will be dispelled once per round for the duration of the spell. The spells that are affected by True Sight are: Reflected Image, Invisibility, Mirror Image, Non-Detection, Improved Invisibility, Shadow Door, Mislead, Project Image, and Simulacrum. The target's magic resistance, if any, does not affect the operation of this spell.~ []
@1025943 = ~Contingency (Evocation) 
Level: 6
Range: Visual range of caster
Duration: Permanent until used 
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None

Upon casting Contingency, the wizard chooses one spell out of his or her repertoire of memorized spells, and then selects a casting condition. Then, when that condition is met (e.g., a wizard with a 'helpless' contingency is stunned), the selected spell is cast automatically and instantaneously, with no additional action required by the wizard. When choosing the level of the spell to be cast, the wizard is allowed one spell level for every three levels of experience, up to 6th level spells at 18th level. Furthermore, the selected spell may only target the caster.~ []
@1025954 = ~Sphere of Chaos (Alteration) 
Level: 7
Range: Visual sight of caster 
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: Special

All enemies within the area affected by the casting of this spell must make a saving throw vs. spells for every round that they remain in the sphere, and if the save is failed one of the following random effects occurs: the target is polymorphed into a squirrel, is confused, bursts into flames, is paralyzed, is disintegrated, is healed by 20 hit points, is randomly teleported, is rendered unconscious, or is hasted.~ []
@1025961 = ~Prismatic Spray (Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 7
Range: 20 yards
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: 70' long cone 
Saving Throw: Special

When this spell is cast, the wizard causes seven shimmering, multicolored rays of light to flash from his hand. These rays span all colors of the visible spectrum; each ray has a different power and purpose. Any creature with fewer than 8 hit dice that is struck by a ray is blinded for 5 rounds, regardless of any other effect. This spell will not harm party members; any other creature that is caught within the area of effect will be touched by one or two of the rays. The effects of the rays are listed below. 

Red: Inflicts 20 hit points of damage, save vs. spells for half
Orange: Inflicts 40 hit points of damage, save vs. spells for half
Yellow: Inflicts 80 hit points of damage, save vs. spells for half
Green: Save vs. poison or die, otherwise suffer 20 points of poison damage
Blue:  Save vs. petrification or be turned to stone
Indigo: Save vs. wands or be feebleminded
Violet: Save vs. spells or be disintegrated~ []
@1025962 = ~I'm warning everyone, so as to get the word out that there are guards on the streets. We've had a... a string of killings, and I don't want any more happening.~ []
@1025967 = ~Dangerous enough for people that look for trouble, but when innocents... This is different. Murder, unlike any I've seen in years.~ []
@1025968 = ~Bandits I can understand; they are easy enough to figure out. What's happening here is... it's murder, but not like I've ever seen.~ []
@1025973 = ~Such a remark I would expect from the killer himself. No, I doubt even you would stoop to the crimes of this... this creature.~ []
@1025974 = ~Nothing. They have nothing to take. He kills them and that is all. Not only is it pointless, but he does it in as painful a way as possible. It's... it's sick.~ []
@1025977 = ~Enough of this. I must go about my rounds. If you find any information about the murders, be sure to let me know. Don't go looking for trouble though.~ []
@1025981 = ~A beggar found a piece of thick leather by one of the crime scenes.~ []
@1025983 = ~No disappointment from me. Been pretty quiet around here, which means he hasn't struck again. I haven't caught him, but at least no one has been hurt.~ []
@1025991 = ~Interesting, but not of much help. Lots of people carry or wear leather.~ []
@1025994 = ~Elephant hide, you say? Could be from the circus then. Their tamer might have had contact with elephants. I'll have him questioned at the garrison.~ []
@1026006 = ~I have found out who it is! It was the tanner, Rejiek!~ []
@1026021 = ~Neither of which is conclusive evidence. Lots of people have leather and a smell could be anything! You killed a man over this?~ []
@1026027 = ~I see. Perhaps there was no other way then. It could have been disastrous, but you seem to have done a good job checking him out.~ []
@1026038 = ~Well, that evidence alone would not have allowed me to act against a businessman, but it seems to have served you well. The locals will appreciate that they are safe.~ []
@1026041 = ~Hey, brat, I'll give you ten gold if you answer a few questions.~ []
@1026042 = ~I don't have anything for you, but maybe you can help me?~ []
@1026045 = ~I... I found the body of... of old Bilver. He never hurt no one! He was all bloody an... an... Maybe other beggars know more. All I did was see him.~ []
@1026046 = ~Actually, maybe you could tell me about the crimes in this area.~ []
@1026053 = ~I knows who it was, I do! I'm sure! It's that witch! She's the mean ol' Missus Cragmoon. Mean evil witch! She smacks you for stealin' cookies, that's how I know she's mean!~ []
@1026055 = ~You won't tell her I told, will you? I... I don't wanna be incarc'rated, or whatever she gonna do! You go talk to her, I'm leavin'!~ []
@1026066 = ~Well, that was quite a mouthful. Faraji is a poor child, and a light-fingered one at that. I would take what he says with caution. He is not so wide-eyed as you think.~ []
@1026068 = ~He said you were an evil witch.~ []
@1026070 = ~I see. This child, that finds me old and a little off my noodle, has called me a witch and you have taken that as basis for murder accusations? I think not.~ []
@1026078 = ~You are mistaken, and I would suggest you drop the matter. Some people need secrets, and pursuing this would certainly expose some of mine.~ []
@1026087 = ~What do you have that smells like guril berries?~ []
@1026088 = ~Let me see. Hmm... looks quite thick indeed. Very rare, but I have seen it before. This is elephant hide. Good for strong armor, but I rarely see it.~ []
@1026097 = ~Locally? Well, let me think. I know of three things with that smell. Guril berries are one, and the bark of the oak is similar. And solik berries, too.~ []
@1026098 = ~What would these things be used for locally?~ []
@1026100 = ~Well, I do a brisk business in guril berries. They are used in folk remedies, turned into topical salves for...*ahem*... intimate afflictions.~ []
@1026110 = ~I'm sorry, I'm closed at the moment. Come back when I have replenished my stock.~ [TANNER02]
@1026123 = ~Nothin'. Not a thing.~ []
@1026127 = ~But... hehehh... but...~ []
@1026133 = ~Not telling. You want? You gotta buy. I found it, right near a body. It's mine, so you gotta pay. You pay... a hundred gold. Yeah, a hundred.~ []
@1026136 = ~No? No! Ok, then you pay half. Give me... forty gold!~ []
@1026148 = ~You got what you want so go! I don't need, because it's not human flesh! That is different! Go and dance where you will! Talk to the seller that buys!~ []
@1026151 = ~Come, my scrumptious little curried chicken... shall we be off to an evening of merriment, hm?~ []
@1026152 = ~I'm sure you're wondering what the nose is all about. It's rather large... even for us gnomes, eh?~ []
@1026153 = ~Go away... you're cramping my style. If the ladies see me with you, I'll never make a coin.~ []
@1026156 = ~Hah! I can unequivocally say that I am the wealthiest and best-loved gnome in the entire city!~ []
@1026157 = ~The lasses love you only for your nose, Bertrand. 'Tis a shame to the rest of us... oh, to be lumped in the same class as a gnomish gigolo! The indignity of it all!~ []
@1026158 = ~How about it, my luscious little porkchop? You... me... together in an embrace that would shock your mother?~ []
@1026163 = ~Excuse me... might you have a coin to spare my poor, venerable mother? She would ask for herself, but she lays in a cold, cold room nearly sick to her death, alas...~ []
@1026168 = ~Yes, certainly... here is a gold piece for her.~ []
@1026170 = ~She's sick, is she? Perhaps you could bring me to her... I might be able to offer her some help.~ []
@1026171 = ~I'm sorry... I can afford to give you nothing.~ []
@1026174 = ~Bless you, my <LADYLORD>! You are a sweet and generous soul... my mother will be indebted to you forever!~ []
@1026180 = ~I'll pay your gold.~ []
@1026196 = ~Oh, thank you thank you thank you! I can taste that loaf now... mmmMMMmmm...~ []
@1026202 = ~Wait. There was something. A smell... besides the blood, I mean. I think I smelled... guril berries. Yes, that's it. Guril berries, or something like it.~ []
@1026203 = ~Hey... you! Give me your money NOW or you're going to regret it... comprehend, yes?~ []
@1026204 = ~Alright, alright... here you go...~ []
@1026209 = ~I comprehend that you're trying to ply your trade on the wrong person... and you're about to be the one regretting it.~ []
@1026210 = ~Smart move. Now... in case the subject comes up... ya never seen me...~ []
@1026212 = ~Yeah? Well... we'll just see about that, won't we...?~ []
@1026215 = ~(grunt!)  Uh! You! You give me money... ALL money... NOW!!~ []
@1026219 = ~You'll have to take it from my dead body, ogre... and that's not likely!~ []
@1026226 = ~Oooh, you sure know how to sweet-talk the ladies. I'll be here; you paid for your time.~ []
@1026241 = ~Hmm, that's the one. This... tree bark... stuff? It was stronger smelling on him though. This is the same, but it's faint. What would make him smell like this?~ []
@1026242 = ~Pierce Shield (Abjuration)
Level: 8
Range: Visual sight of caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None 

By means of this spell, the wizard may launch a massive attack on a target's defenses. The target's magic resistance will be lowered by 10%, plus 1% for every level of the caster, and one spell protection of any level will be removed from the target creature. The list of protections that can be removed includes: Minor Spell Deflection, Minor Spell Turning, Spell Deflection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, Globe Of Invulnerability, Spell Turning, and Spell Trap. The target's magic resistance does not affect the operation of this spell.~ []
@1026246 = ~Don't mind the smell... it's just a bit o' the last catch rubbed off on me.~ []
@1026247 = ~Out on the boats all day... I think I'll be headin' down to the Five Flagons for a pint or two, aye?~ []
@1026251 = ~Ay, now... why are ye looking so crossed-eye at me, hm?~ []
@1026252 = ~So he might have worked with leather? Odd. Well, I hope that helped. You've got what you wanted. Off with you now. Perhaps... no. Goodbye.~ []
@1026253 = ~I... I'm sorry... <cough>  It's just that... I hate the smell of fish...~ []
@1026257 = ~I be tellin' ye... I knows me husband says he be fishin' all day... but I think for certain he's at the Five Flagons!~ []
@1026258 = ~I can clean and gut a fish faster than ye can blink... ye can find our goods down at th' market every day, you can.~ []
@1026261 = ~So... you be the one that solved the murders, aye? What... you be lookin' fer applause? I be too busy.~ []
@1026263 = ~I... I was not looking at anything, good fishwife. I, um, oh never mind.~ []
@1026264 = ~There be a seagull about... an' I've gots meself a sling bullet with 'is name on it!~ []
@1026266 = ~Have ye ever looked a seagull in the eye, eh? There be evil there... pure evil. An' I means to hunt them all... all of 'em!~ []
@1026268 = ~Ye haven't seen a seagull about, have ye? I be Stivan the Seagull Hunter, mighty and famous. Er... care to buys a feather? I haves plenty, I does.~ []
@1026271 = ~You would hurt those poor birds? They are scavengers, only... and I'm sure they have done nothing to you!~ []
@1026273 = ~Wrong! The demons have carried off three of my brothers, they have... they are a plague upon us sent by the gods! AND I SPIT UPON YOU, GODS! <PTEWW!!>  AND AGAIN!! <PTEWW!!>~ []
@1026280 = ~Oh, look, my dear... it is a commoner, trying to speak to us.~ []
@1026281 = ~My dear Lord Feveron... if you insist on demeaning the peasants as they approach us, you will upset them all. I have no wish to start another riot.~ []
@1026285 = ~But... but darling, it is so fun to make light of the peasantry.~ []
@1026287 = ~(sigh)  Very well. My... apologies... commoner. Your smell offends me almost as much as your demeanor, but as a noble I must learn to tolerate both. Now go away.~ []
@1026296 = ~Spell Invulnerability (Abjuration) 
Level: 9
Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: The caster 
Saving Throw: None~ []
@1026297 = ~Oh, thank you, darling... it is so kind of you to say such.~ []
@1026299 = ~Oh, yes, I had almost forgotten. Thank you, Lord Feveron. Mmm... go away, peasant. Shoo! Shoo!~ []
@1026300 = ~I... I'm sorry. Are you addressing us again? Do go away.~ []
@1026302 = ~Eek! The commoner is speaking to me again! What should I do? Shoo... shoo, shoo!~ []
@1026303 = ~I am an escort to the Lord Feveron and the Lady Diana... you will maintain your manners with them or suffer the consequences. Now off with you, citizen, before you make trouble.~ []
@1026305 = ~Spell Trap (Abjuration) 
Level: 9
Range: 0
Duration: 18 rounds
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: The caster 
Saving Throw: None 

This powerful spell creates a barrier of magical protection around the spellcaster. Every spell that hits the barrier is absorbed by the power of the spell trap -- making the caster recall a previously cast spell. For example, a wizard shields himself with spell trap and is then hit by a Flame Arrow (3rd level spell). He gets three spell levels back -- he will regain one spell, up to 3rd level in power.
The spell trap protects against 30 levels of protection (i.e., ten Flame Arrows or five Fingers of Death). The spell trap can absorb any level of spell, from one to nine.~
@1026307 = ~Sorry for bothering you.~ []
@1026311 = ~Why are you closed? Hiding something, are you?~ []
@1026315 = ~Spellstrike (Abjuration, Alteration) 
Level: 9
Range: Visual sight of caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Target Creature
Saving Throw: None 

When this spell is cast at a target creature, it will dispel all of the magical protections that surround that creature. This includes: Minor Spell Turning, Minor Globe Of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, Globe Of Invulnerability, Minor Spell Deflection, Spell Turning, Spell Deflection, Spell Invulnerability, and Spell Trap. The target's magic resistance, if any, does not affect this spell. ~
@1026324 = ~Sandform (Necromancy)
Level: 9
Range: 0
Duration: 1 hour/level
Casting Time: 1 turn
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None~ []
@1026326 = ~Why... thank you, citizens, for saving me from those mongrels. To think I actually thought it was a good idea to keep them as strong deckhands. Ah, well... a reward for your trouble.~ []
@1026330 = ~Chain Contingency (Evocation) 
Level: 9
Range: 0
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: The Caster
Saving Throw: None 

Chain contingency channels some of the magical energy of the mage and releases it only under certain circumstances. Basically, the mage chooses three spells, which will be released under certain conditions such as being hit by an enemy. When this condition occurs all three spells are cast immediately. Spells of 8th level or lower may be used in the contingency. ~
@1026335 = ~I don't know what you are getting at.~ []
@1026337 = ~Your class cannot use a second weapon.~ []
@1026338 = ~Boys... boys... Don't fight over me, please.~ [BUBBLE01]
@1026342 = ~You cannot place a two-handed weapon in your off hand.~ []
@1026350 = ~The guard? Ahh, you mean Lieutenant Aegisfield? Good man. We had a chat and he's sure I had nothing to do with any of the recent crimes. Now, if you will excuse me?~ []
@1026354 = ~Most excellent! I have defeated the loathsome Carbos! Come, my beloved Bubbles... let us go!~ []
@1026358 = ~Bubbles! But... but Bubbles!! But I love you, my chicken pot pie! Come back!~ []
@1026359 = ~Aha! That moron, Shank, is now dead! I am victorious! Come, my Bubbles... let us go and celebrate this blessed event!!~ []
@1026361 = ~Bubbles? But... but, Bubbles?! Honeymelon, where are you going?~ []
@1026362 = ~Shapechange (Alteration) 
Level: 9
Range: 0
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None 

With this spell, a wizard is able to assume the form of one of a number of powerful creatures (mind flayer, iron golem, greater wolfwere, earth elemental, fire elemental, or giant troll). The spellcaster becomes the creature he wishes, and has almost all of its abilities. Thus, he can change into a mind flayer to stun his opponents, and then become an earth elemental to crush them. The wizard retains the same number of hit points while using these alternate forms. Each alteration in form requires only a second, and no system shock is incurred. Although the assumed form has the combat characteristics of the real creature, it may not have all of its immunities.~ []
@1026363 = ~So, you were the one who has been speaking ill of me? You gathered this... evidence? So there's others that will know too? Then it will not stop here.~ [TANNER06]
@1026366 = ~So... you are admitting to being the killer? Why did you do this?~ []
@1026374 = ~I see. You have gathered this... er, evidence? I suppose others will know of this as well then? Then it will not stop with your leaving.~ [TANNER07]
@1026375 = ~Not to disappoint you, but there are many, many people that own leather, you among them, I am sure. I make my living selling it, so I know how common it is.~ []
@1026381 = ~See that you don't. Goodbye.~ []
@1026386 = ~What is your point? It is a common smell, especially on new armor. Many sets are sold each day. I am not responsible for how they are used, any more than a blacksmith would be.~ []
@1026390 = ~Well, that is certainly damning evidence. I mean, who would have new smelling leather armor. Perhaps only half of all the people in Athkatla.~ []
@1026392 = ~You should have run away, little fool! You could not understand! My work must go on!~ []
@1026403 = ~(cough!)  Oh... bless you, my <LADYLORD>, bless you! (cough!)  I did not know how much longer I would survive buried in there as I was!~ []
@1026405 = ~I... I was buried by the men who kidnapped me! (cough!)  They held me for ransom from my family, and after my family had paid they knocked me out.~ []
@1026406 = ~I... I remember being carried here, and thrown into that grave next to another body! And then they buried me alive! (cough!)~ []
@1026407 = ~I am sure... I am sure I would have died if you had not arrived so soon! (shudder!)  What a horrid death these evil men had in store for me! Ohhh...~ []
@1026412 = ~I woke up with this in my hand... I think I must have torn it off his shirt when he threw me in the grave. Here... perhaps it will help you find him.~ []
@1026415 = ~Thank you... I shall do my best to locate these man.~ []
@1026416 = ~Oh, no, I couldn't! These men are still out there... and they will surely come after me and my family if they knew I said anything!~ []
@1026418 = ~Please... you must... you must stop them! I beg of you!~ []
@1026420 = ~Sorry... I have no time to help you. You will have to go to the garrison.~ []
@1026421 = ~I... I thank you for saving my life. But I am still in danger! <cough!>  You... look capable with your weapons... please find these men and stop them!~ []
@1026422 = ~Only that... there was someone who spoke to this man. Perhaps the gravekeeper. You should talk to him, at least... he must have seen something!~ []
@1026423 = ~Thank you... I shall do my best to locate these men and bring them to justice.~ []
@1026424 = ~On second thought, I think there is little I can do. You have your life, now... go to the garrison or not, it is your choice.~ []
@1026426 = ~Oooh, no, I cannot go to the garrison... but thank you for saving me. I must return to my family. I pray these men don't take another victim. Farewell!~ []
@1026428 = ~I am not sure, Viconia... I have a couple of ideas of where to start looking, though, and I must make the effort.~ []
@1026430 = ~But... that is only my humble opinion. Of course.~ []
@1026431 = ~Rampah dance! Rampah no be disturbed. You get going. Talk business when you have important!~ []
@1026432 = ~I was not looking to be a farmer, of course. I just... wanted a place of my own. Where I could find peace.~ []
@1026435 = ~Over time, we formed an awkward friendship. He did not ask why I wore my hood, and I slowly began to trust him. He wondered, though... that was obvious.~ []
@1026439 = ~I woke up to searing pain. While unconscious, they had abused and tortured me... then tried to bury their sins.~ []
@1026463 = ~Then I will show you when we have the time. I will take you through the deepest lands, and you will see the beauty that I know is there.~ []
@1026464 = ~That is, if you have not tired of my company yet.~ []
@1026467 = ~I see what is there. Beauty is irrelevant.~ []
@1026472 = ~W... well. I would... I would miss your company too, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1026474 = ~Ho there, I have worked long and lonely hours and it is good to see a friendly face! Care to see some of my trinkets and far-flung wares?~ []
@1026475 = ~Something... for the lady, perhaps? Oh, yes, I see a glint in the eye. There is romance afoot, and it needs the dancing partner of the adornments of affection!~ []
@1026477 = ~Nonsense! Oh, but perhaps I have overstepped my bounds with my observant eyes. I apologize most profusely.~ []
@1026487 = ~Load times will go MUCH faster if you have done a full install.~ []
@1026489 = ~Oh, come now... you have thrived on chaos, have you not? It has thrown challenge after challenge at you and you have grown stronger and more powerful.~ []
@1026493 = ~I'll not speak of Gorion... or anything else for that matter. Go away.~ []
@1026495 = ~No... I suppose not.~ []
@1026498 = ~What a... charming fellow. Completely insane of course. Out of his mind. Blind as a bat. No idea what he was saying.~ []
@1026499 = ~Yes... yes of course. Out of his mind. Yes.~ []
@1026502 = ~Whatever, Viconia. Let's just get back to our traveling, shall we?~ []
@1026504 = ~Let's... let's get going shall we?~ []
@1026505 = ~Um... I...~ []
@1026529 = ~Pathetic creature! Run away, far away, and don't you ever come back!~ []
@1026540 = ~Call me a fiend, will ya? Why, I've never seen such a cheap funeral in my life! You sold my clothes and kept the casket closed! You picked the flowers this mornin' from near the swamp!~ [LESTER02]
@1026551 = ~Oh, I'll go back, all right... but not before I kill you, you disgusting piece of filth! Prepare to die, Nevin!!~ []
@1026557 = ~There! Stupid git didn't deserve more than a sweater and a kick in the rump, anyway! Hmph!! Now... I wonder where my Calimshite darling went off to... always time for one last quickie...~ []
@1026559 = ~You bastard! Now I'll have to pay to have you reburied! I should have you chopped into mulch and fed to a dog!! Gah! Now... where is that idiot priest...~ []
@1026562 = ~He was a good man, he was. (sniff!)  Just stubborn... refused to give up his coin pouch to a thief. Stubborn fool.~ []
@1026574 = ~What? All right then, what is it you want? What are you trying to pull here?~ []
@1026577 = ~What? What did that little weasel tell you? I knew I shouldn't trust him. I had no choice. Them or me.~ []
@1026581 = ~Hold, there... you have an aura of suspicion about you. I warn you that I am Kamir, Paladin of Helm... I will brook no trespass on this, my darkest of days.~ []
@1026589 = ~I am no more unique than most who come here. My son lies in yon wee grave. I... I failed my oath to protect the lad, and he has been taken from me.~ []
@1026590 = ~You are most decent. I... am not ready to leave just yet.~ []
@1026595 = ~Tirdir? But he's... It was that little weasel Sethle, wasn't it? He told you. I knew I shouldn't trust him! I had no choice though! Them or me!~ []
@1026596 = ~Please... leave us alone. There is nothing more that can be done for our poor Wellyn.~ []
@1026598 = ~Why would someone do this? (sob!)  What could possess someone to kill a little boy? And a halfling, too... he never hurt anyone!~ []
@1026604 = ~Calm yourself, my darling. There is... nothing more that can be done for him.~ []
@1026608 = ~But why?! (sob!)  I just... don't... understand... (sob!)~ []
@1026611 = ~You, there... leave us alone. Can't you see that my wife is upset? Just... just leave us be.~ []
@1026616 = ~Yes... Arvoreen's blessing.~ []
@1026617 = ~This is... a terrible tragedy. My heart goes out to both of you. Life beyond our simple burrows is never simple or easy. Arvoreen's blessing upon your son.~ []
@1026620 = ~(sniff!)  Do you... do you truly think so?~ []
@1026621 = ~Thank you, sir. That is... that is very kind of you to say.~ []
@1026625 = ~I... I couldn't! I can't... I can't stand the blood!~ []
@1026630 = ~And I have. I mean... I mean that I did. I love... loved the lad dearly. Stefan I named him. Strong, honest boy.~ []
@1026632 = ~Who's there? What do you vermin wish now? The guard will hear of this outrage! Who... You are not my captors. Who are you? I demand to be freed!~ []
@1026636 = ~Well, I thank you then. I have been in this place too long. No doubt my ransom was on the way, but I begin to doubt they would have released me.~ []
@1026640 = ~Tell me about this oath, then... surely it cannot be that bad.~ []
@1026642 = ~I tire of this maudlin whining... I'll leave you to it.~ []
@1026643 = ~But I am. I failed my vow. And I know no way in which I can atone for my failure. If... if there was only some way... I would embrace it, gladly.~ []
@1026648 = ~I and my descendants are in your debt. Farewell.~ []
@1026666 = ~An... an orphan, you say? Perhaps... perhaps that would be a way... to atone for my failure. Thank you, my <LADYLORD>... I shall go and talk to them at once.~ []
@1026668 = ~It is no matter. I do not expect you to. But please... leave me to my grief a little longer. I... I am not ready to leave my son just yet.~ []
@1026679 = ~I am Dawnlord Arenthis of the Lathander church... excuse my young charge. Risa doesn't talk much since the recent death of her parents.~ []
@1026683 = ~Indeed it is. And there is very little that can be done for her, as well... other than to put her into an orphanage, I suppose. She is so shy and sad, though, I am sure it will do her no good. Tsk.~ []
@1026684 = ~If only there were someone who would care for her. Hmm. You strike me as a good person... perhaps you would be willing to care for a child in need? What would you say to that?~ []
@1026691 = ~My life is not for a child... but there is a paladin not far from here who I think might be a suitable guardian. His own son has just died... and I think he might be amenable.~ []
@1026694 = ~I would not ask you to care for her, surely... but might you know of someone who would make a suitable guardian?~ []
@1026695 = ~You... you are the one I am to meet? I know of no one else that would approach me. Show me the note if you are who you appear to be.~ []
@1026696 = ~Some compassion would not be out of order for one so young and innocent, I would think. Please... leave us alone, then, if you cannot find it in your heart.~ []
@1026704 = ~Actually, there is a paladin not far from here who I think might be a suitable guardian. His own son has just died... and I think he might be amenable.~ []
@1026708 = ~I wish this over with quick, so whatever it is, it will have to do.~ []
@1026709 = ~A paladin? A true paladin? Perhaps... perhaps that would be an excellent idea. If he is willing, that is.~ []
@1026710 = ~Please, my <LADYLORD>... it would mean so much if you could find this paladin and ask him about this. Risa needs a proper guardian much more than an orphanage. I beg it of you!~ []
@1026716 = ~Forget it... I have better things to do.~ []
@1026717 = ~Our deal is done. May you rot for what you have done.~ []
@1026718 = ~Actually, there is a paladin not far from here who I think might be a suitable guardian. His own son has just died... and I think he might be amenable.~ []
@1026723 = ~I cannot, my <LADYLORD>. I must stay and care for Risa. If you could seek out this paladin, I would be most grateful... and Lathander would smile on you.~ []
@1026724 = ~(sniff!) ... go 'way!~ []
@1026726 = ~Greetings again, my <LADYLORD>. Ach... it still pains me so that Risa, here, has no choice but to go to an orphanage. It would do her little good, I think.~ []
@1026727 = ~Hail once again, my <LADYLORD>. I... please. I ask that you leave me to grieve for my son in peace.~ []
@1026729 = ~Tell me about this oath, then... surely it cannot be that bad.~ []
@1026730 = ~All right... I shall leave you be.~ []
@1026733 = ~The... the locket is lovely, by the way. Thank you.~ []
@1026736 = ~Greetings... greetings to you both. I... I understand that the girl is in need of a guardian?~ []
@1026737 = ~You are a paladin, are you?  I am pleased to meet you.  This is--~ []
@1026739 = ~... yes. Yes, I am most pleased to agree. This is Risa.~ []
@1026747 = ~Oh... you must be very sad...~ []
@1026748 = ~Yes, I am. I miss him very much. I think he would approve, however, of me taking care of you. That is... if you are willing.~ []
@1026749 = ~O-okay... where do you live?~ []
@1026750 = ~Come... I shall show you the church. Thank you, cleric... and thank you, too, my <LADYLORD>. I am... most appreciative.~ []
@1026751 = ~I am most pleased at this wonderful turn of events. Lathander's greatest blessing upon you, my <LADYLORD>, for the part you have played in this. Sometimes... sometimes Faerun can be a kind place...~ []
@1026780 = ~But one's place is not always apparent. Who decides on a person's proper place?~ []
@1026784 = ~Magic Resistance (Alteration) 
Level: 5
Sphere: Protection
Range: Touch
Duration: 3 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Target Creature
Saving Throw: None 

When cast, this spell confers upon the target a resistance to all magic, equal to 2% per level of the caster, up to a maximum of 40% at 20th level. This resistance is set, so if the target already has more magic resistance than the spell would confer, their resistance will actually be lowered to the set value.~ []
@1026793 = ~Is that what you think I am? A traitor? I don't know if I can stomach this. I... I don't want to talk to you of this anymore.~ []
@1026794 = ~I guess that is true. That fool Galvarey sought to do an injustice. He betrayed the spirit of the Harpers, not me. This knowledge will ease my mind.~ []
@1026796 = ~I have been in a similar place as this before, though it was in the company of other Harpers. I will miss those times.~ [JAHEIR95]
@1026798 = ~There must be a way to reconcile this matter.~ []
@1026803 = ~I doubt that it will be that easy. Galvarey was as close to a regional leader as the Harpers have. The events will be told from his favor, I am sure.~ []
@1026806 = ~It would seem that the coldest thing in sight is you. I will seek spring in not talking to you.~ []
@1026807 = ~No better comfort could I ask, <CHARNAME>. I will continue to stand for you if you do the same for me. Together we can... togeth...~ []
@1026812 = ~Her actions were in the wrong, no matter her intention.~ []
@1026815 = ~There are times when you seem almost reasonable, and then you say such things that only make me doubt myself. Perhaps... perhaps they were right? I don't know.~ []
@1026819 = ~Avoid them? The Harpers? What are you asking of me?~ []
@1026827 = ~No! I just... this is so damn difficult to get straight. We should... we should speak of this later. Things will be said in anger... Let's move on.~ []
@1026830 = ~Very well.~ []
@1026831 = ~No, this cannot wait. I don't think I can resolve this if it is not discussed. If this is put off... then all I am thinking must be put off.~ []
@1026838 = ~And I do trust you, but I do not trust myself. I am no traitor, of that I am sure, but what am I if I must hide from my brethren? What am I then?~ []
@1026843 = ~I begin to think that most things are simple to you. You have helped nothing with this comment. I... I do not wish to continue this. Let's just go. Quietly.~ []
@1026844 = ~Yes, but can I? There is no middle ground. I am heading for an extreme of either end. With you at least the choice is mine. It is, isn't it?~ []
@1026856 = ~It is not the weather. I just... something is coming and I do not like how it feels. I don't know what it is, but I do not like how it feels.~ []
@1026860 = ~I hope I can offer you such 'kind' words when you need it. This is no time for humor, thank you. Let's just keep moving, but... stay close, if you would.~ []
@1026862 = ~I... I am sorry, but I need a moment to collect myself.~ [JAHEIRA2]
@1026864 = ~No need to ask. We haven't had time to stop since your meeting with... well...~ []
@1026870 = ~There is no shame in this. You did what you thought was right.~ []
@1026877 = ~No. No it isn't. Blindly on, hitting walls as we go. (sniff) By the gods, let's just get moving. I do so hate getting this sick on emotion.~ []
@1026882 = ~Such a line I have not heard since my early days traveling the hordelands. Thank you for trying to cheer me, but I will manage.~ []
@1026883 = ~Your silver tongue could do with some smithing as well. A bit blunt, I would think.~ []
@1026887 = ~Yes... yes, I suppose I have. How much did I do for you however, and how much was for me alone.~ []
@1026891 = ~No, no it wouldn't. I am sorry, but this will take time once again.~ []
@1026896 = ~Your old injuries feeling alright? I thought I saw you wince a moment ago.~ [JAHEIRA4]
@1026898 = ~What? Ah, yes, just a bit of... of knee trouble. A roll of the eyes for the pain.~ []
@1026905 = ~Oh, no, not in the least, really. I am just... I have to deal with a few things... I have to decide some things.~ []
@1026908 = ~So... could I... could I have a few moments of your time?~ [JAHEIRA5]
@1026913 = ~As inconvenient as it is, go ahead.~ []
@1026919 = ~Jaheira, this is not a 'chat.' This is more a judicial inquiry.~ []
@1026935 = ~No? The Harper in your midst?~ []
@1026936 = ~You are not 'the Harper in my midst,' you are Jaheira by my side.~ []
@1026938 = ~Is everyone an ally or an enemy? Is everything a matter of battle to you? I had hoped it would not be, but I have had growing doubts to the contrary.~ []
@1026940 = ~I... I don't know what to say to that. I still have many concerns that must be addressed, but you seem so...~ []
@1026941 = ~There has been change all around. You may have been affected in ways you don't know.~ []
@1026943 = ~How... hmm... how did the last battle make you feel? Did you enjoy it?~ [JAHEIRA7]
@1026947 = ~I... I am sorry! But I must know! I must know that you are more humane than not! I must know that your... your poison blood has not taken your senses!~ []
@1026954 = ~I guess that would be best, wouldn't it. For... for the best. I will not bother you again.~ []
@1026958 = ~Good morning, my lad. How are ye this morn? I did not wish to startle ye, but I was walking by and could not help but notice this note blowing in the wind.~ [TERMIN02]
@1026960 = ~Jaheira! I would have words with you!~ [DERMIN06]
@1026966 = ~This is a very special case. You have faced little opposition from the Harpers so far. From here on the attacks will increase in severity, unless you come with me now.~ []
@1026975 = ~Well, that was decidedly unpleasant, and more than I wish to worry about.~ []
@1026980 = ~I am going to do exactly what I said I would do. I am going to think about this. All of this.~ []
@1026983 = ~He was Calimshite, I believe. They are fond of slaves. The price for my safety was the favors I bestowed... erotic arts that the Drow have honed for an eon.~ []
@1026985 = ~Actually, I rather enjoyed it: he was quickly my pawn, and the caravan went as I wished. Alas, his heart gave out one night... the guards thought it murder and chased me away.~ []
@1026987 = ~That's horrible... I can't believe he made you do those things.~ []
@1026990 = ~I had heard manhood was available at a price; I am not surprised to find you copperless. Cower before my manner, if you must, <CHARNAME>... you disgust me.~ []
@1026992 = ~I think it's disgusting... but I suppose you had little choice.~ []
@1026993 = ~Oh, get away from me, already. I tire of your ridiculous games.~ []
@1026996 = ~I... I know, I know, my husband. (sob!)  But I saw my poor little Wellyn, I saw him! He comes to me at night and he is not at rest! He was murdered... (sob!) ... and he is not at rest!~ []
@1026997 = ~... Mama? Papa? Is that you?~ []
@1027000 = ~Spirit? I... my name is Wellyn. I just want... I just want my stuffed bear back...~ []
@1027002 = ~Spirit? I've... I've never hurt anybody! My name is Wellyn and I... I just want my stuffed bear back...~ []
@1027004 = ~It's my favorite bear, Littleman... the bad man who came into our house... he, he hurt me and he took Littleman with everything else... (sob!)  I can never go to sleep without Littleman!~ []
@1027012 = ~Oh... (sob)  I just... I just want my Littleman! (sob!)  Where is my Mama? (sob!) ... Mama? Is that you?...~ []
@1027014 = ~Oh, please, please! (sob!)  I just want my Littleman! (sob!)  Why did you take it! ... Mama? Mama, is that you?...~ []
@1027016 = ~I've... I've gone to him... (sob!) ... I've tried to tell him that I just want my bear, please, but he just gets too frightened of me. (sob!)  Oh, please get it from him!~ []
@1027017 = ~... Mama? Mama, do you know where my Littleman is? Do you have him?~ []
@1027018 = ~Yes, Wellyn... here is your bear. You can go to sleep now.~ []
@1027024 = ~You don't? (sob!)  Oh... could you get him? Could you get my stuffed bear, pleeeaaasse?~ []
@1027029 = ~... Th-thank you, <SIRMAAM>...~ []
@1027030 = ~... Mama? Papa? Is that you? Do you have my Littleman?~ []
@1027035 = ~(sob!)  Mama? Is that you? (sob!)  You're not my mama! But... but you have my bear! You have my Littleman!!~ []
@1027036 = ~Oh, please... I cannot sleep without my Littleman! Can I have him... can I have him, please?~ []
@1027037 = ~This stuffed bear? Er, certainly... here you go...~ []
@1027039 = ~What?! You won't give me my bear?! You... you are so MEAN!!~ []
@1027040 = ~Ahhhh... fleshling! This is OUR land in the evening... this is no place for such as YOU!!~ []
@1027043 = ~Aaah! Oh... me pardons... I thought ye were that bloody ghost again...!~ []
@1027048 = ~Oh, aye... unfortunately. A, uh... ghost is sometimes hauntin' me. Terrible, frightenin' thing, that is.~ []
@1027053 = ~Well... yes it is. How did you know that?~ []
@1027056 = ~This ghost you mentioned... it wouldn't be a little halfling boy by the name of Wellyn, would it?~ []
@1027060 = ~I am a, er... merchant of fine goods, me <LADYLORD>. Pleased t' meet ye. Now, if ye'll excuse me... ye are in my room...~ []
@1027065 = ~Oh... er, I don't know. Can't say for sure. Excuse me, but this does be me private room... could ye please leave?~ []
@1027066 = ~This ghost wouldn't be haunting you because it is a little boy you murdered and robbed, would it, hm? Hand over his bear... now.~ []
@1027069 = ~Alright, alright... I'm going.~ []
@1027070 = ~You're... you're here to retrieve his... bear? I, uh... I think I have it around here, somewhere. Yes... let me take a look... ah, yes. Here it is.~ []
@1027071 = ~Give... give that to the little bloody bastard and tell him to stay away from me!~ []
@1027073 = ~I'll spare your life... but don't let me catch you around here again!~ []
@1027075 = ~What?! How... how did you know about that?! Well... you'll not take ME alive!!~ []
@1027082 = ~Alright, alright... I'm going, I'm going... just let me collect me things, here...~ []
@1027083 = ~Oh, it is, it is... I'll just collect me things and I'll be out o' yer hair...~ []
@1027088 = ~Oh... it's you again... what is it ye want, now?~ []
@1027095 = ~Our... our little boy is at peace, now. He appeared to us to say good-bye, and told us that you had rescued his bear. I... I thank you, my <LADYLORD>, you are very kind.~ []
@1027096 = ~Yes, thank you so much. (sniff!)  It is... such a relief. Come, my husband... let us go home.~ []
@1027100 = ~Oh... I am so happy that you have come back!~ []
@1027101 = ~Oy, now! What... what are you doin' sneakin' up on a fella in the middle o' the bleedin' night, aye?~ []
@1027104 = ~You look like you're digging up that grave... what are you, some kind of graverobber?~ []
@1027105 = ~Sorry... didn't mean to bother you.~ []
@1027110 = ~Listen, here... you either cough up some money or I'll report you to the garrison.~ []
@1027113 = ~I'm just diggin' up a bit o' buried treasure... hey, now. Ye gives me the willies, ye does. Ye're in league with the bleedin' garrison, ye are!!~ []
@1027114 = ~No, I'm not... but I'll not allow you to commit this sacrilege!~ []
@1027120 = ~Well... all right. But make a move on, then, or ye'll be regrettin' it mighty soon.~ []
@1027121 = ~Ho, citizen! On orders of the Council, I accuse you of crimes against Amn.~ []
@1027133 = ~You're on the wrong side of the river here, friend. This is Shadow Thief territory and we can't have you committing monstrous crimes without our permission.~ []
@1027146 = ~There may be such a woman... it could be that the answer to your question is playing itself out right now.~ []
@1027147 = ~Jaheira, I don't care that... what? Glad? I thought you wanted this?~ []
@1027170 = ~I am not in a mood to converse with madmen of the sewers. Back to your slime pit, old fool!~ []
@1027185 = ~My one true companion, topsider.~ []
@1027201 = ~No... I enjoy the excitement of this life. Is that so hard to understand?~ []
@1027210 = ~Well, think about it, then. But do so silently... and let us continue our travels.~ []
@1027215 = ~'Passing by?' Athkatla? I see. Well, thank you for... thank you for following me, even if you are only 'passing by.'~ []
@1027220 = ~Then you do not know me well, <CHARNAME>. I am unlike you all. In some ways... if not all.~ []
@1027228 = ~You remove the ring from the finger and it tingles in your palm. There is obviously something special about the ring.~ []
@1027231 = ~Certainly. If you wish to discuss nothing and have no conversation of any type... if you wish to remain an ignorant dalhar, I am only happy to oblige.~ []
@1027232 = ~Notice the lack of Spectral Harpists? They were here at one time, and they would not leave their post unless it was no longer to be guarded.~ []
@1027237 = ~True... but if that were not the case, you would consider such a thing natural, yes? I have seen the custom borne out and cannot grasp the notion properly.~ []
@1027240 = ~Those we kill in self-defense may look like Harper allies, even if they are not. We have no choice, and I will not feel guilty over this tangled web any more.~ []
@1027250 = ~Then we will go together. Rejoin and... and walk with me.~ []
@1027263 = ~You are a cold and vicious woman, Viconia.~ []
@1027266 = ~That sounds like an excuse.~ []
@1027279 = ~You not know the glory of Crragtail! You stupid <RACE> of above, where sun causes rot and dryout! Down here all is moist and soft, and good throne!~ []
@1027297 = ~Peeeyewww... rrrr...~ []
@1027300 = ~I do not tolerate threats from creatures that live in filth!~ []
@1027309 = ~Staff? You want Stick of Many Foods?! You not get! You come to steal greatest treasure of Crragtail empire! Better than Throne of Comfy, or Pipe That Smell Not Quite So Much!~ []
@1027311 = ~RRaagh! Rrget yourr traitorrrr!!!!~ []
@1027318 = ~I do not wish to diminish the glory of your rule, but how does 2,000 gold sound?~ []
@1027320 = ~Grrrr... rrwha?~ []
@1027324 = ~Ehh... how much you say? What wa' dat?~ []
@1027325 = ~2,000 gold for the glory of your realm.~ []
@1027326 = ~I was taunting you. I offer nothing! You live in a fool's realm!~ []
@1027327 = ~Yeah, glory, whateverrrr. Stick yours. Have funs above.~ []
@1027328 = ~Reaagh... wha?!!~ []
@1027331 = ~Wha... RRRAAAGHHH!!~ []
@1027332 = ~Yes, I intend to have power for myself.~ []
@1027335 = ~You wish to have power, do you? I... I think...~ []
@1027336 = ~... I think it is disgusting that a lowly male would desire to rise so far past his place. You are nothing like Shar or Lolth!~ []
@1027337 = ~Ah, I see. As I thought, you are yet the reticent coward. You remind me of the lowly drow males, crawling along the ground on your belly with eyes downcast.~ []
@1027338 = ~The undersea of Laratrak, for example, defies words. To sail across takes two days luent to linoin... east to west... three days trezen to werneth... north to south.~ []
@1027345 = ~Do not be a wael... a fool. I enjoyed it well enough; I killed for sport and necessity, but I took no pleasure in sacrifice solely to satiate her endless desire.~ []
@1027347 = ~They took me to the orlenggin... the sacrificial altar... where a surfacer screamed in agony, and for the pleasure of Lolth I was given a spider dagger to end his life.~ []
@1027348 = ~This human was but a kul'gobuss to me, but it felt wrong. He was bare and chained... helpless. His tears ran freely as he begged for mercy in his unfamiliar tongue.~ []
@1027350 = ~There were... many sacrifices, were there?~ []
@1027354 = ~It is the drow way. But that is... behind me, now. Let us continue our travels, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1027355 = ~My heart is filled with bile at these memories, at any rate. Yes... yes, do let us move on.~ []
@1027356 = ~He... he was no mere male! Is it so difficult for you to believe that I might have cared for another, once?!~ []
@1027357 = ~Yes. Yes, he saved me. I... I am sorry, <CHARNAME>, I do not wish to continue discussing Valas. Excuse me.~ []
@1027361 = ~Our... our relationship was unusual, yes...~ []
@1027362 = ~... I... I am sorry, <CHARNAME>. I do not wish to discuss Valas any further. Excuse me.~ []
@1027363 = ~There are normally no...'brothers', although some males are favored more than others. Most simply exist to serve Queen and House, but this is... not always the case.~ []
@1027366 = ~You mentioned your brother, before... he was a special case?~ []
@1027380 = ~So I will fear no more. I... I value your company, <CHARNAME>. After all we have been through, I must know: do you value my company as well?~ []
@1027383 = ~... of the party? So, business alone has kept you with me. Very well... Best I know now, before... Well, that is quite enough of that. Let's go, shall we?~ []
@1027386 = ~I won't delay us any longer for now. We will speak again on this, in better spirits, I hope.~ []
@1027387 = ~Ah, the dawning of our day, though it is very rarely that we seem to match our sleep cycle to the day or night.~ [JAHEIRB1]
@1027392 = ~Sunrises are but one of, oh, at least two things worth waking to I could think of.~ []
@1027395 = ~Perhaps, though I intend no malice. I would laugh at you as I laugh at myself, and... hopefully I will come to know you that well.~ []
@1027400 = ~No need to. No sunrise could compare with your beauty in the moonlight.~ []
@1027405 = ~Stop.~ [JAHEIRB2]
@1027406 = ~Do you see him? Ready yourself.~ [JAHEIRBX]
@1027410 = ~As you were 'forced' to deal with the Harpers that died in Athkatla?~ []
@1027412 = ~The garish Hold, his political agenda; he was merely using the weight of the Harper name to promote himself. Tell me: what did he offer you?~ []
@1027415 = ~Ah, but the events are not known. What is accepted is that you have killed your brethren and taken up with a known murderer. There is no evidence existing to the contrary.~ []
@1027417 = ~One grows weary. We would have done good works, Jaheira, just from a more profitable perspective.~ []
@1027419 = ~Innocent?! Is that what you call <CHARNAME>? But <PRO_HESHE> is a child of Bhaal! Whether his nature is good or bad it will certainly be disruptive!~ []
@1027423 = ~Ah, your wit is still the most dangerous trait about you, Jaheira. I told you to cultivate it. Little did I know I would be on the receiving end one day.~ []
@1027430 = ~Heh, you and your jokes make me smile far too often, even when I do not want to. People will think I am getting soft.~ []
@1027433 = ~Haha! Shush you! I'm supposed to be feeling bad about this whole thing. Oh, let's just get moving.~ []
@1027442 = ~Nothing, though morale is going to slip if you keep glaring at people.~ []
@1027451 = ~That's what I said but I meant... I'm sorry, I shouldn't need to play these games. I'm just so mad and I don't know how to get it out.~ []
@1027455 = ~He put you in the position of opposing a mentor. It couldn't help but trouble you.~ []
@1027460 = ~I need you to say... what? I don't know either. I'm sorry, this is not fair to you at all.~ []
@1027463 = ~My brother, Valas, was an exception to the standard drow male. He was my childhood friend... and perhaps my only friend, after all is said.~ []
@1027465 = ~He... watched over me and protected me, and I ensured that the worst of the abuses that befell males did not strike him.~ []
@1027466 = ~In the end... he saved my life. He... prevented my sacrifice and killed our mother, giving me the opportunity to flee.~ []
@1027470 = ~He... no longer exists. <CHARNAME>... I am cold and tired and no longer in the mood to speak. Excuse me.~ []
@1027474 = ~(sigh)  Let us... just walk for a while in silence, <CHARNAME>. I am no longer in the mood to talk.~ []
@1027493 = ~So... where was I? Oh, yes. Your part in this. I would like you to go to Mae'Var and join his guild.~ []
@1027495 = ~Sometimes your self-righteous sense of judgement makes me ill to my stomach, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1027496 = ~Yes... so am I. But... that does not mean she will never do so. (sigh)  Come, <CHARNAME>... the road beckons.~ []
@1027499 = ~Alright, fine, I'll stay for a moment. By the gods, Viconia... you're shaking! What is the matter?~ []
@1027501 = ~Then begone, rath'arg... and leave me alone to my misery.~ []
@1027504 = ~I... I dream of Valas, sometimes, and I try to speak to him in my dreams. But he is only a monster, now, and I scream when his horrid spider legs caress me...~ []
@1027505 = ~I think... what can Lolth do to me if she has done this to Valas? What worse torments await me when she finally decides to come?!~ []
@1027506 = ~<CHARNAME>, I am frightened to my very core! Do not leave me alone! Stay with me this night. I... I need to feel your flesh next to mine, to embrace your strength...~ []
@1027507 = ~It will mean... it will mean nothing. Lolth's reach is far... and I fear there is no escaping it...~ []
@1027513 = ~I do not wish to be cheerful; I wish to be miserable, hating everything that has led to what we are.~ []
@1027517 = ~All right... I will stay with you, if that is what you wish.~ []
@1027525 = ~Do not deny me this, <CHARNAME>... I offer to you all the pleasures that a drow woman may bestow if you but hold me this night.~ []
@1027526 = ~I... do not doubt your ability, Viconia. And you are beautiful. But not like this, not in this manner...~ []
@1027527 = ~Very well, Viconia... I shall stay with you this night if that is what you wish.~ []
@1027529 = ~Viconia... not like this. Not because you are desperate... it isn't right.~ []
@1027530 = ~I do. Come to my arms out of view of prying eyes... place your hand against my darkly trembling heart and I will show you the boundaries of passion as only I can...~ []
@1027531 = ~Do not deny me, <CHARNAME>... and do not deny yourself.~ []
@1027537 = ~My mother wished me to recant, to prostrate myself before the Spider Queen and beg forgiveness. She was desperate that I do so, in fact.~ []
@1027540 = ~What if they were the wrong ones? I have turned this over and over in my mind, and the dead have piled up and I have still gone forward.~ []
@1027544 = ~She abandoned me, left me completely without power. I had no brother, no power and House DeVir was, as far as I knew, falling.~ []
@1027546 = ~Come, my children! Fear the power of Talos! Join us in reverent worship to avoid the disasters that are sure to strike us down in the days to come!~ []
@1027547 = ~I thought Talos is an evil god... how is it that he is openly worshipped here?~ []
@1027548 = ~I have heard a bit of Talos... tell me more.~ []
@1027564 = ~I have heard that Lathander is a young and vain god... why would you grant him obeisance?~ []
@1027567 = ~Lathander may be prone to the vagaries of youth but he has other gifts. To serve the Morninglord is to strive for vitality and joy... what is wrong with that?~ []
@1027573 = ~Bah! What does the heart know. It makes you do foolish things for no cause. It makes you forget the dead before you should. It makes you fall in...~ []
@1027578 = ~It most certainly is, supplicant. Enter our most sacred temple, and bask in the glory of the God of Dawns... experience His benevolence for yourself.~ []
@1027579 = ~It... makes you do things that wreak havoc on your mind. I'm a sorry, <CHARNAME>, you should not have to hear this. You have been good and true.~ []
@1027581 = ~I should be happy, but I am not. Even with all we have done to make things right, I am still troubled.~ []
@1027601 = ~And arrogance will kill you. They thought they were right, and we think we are right. Is there so much of a difference?~ []
@1027603 = ~You needn't keep a distance between us. I am in less of a mood now.~ [JAHEIRB5]
@1027606 = ~Should I tailor my mood to yours? You have proven unresponsive in the past.~ []
@1027609 = ~You have questioned our relationship at every step, even as you pursued it.~ []
@1027616 = ~You have questioned our relationship at every step, even as you pursued it.~ []
@1027618 = ~You have questioned our relationship at every step, even as you pursued it.~ []
@1027619 = ~This is a place of the peaceful and divine... not for the likes of you. Begone from here!~ []
@1027620 = ~I do so worry what has become of the missing priests... there are so many who have disappeared it is a terrible concern!~ []
@1027621 = ~I do not trust these preachers... what is this Unseeing Eye? It sounds horrid... and they have all plucked out their own eyes!~ []
@1027624 = ~I pay homage to all our gods, but I serve only Arvoreen. One day I hope to be foremost among His holy swords.~ []
@1027633 = ~Sometimes I feel as if the gods are testing me, little one... but overall, yes, they watch over me most kindly.~ []
@1027635 = ~It just isn't fair... I donate coin to Lathander for prosperity and Helm for protection... and then the Talassans come and burn down my shop!~ []
@1027636 = ~A merchant must cover all his bases and be wary to offend no god... it is a most trying existence!~ []
@1027642 = ~I am trying. You have shown such caring so far. I have taken you for granted as someone that would always be here, even as I questioned our very friendship.~ []
@1027644 = ~I will not make such a mistake again. Of this I am sure.~ []
@1027649 = ~I have... had a realization. I have been walking with my eyes downcast for so long I had forgotten the beauty of the land. I... all we have seen; I had thought never to feel the warmth of nature again.~ [JAHEIRB6]
@1027656 = ~You make me appreciate such things. I never appreciated a simple forest before you.~ []
@1027657 = ~Do we not see nature in everything? Even in the deepest dungeons?~ []
@1027660 = ~Oh, some days I am sure that the gods are all frowning on us. Faerun is doomed! Doomed!~ []
@1027661 = ~There are beings of great power in the planes that are my home... but do you think that they really concern themselves so much with this one? It strikes me as a barren fancy, really.~ []
@1027666 = ~There's no rest fer the wicked, they says... so I plan on prayin' extra hard today, I does.~ []
@1027667 = ~Pardon me fer a teeny bit o' blasphemy... but have ye seen the Morninglord's lasses as o' late? Now I know what 'em priests says about rebirth, I does!~ []
@1027676 = ~All these preachers about for this no-eyed god are a little creepy... I wonder what sins they absolve?~ []
@1027680 = ~By Lathander's grace the entire city has prospered... it is only right that we lay down in devotion to Him.~ []
@1027682 = ~The city is in dire straits with so many of the clergy disappearing... only to turn up as converts of this strange cult. It isn't right!~ []
@1027685 = ~By Lathander's grace... how can you bring one of those dark, evil things here into this part of the city?!~ []
@1027686 = ~I'll walk where I like, rivvil... and you can take your petty religious slurs and throw them in the river, for all I care!~ []
@1027688 = ~Why... that is the most darling little pet you have there, sir.~ []
@1027689 = ~Boo is no pet... he is a fine companion for Minsc. But he seems to like you anyway.~ []
@1027693 = ~And I would stay by the brooks of home if I wished only my reflection. I would like to see some of myself in your face, but not so much that I lose what is you.~ []
@1027696 = ~I must admit that Lathander seems to have the right idea... those gaudy, golden interiors are fit for a true King, if you ask me.~ []
@1027699 = ~Ah, if it isn't Lord Valygar. I am sorry, my lord... we still haven't built a temple to Mystra for your family, yet.~ []
@1027700 = ~Oh, stop it. I'm being serious here.~ []
@1027701 = ~You know very well, my lord, that I am no sorcerer... and nearly all of my family is well beyond the reach of your petty barbs!~ []
@1027704 = ~I do not know what you mean... I have no plans to leave my gnomish lord Baervan Wildwanderer... I owe Him too much, sir.~ []
@1027706 = ~She seems to be well enough remembered, here... but I thought her worship was no more.~ []
@1027709 = ~Indeed! In her time, Waukeen was known and welcomed fondly by all in the great City of Coin! The Promenade was built to honor her and trade prospered throughout!~ []
@1027710 = ~It is sad she disappeared from our lives... many of us still honor her. I am confident that one day she will return and claim all the wealth that is rightfully hers.~ []
@1027713 = ~Perhaps this changes nothing, perhaps everything. I don't care anymore. My heart cannot have nature within and be ashamed as well.~ []
@1027721 = ~We have to be nearing our goal. It has been so long a journey and we've been through so much. I hope this does not end up all being for naught.~ [JAHEIRB7]
@1027723 = ~I could not have come this far without you helping me, Jaheira.~ []
@1027728 = ~There can be no mercy for this creature. What he has done is unforgivable.~ []
@1027751 = ~Who knows, indeed. Yesterday saw friends die; saw blood spilled. Tomorrow...~ []
@1027756 = ~I see. Then stay up and talk with me for a while. I doubt I shall sleep.~ []
@1027759 = ~Perhaps we should take some time to talk.~ []
@1027769 = ~Er... yes... yes, I am. Why do you ask?~ []
@1027772 = ~Ack! I... are you sure? I mean... I have no memory...~ []
@1027774 = ~I... I see. What is it exactly that you want?~ []
@1027779 = ~Heh heh... oh, nothing, Talon Nirkhas. A simple mistake, perhaps, on my part. Please do excuse me. (You are in SUCH trouble, girl!)~ []
@1027780 = ~I see. Talos' blessing on you, then, and... er... good day.~ []
@1027781 = ~(ahem)  It is... not against my vows to drink the cups or sample the flesh of a willing woman. We Talassans favor pleasure in the face of the destruction of the Stormlord.~ []
@1027782 = ~Whew! I am certainly glad that situation was not what it seemed! There are many... ah... celebrations I have but hazy memories of!~ []
@1027783 = ~What are... what are you looking at? Nothing to see, here.~ []
@1027790 = ~The child is mine... like she was the cleric's? Or the gods know only how many other men's?~ []
@1027792 = ~She is? Er... how much do I owe you?~ []
@1027793 = ~Oh, er... perhaps I was mistaken. You look very similar to another I had... spent time with. Excuse me, my lord.~ []
@1027800 = ~I'll give you the money... for the little girl's sake if nothing else.~ []
@1027802 = ~I am afraid you're barking up the wrong tree... I do not have that to give you.~ []
@1027806 = ~Thank you, my lord. My name, by the way, is Miranda... and this is your, um, daughter, Lanie. We appreciate your dedication to duty and will see you anon, perhaps.~ []
@1027810 = ~Not many would, I suppose. She is a goddess of the halflings... representing our ideals of friendship and trust.~ []
@1027812 = ~As you might understand, it is important for us halflings to fit in wherever we can. A home is a home... we may as well strive to make it a pleasant home.~ []
@1027821 = ~Bah! It is the end come upon us! Many of our priests have disappeared... but some have returned to preach for this devil god! Talos will take revenge!!~ []
@1027833 = ~It is a good thing for Cyrando... he has such a way with words. He is a good friend... and I am a poor excuse for a bard. (sigh)~ []
@1027835 = ~The foolishness of this Garrick fellow... does he think the Lady Irlana does not see through his ruse?~ []
@1027836 = ~I am Sir Cadril, Knight of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart. Pleased to make your acquaintance, my <LADYLORD>.~ []
@1027840 = ~If I e'er found a man who could speak as Garrick does, but with fluency and passion... then that man would have my heart, methinks.~ []
@1027841 = ~Greetings to you, my <LADYLORD>. I be Lady Irlana, Knight of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart. At your service.~ []
@1027843 = ~This foolish boy, Garrick, can barely take instruction... sometimes I think he barely has a thought in his head.~ []
@1027844 = ~My heart goes out to the Lady Irlana... but this is as close a simple gnome such as I can ever hope to come to a noble beauty like her.~ []
@1027847 = ~Now, that's not necessarily true, my friend. My cousin Adecan married a fine human woman, he did. He was of the sort that was not fine to look on, as well... but she did appreciate his sense of humor.~ []
@1027850 = ~The lad could tell a joke to save his life, in fact. Once kept a trio of ogres laughing so heartily that they forgot to eat him. Too bad he didn't speak griffon, however... poor Adecan. I hear his last joke was a zinger, although the punchline got cut short.~ []
@1027852 = ~It has been a struggle of duty and honor, good friend... but the gods have treated me well, nevertheless, I think.~ []
@1027853 = ~Ah... Anomen. I see you are... back.~ []
@1027854 = ~I am, Cadril. And there is no reason for your furtive, suspicious glances, either... whether you like me or not.~ []
@1027855 = ~Ah... Sir Keldorn! How do you do? I just spoke to Lady Maria this morning, in fact.~ []
@1027856 = ~I... I see. She is well?~ []
@1027862 = ~Hmmmn... for some reason, you seem rather familiar, too, my dear.~ []
@1027867 = ~You are a bard, man... look into the depths of your heart and draw from that well a potion that will please your lady. Speak of things that will move a mountain by your passion and eloquence! To do aught else would be to shame your profession.~ []
@1027870 = ~Err... Garrick, isn't it? What can I do for ye, Garrick?~ []
@1027871 = ~I, uh... I, uh...~ []
@1027873 = ~I am... here to pledge... to you the love... of a poet and an artist. Take my fragile love, my... sweet, hold it in your... hands as a gaze upon you admiringly. Er... yes, that's right...~ []
@1027875 = ~Oh... I see. Well, thank you, Garrick.~ []
@1027878 = ~(Come with me, my lady and let me... ow! damn insects! Wait, fool, don't say that!)~ []
@1027879 = ~Come with... me, my lady... and let me out damn insects! No, you fool... don't, uh...~ []
@1027880 = ~(Heh... you've got a prize, here, my lady.)~ []
@1027882 = ~Um... excuse me for a moment...~ []
@1027883 = ~Lady Irlana! I wish to, uh, proclaim my undying love... for you. Yes, for you!~ []
@1027885 = ~(Patience, my lady... this could be amusing.)~ []
@1027887 = ~Yes... ummm... okay...~ []
@1027889 = ~Lady Irlana, I am... bedazzled by your... beauty and yawn-struck... by your nobility. What... I would not to do... spend an evening... in your barns.~ []
@1027891 = ~Arms, fool! I, uh... I meant arms. Yes, your arms.~ []
@1027894 = ~Well... it's easy... I, uh...~ []
@1027895 = ~(I can never truly be worthy of a true lady of virtue, my love... I only desire that you see past my faults and give me a chance!)~ []
@1027898 = ~I can never... truly be worthy of a... blue lady of virtue..my love... I only desire you... that you see past... my faults and give... me pants!~ []
@1027904 = ~Thank you, sir knight. I am most fond of the Lady Irlana... and am pleased that she was able to accept love from a simple gnome such as myself.~ []
@1027909 = ~Yes, well, congratulations, again. And farewell to you both, for now... I shall see you on your return.~ []
@1027910 = ~Thank you, Sir Cadril... I shall see you soon.~ []
@1027938 = ~No, I'm sorry, I don't have a reason to speak with you.~ []
@1027939 = ~I don't believe you, Viconia. You opened up to me... and now you snap shut again. Why?~ []
@1027942 = ~Do not attempt to render judgement on my mind, imbecile! Just... leave me be! Let me scour the stain of your touch from me... and be done with it!~ []
@1027946 = ~Bah! Do not attempt to look into my mind and render judgement, imbecile! You haven't the strength or the knowledge! Just... leave me be!~ []
@1027948 = ~You nauseate me, <CHARNAME>... is that not reason enough? I look upon you and I see something that I would rather squish under my boot!~ []
@1027958 = ~I am telling you that I have had rivvin by the dozens, that I allowed their saliva to cover me, allowed them to use me for their pleasures!! And I enjoyed it!!~ []
@1027963 = ~Finally you show some sense! I am drow, foolish jaluk... never forget that! Jal khaless zhah waela!~ []
@1027968 = ~You would not let me repel you, no matter how I tried. I am defeated by your stubborn will and strange regard. My need is real, <CHARNAME>... stay with me tonight.~ []
@1027969 = ~I'm sorry, Viconia. I think it is best if this relationship does not continue... it will never work out.~ []
@1027971 = ~Very well... I shall.~ []
@1027974 = ~Very well, Viconia... I shall stay with you.~ []
@1027975 = ~Come to me, then, my mrann d'ssinss. You have defeated me... now taste your victory...~ []
@1027997 = ~I... I am lucky, <CHARNAME>, to have found you on the surface. To think that I would need to come so far, to such an alien place, to find someone that I could... trust.~ []
@1027998 = ~You are not so terrible, <CHARNAME>... for a male.~ []
@1027999 = ~And you are not so terrible... for a drow.~ []
@1028000 = ~I think I understand what you mean, Viconia... and I thank you.~ []
@1028003 = ~This must not come to pass. The everseeing eye of Helm must be made aware of what they intend.~ [OISIGX02]
@1028006 = ~Do not pout so, <CHARNAME>. I meant no barb by it. This is unfamiliar territory for me, as a drow... although, with you, it does not seem so bad as it once did.~ []
@1028008 = ~There you are. I knew you would come. You have the look of a servant of what is right, a <PRO_MANWOMAN> of good faith and charity.~ []
@1028011 = ~The illithid mind is a stranger landscape still. Their main goal is dominance of others... and they believe that life with the elder brain is the highest form of being.~ []
@1028012 = ~That, and the delight they seem to get from cracking open your skull like a hen's egg and drinking everything swimming inside your head...~ []
@1028018 = ~The Kuo-Toa will trade, but negotiations are fraught with danger. No one Kuo-Toan settlement is the same as the next... they are unstable and prone to profound suspicion.~ []
@1028029 = ~Do not assume kinship solely on appearance. I will decide my alliances.~ []
@1028036 = ~This prophet preyed on the people's need for security. Can you not offer this?~ []
@1028043 = ~Fathers do not exist as you know it. The males service the matron of the house when she wishes to conceive... or when she desires pleasure.~ []
@1028044 = ~Welcome to the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart, young <MANWOMAN>. I am Prelate Wessalen. Walk always on the path of justice, honor, and duty.~ []
@1028045 = ~Amongst the Drow, cruelty and pain are both armor and shield. It makes us deadly... Lolth encourages competition and rivalry to keep us strong.~ []
@1028046 = ~As an adult, he was a useful wizard... and amused my mother enough that she did not sell him into slavery.~ []
@1028048 = ~And I certainly did not expect him to... do what he did. Knowing that he would have to pay the price.~ []
@1028051 = ~Because she never forgives a trespass. She keeps a frightening thrall over her sect... visiting from the Demonweb as often as a peasant visits the greengrocer.~ []
@1028052 = ~It is because I have seen, because I have felt the lash of tentacle rods, that she will... will leave me to think I am safe or free and then she will come for me.~ []
@1028057 = ~I... have a need, <CHARNAME>. A need that must be fulfilled... I must feel your strength within me and around me.~ []
@1028060 = ~'Allo there, pally. I'm Squire Melvin. It's nice t' meet ya.~ []
@1028062 = ~Are you aware that, despite our intimacies, I know little of you other than the usual graces? You've mysteries in you... and secrets. That face holds tales in its creases.~ [VICONI96]
@1028065 = ~We have information that the core of their worshippers are underground and relatively close, though our scrying has only allowed us to see as far as the sewers.~ []
@1028068 = ~Imoen... was then and is now. She's my closest friend.~ []
@1028069 = ~Gorion... a wise man, good teacher and greater friend.~ []
@1028073 = ~What is the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart?~ []
@1028075 = ~Then ask nothing more. I will follow into the depths and return with answers.~ []
@1028076 = ~And what is the reward? I am a <MANWOMAN> of faith, but I must eat as well.~ []
@1028077 = ~Err... I change my mind. I won't anger a deity, especially if it involves the sewers.~ []
@1028081 = ~'Tis an order o' paladins 'n such. Truth, justice, honor, and courage, ye knows.~ []
@1028103 = ~Well, good luck, Melvin.~ []
@1028113 = ~Aye, ya gots a fine look about ya.~ []
@1028119 = ~I'm not sure... I was hoping on being somewhere with you, however.~ []
@1028129 = ~I apologize Viconia... I just didn't expect this from you.~ []
@1028130 = ~It's a pleasurable enough diversion, Viconia, but nothing beyond that.~ []
@1028135 = ~Feh, it is little more than idle fantasy, really. It is good to see that you have a little desire however... perhaps that is something I can work on, hm?~ []
@1028152 = ~May the Morninglord's Dawn find you ever renewed, my friend.~ []
@1028157 = ~I may be tired, but I look forward to showing the arts I learned as a Drow. I hold a degree of... affection... for you, <CHARNAME>. How else am I supposed to show this?~ []
@1028167 = ~Hmm. An odd thing to say. If I had no male to service me in the Underdark I slept alone. I am... unfamiliar with this. How else would you show... affection?~ []
@1028168 = ~Here... let us hold each other tonight, only, and I will show you.~ []
@1028171 = ~As you wish, my mrann d'ssinss... come into my arms and let me show you but a small portion of the drow's vast knowledge of the art of massage...~ []
@1028174 = ~As... as you wish, <CHARNAME>. I feel uncomfortable with this arrangement, but I suppose that... that some rest is not uncalled-for.~ []
@1028176 = ~Is it... is it time to awaken already?~ [VICONI99]
@1028180 = ~I must admit, <CHARNAME>, that I slept more deeply that I have in some time. I have not felt safer in... a long time... than I did in your arms. A unique experience.~ []
@1028185 = ~No... it was more than that. I thank you for your... consideration.~ []
@1028186 = ~I am going to ask you to do something that I would not ask of any but the bravest of the faithful. This beast must be destroyed.~ []
@1028189 = ~I... I have nothing... nothing to answer that with, <CHARNAME>. Thank you for your... consideration.~ []
@1028190 = ~You are awake, I see. That is good. I have been watching you for some time... thinking. I wish to share my thoughts with you.~ [VICONIA1]
@1028195 = ~I know this is not your intention. You have given me... protection, trust and a fair amount of affection, I would think. I am too proud to continue in this vein.~ []
@1028199 = ~Are you sure about this? I... have deep feelings for you, Viconia. I would not want you to waste what could be.~ []
@1028200 = ~To your reward then, for you have performed admirably. You are to receive the greatest gift that we can bestow, one that transcends mere coin or purse.~ []
@1028203 = ~Do not crawl like an infant, fool. Your mewling churns my stomach. Desist and we both rest easier. Let us just continue our travels, <CHARNAME>... I much prefer that.~ []
@1028204 = ~I am sure, <CHARNAME>. You and I know there is nothing that 'could be'. It is ended cleanly... so let us continue on our travels without further argument.~ []
@1028206 = ~In this there is allegiance. Your faith is aligned as ours, though it lacks direction.~ []
@1028210 = ~No... that's fine. Stay, if you must.~ []
@1028212 = ~Very well, I shall stay. But take your pathetic eyes from me... and let us continue our travels.~ []
@1028213 = ~I have... I have an odd feeling. I do not... think... I have ever felt like this before...~ [VICONIA2]
@1028221 = ~I will not be patronized by you, you idiot jaluk! Next time you have something smart to say, shove your head underwater before I do it for you!~ []
@1028223 = ~I am not sure. As drow, we grow to have a natural tendency to feel rock... and to feel magic... and this has similarities of both within it...~ []
@1028224 = ~It is almost as if a dark whisper is traveling over Faerun, searching, seeking out... something. I... fear it is looking for me.~ []
@1028227 = ~Consider always the consequences of your actions so that the least effort may bring the greatest and best reward.~ []
@1028230 = ~Wherever you go, sow seeds of plants, tend the growing things you find, and plant seeds of hope, new ideas, and plans for a rosy future in the minds of all.~ []
@1028234 = ~It... it has the stink of Lolth. She is spinning her web, <CHARNAME>... she is looking for me. Why now? Why?!~ []
@1028235 = ~It... no... there it goes. The feeling... has vanished. But that does not mean it will not return. I... I am suddenly quite cold, inside...~ []
@1028239 = ~Do not worry, Viconia... I am here to protect you.~ []
@1028240 = ~Forget about it, Viconia... there is nothing that can be done.~ []
@1028243 = ~Perhaps... you are right, <CHARNAME>. I am ill at ease, however. If my fears prove to be true, this may be the end of me. I suppose I shall see... when and if it comes.~ []
@1028246 = ~That... feeling! It is back again, but stronger this time! I can feel the ripples of the dweomer... black whispers from the depths of the Abyss!! She has found me! SHE HAS FOUND ME!!~ [VICONIA3]
@1028249 = ~It... it's inside my head! IT'S INSIDE MY HEAD!!~ []
@1028251 = ~There is the strayed one! Gather her, rothe... and kill the others!!~ []
@1028252 = ~Ooooh... that sort of psychic rape by a hound from the depths of the abyss is the sort that I simply will not tolerate! My head feels as if it is barely connected to my body...~ [VICONIA4]
@1028255 = ~I understand that you have saved me, and I am appreciative. The alternative would have been... unthinkable. I am just... a little disoriented...~ []
@1028260 = ~They were handmaidens of Lolth, one a yochlol: a handmaiden from the Abyss. Gated assassins. To think that she would go to such efforts to gather me up, it is almost beyond belief.~ []
@1028262 = ~And... what will she do to take me, next? The Spider Queen is not so easily dissuaded. <CHARNAME>, I despise this terror that threatens to swallow me!~ []
@1028267 = ~Easily and bravely said, <CHARNAME>... but Lolth is no creature to be trifled with. I... I must think. Please, leave me be for a while...~ []
@1028268 = ~I am calm, foolish male... but my fear is justified... the Spider Queen is a thing to be feared! I... I must think, <CHARNAME>. Please, leave me be for a while...~ []
@1028269 = ~Do? I... I do not know. I must think, <CHARNAME>... please, leave me be for but a while...~ []
@1028273 = ~Yes, leave... find some way to save yourself, but I won't have you endangering me or the others!~ []
@1028274 = ~No. Stay here... it is the safest place for you. We will find a way around this.~ []
@1028276 = ~You cast me out?! I should have known it would come to this! All trust... is foolish! Darkness take you, <CHARNAME>, I shall pray for your destruction forever!!~ []
@1028277 = ~I... do not know if there is a way around this. I... please let me think on this, <CHARNAME>... leave me be for a while...~ []
@1028278 = ~Welcome. I had hoped you would come. You bear the signs of one that is good of heart, but that also gives weight to all sides of an argument.~ []
@1028286 = ~You... you are an affront to me... I wish this had never come to be!~ []
@1028290 = ~To the deepest pit of the abyss with my promise! I shall do as I like, you ignorant male!! I... you are an affront to me! I... I wish... this had... never been!!~ []
@1028292 = ~As you wish, <CHARNAME>! This is... easier... for us both, in the end. Begone with you and your ilk, I pray that we never meet again!!~ []
@1028295 = ~I... I... just... leave me be, <CHARNAME>! Just leave me be!!~ []
@1028297 = ~We... we must talk.~ [VICONIA6]
@1028298 = ~This... is not working... between us. It will never work, and I think you know this. There can be only one outcome. It can only end poorly.~ []
@1028302 = ~Love? What is this love? What can it do? Your love will not be enough for us... it cannot provide us a future. You know it is the truth~ []
@1028303 = ~Sooner or later I will fail you, or you will fail me, or Lolth will capture me, or I will cause your death. I am Drow and you are not... there is no happy ending here.~ []
@1028304 = ~We must poison our hearts, my ssinssrigg... we must do what is necessary and cleave us apart before it is too late. And I cannot stay.~ []
@1028306 = ~I thank you, my ssinssrigg... you have shown me something I did not think to find, especially here on the surface. You touched my black soul and I will be forever grateful.~ []
@1028307 = ~If he is lying, then whatever cult he is proposing can only serve to hurt those it bilks into following him.~ []
@1028312 = ~Aluve' ussta mzilst ssin'urn ultrin... farewell, my most handsome conqueror. Until we meet again.~ []
@1028313 = ~Nothing points to the emergence of a new deity. It would be impossible to hide such an event from the Great Guard that is Helm.~ []
@1028319 = ~I... am sorry, Viconia. If only there were some way for you to stay...~ []
@1028332 = ~... I love you, too, <CHARNAME>... in my fashion.~ []
@1028341 = ~Err... I changed my mind. I won't anger a deity, especially if it involves the sewers.~ []
@1028345 = ~I... I regret I am not a creature who can feel things as you do. The capacity... is just not within. I almost wish it was, but darkness and loss are my callings... Shar knows only too well.~ []
@1028351 = ~Hmm. Your refusal is displeasing. Know that Helm frowns upon you, and will do so until you change your course.~ []
@1028368 = ~You have a clear duty here. A lesser <MANWOMAN> might shrink from this, but you must not. The disorder the beast will bring is to be stopped.~ []
@1028377 = ~You are granted a place in Helm's sight. You are aligned with many of us, though you lack direction.~ []
@1028381 = ~Then know the duties: you must be vigilant, fair and diligent. Protect the weak, the unpopular, the injured, and the young. Do not sacrifice them for others.~ []
@1028392 = ~No, I'm sorry, I don't have a reason to speak with you.~ []
@1028395 = ~If there's something that ye be wantin', say so quickly. Delosar's be a busy place and I be always short-staffed... I have little time even for ye.~ []
@1028397 = ~No trouble at all. The door is back the way you came.~ []
@1028404 = ~I hear that the halfling fellow went a built a bloody theater out of his cellar. all th' power to 'im, but most folk I know are only interested in drink. Good thing 'at is, too.~ []
@1028405 = ~I'm sorry... I can be no help to you, my <LADYLORD>. I'm just about run off me feet as it is!~ []
@1028408 = ~This whole business with the murders is unsettling... but I feel a little safer with all the guards here, even if they be addled with wine.~ []
@1028409 = ~I be glad that the murders be over with... but now the constant irritations of the guards is almost too much to bear!~ []
@1028414 = ~You can't be speaking to me... I haven't been called that in ages...~ []
@1028419 = ~That... your goods do NOT work!! You stole my money, you did!~ []
@1028426 = ~Er... alright... fair enough... on yer way, then...~ []
@1028434 = ~And what is it you wish of me?~ []
@1028435 = ~And a lovely job you do.~ []
@1028439 = ~Be wary of those mercenaries from Riatavin upstairs... Dennis and his fellows are e'er up to no good. We'll get them, eventually.~ []
@1028440 = ~You there... I recognize you, I think. Watch your step around here, thief.~ []
@1028444 = ~(hic)  Don' mind me, there... citishen...~ []
@1028445 = ~I... <hic>  I... I am the law! <hic>  I think...~ []
@1028447 = ~The artist is known as Sir Sarles, and he is making an all-too-brief visit. We would be foolish not to seize upon the opportunity to have him work for us.~ []
@1028449 = ~You! <hic>  You're comin' wish me... to me room... or you're under arresht... <hic>~ []
@1028459 = ~Pay for what you must and barter for his service as best you can. Do not stoop to underhanded means... he is worth his coin regardless of the price.~ []
@1028480 = ~I been to the New World city o' Ulatos, mate... off west in Maztica. The governor, there, does treat the natives harshly... It will come to violence soon, I fear.~ []
@1028482 = ~Joy of joys, this morning is a bright one indeed! You have done it, and work has begun already! I cannot thank you enough, and neither can the church itself!~ []
@1028484 = ~Aye, I have heard of such. The priests of Helm in New Waterdeep object strenuously... although I hear nothing has changed.~ []
@1028485 = ~Your reward then. You have earned a portion of the artist's commission, which should cover any costs you incurred quite nicely.~ []
@1028489 = ~I give you a blessed Periapt of Life Protection, that you might prevail against what enemies you may have. You have served well under Lathander. Go in peace.~ []
@1028499 = ~I be in some need of assistance, me <LADYLORD>. There be a fellow within Delosar's Inn, there... Dennis. He owes me a good deal of coin, an' refuses to pay!~ []
@1028500 = ~He promised to pay off me bartab, he did, in exchange for some lessons on the gong. Well, I teached him, I did... an' now he refuses to pay me tab!~ []
@1028504 = ~Er... gong lessons? Are you serious?~ []
@1028510 = ~I've no interest in getting into a fight... find someone else to help you out.~ []
@1028511 = ~The gong be a fine instrument... and it be used in many a rite here in the City o' Coin, me <LADYLORD>... we honors all the gods for business deals, we does. An' besides... it sounds pleasant.~ []
@1028516 = ~I be a poor, poor man, me <LADYLORD>... I have almost nothing to offer ye. I beg of ye to help a destitute teacher find some justice!~ []
@1028521 = ~Aaaah, yer a fine and noble <GIRLBOY>, ye are. Come... follow me inside o' Delosar's and let's have a little talk wi' Dennis, aye? I do believe he is on the second floor.~ []
@1028523 = ~Certainly... let's go and talk to this Dennis fellow, now.~ []
@1028527 = ~I be Dennis... the leader of my mercenary fellows here out o' Riatavin. If you want to keep yer face on straight, you'll stay well clear of us.~ []
@1028528 = ~Fine... so long as you steer clear of me.~ []
@1028532 = ~I have plenty of ale, and so do my soldiers. Last time, <PRO_GIRLBOY>... step back and go away.~ []
@1028533 = ~Well, if you're going to be rude about it, I'll go... just keep clear of me.~ []
@1028537 = ~Are you trying to be funny? I suggest you apologize, little <PRO_GIRLBOY>, before things get... heated.~ []
@1028543 = ~Oy, Dennis, ye mealy-faced sack o' suet! Ye owes me th' coin for me bartab! Pay up or ye'll surely face the consequences!!~ [LOUT02]
@1028544 = ~Don't threaten me, you sorry excuse for a thief... I owe you nothing!~ [LOUTCA02]
@1028546 = ~You've a nerve, drunkard! You took my sweet mother's gong! You stole it and traded it for ale, didn't you?! Didn't you?!~ []
@1028547 = ~... Oh, er... now, I had actually gone an' forgotten about that...~ []
@1028548 = ~... I'll just be on me way, then...~ []
@1028550 = ~Um... me <LADYLORD>? Some... assistance?~ []
@1028553 = ~You'll not restrain this man, Dennis... not while I'm here.~ []
@1028554 = ~Sorry, Vittorio... you're on your own.~ []
@1028555 = ~Well... I, uh...~ []
@1028556 = ~He did. The gong belonged to my mother... it was her dowry and worth a great deal of coin. This damnable lout, here, stole it before my lessons were even finished!~ []
@1028562 = ~... Well, I, um... I may be able to help with that...?~ []
@1028564 = ~... My <LADYLORD>? Would it be too much to ask for you to... um... find this gong for... this gentleman?~ []
@1028566 = ~I... I sold it, I did. To a fence by the name o' Roger... he has 'is hideout in the sewers. I... don't know where, exactly... but it were sold not long ago. He could still have it, he could!~ []
@1028573 = ~Fine. Do what you want... it's got nothing to do with me.~ []
@1028574 = ~That's it, Vittorio... either cough up my gong right now... or you are a dead drunk...~ []
@1028575 = ~(gulp!) ... I, I see...~ []
@1028582 = ~Listen... I know that you're not really involved in this. But I do want my mother's gong back. If you get it for me, I'll not only consider Vittorio's debt even, I'll make it worth your while.~ []
@1028583 = ~I've a few items of potent magic that are worth plenty if you were to sell them... I'd be willing to part with one for the gong returned. What say you?~ []
@1028589 = ~Well, Vittorio... I guess it's just you and me, now. I guess since you don't have the gong... the price is coming out of your hide!~ []
@1028590 = ~... p-please, me <LADYLORD>! I beg of you! Have mercy!~ []
@1028591 = ~Alright. Fine. I'll see if I can locate this gong... if I have the time.~ []
@1028593 = ~... NO! PLEAAASSE!!~ []
@1028594 = ~I... er... I thank ye, me <LADYLORD>! I be most grateful! Er... I think I should be going, now...~ []
@1028596 = ~A fine good business to ye, me <LADYLORD>. I just wanted to thank ye fer handlin' that Dennis fella in th' pub... a fine bit o' justice, that were.~ []
@1028597 = ~... er, I do so hope ye finds the gong soon, me <LADYLORD>...~ []
@1028601 = ~Well, Vittorio... I suppose that means your time has ran out, hasn't it?~ []
@1028604 = ~I have no intention of continuing the search... but nor will I allow you to touch this man, Dennis!~ []
@1028606 = ~I sold it to a fence by the name of Roger not too long ago, I do think. He... lives in the sewers below th' city, although I knows not exactly where. He... he should still have it...~ []
@1028607 = ~... My thanks, me <LADYLORD>... yer a kind one...~ []
@1028609 = ~So... you haven't found it, yet. Does this mean that you no longer intend to look?~ []
@1028612 = ~That's correct... but nor will I allow you to touch this man, Dennis! You'll release him at once!~ []
@1028615 = ~You have the gong? Excellent. Mother will be very pleased. As I promised, here is your reward... it should fetch an excellent price, unless you find another use for it.~ []
@1028616 = ~And you, Vittorio... you can go. But I warn you to stay out of my way... I don't even want to hear your name, you foul drunkard!~ []
@1028617 = ~... There is... there is just th' wee little matter of me bartab...?~ []
@1028618 = ~Grrr. You've got gall. But... I suppose I've got my gong. I'll pay half of your tab, fool. Now get out.~ []
@1028619 = ~Y-yes, yes, of course. And thank ye, me <LADYLORD>... I am most appreciative! You are so kind!~ []
@1028620 = ~Ye has the gong! Oh, thank ye, thank ye truly! Er... Dennis... the good <LADYLORD> has the gong...?~ []
@1028621 = ~Wh... what? That gong you have! That is my mother's gong! How did you get that?! Give it to me immediately!!~ []
@1028622 = ~It's yours? Very well, I have little enough use for it... here you go.~ []
@1028626 = ~My thanks! I have been looking for this ever since that drunken lout stole it! Here... take this magic item as a reward... it will fetch you a fair price if you wish to sell it.~ []
@1028629 = ~Hmmm... I suppose I could do that. Here... I have 500 gold pieces. That's a fair price for the gong... I'll not offer a copper more.~ []
@1028630 = ~Then I'll take it from your dead body! Men... attack!!~ []
@1028633 = ~Priestess of Ilmater~ []
@1028645 = ~Oh, you must be the messengers come to beg the service of Sir Sarles. It's a great honor to be refused by him, so don't feel bad when you leave empty-handed.~ []
@1028647 = ~Riatavin, to the far south, is rebelling against the Council... we be mercenaries hired to fight against Lady Aura and her kin.~ []
@1028658 = ~I am the mage of this mercenary troupe... I get paid well, and I'll thank you to leave me be.~ []
@1028659 = ~It matters not that Riatavin has petitioned to join Tethyr... their rebellion will not succeed. We shall crush them.~ []
@1028660 = ~The Cowled Wizards do not prevent mages from operating with the army... or with mercenaries. Especially mages of my skill.~ []
@1028666 = ~Helm has sent me forth. His everseeing eyes wish to gaze upon your work.~ []
@1028669 = ~Our fight against the town of Riatavin has been blessed by the gods... we shall surely prevail.~ []
@1028671 = ~I am the priest and healer of this mercenary group. I am their spirit and arm of faith... and I can battle as well as any of the men.~ []
@1028673 = ~Hmmn. I don't remember seeing you down here before. New customers, perhaps? Me name be Roger. Is there something that you... need?~ []
@1028675 = ~Yes, you will be gaining the favor of a powerful faith.~ []
@1028682 = ~Oh... odds and ends, mostly. I buy things from people who acquire things, and I don't ask where they acquire them from. And then I sell them to others. A redistribution of goods.~ []
@1028692 = ~No, what I need has not changed, and I have said so to your masters. The gold offered is sufficient, and I am just fine without the flattery.~ []
@1028702 = ~You are told? Have you not checked? Gathering the materials is not the job of a fine artist such as myself. Go speak with an ore merchant or somesuch.~ []
@1028705 = ~I recall the name of one that was referred to me on my last visit. Jerlia was her name, I believe. Speak with her. She has exotics occasionally. Try the Promenade.~ []
@1028707 = ~Alright, then. Remember... you haven't seen me, aye?~ []
@1028709 = ~What are you? Some kind of crime-fighter that scours the sewers? I be mindin' me own business, and that's all it is... business. If ye has a problem with it, then be on yer way.~ []
@1028714 = ~I'll be leaving, then... I've no interest in doing business with you.~ []
@1028715 = ~You have heard my conditions of service. Provide what I wish or I will not work for you. Check the Promenade if you seek an ore merchant.~ []
@1028716 = ~Well, I did not expect to see you back here so soon. Perhaps next time I should request to work only in blood-forged meteoric adamantite.~ []
@1028720 = ~I suppose I could part with a few coins for the deed. I tell you what... dispose of the sea troll beastie for me an' I'll be pleased to pay you 500 gold pieces, aye?~ []
@1028723 = ~I thank you on behalf of the followers of Talos.~ []
@1028730 = ~Our business is concluded. The piece will be delivered when it is done. I will dispatch a messenger to collect my fee and tell your church of my decision.~ [SARLES07]
@1028733 = ~How about rewarding me with something... say, a gong?~ []
@1028736 = ~Ahhh, I see. Well, I'll tell you what... do a little favor for me and I'll tell you who I sold that particular gong to, as well as where you can find 'em, aye?~ []
@1028744 = ~I sold it, through an envoy, to a troll shaman. Errr... Grae, I believe her name to be. Lives in a troll mound near Trademeet, ye can't miss it.~ []
@1028747 = ~I can't imagine she's the type to receive visitors... an' I believe the mound to be guarded by trolls a'plenty. But if ye want it, that's where it'd be.~ []
@1028753 = ~Heh heh. Looking for a reward, are we? Well, I can't say that it isn't deserved. Here... I have a few spare coins. 250 of them, all told. Thank ye kindly for the deed.~ []
@1028756 = ~Get rid o' the beastie that has been plaguing me about here... the sea troll t' be specific... an' I'll be pleased to tell you all I know. Aye?~ []
@1028766 = ~Ach, calm down, mate. You don't frighten me... I've dealt with harsher types then you. And besides... harming me won't find you out where the gong lies, now, will it?~ []
@1028773 = ~Actually, it's not that important to me... I'd much rather just kill you!~ []
@1028783 = ~(gulp)  er... how about I just start RUNNING FOR MY LIFE!!~ []
@1028788 = ~Well hello to you again, mate. I still notice that the beastie is runnin' around, yet... are you not plannin' on finishing our deal?~ []
@1028789 = ~No, no... I'll go back and finish the job.~ []
@1028791 = ~That's right... I've no interest in continuing this task.~ []
@1028795 = ~An excellent job, mate! Finally, my stores will be plenty safe from that troll's bug-eyed intrusions. Now, then... what was it, again, that you were lookin' for as a reward?~ []
@1028796 = ~He's in disguise. His kind doesn't look all that different, and as long as he's left alone, he's fine. Not a bad guy, once you get to know him.~ []
@1028800 = ~Err... 1,000 gold pieces.~ []
@1028807 = ~Did I promise that? Well, mate, here you go... an' a thanks to you for a deed well done. Anything ye need in the future, don't be hesitating to look me up.~ []
@1028811 = ~Heh... you must be thinkin' me mighty stupid, mate. If I remember right, I offered you 500 gold pieces. An' here it is... no need to be greedy, aye?~ []
@1028816 = ~Ahhh... always good to speak to you, mate. What is it, exactly, that you need?~ []
@1028828 = ~Ye be lookin' a mite out o' place, <GIRLBOY>. What brings ye above yer station? Found a gold mine?~ []
@1028832 = ~We seek a valuable gong that was sold to you by a fence in Amn... tell us where it is!~ []
@1028835 = ~Bonny good luck, then!~ []
@1028842 = ~Now the bastards fawn over me but horribly, all the while eyeing me purse.~ []
@1028843 = ~(hissss)  Wait! (gasp!)  I... I will tell you where the gong is! Mercy, humans!~ []
@1028848 = ~(hissss)  The gong... I sold it to Drush... an ogre mage. In the tower to the northeast, beside the house of the witch. He is gone but said he would return today.~ []
@1028857 = ~If this could ruin you, I should offer no less than 1,000 gold.~ []
@1028861 = ~(hissss)  You are... honorable? I... I must flee!~ []
@1028868 = ~Yes, we come in peace... why are you not attacking us?~ []
@1028874 = ~That depends... what are your intentions?~ []
@1028876 = ~Actually... I'm looking for a particular gong. Grae the troll shaman supposedly sold it to you.~ []
@1028879 = ~No reason... I'll be on my way.~ []
@1028881 = ~Blasted, vile, ignorant humanoids! Very well, then... feel my wrath!!~ []
@1028883 = ~As you wish, humanoids. You are welcome here at any time, so long as your intentions are peaceful... perhaps I will see you once again.~ []
@1028884 = ~I see. My kin have been here since the time of Umar... ever since then, the humans have come farther and farther out into these lands. Perhaps I should move on, soon. It is something to consider.~ []
@1028885 = ~Feel free to make yourselves at home... although I know that humanoids do not often find ogre tastes appealing. I would ask that you not steal anything, but beyond that you are welcome.~ []
@1028887 = ~I am sorry, but I cannot give this information out without compensation.~ []
@1028888 = ~A gong? Oh... that. Well, yes, I do have that... I saw it the last time I made a visit to the troll mound and thought it was of an adequate size to shovel cow dung. What do you need with it?~ []
@1028889 = ~It sounds like the end of me for a mere pittance. No, that is not enough.~ []
@1028891 = ~Do not concern yourself with our reasons... the fact is that we wish to have the gong.~ []
@1028894 = ~Very well, I will offer 1,000 gold to compensate you.~ []
@1028896 = ~Forget it! Give me the gong, now... or else!~ []
@1028899 = ~I happen to have one, here... let's trade.~ []
@1028901 = ~Hmmn... yes, this will do just fine. Here is the gong. Thank you. Um... sorry for the smell on the gong... can't be helped. Ol' Bessie here has a... problem...~ []
@1028903 = ~Hmph. I don't know... where do you humanoids normally get such things? Do they not sell them in your cities? I am not an expert at your ways.~ []
@1028907 = ~It is your custom, humanoids, to perform trade... is it not? I use this gong, even if it is not for something important. I expect something in return if I am going to give it up.~ []
@1028915 = ~Yes, I have. Here... let's trade.~ []
@1028917 = ~No... but you're going to give me that gong... right NOW.~ []
@1028918 = ~No... but I'm going to keep looking.~ []
@1028920 = ~Greetings, humanoid. Make yourself welcome, as I have said earlier. Please excuse me, however... I am quite busy at the moment.~ []
@1028923 = ~I don't understand... why aren't you attacking me?~ []
@1028924 = ~No... I'll be on my way.~ []
@1028925 = ~Greetings to you, my <BROTHERSISTER>, and welcome to a refuge for the suffering and those in need. Ilmater offers shelter and healing to all who desire it... what is it that I can do for you?~ []
@1028929 = ~Of course, my <BROTHERSISTER>... please come with me.~ []
@1028931 = ~As you can see, there is much call for the Crying God's compassion here in Athkatla. We would ask that you give, if you can afford... if not, it is no matter.~ []
@1028942 = ~Have you seen the theater at the Five Flagons? I hear the troupe, there, puts on quite an excellent show.~ []
@1028946 = ~I hear there's been several kidnappings within the last few months... and none of them ever turned up, even though the ransom was paid!~ []
@1028947 = ~The weather's been quite foul over the last few weeks... storms, hail and fog a'plenty. It's a wonder we get any sea traffic at all.~ []
@1028954 = ~It is called the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart, fool. And we do more to battle evil than you could comprehend. Look to your own actions, first, before you look to others'.~ []
@1028955 = ~My goodness... so many men in uniforms, here, I hardly know where to start!~ []
@1028971 = ~Mmmm... you, there... you're a Thayvian, aren't you? I've heard some very good things about the men from Thay...~ []
@1028982 = ~Heh. There do be certain advantages to possessing a smaller stature... foremost among them be easier access to the honeypot pleasures of the female. Heh heh.~ []
@1028988 = ~(mumble) ... Mmm... where be the l'il serving wench?...~ []
@1028990 = ~(mumble) ... Eh? Who be you? You nar be me wife, are ye?... (shudder) ... I nay'er want t' see that battleaxe tonight, aye?...~ []
@1028992 = ~(mumble) ... Have a seat if ye likes...~ []
@1028993 = ~(mumble) ... Buy me an ale, aye?...~ []
@1028997 = ~Ew... a commoner peasant! Out, out at once!!~ []
@1028999 = ~Excuse me, my <LADYLORD>... but this IS our room you are intruding into? I would request that you leave.~ []
@1029000 = ~Oh, it's not so bad now, is it? You've got a close approximation of what you need, and I have fair compensation for the demand on the item.~ []
@1029001 = ~Hmm... you wouldn't be the room service, would you?~ []
@1029004 = ~The price for that knowledge is 1,000 gold. Do you wish to pay that instead?~ []
@1029015 = ~Tsk, tsk. Not even a challenge anymore. The big folk are getting more than a little inbred.~ []
@1029019 = ~Perhaps I should just ask about your source. That was 1,000 gold, wasn't it?~ []
@1029022 = ~Why, hello there... so nice to see someone of decent culture in this little horrid inn. Too bad we have no servants with us to host you properly.~ []
@1029025 = ~Ah... if you are one of the servants, I would like a cup of elven wine, please. And perhaps a bit of pheasant, too... I'm feeling peckish.~ []
@1029030 = ~I have no home but th' mud in th' streets... except that I am allowed t' stay in the temple, sometimes.~ []
@1029032 = ~Please, me <LADYLORD>... could ye spare a bit o' coin for a sinner in need? Please... but a single coin would do!~ []
@1029037 = ~I... understand, my <LADYLORD>. Go in peace wi' ye.~ []
@1029045 = ~Then your unkindness was thoughtless and undeserved. Please... go.~ []
@1029051 = ~I have seen the Crying God heal many... and demand nothing in return. He is a glorious and benevolent god, indeed.~ []
@1029052 = ~Ilmater helps those in need... all of us in the slums could use his aid, I think.~ []
@1029054 = ~Praise Oghma, the beneficent master of knowledge, invention and inspiration. Come, seeker, and be welcome within his temple. What can I provide for you?~ []
@1029064 = ~Oghma teaches that knowledge must be collected and disseminated, and wisdom applied to its use. The Wise God teaches that ideas must never be stifled.~ []
@1029073 = ~This is not illithium! You have cheated my art! Illithium holds no oil or grime! A handprint on illithium is an impossibility!~ [SARLES08]
@1029075 = ~We seek to spread knowledge and to curb falsehood and rumor... especially with regards to history.~ []
@1029079 = ~The things that are studied in the Oghmanyte orders are far beyond most people's comprehension. We shall teach them... in time.~ []
@1029085 = ~Of course, my <BROTHERSISTER>... please come with me.~ []
@1029094 = ~The most important element of illithium is that it will bear no dirt or grime! Cast as illithium, my work need never show the taint of another mortal's hands!~ []
@1029097 = ~Then it should have been nothing! I have made my wishes clear, and you have made a mockery of them!~ []
@1029099 = ~I can hardly ever sleep well... I have bad dreams in the night. But sometimes Ilmater comes to me and comforts me and I sleep real good.~ []
@1029100 = ~I was assured it had the same attributes as your metal.~ []
@1029102 = ~Gosh, <SIRMAAM>... could you... afford a little gold piece? I am so hungry and it's hours until we eat...~ []
@1029109 = ~... I... yes, <SIRMAAM>... I'm s-sorry...~ []
@1029110 = ~My mommy died giving me birth, and my daddy died in the war. They left me all alone... an' I was sent here.~ []
@1029119 = ~... I... I'm sorry... I just want my mommy...~ []
@1029133 = ~I don't see why. This new piece is a welcome understatement. Looks as though it represents the shadows receding from the dawn. Fine work.~ []
@1029191 = ~Nowhere. This place is unfriendly to even the pathetic dwarves of hill and mountain. Alright, fool, you wish to share my problem, I'll give it to you.~ []
@1029192 = ~Nothing. Very few opportunities for mercantile trade in this place when you are even a hill or mountain dwarf. Alright, fool, you wish to share my problem, I'll give it to you.~ []
@1029193 = ~You want illithium, you can wait for it. We mine it deep in the earth, and it's dangerous going. It's rare enough when production is normal.~ []
@1029198 = ~You want to go chasing after him, that's your business. It's lost to me anyway. I show my face and he'll have the guards on me just for being duergar.~ []
@1029199 = ~ Ah Hah!~ [MAZZY36]
@1029202 = ~ Ach... missed!~ [MAZZY37]
@1029208 = ~Spider Spawn (Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 4
Range: 40 yards 
Duration: 6 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

Upon casting this spell, the wizard conjures one or two fully grown spiders to do his or her bidding. The type of spiders that appear depend upon the level of the wizard casting the spell.

7th: giant spider
9th: phase spider
12th and up: sword spider

When the spell is cast there is a 20% chance that two spiders of the proper type will appear instead of just one. These spider(s) will remain under the wizard's control until slain, or until the spell duration expires.~ []
@1029214 = ~Summon Nishruu (Conjuration/Summoning) 
Level: 6
Range: 40 yards 
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

With this spell, the wizard may summon a Nishruu, a magical being of considerable power. At first glance, a Nishruu appears to be some sort of mist; closer examination will reveal a boiling, churning red mass of vapors and shapes that moves with a life of its own. Drawn towards magic like a moth to flame, the Nishruu feeds on the energies surrounding and used by wizards. Luckily, there is no question as to the loyalty of the creature, and it will not attack its summoner, even though it would like nothing better. Each time a Nishruu wraps its tendrils around a target, there are two major effects. First, all charged magical items possessed by the target will be drained by one charge, destroying them if only one charge remains. Second, the affected wizard will lose one memorized spell, chosen at random from the highest possible spell level. Excluding Death Spell and Death Fog, the Nishruu is completely immune to magic; further, magic will actually heal this creature. The Nishruu will remain under the wizard's control until killed, or until the spell duration expires.~ []
@1029220 = ~Summon Hakeashar (Conjuration/Summoning)
Level: 7
Range: 40 yards 
Duration: 8 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

This spell is similar to the 6th level wizard spell Summon Nishruu. The Hakeashar is a more powerful version of the Nishruu, having more hit points, better attacks, and immunity to normal weapons. With this spell, the wizard may summon a Hakeashar, a magical being of considerable power. At first glance, a Hakeashar appears to be some sort of mist; closer examination will reveal a boiling, churning red mass of vapors and shapes that moves with a life of its own. Drawn towards magic like a moth to flame, the Hakeashar feeds on the energies surrounding and used by wizards. Luckily, there is no question as to the loyalty of the creature, and it will not attack its summoner, even though it would like nothing better. Each time a Hakeashar wraps its tendrils around a target, there are two major effects. First, all charged magical items possessed by the target will be drained by one charge, destroying them if only one charge remains. Second, the affected wizard will lose one memorized spell, chosen at random from the highest possible spell level. Excluding Death Spell and Death Fog, the Hakeashar is completely immune to magic; further, magic will actually heal this creature. The Hakeashar will remain under the wizard's control until killed, or until the spell duration expires.~ []
@1029243 = ~Young fools want a god to walk with them, but that is not the way. It demeans a god to walk with the flock, just as if I supped with insects.~ []
@1029270 = ~It is a beholder cult! The 'worshippers' are probably magically enslaved.~ []
@1029275 = ~May The Destroyer guide your hand in the battle to come.~ []
@1029279 = ~Serving Talos and living through the experience was reward enough.~ []
@1029292 = ~Insanity! You... you tempt the fates like a mad<MANWOMAN>! Perhaps you will serve with your mindlessness, but you will never be of the chosen.~ []
@1029293 = ~Talos would have welcomed you to the ranks of his chosen, but you have turned away. Madness.~ []
@1029305 = ~But nothing is ever easy. Aside from his enormous commission fee, he claims he will work in nothing short of pure illithium - a metal more valued than gold!!~ []
@1029321 = ~You will have to secure enough illithium to keep him happy, and convince him to accept an affordable commission. Discuss this with Sarles, he may be reasonable.~ []
@1029322 = ~The Unsleeping Eyes of Helm have much to keep them busy now! We have received word that Sarles will work for us! I cannot thank you enough.~ []
@1029324 = ~But mere gold is not worthy of your service. You are of the chosen of Helm. You deserve greater tools with which to spread the word of Helm.~ []
@1029356 = ~There is more to be done. An artist visits Athkatla now. Only Prism of Nashkel was more accomplished, but his work was sickly sweet and his death deserved.~ []
@1029361 = ~Convince him to work for Talos. Use whatever means you must. Other churches are trying the same... if you cross their representatives, kill them.~ []
@1029370 = ~You are as much use as Talos sees fit! Do you refuse this task?~ []
@1029374 = ~Find his damnable illithium and make him accept a reasonable commission. He may rethink his demands if you press our point in discussion with him.~ []
@1029392 = ~What is the disturbance, Talon? Talos alone reserves fury in his own temple. Ahh, is this to be the new tribute you have commissioned?~ []
@1029399 = ~Well, he'll kill us both if I tell him now. You are very lucky, though perhaps Talos did guide you through this mire.~ []
@1029407 = ~Aye, burn the elf! Her dark and fiendish kin rose up from their underground homes and killed my father and brother! They are all evil, I tell you! All of them!~ [VICG201]
@1029419 = ~As ye will. (Can't read, eh? 'Tis a fine pickle the Amnish school system's get itself into.)~ []
@1029425 = ~What are you doing?! Why have ye interfered with the judgement of Beshaba?! Her will must be shown to the people!~ [VICG107]
@1029431 = ~And lo, the judgment of Beshaba has been called upon this most evil of drow, and she has been found wanting! May the people see their salvation from your evil in the Maid of Misrule! Pray that she is merciful, foul one!~ [VICG106]
@1029433 = ~Huzzah! Huzzah!!~ [VICTO302]
@1029436 = ~I owe you my life, abbil... you have saved me once again. I did nothing to provoke their attack, I tell you! I was passing through the city when the man guessed my identity under my hood.~ [VICONIB3]
@1029437 = ~I was surprised and he called out to others, revealing me. I suppose they assumed I was here to spy on them... fools! They are so quick to fear, these rivvin!~ []
@1029438 = ~But, come... we must be on our way soon if we are to avoid drawing another crowd. I distrust these barbaric people too much to hang about.~ []
@1029446 = ~I have a duty for you to perform. It has been requested of us that we assist the temple of Lathander in their dispute with the worshippers of Talos.~ [TELWYN07]
@1029452 = ~I found the stinking drow in the market, hiding under her cloak and hood, sneaking amongst us surely for an evil purpose! She'll pay, all right... just like all of her kind will one day pay!~ []
@1029454 = ~I do as Talos wills!~ []
@1029458 = ~This drow is just like all the rest, I reckon... if we don't burn her now, she'll murder any one of us soon enough!~ []
@1029459 = ~She was up to no good, she was! Sneakin' around the markets, hidin' from us in her cloaks! A spy... or an assassin! Burn, I says!!~ []
@1029460 = ~This is only right and fair... all the drow elves are evil to the core and this one is surely no exception! This will show them that we can't be pushed around!~ []
@1029463 = ~Oh my... I wonder if this drow means we are to be invaded by an army of them, soon! Black elves bursting from the ground! Oooohh...~ []
@1029466 = ~The High Mornmaster of the Lathander has sent word you are to be congratulated. You have done well by helping the balance of power here.~ []
@1029467 = ~Very well... I think I'll enjoy this.~ []
@1029470 = ~We found her in the market... attempting to hide her identity! No doubt a spy... we have taken the law into our own hands and it is good!~ []
@1029471 = ~Stand aside and watch... or join us, if you wish, my <LADYLORD>! Either way, justice will be done!~ []
@1029478 = ~We know the culprits, they have not concealed their crime. Talassans, slinking from their temple to degrade our worship, hired common thieves for the deed!~ []
@1029480 = ~<CHARNAME>... you... you abandon me?! I have done nothing to warrant this! Og'elend! Traitor! Iblith! Oloth plynn dos!!~ []
@1029491 = ~Do you demand more of your lord? Will you not march into danger for your faith?~ []
@1029498 = ~We shall see.~ []
@1029503 = ~I was merely concerned about the proper tribute to Helm for this task.~ []
@1029508 = ~So much to do, so much to do... and so very little time. It's never anything around here but run run run!~ []
@1029510 = ~Mmm... I haven't been to one of the spa tubs in ages. It's the only luxury we, here, in the city really have.~ []
@1029513 = ~There was the oddest little gnome around here selling things like weapons and the like. ... I could have sworn I remember seeing him selling turnips last month.~ []
@1029516 = ~Ah... you wouldn't be here to sweep the street, would you, sir?~ []
@1029517 = ~I am dressed as I am... and somewhat dirty... because of the time I have spent in the woodlands, sir. I am NOT a street-sweeper.~ []
@1029519 = ~Umm... weren't you dragged in here, earlier? I could have sworn they were going to burn you.~ []
@1029520 = ~Yes, that was I, rivvil... no thanks to your strange breed of law enforcement that you have in this city.~ []
@1029524 = ~Don't ye go near the docks... I warn ye, it's dangerous and nearly unguarded. Fie on the guard, fie!~ []
@1029525 = ~Why, Lord Keldorn... pleased to meet you, sir. I just came from droppin' off Leona at yer estate, I did.~ []
@1029527 = ~Well, if it isn't Jan Jansen. You incorrigible old gnome, you! Married a lass yet, hmm?~ []
@1029528 = ~I am not that old, madam. And I assure you... should I decide upon a bride, you will be the first to know.~ []
@1029530 = ~I am looking for some workers to add onto my manse... might you be interested?~ []
@1029531 = ~I understand that the Jysstevs are hosting a famous artist... I do hope he will put on a display for us!~ []
@1029535 = ~Let me see... you are the de'Arnise girl, aren't you? Why aren't you decently married yet?~ []
@1029537 = ~If you weren't aware otherwise, this is certainly the part of town to see and be seen in. Hm... but, then, you're a commoner.~ []
@1029538 = ~(yawn)  Oh, I apologize... were you actually speaking to me?~ []
@1029546 = ~The Morninglord does not require your talents at this time. He will call if need be.~ [SAINXX08]
@1029548 = ~I am telling you, my brother... the correct way to approach life is to accept its travails. One must bend as the willow and see the obstacles that the gods place in front of you as challenges to be overcome.~ [PHIX0101]
@1029549 = ~You continue to be a fine resource for the Morninglord. Your service has been exemplary, and you have earned your place within the temple order.~ []
@1029552 = ~Don't be moronic. You must struggle! Through struggle we grow stronger! Only the strong survive! And I am not your brother.~ [PKIX0201]
@1029553 = ~Strength comes through wisdom and pliancy... one must be flexible to accept the things that come. Struggle only brings futility, my son.~ []
@1029554 = ~Struggle and adversity bring strength, not futility! War and violence weed out the weak and unhealthy, strengthening all! And I am not your son.~ []
@1029561 = ~Well, now I suppose you were right, after all. Dead right. Hah ha! But I get the last word. Come, Huntley... let's go.~ []
@1029565 = ~Er... what the most magnificent Lord Pehllus means is that he is... far too busy... er... surveying the city to speak with you at the moment...~ []
@1029567 = ~Um... what the most gracious Lord Pehllus means to say is... er... that he is waiting to meet a most lovely woman by the name of Oriona, and you are obviously not she.~ []
@1029569 = ~Err... the Lord simply means to introduce himself, I am sure. Bow before Pehllus Tanislove, one of the most powerful nobles of Athkatla and priest to the goddess of joy, Lliira.~ []
@1029570 = ~Hmmmn... now, I am quite sure that I don't --~ []
@1029571 = ~Uh... the Lord Pehllus means to say that he is currently not aware of your name...~ []
@1029573 = ~Yes, of course, your Worshipfulness... my apologies, your Grace...~ []
@1029578 = ~Er... ah... here's a platinum piece, good man. Go play your instrument... somewhere...~ []
@1029580 = ~Perhaps people just need a swift kick in the punctuals!~ []
@1029582 = ~No, I seldom have time for reading. Too much work to be done!~ []
@1029584 = ~Then they are dead! Dead!~ []
@1029587 = ~Who? Me? I'm... I'm nobody. I'm just a toady.~ []
@1029594 = ~Um... I have nothing to do with raising the taxes, all right?~ []
@1029595 = ~A crowd actually hauled a drow in here earlier... I... I think they're going to burn her! Why won't anyone do something?!~ []
@1029601 = ~Hmmn... that's three trade bars... and fifty dantars... how much is that in gold...? Hmmn...~ []
@1029602 = ~Hmmm... have you paid your taxes? I wonder if you're on my list. I must have you somewhere...~ []
@1029603 = ~I only collect the home taxes... harbor taxes are collected at the docks. If you want to pay for your trade booth, do it at the main office.~ []
@1029605 = ~Wait one minute... you! You're Jan Jansen, aren't you? Four years behind on your home tax? Selling without a license?~ []
@1029609 = ~Young lady... why are you giving me such a queer look?~ []
@1029615 = ~We have hired a thief, and he has stolen a Dawn Ring from the Lathander temple. Find Travin in the Slums at night, collect the ring, and return it here.~ []
@1029616 = ~Now I could let you in on some delicious secrets of some of the most powerful men in Athkatla... but that would be telling, wouldn't it?~ []
@1029620 = ~When you've got it, you've got to use it to your advantage... you know what I mean, yes? My two mansions and three cottages tell me I'm right.~ []
@1029621 = ~Mmmm, darling, with lovely, dark skin like that... you could earn more than a living here, let me tell you.~ []
@1029625 = ~Why, Lord Keldorn! You've jumped into a river to avoid me, before, and here you are! Have you... changed your mind? (chuckle)~ []
@1029626 = ~Er... ah... my lady! I... I am a married man!~ []
@1029630 = ~That is quite enough of that! I... ah... I have urgent business elsewhere. Excuse me, my lady.~ []
@1029632 = ~I merely meant that I give great value to my service to Talos.~ []
@1029642 = ~~ []
@1029654 = ~I've just been enumerating the tax landholds in the colonies... and a ship just arrived from Maztica telling me that three villages have been burned to the ground by the natives! All that work, gone!~ []
@1029661 = ~Er... you look like one of those men from Rashemen... you're not here to ask for anything are you? Last time that happened, things got messy...~ []
@1029664 = ~I'm sorry, sir... we don't allow dwarves in these buildings.~ []
@1029666 = ~Hmmn... we seem to be all out of the vellum forms for tax concessions. I guess the city goes without them this year... oh, well.~ []
@1029671 = ~I've got a form for claiming land in Maztica around here somewhere... you have full rights to kill the natives, too...~ []
@1029684 = ~The Dahaunarch is in the city... but I am afraid he is out on Council business right now and isn't expected back soon.~ []
@1029685 = ~The Namarch is in Athkatla... but he is entertaining a dignified guest at his home and isn't conducting business.~ []
@1029686 = ~The Meisarch... the highest of the Council... is currently at Riatavin dealing with the rebellion, according to my knowledge.~ []
@1029687 = ~The Council of Six rules all of Amn, yes, but also the city of Athkatla... but they aren't currently sitting. The bureaucracy is overseeing things here at the moment.~ []
@1029688 = ~... Oh, ah, Lord Corthala... I'm afraid that the Council simply isn't willing to hear from you again regarding --~ []
@1029690 = ~... Mm, ah, yes... the daughter of Lord de'Arnise. The Council is taking the matter of your father under advisement. We can let you know in, say, three to four weeks?~ []
@1029694 = ~We will deal with the Sythillisian forces and the rebels down near Riatavin, not to worry. Nothing will ever threaten the City of Coin, itself.~ []
@1029696 = ~Don't get out of line, citizen... especially here.~ []
@1029698 = ~All I want to do is find out why my little farm was taxed as a castle! It's outrageous! They have it listed as a castle, and that's it for them... they refuse to believe otherwise!~ []
@1029700 = ~I even had a herald come and actually see my farm. He decided it would be too much work to change the mistake that has my farm listed as a castle... so he said that he saw a castle there and left!~ []
@1029702 = ~My family is one of the wealthiest in Athkatla... we have interests in the gold mines up north and the shipwrights here in the city. So I will thank you not to stand too close..~ []
@1029703 = ~I don't suppose you're from one of the mercantile companies, are you? No... I didn't think so.~ []
@1029709 = ~Hmm... hmmn. Yes, you'll do. You... the pretty elf, there. I need a new mistress, and I think you'll do nicely.~ []
@1029710 = ~Not... not in a million years, you foul beast! <CHARNAME>... let's get away from him, please...~ []
@1029713 = ~Hmph. You there... any reason in particular that you're here?~ []
@1029716 = ~Retrieve the document in any manner that you wish. I would suggest using guile (but such subtle means are beyond these monkeys, I am sure.)~ []
@1029717 = ~~ []
@1029724 = ~This cloak is a powerful, evil thing. Made from the poorly stitched together skin of innocent nymphs, it grants the wearer immunity to fear and panic.

STATISTICS

Equipped Abilities: Immunity to fear and panic
Not Usable By:
 Wizard Slayer~ []
@1029725 = ~A mind-controlled creature cannot speak to you of his own free will.~ []
@1029727 = ~ I could not focus properly. My casting has failed.~ [MAZZY42]
@1029730 = ~ I am pleased that you came across me when you did... this group does good things.~ [VALYGA03]
@1029735 = ~There isn't anything interesting for you to see here, <GIRLBOY>... an' I don't let strangers crawl around my prison without reason. Off you go.~ []
@1029737 = ~ I left the forest to work with fools... I must be mad.~ [VALYGA04]
@1029740 = ~I'll just pretend I didn't hear that. Now leave, before I forget that rending you limb from limb might make you feel... unwelcome.~ []
@1029741 = ~Go on and talk to yer friend, if you wish. He's not goin' anywhere, that's for sure.~ []
@1029750 = ~This is a very secure prison, my friend... I wouldn't try anything, if I were you.~ []
@1029753 = ~I'm keeping an eye on you... no funny business.~ []
@1029754 = ~I'm sorry, but the prison is closed during the evening... no outside admittance is allowed. If you wish to visit a prisoner, return in the morn.~ []
@1029783 = ~ So be it... but involve me with any filthy magic and I swear there will be a hell to pay.~ [VALYGA35]
@1029788 = ~I could not afford my taxes... so I am thrown into this abysmal pit. Oh, how the gods have cursed me!~ []
@1029789 = ~Oh, my <LADYLORD>... please get me out of this terrible place!~ []
@1029791 = ~They... they're going to ship us off to Maztica to be laborers! You can't let that happen to us!!~ []
@1029792 = ~I... I've been framed! Yes, framed!~ []
@1029803 = ~The bridge will rise for those who belong. Speak of the bridge to show you belong. Show you belong or suffer the end.~ []
@1029811 = ~ This will ensnare any that tread near by.~ [VALYGA43]
@1029817 = ~Ruin may end in death, but not always, and not with certainty.~ []
@1029841 = ~Calm down, Cohrvale. Mr. F. don't like ye killing people in the streets.~ [BREGG01]
@1029879 = ~I am truly sorry, <SIRMAAM>... no admittance without a ticket. You will need to speak to the receptionist to purchase one.~ []
@1029881 = ~Most gracious of ye, <SIRMAAM>. Ye may enter the theater, as ye wish... just show your ticket to yon ushers, please.~ []
@1029882 = ~It is a most dramatic play put on by the fine members of the Sigil troupe. 'Tis better to see than to be described... would ye like the ticket, then, mayhap?~ []
@1029883 = ~Certainly... here is your 5 gold.~ []
@1029892 = ~Alright... here is your 5 gold pieces.~ []
@1029895 = ~Thank you, <SIRMAAM>... go on inside. Hope you enjoy the play.~ []
@1029897 = ~Thank you, <SIRMAAM>... go on inside.~ []
@1029898 = ~No, Kirinaldo, I cannot! Oh, Rodrigo... Rodrigo! My fair love, where hast thou gone?!~ [FFACT201]
@1029899 = ~Your lover has abandoned thee, sweet Lunisia. You have only one option left... turnest thou to me and let us be wed at last!~ [FFACT101]
@1029901 = ~Uh... here I am! Here I am, my... uh... sweetums...~ [FFBIFF01]
@1029902 = ~Say... that's not the actor they had last time!~ [FFCR0101]
@1029903 = ~Ah... yes, Rodrigo! Rodrigo, it is thee at long last! But where have --~ [FFACT202]
@1029904 = ~I've been... uh... across the sea, my fair... um... my fair one. Y-yes, that's it. Across the sea and, uh...~ [FFBIFF02]
@1029905 = ~(ahem)... And perhaps on the new lands, my lord?~ [FFACT203]
@1029906 = ~Yes, that's it! On the new lands. Yes... um...~ [FFBIFF03]
@1029908 = ~Ugh! Where's the actor that was here last time?! Pfaugh!!~ [FFCR0201]
@1029909 = ~(AHEM!)  But... is it Rodrigo? No! No!! How can this be?!~ [FFACT102]
@1029910 = ~Well you should be so... um... confused? (It is confused, right?)~ [FFBIFF04]
@1029912 = ~Baffled! Yes, well... you should look so baffled, my lord... um... Kirinaldo! 'Twas you who... who... who...~ [FFBIFF05]
@1029913 = ~Oh, terrible! Get him off the stage!!~ [FFCRO401]
@1029914 = ~... who... um... which that... uh... in a way...~ [FFBIFF06]
@1029917 = ~(sigh)  Yes, you are correct, Rodrigo. 'Twas I that arranged for thy trip across the great ocean! 'Twas... er... um... truly fiendish of me! But how did thy ever come to return so quickly?~ [FFACT103]
@1029918 = ~Uh... I forget... I'm just the understudy...~ [FFBIFF08]
@1029922 = ~Boo!! BOO!! That's awful! Terrible!~ [FFCR0102]
@1029923 = ~... Ooh... uh.. oh dear...~ [FFBIFF09]
@1029924 = ~I... I am sorry, good folk of the audience. As you can see, things are not quite right with our troupe due to circumstances beyond our control.~ [RAELIS07]
@1029925 = ~I beg of you, good people, come back another day when we have restored matters... we shall prove to you then that the Sigil Troupe is worthy of your attention and coin, and we shall do so for free, of course.~ [RAELIS08]
@1029926 = ~And, one final... odd... request, good folk. If you, or another... knows of those who are skilled in the arts of sword and adventure... do send them to speak to me. It is a matter of utmost urgency.~ [RAELIS09]
@1029930 = ~If you have business with us, my <LADYLORD>, I suggest you speak to Raelis. She is the leader of our troupe and our mentor... and she can tell you of our difficulty.~ []
@1029931 = ~You are most gracious, my <LADYLORD>, to offer your assistance. We thank you, truly... and I am sure Haer'Dalis will appreciate your help, as well!~ []
@1029940 = ~The current step may be your first and may also become your last. The other two are abstract; this one is yours to choose and shape, though duty may force the choosing.~ []
@1029945 = ~Hello.~ []
@1029950 = ~I'm sure it would make you feel important, but I've simply no interest in you. I think you'll find we care about very little at all.~ []
@1029951 = ~Oooh, yes, very threatening. I suppose you are expecting the appropriate response. All right then. Oh my, please spare us. Your descent into our city makes us oh so fearful.~ []
@1029956 = ~Ah, you wish the exposition. Typical. I should really write this down so I don't have to keep repeating it. Not that we have had a lot of visitors.~ []
@1029957 = ~We are the guardians. We guard the temple. This is very important because every few hundred years someone almost wanders this way.~ []
@1029958 = ~Ah, hello... I am afraid if you are looking for a refund for tonight's performance, I can only tell you to come back when our troupe is not in such disarray.~ [RAELIS02]
@1029961 = ~This invisible ring cannot be removed from its owner.~ []
@1029965 = ~Who are you people? I don't quite... recognize what race you belong to, if you'll pardon my asking.~ []
@1029969 = ~Who are you people? I don't quite... recognize what race you belong to, if you'll pardon my asking.~ []
@1029978 = ~I understand what you ask, child. We are people from distant lands and all of us are of mixed heritage. Please, my good <MANWOMAN>... will you aid us?~ []
@1029982 = ~His name is Mekrath, I believe... I know that his lair can be accessed through the city's sewers, though where exactly it lies is a mystery.~ []
@1029987 = ~I am... unsure of your particular customs, but it has never been this Sigil's fortune to be treated fairly by the many city authorities that we have come across.~ []
@1029988 = ~As well, though Haer'Dalis might be released, would the gem be returned? The wizard could say it is his... and we could offer no proof to the contrary.~ []
@1029989 = ~No... we must have our brother and his gem both safely returned, with no questions asked of us due to our strangeness. This is the best way.~ []
@1029992 = ~Very well... I shall do as you ask.~ []
@1029993 = ~Sorry... not interested.~ []
@1030001 = ~Fly, then... fetch our brother away from his captor however you might, and return to us soon. My prayers go with you, my good <MANWOMAN>.~ []
@1030010 = ~Forget it... I've decided not to continue this task.~ []
@1030011 = ~Excellent, child... the fortunes of our troupe fly with you.~ []
@1030021 = ~All the members of the Council are kept secret... that way, nobody knows who to bribe, you see.~ []
@1030025 = ~The rebellion in the south is caused by demi-humans, that's what I think. Never mind ogres and such... it's the elves and the like that are behind it all!~ []
@1030027 = ~Amn should send more ships and people to the New World... our colonies there should supercede all the others and bring great glory to our nation!~ []
@1030028 = ~Have you never wondered who is on the Council of Six? I think it's all wizards, that's what... the wizards rule us secretly!~ []
@1030029 = ~I sometimes think there is no Council of Six... and that the Cowled Wizards and the Shadow Thieves rule all of Amn in secret!~ []
@1030031 = ~Believe me, rivvil... if the drow were here to rule, you would be well aware of it by now.~ []
@1030033 = ~You Amnish are too closed-minded about the demi-human kin that live amongst you in peace... they are not so different from you as you seem to think.~ []
@1030038 = ~When I am finally in the army, I wonder if I will sail to Maztica and join the colonial forces there... what a wonder it would be!~ []
@1030039 = ~I wonder if the army would send me down south to fight that ogre fellow and his false 'Sythillisian Empire'? We would show those creatures what a real war is!~ []
@1030046 = ~Hmph. I have been in the army, friend... and it is much more dreary than you think. The victories, too, are few and far between... and hardly worth the price you are forced to pay.~ []
@1030057 = ~You there, elven lass... you have the bearing of one of the lovely courtesans I have seen in this wealthy district. Might I be correct in that observation?~ []
@1030058 = ~The deal which placed us here has been followed to the letter, and we are never to be released from service no matter how pointless the task.~ []
@1030061 = ~You will fail. You cannot help but fail. We know this. We expect nothing other.~ []
@1030063 = ~Hmm... I have seen you entertaining somewhere, have I not? Might you be for hire, sir? I have a rather important function that I am hosting a week from now.~ []
@1030070 = ~Business has been poor this year... I may have to go without that lovely lacquered new carriage I had my eye on. (sigh)~ []
@1030071 = ~Well... will you look at that? A little halfling all dolled up in armor and such. Why, aren't you just the cutest thing?~ []
@1030074 = ~Wait one moment... I had my change-purse here but a scant moment ago? Where could it have gone? How shall I ever do my afternoon shopping?~ []
@1030075 = ~We cannot petition the unknown. We have not seen a sign for ages and his name is lost to us now. No, nothing is directed at the temple except loathing.~ []
@1030078 = ~(hurrrm... hurrrmmm)  Very well. You look like one who might... appreciate... such entertainments. There is more to my little place than meets the eye.~ []
@1030082 = ~Then you have all the mind you need. We have long accepted our fate. There is no end to the duty. Rail against whatever beast is there, but it will do you no good.~ []
@1030083 = ~I do not know and I do not care. You can do nothing here. There is no end to the duty. Rail against whatever beast is there, but it will do you no good.~ []
@1030087 = ~What manner of creature was in there? It actually wanted me to attack it.~ []
@1030088 = ~Was your god always as warlike as the beast in there?~ []
@1030098 = ~<CHARNAME> walks here, and I have disposed of your little guardian.~ []
@1030107 = ~You cannot have Boo, little girl! But you may pet him and make pretty cooing noises if you wish.~ []
@1030121 = ~Yes, certainly... here you go.~ []
@1030127 = ~Then it is little wonder I cannot defeat the beast. It is their loathing and pathos, and it has become their object of worship, whether they know it or not.~ []
@1030128 = ~Of course, my <PRO_LADYLORD>... we cannot all afford to help. I shall leave you alone, then.~ []
@1030129 = ~I... I apologize most profusely, my <PRO_LADYLORD>... I meant no offense! I am simply in dire straits. I... shall leave you be.~ []
@1030132 = ~I weep for my children. Their hate sustains this place, though they would intend otherwise. Had they not thought of me at all I would have perished, and soon after so would they.~ [RIFTG07]
@1030133 = ~I... am sorry, sir... truly I am. But all the people with spare coin are here... and...~ []
@1030136 = ~Ah, we be quite ahead on this project, aye? 63 days in and we can almost be beginnin'! But we can't continue, now... poor Jerro has gone and busted his foot...~ []
@1030137 = ~63 days and countin'... we'll be here by next year, I swear! I would get started on me work, o' course, but I've had a bit o' a head rush. Must sit down for a mite.~ []
@1030143 = ~... Oh. I see. Well, it seems I was mistaken, then. My apologies.~ []
@1030149 = ~63 days into the project... we should be done diggin' the first section by, oh, say, 100 days or so. I would keep workin' now, but me tummy is rumblin' somethin' fierce!~ []
@1030150 = ~'Tis a fine job working for the government. The overseer doesn't bother us... sleeps and drinks, mostly.~ []
@1030152 = ~We're a team... a team, that's what we are... and as long as we stick together, nobody can make us work!~ []
@1030154 = ~If you have a problem, talk to the overseer. No, I don't know where he went... probably sleepin' somewhere.~ []
@1030171 = ~The cause is simple. You will take the great device, the piece that I possess, and you shall combine it with the piece the creature already has.~ [RIFTG09]
@1030172 = ~Tell my people that you carry the piece that I give you that you might deplete it; that you go to restore its components so that it may be disposed of as a whole, not in part. My people must know I intend to destroy it when you return... but more, they must know I intend to end their service.~ [RIFTG11]
@1030177 = ~Er... yes, I am, actually.~ []
@1030180 = ~The energies of my followers are directed at this place, not at me. Should I try to leave, I would likely lose my form, only to return in the temple some years later.~ []
@1030182 = ~This is the abode of Lord Keldorn and his family, <SIRMAAM>. I take it you are... not expected, then?~ []
@1030187 = ~I know Keldorn... if it's all the same to you, I shall wait for him here.~ []
@1030191 = ~Is that so? Well, I do not recognize you and I find it highly unlikely that the Lady Maria knows of you. Please leave the estate at once, <SIRMAAM>... I'll not have strangers poking about.~ []
@1030193 = ~(sigh)  Lord Keldorn is a knight of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart, <SIRMAAM>. As I do not recognize you, I shall assume you are a stranger. Please leave at once!~ []
@1030198 = ~The destruction of a beast that is using you. I know not if you know its nature, but you will stand little chance against the thing without the great device.~ []
@1030220 = ~Have you enjoyed your visit? Of course you found nothing and of course you will leave empty handed. There is... you...~ []
@1030225 = ~Some idiot thief has stolen my necklace! Talos curse you for there shall be no services offered this day!~ []
@1030226 = ~Oh, my... this business between Master Keldorn and Lady Maria is just terrible! You may come in, my <LADYLORD>, but I would ask that you not disturb the Lady.~ []
@1030227 = ~You have the great device! What are you doing with that? It cannot be moved! It has not been moved in a millennium!~ []
@1030228 = ~It is the will of your god that it be taken from this place and weakened!~ []
@1030230 = ~I do not believe you. Nothing has changed here in ages. If you have the great device it is only because our god is weaker than we imagined.~ []
@1030231 = ~A sad, sad state of affairs, my <LADYLORD>. Lady Maria is imprisoned and the children are understandably upset... I beg that you do not disturb them.~ []
@1030236 = ~I was not going to try. You simply show how weak our god truly is. It changes nothing. We will remain trapped here, whether we've something to guard or not. Go, and be done with you.~ []
@1030243 = ~I am sorry, my <LADYLORD>. The master of this house is dead... I shall have to ask you to leave.~ []
@1030251 = ~Who are you?! What are you doing prowling about my home?!~ []
@1030254 = ~(sob!)  You are... the companion of my husband? (sob!)  Away with you! Away! You do nothing but take him further from my side! Oh, I am doomed!~ []
@1030265 = ~This cannot be. You cannot be the herald of change. It is not possible. I... I must see for myself. I must hear the word. We all must.~ []
@1030269 = ~I intend to work things out with your mother, child. Please... wait but a short while.~ []
@1030271 = ~(sob!)  Go away! (sob!)  I don't want to talk to anybody... especially daddy!~ []
@1030275 = ~Who are you?! Oh, my... thieves! THIEVES!!~ []
@1030278 = ~I wish we could have just been left with Lord William! He was a better father, at least! Just... just leave me alone!~ []
@1030283 = ~What we placed was earned! We were abandoned to our endless duty while our lord slept! Our faith weakened and we... and we abandoned him, except in curses.~ []
@1030289 = ~I remember this place... creatures among two apprentices, as I recall. I can assure you they are all dead, now.~ []
@1030290 = ~Is that so? Well, then... you have done us a favor already. You may go inside... but I warn you to keep to the first floor, my friend.~ []
@1030291 = ~I hear. You who have suffered, who still suffer. The time is at an end. Letter of the law states that we guard until the end of time. Our time has ended.~ [RIFTG14]
@1030294 = ~Praise be to the keeper of time, that he should let it end for the just.~ []
@1030295 = ~This is the end of things. Rest your mind in my heart. Rest.~ [RIFTG15]
@1030300 = ~Why do you speak in riddles, girl?~ []
@1030301 = ~You will see. I cannot see, but that's because it's mine. You will see. Cannot fight it.~ []
@1030302 = ~I am nine years in this life. They say my soul is the oldest of us. I am tired. Go see what we made. It's pretty. I wish I could see it. Can't fight it.~ []
@1030326 = ~What is this? Intruders within Mekrath's domain? What brings you here, foolish <MANWOMAN>... speak quickly, for I do not suffer errant fools gladly!~ []
@1030329 = ~Do not threaten me, wizard... I go where I like.~ []
@1030330 = ~Sorry to intrude... I shall be on my way, then.~ []
@1030335 = ~You'll release him to me... and his gem... or you'll meet your end at my hands!~ []
@1030336 = ~Ha ha... spoken boldly, <MANWOMAN>. I may have a use for one such as you, if you truly seek adventure. Might you be interested in such an... escapade?~ []
@1030337 = ~I might be... what sort of task do you speak of?~ []
@1030338 = ~Adventure comes with its rewards... name what you offer and I'll consider it.~ []
@1030349 = ~Perhaps he is at that, it matters little to me. He stole into my sanctum as a thief... I captured him and it amuses me to keep him as my slave.~ []
@1030352 = ~Regardless, you'll turn him... and his gem... over to me at once!~ []
@1030353 = ~My price, hm? Well... I do have a minor matter that needs to be taken care of. Perform the task and I shall hand the foolish thief over to you. Agreeable?~ []
@1030357 = ~His gem? Ah... THAT gem. I see what game you are up to, little <MANWOMAN>, and it shall not work! I'll not be divested of my gem by thieves and fools!!~ []
@1030360 = ~Ah, this is the one! Tch... the moronic beast has cracked it! Pfah! It shall take weeks to repair. I certainly hope you killed the imp for this indignity!~ []
@1030362 = ~He escaped... and took a rather important device I was experimenting on. A mirror. Unusable if you do not know the proper incantations. I would like it back.~ []
@1030364 = ~The imp has likely escaped to the sewers... and your travel there would save me the time and aggravation of retrieving it.~ []
@1030366 = ~A word of caution... the imp may have picked up an incantation or two and may have... used... the mirror. One can only guess what it might have summoned up.~ []
@1030368 = ~I remember the imp... and I have the mirror with me, here.~ []
@1030369 = ~I remember the imp... and I have the mirror with me, here.~ []
@1030370 = ~Very well... I shall seek out this item and return.~ []
@1030372 = ~Forget it... hand over the actor and his gem now, or suffer your end at my hands!~ []
@1030378 = ~But... you must be rewarded, as we agreed. There is a slave... a thief I caught recently... that should be more than adequate.~ []
@1030384 = ~Good. I am going to find some materials to fix this blasted mirror. I trust we shall not be seeing each other again... I shall not be disturbed a second time.~ []
@1030387 = ~Well... what is it? You have the mirror, I assume?!~ []
@1030390 = ~No, I don't... and I do not intend on getting it, either.~ []
@1030394 = ~You again?! I tire of these constant interruptions!! What is it NOW, foolish <MANWOMAN>... and your answer had better be a good one!!~ []
@1030395 = ~You have a captive... I wish him turned over to me right now!~ []
@1030396 = ~Do not threaten me, wizard... I go where I like!~ []
@1030398 = ~You will die, wizard... good enough an answer?!~ []
@1030399 = ~Very well... I shall leave you to your irritable solace, then.~ []
@1030404 = ~What is this disease that you are afflicted with?~ []
@1030423 = ~I refuse to take your charity. You'll simply have to wait.~ []
@1030428 = ~Most excellent! He is free so, please, take him and go. Remember, you do owe me 200gp.~ []
@1030444 = ~Ahhh... my head spins with sullen fire and strange, lurid notions instead of memories. But... what is this?~ [HAERDA02]
@1030445 = ~... My... my head clears, filled with stars and liquid fire... and I see before me the new holders of my shackles? The wizard has released me, I see, only to pass my reins to another.~ [HAERDA01]
@1030453 = ~And what if I want to lounge about your home? Who will stop me?~ []
@1030460 = ~My well-paid guards of course. No doubt it would reflect very bad upon you to conflict with sanctioned city militia. I may be a simple collector of tomes, but I know the value of security.~ []
@1030465 = ~Welcome to the home of Acton Balthis, currently Vice-Regent for the Council of Athkatla, my <LADYLORD>. Er... Lord Balthis is not here, might I ask your purpose?~ []
@1030473 = ~I am here to help myself to your lord's belongings... kindly step aside.~ []
@1030474 = ~I was just looking around... I'll be on my way.~ []
@1030481 = ~What if I were to try and retrieve it myself?~ []
@1030482 = ~I don't much care who brings it to me. I will pay you as much as the other fellows. Just don't damage the thing. It's entitled 'The Book of Kaza.' Off with you. A word of advice however:  you'll need help from one of the other fellows, only they know where the book is.~ []
@1030494 = ~You said that Lord Balthis was Vice-Regent for the Council... but I thought members of the Council were secret?~ []
@1030516 = ~Korgan? I thought you were dead. Ahh, perhaps Shagbag and those others were getting ahead of themselves.~ []
@1030521 = ~I ain't above putting a load of me fist in a few faces though, and sure enough they will get it. I'll off then, and catch them before they deliver the paperbound.~ []
@1030523 = ~Either way, I will win. Good luck then.~ []
@1030525 = ~Luck ain't no mattermind. Let's away to the garden of the dead. Methinks there be the best bet for the reader. I've a swift kick in the codpiece fer each of the gong-farmers ahead of us as well.~ []
@1030527 = ~ I serve Shar above all others, but I shall remain with you... for now.~ [VICONI35]
@1030539 = ~~ []
@1030543 = ~ I am not worried. I am sure these... setbacks are only temporary.~ [YOSHIM04]
@1030560 = ~Nothing is mattering all that much. I's just lamenting the turn of the coin that has taken me bookgold. I bet me lost partyboys have long gone with the loot by and by.~ []
@1030566 = ~ A... little help, here...~ [YOSHIM15]
@1030568 = ~ Ah, yes... the city. With all its people and their accumulated wealth, yes?~ [YOSHIM17]
@1030570 = ~ What do they say... about daylight and thieves? Oil and water?~ [YOSHIM19]
@1030577 = ~ Sou desu ne?~ [YOSHIM26]
@1030601 = ~No, no, I dinnae think such a thing will happen. You'll be a day's dead before you get a coin for yout threat. I ain't one to bargain.~ []
@1030602 = ~Then set your fury on the ground and we'll see if it stands up. I doubt it muchly.~ []
@1030610 = ~Chief Inspector Brega, at your service. I work under the Magistrate investigating the crimes of this city, and there are plenty that require my attention, believe you me.~ [BREGAX07]
@1030612 = ~I am told that magic is illegal in Athkatla... is this true?~ []
@1030618 = ~ I must apologize, but I can carry no more. I have set your item upon the ground.~ [YOSHIM39]
@1030625 = ~ A momentary lapse, perhaps, but I fear this course will upset the greater picture. We must strive to maintain balance within ourselves.~ [CERND05]
@1030628 = ~ I will lead with gentle certainty, as the river shapes the rocks it flows through.~ [CERND08]
@1030635 = ~Very little. Lieutenant Aegisfield is in the Bridge District as the main investigator. All I can say is to watch yourself at night if you must be out.~ []
@1030636 = ~I am told that magic is illegal in Athkatla... is this true?~ []
@1030637 = ~I am told that magic is illegal in Athkatla... is this true?~ []
@1030663 = ~The handling of magic users is not my province. Only the Cowled Wizards know for sure... what matters to the Council is that they deal with it.~ []
@1030671 = ~The Cowled Wizards arrested two magic users. Shadow Thieves were also involved, apparently attacking one of the wizards. Beyond that... no, I know very little.~ []
@1030677 = ~ Nature acts in the simplest way.~ [CERND34]
@1030679 = ~ A bird in hand gathers no moss... or some such.~ [CERND36]
@1030684 = ~ I have taken something, though everything belongs to nature.~ [CERND41]
@1030691 = ~(sigh)  I'll tell you what my job isn't... it isn't being forced to listen to idiots like yourself. Good day.~ []
@1030696 = ~Ahhh, good business to you, my <LADYLORD>! My name is Quataris... might you be interested in some artwork? A painting to add style to your abode?~ []
@1030703 = ~I am sorry, friend... I see there is nothing here to interest you. If you ever run across any... spare... works of art, I am always happy to buy. Otherwise, good business to you.~ []
@1030709 = ~ I'm busy, okay? I'm busy!~ [EDWIN24]
@1030714 = ~ One day... one day...~ [EDWIN29]
@1030744 = ~Watch your step... there are a lot of valuables, here, and they are protected well.~ []
@1030746 = ~ Gotcha good!~ [IMOEN42]
@1030752 = ~ The magic fizzled.~ [IMOEN48]
@1030762 = ~ You want a fight? I'll show you a fight!~ [IMOEN16]
@1030763 = ~~ []
@1030778 = ~~ []
@1030834 = ~Hear ye, hear ye! All the news that's fit to bellow! Today's latest: diplomatic overtures in Riatavin! Council of Six foresees resolution to southern troubles!~ []
@1030835 = ~Riatavin? What's going on there?~ []
@1030837 = ~Listen up, all. Riatavin and Trailstone petitioned to join Tethyr a few tendays ago, but talks collapsed under covenants gone bad. Now Riatavin wants back in.~ []
@1030838 = ~The real tales behind the proclamations! Each morning I've scuttlebutt on the fat and dirt on the pure. The call of the cock and I roll from my rock!~ []
@1030839 = ~Allo! Allo! More Tethyrian exiles landing in Athkatla! Hear ye! Hear ye! Expelled for familial misdeeds! Oh shudder to think of all the red ink!~ []
@1030840 = ~Umar was a witch who terrorized Amn a long time ago. My mother says the hills were named after her, but she disappeared so long ago nobody remembers what happened.~ []
@1030841 = ~Exiles? What's this all about then?~ []
@1030844 = ~The Year of the Tankard has been a tough one for the rich and pampered trying to grind out a living on the backs of the poor down south.~ []
@1030845 = ~Every morning I'm here, keeping the faith, protecting the righteous, and crucifying the guilty! Drop by to gnaw the fat and feast on the foolish!~ []
@1030846 = ~Splint mail is a variant of banded mail, in which metal strips are applied vertically to a backing of chain, leather, or cloth, rather than horizontally as with banded mail. Since the human body does not swivel in mid-torso as much as it flexes back to front, splint mail is more restrictive in battle. This suit of armor is enchanted, granting the wearer a bonus of +1 to their armor class.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class: 3
Weight: 10
Requires: 8 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Bard
 Druid
