 Kensai~ []
@1030852 = ~I... I am glad that Quayle yet lives. And... and I have found you, <CHARNAME>. Perhaps the gods have begun to forgive my foolish pride.~ []
@1030853 = ~Yes, it was. I disregarded my teachings and I have paid for it. I was taken from my home forever and bereft of my wings... a great and final punishment upon me.~ []
@1030854 = ~I... I have paid for it, <CHARNAME>. But saving that child was all I could do! I hope he lives, yet... and I cannot believe that you would be so cruel as to cast that in my face!~ []
@1030859 = ~He's dead, Aerie... and nothing's going to change that.~ []
@1030860 = ~Please no more tears, Aerie... I am quickly growing tired of this.~ []
@1030862 = ~Quayle befriended me when I was caged. H-he would... bring me things. To eat... or to make me more comfortable. And he would teach me, sometimes.~ []
@1030863 = ~He hated the owner for keeping me caged. And... and when they had to cut off my wings, he took me in. He taught me all he knew, and gave me my faith in Baervan Wildwanderer.~ []
@1030864 = ~I was happy... of a sort... while I was with him. I owe him so much.~ []
@1030865 = ~I don't mean it that way, <CHARNAME>. I... I am here because I must be... because I have to find my own way. I... simply miss Quayle, still. I don't know... is that not right?~ []
@1030866 = ~I... I know that, <CHARNAME>. His loss is a chill dagger in my heart. If I speak of him, it is because he was one of the rare things since my capture that had given me happiness.~ []
@1030867 = ~Quayle... he was one of the rare things that gave me happiness since my enslavement. If this is so disturbing to you then I shall not speak of it... or... or to you, for that matter.~ []
@1030871 = ~Oh. I'd hoped that you might be someone important so that I could travel with you. You are nobody, so goodbye.~ []
@1030873 = ~Baervan is called the Masked Leaf... he is the gnomish god of nature. I... I know it is strange for an elf to pay him homage, but that is the way it is.~ []
@1030875 = ~I was always entranced by Quayle's tales of Baervan's escapades with his raccoon companion, Chiktikka Fastpaws. They were filled with humor and kindness, and indicative of Baervan's gentle nature.~ []
@1030878 = ~Baervan brought me my faith back... he gave me peace when I needed it most. And I shall always pay him homage in my heart. Is that so strange, <CHARNAME>?~ []
@1030881 = ~I don't need a kid following me around.~ []
@1030889 = ~Ha, you are probably correct. I am a flightless elf lost in a strange land and am plenty strange, myself. What I would not give, sometimes, to forget what I have known.~ []
@1030892 = ~Is it so bad that it should threaten you? But, then, I am mightily odd myself. A stranger, alone and cast off from all I have known. If only... if only you could understand.~ []
@1030893 = ~Helmsport is the apple of New Amn's eye. Enter Waterdeep, seeking to expand her influence and ruthlessly plunder under the guise of diplomacy.~ []
@1030894 = ~Have you traveled much? I have been over much of Amn and Tethyr with the circus... although it was not always the most pleasant way to voyage.~ [AERIE94]
@1030897 = ~Oh great, I'll just run and grab my things! Mother, did you hear...~ []
@1030899 = ~Don't whine to me about the circus, Aerie... my travels have not been by choice, either, and likely less pleasant than yours.~ []
@1030900 = ~The Council of Six send an armada of Helm-priests and sellswords to expel the Waterdhavian traders before the natives sniff the winds of change!~ []
@1030905 = ~I have not been that far north... the circus mainly made its way around Amn and further south. I've been to Eshpurta and Murann, among other places... but people are all the same.~ []
@1030908 = ~They gawked at me when I was caged... pointed and were cruel. Once I was out of my cage, the people were no kinder... if it were not for Quayle, I could not have stood it.~ []
@1030909 = ~I... I think I am glad, finally, to be traveling away from the staring and jeering crowds. I am away from prying eyes, voyaging freely... on the ground, at least.~ []
@1030910 = ~And... and I am glad to be traveling with you, <CHARNAME>. You have saved my life and... made me feel very welcome.~ []
@1030917 = ~Don't flatter yourself... you're here because you're useful and that's it.~ []
@1030922 = ~As you wish, <CHARNAME>. It... it was only an errant wish for talk and nothing more.~ []
@1030924 = ~I... I am not whining, <CHARNAME>! I know that you have not had an easy time, but neither have I! Must you... must you be so cruel?~ []
@1030925 = ~Always! But be a dear, be sincere and get your ass on outta here. Let's foreclose on this topic. It can change, change fast and change she will!~ []
@1030926 = ~You... you are making me blush, <CHARNAME>. Th-thank you.~ []
@1030928 = ~I... I see. Th-then I shall endeavour to remain useful for you, <CHARNAME>. To travel with you, if nothing else.~ []
@1030930 = ~I see... I see I was mistaken. If my presence makes it so unbearable for you, <CHARNAME>, then perhaps I should leave...~ []
@1030934 = ~No... I apologize, Aerie. I meant nothing by it.~ []
@1030936 = ~Waterdhavians run amok in New Amn while the peace is policed! Seems the New World has all the Old World problems!~ []
@1030938 = ~Every morning my soapbox is set, my mouth full of moxie and my head swims with tales from across Faerun! All true! All timely! All told with aplomb and vigor!~ []
@1030941 = ~Then... then I shall stay with you. For now.~ []
@1030947 = ~Hear ye! Hear ye! The Rebellion she truly begins today! Today of all days! Riatavin and Trailstone have defected! 
~ []
@1030949 = ~It... it is nothing, truly, Haer'Dalis. I am simply... thinking of a time when I still had my wings. Sometimes... sometimes the memory still wrenches my soul.~ [AERIE74]
@1030952 = ~I'm Rebecca. You're my idol, <CHARNAME>. I have been following your exploits for months.~ []
@1030954 = ~Do you? I... mean no offense, Haer'Dalis, but I find that hard to believe, if you have never flown.~ []
@1030962 = ~"My fall was not the thing, my love,
 I thought I bore it well
 but to stare up into the heavens
 from the darkened plains of hell
 and think that I, too, once walked those
 endless heights
 is a pain I cannot tell."~ []
@1030964 = ~Damage control for the Council now comes in the form of arbitrators sent to Darromar to restrict the involvement of the Tethyrian government.~ []
@1030968 = ~With the dawn and a yawn comes new tales and old friends.  I'm all over it, like the stench on dung! Check here each morning for the latest on the latest!~ []
@1030969 = ~That's... that was very lovely, Haer'Dalis.~ []
@1030970 = ~They are but simple words, my dove. For this bard to understand but a tiny fraction of your pain has cleft my heart in twain. You... have my deepest sympathy, sweet, lonely Aerie.~ []
@1030971 = ~I... th-thank you.~ []
@1030980 = ~Oh... but you will surely laugh at me for such an admission.~ [AERIE75]
@1030996 = ~You flatter me, now, Haer'Dalis. But... yes, my mother used to tell me that I would be a fine actress. I... I used to dream of fluttering onto the great stage in Faenya-Dale...~ []
@1031007 = ~You are funny and strange, Haer'Dalis... but I thank you for the compliments, nevertheless.~ []
@1031009 = ~Oh? Have you, Haer'Dalis? And to what manner of role shall I be subjected, then?~ [AERIE76]
@1031010 = ~You wound me, fair one... I have deliberated over the choice for quite some time, now. I have weighed carefully each play that canters through my head and chosen one that compliments you most fruitfully.~ []
@1031011 = ~'Tis the lead of a Sigil play called 'Tersis'... written, if I remember, by a rather haggard tiefling gifted with the madness of true talent.~ []
@1031013 = ~You would play the goddess, herself... fallen from favor and bearing the slings of accusation and scorn with grace and confidence. With chin held high, she strides towards her former peers and dares to challenge the false verdict of the higher powers!~ []
@1031014 = ~That... that sounds lovely, Haer'Dalis... but it's hardly me.~ []
@1031015 = ~Ah, but it is, my mourning dove. You have suffered the cleansing torments, borne under the impossible strains... and I'll wager there's a steel in your heart that you've yet to lay claim to!~ []
@1031016 = ~Oh, I don't think I ever could... I don't think you know me, really...~ []
@1031017 = ~I know you better than you think, my dove. The true thespian reaches down into a well of dark waters within them... a place where others dare not look. And you've a deep well, fair Aerie... be not afraid to dive within!~ []
@1031018 = ~You've a pretty way with words, bard. Well... I think I'll disappoint you surely, but if you wish to teach me your play I won't object to it.~ []
@1031020 = ~That's all I ask, my dove... and this bard cannot wait to see the results of this first act now unfolding...~ []
@1031022 = ~What is it, Aerie? By the gods... you're drenched with sweat! What's wrong?!~ []
@1031023 = ~I... (gasp) ... I was having a dream. A most dreadful nightmare!! Please... please sit with me for but a short while... I am shaken to my very core...~ []
@1031028 = ~(shudder)  I... I was back in the circus, after my owner had decided that my wings had become too diseased. I had been laying in my cage, sweating and delirious for days...~ []
@1031030 = ~... his men came and pulled me out, and my wings burned so! I could barely cry out, I was so weak! And... and they began to saw off my wings... hacking at them with rusted knives!~ []
@1031031 = ~(shudder)  I screamed and screamed! They... hacked off... my wings and then used... torches to seal my wounds. Oh, <CHARNAME>...! (sob!)  Oh, <CHARNAME>, I... I...!~ []
@1031032 = ~I... (sob!) ... I didn't mean to bother you. Please forgive me... it won't happen again...~ []
@1031033 = ~It's alright, Aerie... that was a long time ago. Calm yourself...~ []
@1031034 = ~Shhh... calm yourself. I understand.~ []
@1031036 = ~It... it felt like I was there again! I can... I can still feel my wings being torn from my back...~ []
@1031037 = ~I... I'm sorry, <CHARNAME>. It was so long ago, I should not still be so torn. I... I must resign myself to my fate. Come... let us continue on with your journey...~ []
@1031038 = ~I have been thinking... I shall never fly again, never taste the freedom of my wings, I am sure of it. I... I don't know if I can face this wretched existence on the ground...!~ [AERIE96]
@1031042 = ~Don't say that... we'll find some way to restore your wings, I promise!~ []
@1031043 = ~If you continue to act so weak and maudlin, then I agree... you'll never survive.~ []
@1031046 = ~We'll find a way to restore your wings, Aerie... I promise you that.~ []
@1031048 = ~Find the strength?! Find the strength?! How can you be so cruel as to cast that at me?! I... I am a member of a proud race... my wings were everything to me!~ []
@1031049 = ~I can never go back to Faenya-Dale! I could not face them without my wings! Here I am, stuck like an insect crawling on the dirt...~ []
@1031050 = ~And you tell me to simply be strong?! W-well... what am I supposed to be strong for?!! I... I hate this existence...~ []
@1031053 = ~I can never go back to Faenya-Dale, never look another of my kind in the eyes again! I could not face them without my wings!~ []
@1031054 = ~Y-your promises are empty! I... I h-hate myself and this l-life! Just... just stay away from me!~ []
@1031055 = ~How... how could you be so cruel? (sob!)  I... I h-hate this life... I hate m-myself... and I hate you! Just... just stay away from me...! Just stay away!~ []
@1031056 = ~I... I am sorry for the way I yelled at you. I sometimes feel... as if I have been weighted down by many stones... but I should not have reacted so to your words.~ [AERIE97]
@1031057 = ~It's alright, Aerie... but you are going to have to accept your fate and find a way to deal with it.~ []
@1031059 = ~Forget it... if you can't deal with your problems, I'm not about to let you drag me into them.~ []
@1031060 = ~I... I suppose you are correct. But how can I? Tell me how I can ever accept this, <CHARNAME>?~ []
@1031062 = ~You've got to find another reason to live, Aerie... something else to hold onto.~ []
@1031063 = ~Don't look to me for the answers... I don't have them.~ []
@1031064 = ~I will try to carry on with you, <CHARNAME>. I just... I just don't know if I can. But I will try.~ []
@1031065 = ~I understand, <CHARNAME>. I will try... to deal with it as best I can. I just don't know if I am strong enough. Please forgive me...~ []
@1031066 = ~Be strong? I... I'll try, <CHARNAME>. I just... I just don't know if I can, but I will try.~ []
@1031067 = ~I just wish I knew what that was. It was once so easy... why have the gods punished me so? I shall try, <CHARNAME>... I will try to be strong. I just... don't know if I can.~ []
@1031068 = ~Yes... I know. I must find the answer on my own. Nothing... nothing could make me sadder, I think.~ []
@1031069 = ~Why must we always be fighting? All I see is bloodshed and battle... and it drains me. Do you... do you not yearn for a life of peace and contemplation?~ [AERIE98]
@1031073 = ~Sometimes battle is required, Aerie... it is not something that I have a choice about.~ []
@1031074 = ~Struggle and combat bring strength, Aerie... and I have needed all my strength just to survive!~ []
@1031076 = ~And yet it continues on and on. I... I don't know how much more of this I can take. I feel so empty inside...~ []
@1031080 = ~Fighting has brought me strength, Aerie... the strength to survive. You could use the same.~ []
@1031082 = ~You have a choice, Aerie... you can always go back to the circus, if you wish.~ []
@1031083 = ~Strength... always you talk of strength and being stronger. I... I do not know if I have your strength, <CHARNAME>. I am beginning to think it is almost not worth it...~ []
@1031084 = ~(sigh)  I will, <CHARNAME>. I will stay so quiet that you shall not even hear me... nor notice when I am finally gone, I suppose, and more's the better when that happens.~ []
@1031085 = ~I... do not wish to go back to the circus, <CHARNAME>. There is nothing for me there. I just... I just wish I had your strength... that it was easier to forget what I once was.~ []
@1031095 = ~Noses are akimbo about Maztican gold falling into chubby fingers while Riatavin and Trailstone are left reading from the wrong books and the dogleg ledgers!~ []
@1031099 = ~Their petitions have been renegotiated and the Council is flabbergasted with this latest episode! A curse and a wail in protest as Amn is rent asunder!~ []
@1031100 = ~Prick up your ears and hear this woeful tale of loss. Half a tenday ago, the Council was talking with Riatavin about welcoming them back into the family fold.~ []
@1031101 = ~This turn of events could draw Athkatla into a trade war! A war, alas friends, no one can win! Oh for grief if it's embargoes and sanctions!~ []
@1031102 = ~Awaken ye to the song of the sea! The story was delivered by pearl! The council abandons hope on getting back Riatavin and Trailstone! Hear all about it!~ []
@1031103 = ~What happened there, Neckeith?~ []
@1031108 = ~It's a blight on Amnian commerce! The Merchants' Chosen of Riatavin took the money, split the difference, and bit the hand that fed them all in one fell swoop!~ []
@1031109 = ~Now Riatavin is still bitter over its red ink in the Maztica deal. Riatavin's merchants are denying Amnian access to trade routes in their territory!~ []
@1031142 = ~Does anyone really give any sort of damn about this Riatavin nonsense?~ []
@1031144 = ~Some drunken sailor just walked by with your mam on one arm and a tankard of bathtub gin on the other. Now go away, kobold! You bother me.~ []
@1031145 = ~In retaliation for treating the Duchess of the Purple Marches like a common kobold, Queen Zaranda accepts petitions from the two renegade outposts!~ []
@1031146 = ~The comely Queen Zaranda of Tethyr is outraged at the Council of Six, treating her Lady Haredown so shabbily, and by rote, her country!~ []
@1031147 = ~Riatavin now lays claim to land south of the Tejarn Hills! The Council lurches all trade to a deafening halt! Our Six are dragons, and wily ones at that!~ []
@1031149 = ~I... I need you to tell me what the worth of a life on the ground is. Is there anything to compare to the freedom of living in the clouds?~ [AERIE99]
@1031151 = ~Good business, gathered friends! I've got dirt that might hurt and you'll scarcely believe the cloak-and-dagger conspiracies! Two old adversaries resurface.~ []
@1031152 = ~There's no point in your musings, Aerie... this is the way things are and there's no avoiding them.~ []
@1031154 = ~No... they can't be. Everything of beauty can be seen from the sky. And there are so many places you cannot go if all you can do is walk.~ []
@1031159 = ~Yes... I'll have to get used to it. An unpleasant prospect, when a life looms over you without joy or freedom. I... I don't know if I can, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1031163 = ~I don't mean to bother you, <CHARNAME>. I am used to remaining in cages, neglected. I'll... just keep my thoughts to myself from now on.~ []
@1031164 = ~Are there better parts, <CHARNAME>? How would I recognize them if I discovered them? I... I just don't know if I can wait for them to come along.~ []
@1031165 = ~Just... just ignore me, <CHARNAME>. I must seem very pitiful and wretched to moan so all the time. You must despise me.~ []
@1031166 = ~Search for them? I'm not sure I would even recognize them. Nor do I think I can go on much longer... I just can't... stand it any more.~ []
@1031167 = ~A coward. Y-you're likely right, but it's still cruel to say so. How you must despise my weakness and moaning. I... I'll not bother you any longer, <CHARNAME>...~ []
@1031168 = ~W-we're stopping? (sob!)  Oh... I... I just feel like collapsing here and dying. I just don't think I can go on.~ [AERIEA1]
@1031169 = ~Perhaps it is better and more fitting if I just... just die. Like a bird whose wings are broken, I am useless, <CHARNAME>... utterly useless. *sob!*~ []
@1031171 = ~I've... I've had enough of this life! (sob!)  P-perhaps it would be better if I... just went back to the circus...~ []
@1031176 = ~Y-you are so heartless! I... I will go! Forgive me, Baervan, but I can do this no longer!!~ []
@1031177 = ~Y-yes... forgive me, <CHARNAME>... I tried, I really did. I... I'm just not strong enough. G-good-bye...~ []
@1031178 = ~But I have, <CHARNAME>, I have! I... I just don't have the strength! I'm so useless...~ []
@1031181 = ~(sob!)  I... I can't!~ []
@1031184 = ~N-no... no, I don't want to die. Maybe... maybe I will think on what you have said. Let... let me just sleep... for now.~ []
@1031185 = ~I have been thinking, and you are right. I have been foolish. I may not have my wings, but I have everything else, especially... my life, and people who care for me.~ [AERIEA2]
@1031186 = ~I am such a silly woman. Whining and crying... I must seem so ridiculous and petty. No man will ever want me, I think... I feel so embarrassed.~ []
@1031187 = ~Well... it's good to see that you're feeling better, at least. Let's just continue our travels, shall we?~ []
@1031189 = ~I'm glad you're better... but you're wrong, still. There are many reasons a man would want you... not least of which is your beauty.~ []
@1031190 = ~Certainly, <CHARNAME>. And... thank you... f-for your encouragement to me.~ []
@1031191 = ~O-oh... I didn't know you f-felt that way. I... I will just stay out of your way, then... for now.~ []
@1031195 = ~Oh... I see. Well... thank you, <CHARNAME>. Umm... do you... do you think I'm beautiful? I mean... do you feel all these things about me?~ []
@1031196 = ~Don't mistake me, Aerie... you are beautiful and everything, but I would prefer we maintain our friendship. Let's just continue our voyage, shall we?~ []
@1031198 = ~And I care for you, <CHARNAME>. Th-thank you... for everything you have done... for me. I feel... much better.~ []
@1031200 = ~I've read the play, yes... but, Haer'Dalis, I still honestly don't think I can play this Tersis character.~ [AERIE77]
@1031202 = ~Well... the scene where the goddess confronts Lord Jhovan, the ruler of the gods. She chastises him rather... forcefully...~ []
@1031204 = ~(giggle)  Oh, Haer'Dalis... I could never do that! The words would sound like a mouse were speaking them, coming from me. I've no such voice in me...~ []
@1031205 = ~The voice is in you, my dove. You have but to cast about for it. Come... enact the passage for me.~ []
@1031207 = ~(sigh)  I... I'll try. "H-hold, my Lord... I will n-not... not be judged..."  No, no... it's just no use.~ []
@1031211 = ~Haer'Dalis! What a cruel thing to say!~ []
@1031213 = ~Fine.  "H-hold, my Lord... I w-will... n-not... not be... --"~ []
@1031216 = ~"H-hold, my Lord! I will... n-not... not be... j-judged --"~ []
@1031220 = ~"Hold, my Lord! I will not be judged by the lowest of my brethren, nor shall I be judged by my King! I refuse to be silent! I am Tersis! And I WILL be heard!"~ []
@1031222 = ~I... I did it, didn't I? Th-thank you, Haer'Dalis! That... that felt wonderful!~ []
@1031223 = ~Ha! What is it now, my fair Aerie? You think I am not looking at you, but I can spy your desire to put the bard to the question. Go ahead, my dove... I'll not mind.~ [HAERDA71]
@1031224 = ~Well... I was only wondering... um... my scenes that I read to you the other day. Was I... was I any good? Please tell me truthfully.~ [AERIE78]
@1031227 = ~What of other news?~ []
@1031229 = ~How's this? Your mother was a jackal and your father was an ass, which make you, urchin interruptus, a jackass! Now stop disrupting my train of thought!~ []
@1031230 = ~You... you aren't just saying that? I'm not that good...~ []
@1031231 = ~Your skill needs to be sharpened, 'tis true, but the talent is plenty and full. And I do not exaggerate, my dove... your mother saw it true when she mused o'er your life upon the stage.~ []
@1031232 = ~A cauldron of cold intrigues! A witches brew of bad news! Cyricists of the Twin Towers of the Eternal Eclipse are wooing the ogre magi Sythsillis and Cyrvisnea.~ []
@1031233 = ~Ha... it's too bad, then, that there's nowhere to perform our piece.~ []
@1031236 = ~Blackwill Akhlmere, of the horse-breeding Akhlmere empire, requires aid! The Giant's Eye Trading Company has run into Cyricists at the Mountain of Skulls.~ []
@1031237 = ~Word of our acts would spread... and we would be in demand all over Amn! Bugbears would stand beside great nobles, shouting out your name and mine! The toast of Kings and Queens, my dove... just imagine it!~ []
@1031238 = ~Ha ha ha! You are a silly man, Haer'Dalis!~ []
@1031241 = ~Blackwill offers sellswords to the Sythillisian Empire for the attack on Murann. The Green Fields Consortium keeps a close eye on events!~ []
@1031243 = ~Ear to the ground and eyes wide round, check with me every morning for the true book lowdown on the high-born and the skinny on the fat! Good business!~ []
@1031244 = ~"Aye... Tersis has come to you, my Donner. Your yearning has called to me across the void, and against all sober advice, I have come."~ [AERIE79]
@1031245 = ~Good business! You could cook a hen's egg on your forehead this morn! Riatavin is in hot water this day! Caravans disrupted and contracts corrupted!~ []
@1031248 = ~"Then let me sing your praises while I can, my Queen. Let me tell you how I adore your flaxen hair, your porcelain skin... let me tell you how I long to brush my hand across your pale cheek..."~ []
@1031249 = ~Er... Haer'Dalis...?~ []
@1031251 = ~Haer'Dalis, your words... your words aren't in the play.~ []
@1031252 = ~Forget the play, my mourning dove... I speak what is in my heart. My words come unbidden to my lips, for you have captured my soul in your innocent hands.~ []
@1031254 = ~I... I thank you for your words, Haer'Dalis... but...~ []
@1031256 = ~E-enough... please. I... I am flattered... but... but I was not expecting this. Please... leave me alone but for a while...~ []
@1031257 = ~Aerie... my sweet dove... I have given you time to ponder my words, but my aching soul yearns for requitement. Do you not feel some measure of love for this solitary bard? I beg you to say that you do!~ [HAERDA73]
@1031261 = ~Haer'Dalis... this is all s-so... sudden...~ [AERIE80]
@1031262 = ~It is not sudden, my love, but rather it is momentous... a revelation of affection that has stricken me like a most welcome affliction!~ []
@1031263 = ~Tell me that you feel similarly, my mourning dove, and I'll be yours forever more, my heart lain at your tender feet. Or tell me that you have no love and I'll be forsworn... but say it true!~ []
@1031264 = ~I... I do not deny that I hold you in great esteem, Haer'Dalis. You have been most kind. It... it is just that...~ []
@1031266 = ~I... I don't know. I truly don't...~ []
@1031271 = ~I... I know this may seem an... odd question. But I need to know... how do you... f-feel about me?~ []
@1031272 = ~I love you, Aerie... I thought you knew.~ []
@1031274 = ~Feel? You are a friend... no more and no less.~ []
@1031276 = ~It... it cannot wait, <CHARNAME>. Or, at least, my heart will not let it wait.~ []
@1031277 = ~Alright... what is the question?~ []
@1031279 = ~Ah... no... no, I did not know. I suspected... and hoped... but I did not know. Oh, <CHARNAME>, this is so terrible!~ []
@1031280 = ~Oh, that sounds all wrong! I... I do care for you very much, <CHARNAME>! I do! But I... I also care for Haer'Dalis! This is... so confusing... I must think about this...~ []
@1031281 = ~Oh, <CHARNAME>... I... th-thank you for saying so! My heart is fluttering so... oh, this is so terrible!~ []
@1031282 = ~No, you will have no victory here! Rejiek must work on!~ []
@1031283 = ~I... I see. That answers my question most... f-fully. Th-thank you, <CHARNAME>... I think of you as a... friend... as well.~ []
@1031284 = ~I... I see. F-forget about my question, then, <CHARNAME>. It... it does not matter, really.~ []
@1031288 = ~My raven! If you would but hold and step aside, but for a moment... this hapless bard would make a private plea of you.~ [HAERDA74]
@1031289 = ~What is it, Haer'Dalis?~ []
@1031291 = ~Not now, Haer'Dalis. This isn't a good time.~ []
@1031292 = ~You are man worthy of my dove's affections... of this I am sure. But this sparrow asks of you to turn away from her and to allow her affections to settle on myself! My heart yearns for her and I beg this favor of you!~ []
@1031294 = ~I cannot simply switch my feelings on and off at will, Haer'Dalis!~ []
@1031295 = ~The choice is hers, Haer'Dalis. Not mine nor yours.~ []
@1031296 = ~(sigh)  Very well, Haer'Dalis. You may have her for yourself, if that is your wish. And if she'll have you.~ []
@1031301 = ~But you must, <CHARNAME>, you must! I cannot bear to watch my dove with another... and you are a man who could surely have another! I beg of you not to twist my heart!~ []
@1031302 = ~It is not even up to me, Haer'Dalis... it is up to Aerie whom she chooses. I cannot give her to you.~ []
@1031303 = ~The answer is no, Haer'Dalis! And I meant it!~ []
@1031304 = ~If she means that much to you, then very well... I will step aside.~ []
@1031305 = ~But she is a fragile flower, my dark hound... she will wish to hurt neither of us with such a momentous choice! And I cannot bear to be without her!~ []
@1031307 = ~Please... step aside, <CHARNAME>, and let our true love be unfurled!~ []
@1031308 = ~I love her too, Haer'Dalis. I can't just give her to you.~ []
@1031309 = ~Very well... if she means that much to you, I will not interfere.~ []
@1031310 = ~The heavens sing with your praises, my hound! You have made this poet's heart leap with joy! I will not forget this, <CHARNAME>... you have made our union possible and I thank you with all of my soul!~ []
@1031312 = ~I can imagine only one outcome to this black path you have placed us on. We shall see which of us my dove chooses... and what agony results of it!~ []
@1031316 = ~My mourning dove... the time has come for you to make a choice between us. I beg of you to decide, as my ailing heart can wait no longer!~ [HAERDA75]
@1031317 = ~I... oh, Haer'Dalis! I never expected for any of this to happen! I... I love both you and him in different ways... I cannot simply... choose between you!~ [AERIE82]
@1031318 = ~Please... can't you understand that? I beg of you not to press me!~ []
@1031319 = ~I... I see, my dove. There is only one option that remains, then. <CHARNAME>... I challenge you to a duel... a fight to the death for the love of our lady Aerie.~ []
@1031321 = ~Very well... a duel it is.~ []
@1031322 = ~You want to duel for Aerie? Haer'Dalis... if she means that much to you, then I will not interfere.~ []
@1031323 = ~There is love... or there is death, my dark hound. My honor demands no less. Look within your heart and you will understand.~ []
@1031325 = ~Aerie is right, Haer'Dalis. We should not fight. Put down your swords and let us talk.~ []
@1031326 = ~Step aside, Aerie... the bard wants a duel and he'll have it.~ []
@1031327 = ~<CHARNAME>? Y-you would... you would simply give up on me? Give up on your feelings for me?~ []
@1031328 = ~Can't you see, my dove? It is I who love you with zeal... it is my passion that yearns for you. <CHARNAME> is a good man... but even he sees that my love is the love that is true.~ []
@1031329 = ~I... I do love you, Haer'Dalis. I am glad that you did not f-fight over me, but I must... I must have time to set my heart straight. Please... g-give me time.~ []
@1031330 = ~Of course, my dove... take all the time you need. My heart shall still pound hotly for you a day or an eon hence. And thank you, <CHARNAME>, for your understanding...~ []
@1031333 = ~Aerie... my love... do not restrain me from combating my foe for your affection! Our blades must meet, it is the only possible end!~ []
@1031334 = ~No, Haer'Dalis! It is NOT the only possible end! I said I would not allow you to fight over me and I meant it!~ []
@1031335 = ~I am not something for you to become impassioned over like a jewel or a poem, Haer'Dalis! I do not think your love is real, if you would resort to violence to prove it!~ []
@1031336 = ~I love <CHARNAME>. I love him deeply and without hesitation... and I know he feels for me, as well. And that... that is how it shall be.~ []
@1031339 = ~I... see. My... my heart aches to hear these words, my dove... but I sense they are true. If I offended you... I apologize...~ []
@1031340 = ~And I apologize to you, <CHARNAME>, if my heart was foolish and o'erquick. I cannot deny what I feel, however... and I cannot stay and watch my dove stay with another.~ []
@1031341 = ~Until... until we meet again, <CHARNAME>. And... and farewell, my lady love...~ []
@1031345 = ~If you would resort to violence to prove your love for me, than you are not the man I thought you were! I... I love Haer'Dalis... I know that to be true, now.~ []
@1031346 = ~Yes, my bard... I do love you. <CHARNAME>... put down your arms and accept that... that this is the way it will be. I... I am so sorry.~ []
@1031348 = ~I... I can't bear to watch you with another, Aerie.~ []
@1031351 = ~It... it breaks my heart that I must leave you... but leave you I must, then.~ []
@1031352 = ~And I with you, my dove... wherever you go, I shall be with you.~ []
@1031353 = ~I'm sorry that this couldn't have... worked out better. Farewell, <CHARNAME>... I hope... I hope that we meet again, someday.~ []
@1031356 = ~I... I suppose I was correct, then. Your feelings do not run as deep as those of my bard's. Come, then... I would be glad to fight by your side. Let us continue your quest.~ []
@1031360 = ~I have... something that I must ask of you... an awkward question, if you will.~ [AERIEA3]
@1031363 = ~I have been thinking about you quite a bit as of late. I know this may seem an... odd question. But I need to know... how do you... f-feel about me?~ []
@1031364 = ~I love you, Aerie... I thought you knew.~ []
@1031366 = ~Feel? You are a friend... no more and no less.~ []
@1031368 = ~It... it cannot wait, <CHARNAME>. Or, at least, my heart will not let it wait.~ []
@1031373 = ~Well, it will still have to wait, regardless... this is not the time.~ []
@1031374 = ~And I love you, too, <CHARNAME>. Ooh, this is a most wonderful relief. You have been... so kind and helpful to me, I am glad of your love.~ []
@1031375 = ~Come, then... let us continue on our travels and we can speak more of this later.~ []
@1031376 = ~And I, too, care for you. You have been... so kind and supportive. I... I thank you, <CHARNAME>. I feel awkward, but I am most pleased that you have requited my feelings.~ []
@1031378 = ~As... as you wish, <CHARNAME>. Forget my question, then... it was of no importance.~ []
@1031379 = ~A... a friend? Then it is... then it is good that I have asked this. I am glad we are friends, <CHARNAME>... let us continue on your quest and I shall be glad to fight by your side.~ []
@1031380 = ~Haer'Dalis? Might I have a... a word with you?~ [AERIE87]
@1031394 = ~I... I just wanted you to know... I've noticed the amount of time you've spent with me...~ []
@1031396 = ~This sparrow shall not come betwixt the two of you. Be merry, my swan... its glow suits you well. And who knows? Perhaps I shall play at your wedding!~ []
@1031400 = ~What about Baldur's Gate? Heard anything from there?~ []
@1031401 = ~Th-thank you... but I wanted you to know that I... that I have feelings. For <CHARNAME>. I... didn't want you to get the wrong idea...~ []
@1031404 = ~Well, I'll not lie to you, my mourning dove... I had my eye set upon your gentle heart. But 'tis always a grand thing when two friends join in love.~ []
@1031405 = ~Ha ha! Oh, you rascal! It... it's nothing like that! But... but thank you for your understanding...~ []
@1031407 = ~I... I've been thinking about some of the things you've told me. I... I wanted you to know that I've come to a decision.~ [AERIEA4]
@1031408 = ~The first caravans from the East arrive in Riatavin, and the Merchant's Chosen buys up all the shipping contracts, cargo and goods! Everything!~ []
@1031410 = ~Not right now, Aerie... this isn't the best time.~ []
@1031412 = ~It'll be a cold day in the Nine Hells before I read from anything other than the clean book! Good business!~ []
@1031414 = ~Hear ye one and all! The mercantile families of Amn demand the Council declare war over the most grievous crime of all -- disruption of trade!~ []
@1031421 = ~Riatavin's purchase of caravan contracts has incurred the wrath of Amn's richest citizens. And upsetting the wealthy is none too wise!~ []
@1031422 = ~Riatavin has also moved the fiscal center south, away from greedy fingers and watchful eyes! Oh the plot she thickens by the minute!~ []
@1031423 = ~The sun rises today with fear in her eye! The Council has moved on Riatavin! Sellswords on the march by the hundreds! Carnage! Murder!~ []
@1031427 = ~Why is it always about Riatavin and trade gossip? I'd like to hear about something else for a change.~ []
@1031430 = ~Two rich families -- the shipwrighting Argrims and the gold mining Lurraxols -- hired every sellsword in the kingdom to lay siege to Riatavin!~ []
@1031431 = ~Reclaiming their trade route access is all that matters! A force of ten thousand lays in wait for the impending strike on Riatavin!~ []
@1031433 = ~I am determined to... to face this life on the ground, <CHARNAME>. My wings are gone and that can never be changed. I must learn to appreciate the beauty that I can still see.~ []
@1031434 = ~Hear ye! Dawn arrives with the sweet chime of profit! Good business! The Shadow Thieves have entered the Riatavin fray!~ []
@1031435 = ~And I... I hope that you will be here to teach me about it, <CHARNAME>. To show me how one can live on the ground and still... still be happy.~ []
@1031437 = ~I am mourning the loss of my fellow adventurers... it was a long and hard week to drag their bloody bodies back to the city.~ []
@1031439 = ~Stand away, fool... I am a warrior-born and I mourn my fallen. I shall not be disturbed.~ []
@1031442 = ~Again it's Riatavin, ten days in a row! How about other stories for once?~ []
@1031443 = ~Leave me be... go find my ubiquitous halfling companion if you wish to chat merrily with someone.~ []
@1031444 = ~Confusion must be your sole bedfellow, traveler. If you had a brain you'd have it on the ground playing with it. Good business!~ []
@1031445 = ~They were good friends... and mighty fighters. I shall miss them.~ []
@1031446 = ~There is a story about a clueless prat with a town crier's foot broken off in his arse. Step aside for those who'd hear the mouth that roars!~ []
@1031447 = ~Shadow Thief assassins failed in their attempt last eve to kill the rulers of Riatavin with poisoned food and special delivery scorpions!~ []
@1031449 = ~Seven sets of severed feet are found in Riatavin alleys, and martial law is imposed in the Gateway City!~ []
@1031459 = ~Other criers deliver banality and belly laughs at the cost of truth, but yours truly only speaks from the right book!~ []
@1031460 = ~I doubt it... we'll be lucky enough to stay alive with death waiting around every corner for us.~ []
@1031461 = ~It was nothing complicated, <CHARNAME>... but if you say it is a bad time, then I will have to believe you.
~ []
@1031462 = ~Local sellswords march to Eshpurta to join the wily General Craumerdaun in his charge against Riatavin.~ []
@1031463 = ~Garrisons will join up along the Eshpurta and Gem Roads. The Citadel already marches upon Riatavin. Woe to the Merchant's Chosen in the Gateway City!~ []
@1031467 = ~Yes, I know that our life has its risks... but I have a feeling that Baervan has had his hand in my path. We shall see what the gods have planned for us, I suppose.~ []
@1031470 = ~Our life is filled with uncertainty, that is true... but you could at least make the attempt, <CHARNAME>. Well... we shall see, I suppose, what the gods have in store for us.~ []
@1031474 = ~Yes, it was a great adventure... and a successful one, as well. I defeated my half-brother and stopped a war.~ []
@1031476 = ~Oh, I know it must sound strange to hear me say it... but if I'm going to face my life as it is, I want to experience everything that I can.~ []
@1031477 = ~I want to feel the thrill and fear of combat... to pit my magic against our foes. I want to be awed and terrified... to feel everything that my life has to offer me, good or bad.~ []
@1031480 = ~No... I am glad to see the change in you, in fact.~ []
@1031483 = ~I have lost much... as you have. But I am beginning to think that perhaps I might be able to gain something back, as well. I look forward to freeing myself from my doubts and fears.~ []
@1031484 = ~Many people speak reverentially of you. You have gained much... and I want to have that, as well. I want to shed my doubt and wring whatever I can out of the life I have.~ []
@1031485 = ~You always disregard what I am thinking, don't you? Obviously, I was mistaken about you. I'll just... keep to myself, if it's all the same to you.~ []
@1031486 = ~Dawn breaks as does news of the Sythillisians! Fort Ishla falls under a humanoid onslaught! No one is spared! An unparalleled tragedy!~ []
@1031487 = ~The Sythillisians? That doesn't sound good, crier.~ []
@1031491 = ~Pull my finger and you're guaranteed something special -- I had a feast of Maztican spiced noonmeats last eve! Now move aside!~ []
@1031492 = ~The Skullgnasher army of giants and the Spearbiter goblins laid waste to Fort Ishla! The monsters have set their sights on slaughter!~ []
@1031493 = ~Good... that makes me feel a little better. It is strange to be thrilled and yet shivering at the same time... I am free, and I am traveling... and I feel like I am flying.~ []
@1031494 = ~Thank you, <CHARNAME>... I am glad of it, as well. I... I am free... and traveling... and both excited and nervous at the same time. I almost feel as if I am flying again.~ []
@1031495 = ~The Small Teeth bred the filthy legions that took our outpost! No Amnian soldier escaped the massacre -- a thousand families fatherless!~ []
@1031499 = ~Just to Baldur's Gate and several other places along the Sword Coast up north... so far, at least.~ []
@1031500 = ~Not now, Aerie... this isn't a good time to talk.~ []
@1031501 = ~I have never been that far north... nor have I traveled anywhere outside of the circus. I have been told about some of the other places in the world where one can go, however...~ []
@1031502 = ~Hear ye! Sythillisians foreclose on Gambiton! The chatter of coins cannot stop the unholy onslaught of the humanoid war machine!~ []
@1031503 = ~Calimshan is supposed to be a great place of sand and silks, merchants of all kinds... there are supposed to be strange and exotic dancers and great, spiralling towers.~ []
@1031504 = ~The Moonshae Islands are supposed to have magnificent mountains and waterfalls... along with beaches of blue sand and ancient forests that time has barely touched.~ []
@1031508 = ~And... and the jungles of Chult! Towering trees and vines, exotic spices and flowers that smell of the sultry heat... rainstorms that last for days...~ []
@1031510 = ~I... I want to go to these places, <CHARNAME>! I want to voyage there and see their beauty for myself... I want to stand there and feel it... touch it with my hands.~ []
@1031511 = ~That sounds wonderful, Aerie... I wouldn't mind joining you someday.~ []
@1031512 = ~It's translated in the ancient tomes of yore as "Do us all a favor and shut the hell up."~ []
@1031515 = ~Gambiton is trampled flat,  its people have all fled screaming! The King's Arch is destroyed and no one can escape to Esmeltaran!~ []
@1031516 = ~I see. Alright, <CHARNAME>... I'll be quiet, if that's what you want.~ []
@1031517 = ~Heavy rains are pummeling the region out of season, thwarting Amnian efforts to reach the Hillfort Ishla and reckon the true caliber of damage!~ []
@1031518 = ~I would like that, <CHARNAME>... although, of course we must pay attention to surviving, first. Likely, we will face death many times... but it is pleasant to dream, isn't it?~ []
@1031519 = ~Oh, I know. I do not plan on running off to go to these places. I know we face death, here, and will many times. It is just... pleasant to dream, isn't it?~ []
@1031520 = ~And who are you to say it will never happen? I know I face death fighting by your side... and I am happy to do so... but I would like to dream of the future, as well.~ []
@1031521 = ~The only people who are rejoicing in Athkatla are the followers of Talos, thrilled with the destruction wrought from nature's blind, storming fury!~ []
@1031522 = ~I... I would have thought you capable of dreaming, <CHARNAME>. Not everything must be hard steel and stern decisions.~ []
@1031529 = ~Nothing, nothing at all. This wasn't meant for you then. Good day to you.~ []
@1031531 = ~No, no, that wouldn't be it. Do stop wasting my time, will you?~ []
@1031533 = ~What? Who are you? No matter. You'll be dealt with soon enough if you are crossing the Rune.~ []
@1031535 = ~I've been wondering... do you have any advice for me for combat?~ [AERIEA7]
@1031537 = ~Stay in the back and use your spells... that's the best help you can be.~ []
@1031542 = ~I know how you feel about my being strong, <CHARNAME>... and I want to fight well by your side. I... I don't want your foes, powerful as they are, to get the best of you.~ []
@1031543 = ~Well then, I trust you have the blood and the unfinished armor? You do fine work, but it requires my special touch to finish it off.~ []
@1031545 = ~I smell the scent of dragon blood, but I do not see the unfinished skin armor. Do not delay, bring both the blood and armor to me and I will make a suit of legend.~ []
@1031546 = ~Fine work takes time. You must give me the full four days before your armor is done. Leave me.~ []
@1031547 = ~I have completed the task, and your armor is done. Beautiful it is. Here, examine it in your own hands.~ []
@1031549 = ~Hear ye! Esmeltaran falls to the Sythillisians! Esmeltaran falls! Defenders of the city are crushed to pulp by the unstoppable force!~ []
@1031551 = ~I shall try to improve my skills with magic, over and above what my uncle Quayle was able to teach me. I suppose... I suppose that is the best way I can aid you.~ []
@1031553 = ~I know that you are determined to combat evil... and I wish to do so, as well. I don't want to be a burden... I want to be effective. I want to survive so that I can see the world.~ []
@1031556 = ~I think that's what I have been doing... I know I'll never be that good with weapons as some of your other companions are. If... if you need me to fight by your side, <CHARNAME>, I will do so... to the death, if need be.~ []
@1031557 = ~Well, stop drinking turpentine and get yourself an honest profession. Step away so that the citizenry can gain proxy to the truth spoken from the right book!~ []
@1031558 = ~None at all, <CHARNAME>? I... I don't want to be a burden to your group. I want to fight effectively by your side... and survive, so that I may travel the world with you.~ []
@1031559 = ~I... I know that it might be difficult to foresee what is to happen in the future... but do you have any plans? Once this is all over, I mean...~ [AERIEA8]
@1031562 = ~The Skullgnashers and Spearbiters descended upon Esmeltaran. In a matter of hours the city was overrun with giants and goblins! Picture that!~ []
@1031565 = ~I don't know... I was thinking of settling down somewhere...~ []
@1031569 = ~Well... do you see yourself traveling? Or settling down? Do you... do you see yourself with me?~ []
@1031571 = ~I would prefer to be with you, Aerie... if the gods are willing.~ []
@1031573 = ~You want to settle down? Here in Amn, perhaps? Do you... do you see me in that picture?~ []
@1031575 = ~Of course I see you... if you see yourself, that is.~ []
@1031576 = ~Nope... I don't see you there. Sorry.~ []
@1031577 = ~Yes... you have god's blood in you, I'm told. When you... when you travel, do you see me traveling beside you?~ []
@1031579 = ~I'd want you beside me... if you wanted to be there.~ []
@1031580 = ~Good business! It's a hot one here, but not as hot as the standing air down south! The Amnish army reaches Hillfort Keshla!~ []
@1031586 = ~Oh... don't you... don't you want to be with me? In the... future, I mean?~ []
@1031587 = ~Of course I do... if it's possible.~ []
@1031588 = ~Over half of Keshla's contingent has been assimilated into the big, bad band of bastards! Battle plans are drawn up, and Riatavin is ripe for an ass-kicking!~ []
@1031589 = ~There's no point in talking about it, Aerie. Nothing is sure in my life... and I have lost too many people to start forming new attachments.~ []
@1031591 = ~That's... that's good. I would like to be with you, if the gods will it. Th-thank you, <CHARNAME>... I just... I just wanted to be sure that you felt the same for me.~ []
@1031592 = ~Three days march separates our brave lads form liberating the agitators! Three days to certain doom for the firebrands with an axe to grind!~ []
@1031593 = ~I do... but I also want to be with you. I... think I want to be with you more. You are more exciting and thrilling than any wonder of the land that I could encounter, I think.~ []
@1031594 = ~But... that is... that is only if you want to be with me, too. Do you?~ []
@1031596 = ~There's no point in talking about it, Aerie. Nothing is sure in my life... and I have lost too many people to start forming new attachments.~ []
@1031597 = ~Well, no... not really.~ []
@1031598 = ~Heavens above she's a hot one this morn! Good business! Riders from the Amnian army reach Hillfort Torbold!~ []
@1031599 = ~Ah. So you end it with cruel finality. I... I suppose I should have expected that from you. I was... hoping for something more, <CHARNAME>. I suppose I shall look elsewhere...~ []
@1031600 = ~Continue, crier.~ []
@1031601 = ~How ironic... that you would push me to be strong, and yet be too frightened to attach yourself to someone. I... was hoping for more, I suppose I shall look elsewhere.~ []
@1031607 = ~My love...? I... I know that you are tired from the day's travels and that you wish to rest, but I... I wish to ask you something, before you retire to your blankets...~ [AERIEA9]
@1031608 = ~A third of Torbold's troops head east to join forces marching on Riatavin! Soon after they depart for Keshla, straggling wounded arrive from Esmeltaran!~ []
@1031609 = ~Olehm now bolsters morale and readies his troops and fort for full scale war!~ []
@1031613 = ~Here... come with me away from the eyes of the others. We will not be very far from them. I simply wish privacy.~ []
@1031614 = ~Now that we are alone... let me speak for a moment. You have led me to a tremendous discovery, <CHARNAME>... I have found that I do not need wings to fly.~ []
@1031615 = ~I... do not have much experience with love, <CHARNAME>. With your urging, I have become eager to experience many things... and now I wish to experience this.~ []
@1031616 = ~I... I will show you my body, <CHARNAME>... and I hope it pleases you. Would you... would you stay with me this night, <CHARNAME>? Will you show me what true love consists of?~ []
@1031619 = ~Er... I can't get past those huge lumps of scar tissue on your shoulders. I'm really not in the mood.~ []
@1031620 = ~Get lost, Aerie... I'm really not interested in being your tutor.~ []
@1031621 = ~Very well... what is it that you wish?~ []
@1031622 = ~Not now, Aerie... I'm too tired to discuss anything.~ []
@1031623 = ~Please, <CHARNAME>... the time is right and I must speak to you of this.~ []
@1031627 = ~I... I see my wishes have no bearing on your moods. As... as you wish. I will sleep by myself tonight and from here on. Good night, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1031630 = ~Poor roads can't deter the stalwart General Craumerdaun from marching to Esmeltaran! The hardy contingent changes its course from Riatavin to the occupied city!~ []
@1031632 = ~C-come close to me, then, <CHARNAME>. Let me feel your hands on my skin... let us lay together so I may experience your love and become a woman at last...~ []
@1031633 = ~I... don't know what love is, <CHARNAME>. But... maybe it would be better to wait until all of this is over. The thought of laying with a man frightens me a little, I must admit...~ []
@1031634 = ~Stay with me for the night, then, <CHARNAME>, and hold me to you. I... don't want to be alone, and I so desperately need to be near you...~ []
@1031635 = ~Hear ye! More news of the scurrilous Sythillisian's Empire! Horrors abound as the legions of evil march on Imnescar!~ []
@1031636 = ~As you wish... that I am more than willing to do.~ []
@1031637 = ~Forget it, Aerie... I'm not interested in someone who is so needy.~ []
@1031638 = ~Let's whack something eeeeevvvvillllll...~ [SSWORD10]
@1031645 = ~How about some other story?~ []
@1031679 = ~So you send me away with... with your cruel words. I... I thought I loved you... and yet you cut me open without hesitation. I... should have known better, I suppose.~ []
@1031680 = ~Very well, <CHARNAME>... I shall go and sleep by myself and console myself that it is better that I never allowed one such as you to touch me. I... shall not trouble you further.~ []
@1031685 = ~So... you are awake at last? I have been... watching you sleep for some time, now. It calms me, watching you... and it gave me time to think.~ [AERIEB1]
@1031686 = ~I've been... thinking about last night. You were right, of course... it isn't the right time to experience love when we are always in danger of perishing.~ []
@1031687 = ~I was so eager to experience everything new that I... did not think. Thank you for respecting me. I... I love you... and I want our first time together to be something special.~ []
@1031688 = ~I love you, too, Aerie... and I agree.~ []
@1031689 = ~Yes, well... let's just continue our travels, shall we?~ []
@1031691 = ~Let us go, then and find this Irenicus. Once this is over, I want to experience everything with you. I... I never thought I would find something... better than flying. Thank you.~ []
@1031692 = ~Of course, <CHARNAME>. Let's... finish your quest, and then we can see where we stand. And where we can go from there, yes?~ []
@1031693 = ~In... in case I die... or in case we part ways... I just wanted to tell you, <CHARNAME>, that I never thought I would find something better than flying. But I have... and thank you.~ []
@1031694 = ~I am? I had thought you had cared for me. But... perhaps you kept me away because... because you did not care enough for me. I had not thought of that.~ []
@1031695 = ~I am too quick to assume, <CHARNAME>... and I have much to learn. I wish you would have been gentler with me, but you have taught me much, and I thank you.~ []
@1031696 = ~Let us just... continue on your quest. I shall trouble you no further... and will look to further my experience elsewhere.~ []
@1031697 = ~So... you are awake at last? I have been... watching you sleep for some time, now. It calms me, watching you... and it gave me time to think.~ []
@1031698 = ~You... have made a woman out of me, <CHARNAME>. I love you more deeply than I can say and can only thank you for what you have done for me.~ []
@1031699 = ~But... at the same time... I cannot help but think that things need to be slowed. I am so full of emotion... I want to experience too much and am doing it all too quickly.~ []
@1031701 = ~My heart clenches at the thought, but we must stop ourselves from going down this path. I need to... to find out more about myself... before I can attach myself to another. I... hope you understand.~ []
@1031703 = ~I do... but maybe you need to find your own way, Aerie.~ []
@1031708 = ~The Most Noble Odor of Radiant Farts are pathetic.~ []
@1031712 = ~If... if that is what you think I should do... then perhaps I must. I... I shall miss you, <CHARNAME>. I shall always hold you dear in my heart.~ []
@1031716 = ~I think you will find the amount adequate. 10,500 gold is no small fortune, though I think you deserve a little more. From my personal armory, a sword.~ []
@1031720 = ~But, come... a new day awaits us, <CHARNAME>. Let us... let us see what it holds.~ []
@1031722 = ~One day we shall meet again, <CHARNAME>... and I... I hope that I will be ready to love you then. F-farewell...~ []
@1031723 = ~I... I am doing this because I must, <CHARNAME>. My life has never been my own... I am frightened by the unfamiliar and I am unfamiliar with most everything.~ []
@1031733 = ~I need to... find out more about myself, <CHARNAME>... I need to become familiar with and experience everything... but slowly. And with you it will never be slow.~ []
@1031737 = ~I... I do love you, <CHARNAME>, and I hope you understand. If you would find it too hard... if you want me to go now... I will understand.~ []
@1031739 = ~No... please stay, Aerie.~ []
@1031743 = ~Aerie, this... this bard can wait no longer for your thoughts to settle upon his heart. I... I must know now what you feel, my dove.~ [HAERDA76]
@1031744 = ~We'll go now and retrieve this Cup for you, although it hardly seems a test of our abilities.~ []
@1031745 = ~Oh, Haer'Dalis... I... I am not ready to...~ [AERIE83]
@1031748 = ~What do you say? Care to have your name placed above a young guild of Shadow Thieves?~ []
@1031749 = ~Without question. I will do my best to turn it into a prosperous guild.~ []
@1031762 = ~Why... that's sweet, Haer'Dalis. I'm... I'm honored.~ []
@1031765 = ~But I will know it, sweet Aerie, if you but declare your love for me. Allow me to salve your wounded heart, Aerie... allow me to caress your pale skin and show you that my love is true.~ []
@1031766 = ~I... I do love you, Haer'Dalis. You have swept me off my feet... and I can no longer deny it.~ []
@1031773 = ~It is nothing, Haer'Dalis. Just... just some errant thoughts.~ [AERIE84]
@1031775 = ~Tell me anyway, my love. Your poorest word is a sweet poem to this bard's ears... and I would not have you experience a moment of fluster, if there was aught I could do for it.~ []
@1031780 = ~Well... I was just wondering, Haer'Dalis... where do you see us in the future? You have spoken of plays and acting... have you been serious?~ []
@1031781 = ~Ah... the future. I see.~ []
@1031782 = ~Your love has given me new hope, my bard... I want to see what life has to offer, no matter my lack of wings. I... I want to travel, to see this world. Will you... be there with me?~ []
@1031784 = ~Time holds its own counsel, my love... and destiny plays such a game with this sparrow that even I cannot foresee the outcome.~ []
@1031787 = ~Live in the moment? I... I have always done that, Haer'Dalis. I want to live for the future, now... don't you?~ []
@1031789 = ~I could not, even if I cared to, my sweet dove. Here... let me sing to you...~ []
@1031791 = ~"When Man was made it was said
 he would have eyes in the front of his head.
 But the first Man was scared,
 as he saw before him, lay bared,
 the future... and in it, he was dead."~ []
@1031794 = ~Hmm. A limerick for every occasion, Haer'Dalis?~ []
@1031798 = ~Ah, my dove... I see you have finished perusing my latest play. Would you care to act out a scene or two?~ [HAERDA78]
@1031799 = ~Actually, Haer'Dalis... I have a question. All your plays... they seem to end in tragedy or destruction. They are all so... so dark. Have you no happy plays?~ [AERIE85]
@1031801 = ~I would like to offer you the opportunity to help the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart. Are you interested in hearing my proposal?~ [KAYLXX07]
@1031805 = ~That is a shame, truly, for we have no one else to turn to at this time. If you change your mind, please come back and speak with me.~ []
@1031827 = ~Ahh, my sweet Aerie. I write my plays as befits the creed of the Doomguard. All things end in destruction and tragedy... to think otherwise would be foolish.~ []
@1031829 = ~Foolish? You... you can't honestly think that. Is there no room for hope in your world?~ []
@1031830 = ~Even hope is eroded, my dove. All things break down, over time... all things come to an end. 'Tis the natural order of the multiverse. Who am I to question this?~ []
@1031833 = ~But... but you can't embrace destruction... you have to fight against it, don't you?~ []
@1031834 = ~On the contrary, one must assist the multiverse in attaining its goal. One day, all things will cease to exist... this is the way it shall be. The Doomguard stands to assist this goal.~ []
@1031835 = ~But why would you... why would you even build a home or... or fall in love... if you thought that way? If all things decay, why start anything?~ []
@1031839 = ~A brief and...? No... no! Love should be enduring! It embodies hope and strength... are you saying that you expect it to end?~ []
@1031842 = ~Of course I do. Ah, but I see I have upset you, my dove. Let me reassure you that the multiverse shall not end in my lifetime... at least I do not expect it to.~ []
@1031843 = ~And while I know that our love must end, I do not expect it to do so soon. The Fates will decide, and until then I shall love you truly and with all the heart I can muster.~ []
@1031846 = ~No... no, I... I just want to know that you'll love me... and that you'll be there for me... that is all.~ []
@1031849 = ~I... I guess that'll have to be enough. For now.~ []
@1031853 = %Dradeel's Recipe:

MONKEY BALLS (makes ~40)
A) 1/2 c.   peanut butter
     1/3 c.   honey
     1/2 c.   granola
     1/2 c.   crushed 'cheery' cereal
     dash      nutmeg
     dash      cinnamon
     1/2 c.   oatmeal

B) 1 c.      sugar
     1/4 c.   cocoa
     1/4 c.   butter
     1/4 c.   milk
     1/4 tsp. vanilla

INSTRUCTIONS:
    Mix ingredients in (A), except oatmeal. Roll into small balls about
the diameter of a coin. Coat balls in oatmeal.
    Boil ingredients in (B) together for 3-1/2 to 4 minutes. Take from
heat. Dip balls in chocolate using spoon or toothpick. Chill and
serve.

    Monkey balls are to be served with the following poem on prominent
display:
"Monkey Balls"
These sweet and gracious monkey balls,
Served on plates and sold from stalls,
Bring madness to these hallowed halls
Of urban academe.

Huzzaks for chocolate monkey balls!
We'll eat them 'til the ceiling falls,
'Til Time, herself, tears down these walls
Of urban academe.

So buy yourself a monkey ball,
Savour it and then stand tall,
A bulwark 'gainst the deaf'ning call
Of urban academe.
                    -by Ergo the organ-grinder% []
@1031865 = ~The Vampiricus Omnibus: Unabridged
Ending the Plague of Teeth

This tome is quite ancient, and you do not recognize the tongue in which it is written. Fortunately, Bodhi has scrawled a translation of selected passages in the margins, as well as further questions she apparently wished to ask on the subject.

Stuat tuo Gotha: 
The resolution:
With the witch at the fore, long previous to her treachery, we did stride the hills of Umar seeking comfort in our hour of need. The time had come for the living to mourn no more, and the blades that were fettered by sentiment were cut free, and it was decided that we would speak for our lives with the sinews of our sword arms. The honored dead that did take flight in the darkness of shadow would no more receive sorrow from those of us that had lost their friends and relatives to the plague of teeth. 

Mornat de'pas Golvana Fathorn:
Battles when came the dead:
There came we, the army of light, armed with faith and conviction, and we did march unto the tombs of the restless dead during hours of day. With wooden edge we struck down master and slave, though many paid for each thrust with their lives. In the fallen there was the danger of a scourge anew, and many of the newly infected seemed doomed to walk again with dire purpose. 

Aegato Davon:
The plea:
"No more" cried we! No more would we lose to the plague. These new fallen could not be abandoned. We had fought for our lives and theirs, and they would not be taken. To the Temple we went, to the god of Sun and Light. Amaunator would save them. Amaunator, whose touch turns shadows to fire. In the arms of the Sun god were the infected placed, and the hearts of their dark masters were laid there with them. Blood did burn, and the dead returned, but not as undead or unliving, but alive and freed from taint. Many did walk the light side home, when last the plague did fall.

Relevance of archaic worship of Amaunator?
Origin of vampiric plague?
Any link to a modern cure to be worried of?
Historical document or historical fiction?

A final note is scribbled...

*Interrogate Oghma monk at Docks district temple about further information. He should be able to provide more information on reversing vampirism*~ []
@1031867 = ~No you are not, but what does that matter? Mae'Var was ideal, and yet he conspired to ruin everything. You are inexperienced, but I can at least trust you.~ []
@1031868 = ~I give up... I can't go on... there's no point... I must die~ []
@1031873 = ~Excellent, I look forward to seeing what you can do. Return to Mae'Var's vacant office. I will have it seeded with a few promising young thieves.~
@1031876 = ~This is the ornate coffin of the vampire Dace. Strange markings on the side, upon closer inspection, turn out to be the word 'Madness' etched over and over again, covering the coffin.~ []
@1031884 = ~Aerie, my dove... are you well?~ [HAERDA79]
@1031885 = ~I've just... I've just been thinking. About all this death, all these... horrifying things Irenicus has done. He actually stole a soul and... and all these people died for nothing...~ [AERIE86]
@1031886 = ~And for what? Some 'vengeance' that Irenicus wants! For that he throws people aside like mere objects?! I... I cannot believe that such evil is allowed to exist!~ []
@1031887 = ~Haer'Dalis! We must scour the face of Faerun of such foulness! The very stink of it clogs my every breath! No mercy! No mercy must be shown to such evil!!~ []
@1031888 = ~And you, <CHARNAME>... I now see much of the same mark of evil in you. I will watch you carefully. You have earned my respect, but I will not tolerate the callousness I see in you any longer.~ []
@1031889 = ~False friend! I am loath to think that I have lent my hand to your cause. I shall go to my father without you! Pray that our paths do not cross again!~ [ANOMENC5]
@1031893 = ~I am not here to destroy, Haer'Dalis! I want to stop Irenicus! I wish to fight against evil that exists in this world!~ []
@1031894 = ~I will not sit idly by and be pathetic! I have paid too much attention to my own sorrows and experiences... and not enough to the evil that has surrounded me!~ []
@1031895 = ~Speak as you will, my love, but you serve entropy, nevertheless. Your innocence has faded, as it should, and you have become a maiden who shall bring the end of others... my philosophy proven!~ []
@1031896 = ~I don't care a whit for your philosophy, Haer'Dalis! I am so full of anger that I cannot control it... and this callous evil that I see, it will pay!~ []
@1031897 = ~As I said, my dove... and pleased I am to see it.~ []
@1031899 = ~Again, a natural end that has come... no less than expected, though I'll mourn its passing.~ []
@1031900 = ~So be it! Come, then, <CHARNAME>... let us go and complete your quest. I shall fight by your side until this is over... and then I shall make my own way in the world for once.~ []
@1031901 = ~ No effect? I need bigger sword!~ [MINSC38]
@1031909 = ~Golders is it? Will 10 gp be enough for you?~ []
@1031911 = ~The heat's gone to yer steel-clad brains, then. Take yer madness elsewhere... we've enough to worry about with all these murders an' like business.~ []
@1031918 = ~His daughter was a tom-fool tin-head adventurin' type just like you... died young just this past season. You still with me? Good, then I won't have t' repeat meself.~ []
@1031919 = ~Not long after she died, a bunch of other tin-heads came lookin' for her, said she had somethin' of theirs.~ []
@1031920 = ~Heh, ol' Hendrick just took 'em outside an' pointed to her grave marker and told 'em to get the hell off his land 'cause they had somethin' of his, too...~ []
@1031936 = ~Heh, you again, is it? Begone, tin-head... I've more important things t' worry about.~ []
@1031950 = ~Why, that's Jeb's place. Nothing good ever came of that scoundrel. Not since his wife died, at any rate.~ []
@1031963 = ~A druid must be level 14 to be able to challenge for the leadership of a druid grove. Only a player character will be offered leadership.~ []
@1031970 = ~'Ere then, move along now. This place ain't open to simple gawking. Don't make me says it more than once.~ []
@1031976 = ~Errm... calm down, everyone, please. I assure you that everything that can be done is being done...~ [MINIST08]
@1031979 = ~Well... they haven't come back yet, no...~ []
@1031982 = ~Now, now, people... come, this is no time to panic...~ []
@1031983 = ~Please... listen to my husband!~ []
@1031984 = ~(ahem)  Yes... well... we are looking for another group of adventurers, here, to handle the situation...~ []
@1031990 = ~People, please! We must first find out what happened to our ranger, Merella... and then track down the source of these murders. More adventurers will come soon.~ []
@1031992 = ~Aye! Ye better be doin' something, mayor... or we need t' be fleein' our homes soon.~ []
@1031993 = ~Ye best be doin' something, mayor... or we need t' be fleein' to the city for our safety!~ []
@1031994 = ~Errrm... hello? I don't recognize you... you must be new to Imnesvale. Is there something I can help you with?~ [MINIST02]
@1031995 = ~Actually, I spoke to a boy by the name of Delon in Athkatla... he said you were in need of assistance.~ []
@1031996 = ~I saw your speech outside of the village... you in need of an adventurer?~ []
@1031999 = ~You did? Then the boy did get to the city after all. Ah, I am pleased to hear it! You... you have come to our aid, then, yes?~ []
@1032002 = ~Investigate the deaths in the Umar Hills.

The Mayor has thanked me for eliminating the ogre and his band, and has asked that I rest in the village... or at least return in seven hours or so, as he must travel to obtain my reward.~ []
@1032009 = ~Oh, stranger... my little Imnesvale is in dire straits. We are dying quickly, and yet we cannot leave. You look like a hearty sort... will you aid us?~ []
@1032027 = ~Ah, I see. Well, do be careful, stranger... the killings have made Imnesvale a very inhospitable place, indeed.~ []
@1032029 = ~Herrrm... yes, of course. It's a gruesome business. I'm sure that little Delon told you some of the story, but I should elaborate on it for your benefit.~ []
@1032030 = ~I's been keeping up of <CHARNAME>'s friends, so's I knows you are okay. In you go, if you like.~ []
@1032032 = ~We've had a run of... killings and disappearances here, as of late. People murdered in their beds... their bodies disappearing... bodies found with the skins inside out.~ [MINIST06]
@1032038 = ~I'll keep that in mind.~ []
@1032040 = ~Anything you need? Anything at all, you just ask.~ []
@1032044 = ~Sorry, but I can't afford to buy anything, and all my stock is being shipped to the main guild office. Can't fund a fence if the guild branch has collapsed.~ []
@1032045 = ~Everyone's frightened... but they're scared to leave, as well, lest they get caught out in the wilderness by whatever has been doing the killing.~ []
@1032048 = ~Welcome to the guild. I haven't heard much about you, but if Renal says you're alright, I'll take his word on it.~ [JARIEL02]
@1032049 = ~It's the ogres, my husband... you know it is.~ []
@1032050 = ~Errrrm... my wife, Eina. And, yes... many people think it's that group of ogres who moved into the area just before the killings began. Likely is, too.~ []
@1032052 = ~And still others claim Umar, herself... the great witch of the hills... has returned. Legend has it she was responsible for deaths much like these ones.~ []
@1032053 = ~They're in the hills... too close to the village, I say!~ []
@1032055 = ~Yes... true. I suppose I should warn you... I've already hired the famous knight, Mazzy Fentan, and her troupe... but they haven't been back.~ []
@1032057 = ~To be honest, I think you should check on the ogres and their fellows before chasing after legends and such. So... will you... will you help us?~ []
@1032061 = ~No... I don't think I'm interested.~ []
@1032062 = ~Herrrm... well, my village is in dire need. I'll tell you what... if you end the murders, I will give you the armor that belonged to our first ranger protector.~ []
@1032067 = ~Let's not have an antagonistic relationship, <CHARNAME>. I am your lieutenant, and I will need to be able to trust you.~ []
@1032074 = ~Well, you have a stable of several thieves here, which I will introduce to you. Each has a specialty, and each has more thieves under them.~ []
@1032080 = ~Renal 'the Bloodscalp' runs the Shadow Thieves in the city... and he is the leader of numerous guildmasters that ply their dark trade throughout Athkatla.~ []
@1032081 = ~Very well... I will make the attempt.~ []
@1032086 = ~You cannot use a party required transition while someone is in a store.~ []
@1032105 = ~But... but you have come all this way, my <LADYLORD>... are you sure you will not reconsider?~ []
@1032110 = ~(sigh)  That is too bad, my <LADYLORD>. Do be careful around these parts, then... I wouldn't want more victims claimed in these strange killings.~ []
@1032112 = ~You can continue with all your thieves in prison, but you will get no profit. No use getting mad at me... if I die, the guild fails. I have Renal's ear, you see.~ []
@1032115 = ~Now, would you like to discuss the patterns your thieves will assume this week? They are operating at a low level of risk right now, just covering the quota.~ []
