 Beast Master~ []
@1032197 = ~Errrm... ah! It is Mazzy Fentan, our adventurer knight returned to us! But... these other folk with you... I do not recognize them...~ []
@1032200 = ~It is, mayor. The Shade Lord will bother you no more. It had possessed the body of Merella, your ranger... who died once the shade was destroyed.~ []
@1032201 = ~It seems the Shade possessed your ranger and committed his evil acts from her body. My own companions are dead... and Merella was killed with the Shade, sadly.~ []
@1032203 = ~It is not destroyed yet, mayor, but <CHARNAME> assures me that we shall. I trust <PRO_HIMHER>... were it not for <PRO_HISHER> timely intervention, I would surely be dead.~ []
@1032210 = ~No... I have no interest in returning to that Shade Lord's cave.~ []
@1032211 = ~Oh... I see...~ []
@1032215 = ~Very well... I shall make the attempt.~ []
@1032216 = ~Forget it... I've no interest in the task.~ []
@1032218 = ~Eh? <CHARNAME>... you have returned... and I see you have brought with you our lost adventurer knight!~ []
@1032224 = ~Ah... my <LADYLORD>! You have returned... I take it that the dreadful shade creature has been dispatched? Is my village now safe?~ []
@1032226 = ~Not... not yet? Then... why have you returned? Is there aught amiss?~ []
@1032229 = ~Oh... that is a relief. Please... I beg of you! Destroy this creature as soon as you can!~ []
@1032230 = ~Oh... I see...~ []
@1032231 = ~I... I am greatly disappointed. If... if you change your mind, please do tell me, yes? Imnesvale... we don't have much time, I think.~ []
@1032232 = ~Yes, my <LADYLORD>? Is there... is there something you need?~ []
@1032245 = ~I believe the wolves... or wolf-like creatures... are responsible for your problem.~ []
@1032247 = ~You mentioned being in need of adventurers when we last spoke... are you still?~ []
@1032249 = ~That is most excellent news. That group has frightened the village for too long... I have no doubt they are responsible for everything that has happened.~ []
@1032250 = ~Thank you, my <LADYLORD>. I... I must go and acquire your reward. I will not be back for a few hours. You could rest at the inn,  or come back later for it.~ []
@1032252 = ~I would prefer to have it now... I don't like waiting.~ []
@1032254 = ~I apologize for the delay. I will be back in about seven hours or so with your reward... come and see me then, my <LADYLORD>.~ []
@1032255 = ~I... I am afraid I do not have any reward here for you, my <LADYLORD>. I do not keep such valuables where... where others can get at them...~ []
@1032256 = ~Oh... well, I will be back in about seven hours or so with your reward. Errrm... anytime after that will be fine, as it pleases you.~ []
@1032257 = ~Wh-what? But... but I was sure that those monsters were the killers! What makes you so certain that they are not?~ []
@1032259 = ~Madulf has had his own people going missing... much the same as yours. He is as worried as you are.~ []
@1032262 = ~Ohhh... that isn't good news at all. If ogres can be worried, what should we be?~ []
@1032263 = ~Actually, Madulf sent me with a proposition... he and his people will provide protection for the village in exchange for peaceful relations and a bit of trade.~ []
@1032270 = ~He... he has? I... I must say... that might not be such a bad idea. If this ogre can be... can be trusted, that is.~ []
@1032271 = ~Thank you for bringing this to my attention, my <LADYLORD>. I will have to... go and talk to them, I suppose. We could both benefit from this.~ []
@1032273 = ~Since... since the ogres are no longer a possibility, all I can suggest is you go to Merella's cabin. There must be some evidence of what happened to her!~ []
@1032275 = ~If... if that is the case, my <LADYLORD>, then I beg you to go and destroy these wolves! They cannot be allowed to continue their carnage!~ []
@1032278 = ~I'm well prepared. Perhaps I can solve this mystery.~ []
@1032280 = ~Please... you... you agreed to help my village and I ask that you not abandon us now!~ []
@1032282 = ~Ah... er... there is a problem, my <LADYLORD>. You... you said that you had killed the ogre and his band quite some time ago, yes?~ []
@1032284 = ~Well... it seems that only a few hours ago, one of the more distant farm families in Imnesvale was attacked and... and killed. It was just like all the others.~ []
@1032285 = ~What... what terrible news! The ogre and his band could not have been doing the killing, after all...~ []
@1032286 = ~Greetings to you once again, <GABBER>! Do not think that Imnesvale has forgotten the fact that you have saved us from doom... and possibly worse!~ []
@1032287 = ~You should know that Madulf has agreed to protect the town... and the merchants are pleased to provide him with food and other sorts...~ []
@1032290 = ~He... he has? I... I must say... that might not be such a bad idea. If this ogre can be... can be trusted, that is.~ []
@1032293 = ~Very well... you are welcome to stay in Imnesvale as long as you like, however.~ []
@1032311 = ~I'll tell ye what is going on, me <LADYLORD>... the wolves that have been in the hills these past years are coming at us, they are!~ []
@1032312 = ~Fer weeks, now, they've been preyin' on us... sneakin' into the village at night and tearin' people apart. Then their bodies disappear the next night.~ []
@1032313 = ~The first of your thieves is Hanz. He specializes in house breaking and safe cracking. Nobles are a favorite target of his.~ []
@1032314 = ~'Tis a gruesome sight t' be sure. I've seen 'em, too... them wolves look at me from afar with smarts in their eyes. 'Tis the truth!~ []
@1032318 = ~Name's Groos. Came into the village with some of the other herders after some of us started being slaughtered... or just plain disappeared. Herders, farmers... anyone in the outlying lands.~ []
@1032320 = ~The rest of the village is full o' fools! Them ogres... I seen 'em and they ain't so bad. And the Umar stuff is nothin' but a load o' nonsense!~ []
@1032326 = ~I be Nelleck... one of the Imnesvale guards, is all. Wish I could go and do more against 'em wolves, but I can't leave the village alone, true enough.~ []
@1032333 = ~Bloody mayor hired a halfling runt and her troupe to find out what's been happenin'. They haven't come back... wolves ripped 'em apart is my guess.~ []
@1032336 = ~Alright. How high of a quota should be set for him? This will of course mean burgling more or less houses, so there may be increased risk to him.~ []
@1032345 = ~Led by a big ogre fellow... Madulf,  I think. Wants to be left alone. Fact that he'd talk first rather than kill ye makes him not th' worst sort in my books.~ []
@1032347 = ~They used t' belong to that big rebel army down in the south o' Amn... deserters likely. Seen 'em on my patrols... don't look like they're up to anythin'.~ []
@1032358 = ~Yer a mighty respectable sort, I suppose. I'd've thought it was them wolves causin' the problem... good to know they're gone, too, though.~ []
@1032359 = ~I hears that you set up them ogres to help protect us, too. I could surely use th' help... an' the merchants are cacklin' like hens at the extra business.~ []
@1032368 = ~They've brought in most of the outlyin' farmers and herders... no one's safe if they're alone for a minute. And even here ye ain't safe!~ []
@1032369 = ~Me an' Johanna have been tryin' the best we can... fool son Dirbert is jus' goin' to get himself into trouble with no work to do, though.~ []
@1032371 = ~Ay, now... aren't ye the wee halfling lass that the mayor hired? What happened to all yer other fellas?~ []
@1032374 = ~Dead, good sir. An ignoble death, as well... I hope you appreciate that they died in an effort to bring your safety.~ []
@1032385 = ~Now... if I could only find me fool son Dirbert. Some fool bought the boy a sword an' off he ran like a yardape.~ []
@1032387 = ~Now... if I could only find me son Dirbert. Damn fool somehow got 'hold of ale and is likely off turning some outhouse into a vomitorium. Ah, well...~ []
@1032392 = ~Now... If I could only find me son, Dirbert. Damn fool got 'hold of a sword and some ale. Ran off t' be a bloody adventurer. Watch, now, he'll be hacked t' pieces by a kobold, no less.~ []
@1032397 = ~Try for the better targets.~ []
@1032399 = ~Try for the homes of nobles.~ []
@1032401 = ~I beg of you, my <LADYLORD>... please help us! Find out what is killing everyone and put an end to it!~ []
@1032403 = ~I suppose the peace with those ogres is... is good, as well. I don't know what I will do if I see one of them come to the village, however. They are so frightening!~ []
@1032406 = ~Hanz is unfortunately dead. There is nothing that can be done for him.~ []
@1032417 = ~Your current instructions should pose very little difficulty for him. I'll wager he would even like more of a challenge.~ []
@1032418 = ~Your current instructions should pose very little difficulty for him. I'll wager he would even like more of a challenge.~ []
@1032419 = ~He will not likely appreciate such risky directions, but he will obey them as you command. I'm sure he will prevail against the odds.~ []
@1032420 = ~He will not likely appreciate such risky directions, but he will obey them as you command. I'm sure he will prevail against the odds.~ []
@1032421 = ~He is not likely to be too troubled by your directions. Fairly low difficulty for a housebreaker of his skill. I'm sure he will prove quite profitable.~ []
@1032429 = ~Invisibility 10' Radius
(Illusion/Phantasm) 
Level: 3
Range: 0
Duration: Special 
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: 10' radius
Saving Throw: None 

When cast, this spell causes all creatures within a 10 foot radius of the caster to vanish from sight and be undetectable by normal vision or even infravision. The spell remains in effect until it is magically broken or dispelled, until the wizard or recipient performs any action which cancels it, or until 24 hours have passed. The invisible being(s) cannot open doors, talk, or attack without immediately becoming visible, although the invisibility does enable them to attack first.~ []
@1032440 = ~How selective should he be in his clientele? It takes quite some time to make sure a job is on the level. More time to research will mean less profit.~ []
@1032442 = ~He should be very selective. I don't want him taking undue risk.~ []
@1032444 = ~He should take his time on the target.~ []
@1032455 = ~Exterminations are the way to go. They will pay better because of the risk.~ []
@1032457 = ~No, I don't want him to waste his talents. Have him seek out... pest removal jobs.~ []
@1032461 = ~Very well. I will inform Goshan of your instructions.~ []
@1032462 = ~Very well. I will inform Goshan of your instructions.~ []
@1032463 = ~Very well. I will inform Goshan of your instructions.~ []
@1032464 = ~Very well. I will inform Goshan of your instructions.~ []
@1032472 = ~No, he can rest for a few days.~ []
@1032474 = ~There is a small amount of risk in the task ahead, but bad luck can always strike. I will wish him well in his duties, and we shall see how he fares.~ []
@1032475 = ~There is a small amount of risk in the task ahead, but bad luck can always strike. I will wish him well in his duties, and we shall see how he fares.~ []
@1032478 = ~This should be a fairly easy series of tasks for Goshan. We shall see though. Things have gone wrong before.~ []
@1032479 = ~This should be a fairly easy series of tasks for Goshan. We shall see though. Things have gone wrong before.~ []
@1032480 = ~This is a reasonably difficult series of instructions for Goshan, but I'm sure it will all work out in the end.~ []
@1032481 = ~This is a reasonably difficult series of instructions for Goshan, but I'm sure it will all work out in the end.~ []
@1032482 = ~The next of your guild thieves is Kretor. He has a stable of pickpockets below him, and he makes sure that the purses of pedestrians are none too safe.~ []
@1032492 = ~Very well. One last thing; Should he bribe the owners of the establishments he works out of. It is always good if the witnesses are sympathetic to the accused.~ []
@1032501 = ~Go straight for the rich areas. I don't want peasant money.~ []
@1032502 = ~Stay amongst the revelling crowds. They will not notice a thief as easily.~ []
@1032519 = ~I will effect his release then. Do you wish to assign him duties now, or will you wait?~ []
@1032522 = ~He will have to wait.~ []
@1032526 = ~The guidelines you have set mean an easy time for Kretor, though it is never certain how things will come to an end.~ []
@1032527 = ~The guidelines you have set mean an easy time for Kretor, though it is never certain how things will come to an end.~ []
@1032528 = ~Your tasks mean a rough few days ahead for Kretor. I'm sure he can manage, but it will be difficult.~ []
@1032529 = ~Your tasks mean a rough few days ahead for Kretor. I'm sure he can manage, but it will be difficult.~ []
@1032530 = ~Things should go well. What you have outlined is not too difficult. We shall see though.~ []
@1032531 = ~Things should go well. What you have outlined is not too difficult. We shall see though.~ []
@1032532 = ~The next few days may be a little difficult with what you have ordered. I'm sure it will turn out for the best though.~ []
@1032533 = ~The next few days may be a little difficult with what you have ordered. I'm sure it will turn out for the best though.~ []
@1032544 = ~Very well. Morsa prefers to bring in small amounts of items for individuals, as they are harder to detect. But she can bring in large shipments for guilds.~ []
@1032547 = ~Now to contents. She prefers benign substances, but she can get dangerous spell components for mages. These are harder to transport, but they pay higher.~ []
@1032548 = ~She tries to stick to jewels and the like, but she can also bring in dangerous goods for mages and other deviants.~ []
@1032565 = ~I will inform Morsa of your decisions.~ []
@1032566 = ~I will inform Morsa of your decisions.~ []
@1032567 = ~I will inform Morsa of your decisions.~ []
@1032568 = ~I will inform Morsa of your decisions.~ []
@1032570 = ~Morsa is dead. It is a great loss, and there is nothing to be done about it.~ []
@1032576 = ~She will have to wait.~ []
@1032580 = ~The conditions you have set will be extremely dangerous for Morsa. I'm sure she can handle it, but I'll wager it will be difficult.~ []
@1032581 = ~The conditions you have set will be extremely dangerous for Morsa. I'm sure she can handle it, but I'll wager it will be difficult.~ []
@1032586 = ~You have one more rogue. Varia's preferred activity is providing 'protection,' and keeping embarrassing facts about powerful people safe... for a fee.~ []
@1032587 = ~I don't see what all the fuss is about. 'Tis the ogres who have been killing everyone... that's what monsters do!~ []
@1032588 = ~You look like the decent sort who can hold a sword... why don't you go and slaughter those ogres and save us all a lot of trouble?~ []
@1032594 = ~Haha! You are of course joking with me. You know full well that your guild quota must be paid to Renal, lest he take your charter from you.~ []
@1032601 = ~I'll just have her stay as she is. She knows her business, I am sure.~ []
@1032603 = ~My... my poor drunken baby is leading a pair of other boys around the countryside... and he's armed! Oh, how did this happen? I'm so worried... those ogres are going to eat him, I just know it!~ []
@1032604 = ~You... I remember you. You're the ranger who came to buy some food before you went out into the hills, didn't you? Are... are you replacing Merella?~ []
@1032606 = ~Nay, my lady. I'd happily settle in your hamlet and be your ranger, but I doubt that it will be my destiny.~ []
@1032612 = ~Ah! A good day to you, <SIRMAAM>... it is nice to see a new face in the village, for once. We haven't had many travelers through here since all these killings began, naturally.~ []
@1032615 = ~People don't need to get hurt in these deals.~ []
@1032617 = ~I'd be pleased to show you some of the goods I have to sell, although I must warn you... our mercantile company hasn't had much opportunity to deliver lately, so goods are spare.~ []
@1032622 = ~Ah! Now that's a tale and a half. Mind you... don't listen to the dribble these villagers might tell you... they'd have you half-believing that a five-hundred-year-old witch is on the prowl.~ []
@1032640 = ~Always willing to satisfy a customer... with gold, that is.~ []
@1032642 = ~Well... some people still think the problem can be solved. I hear the mayor hired a band of adventurers to look into it, but they've disappeared.~ []
@1032643 = ~I will inform Varia of your directions.~ []
@1032644 = ~I will inform Varia of your directions.~ []
@1032645 = ~I will inform Varia of your directions.~ []
@1032646 = ~I will inform Varia of your directions.~ []
@1032647 = ~No one wants to travel alone, but if something isn't done soon, they might decide to all leave together. 'Tis a shame... this is a prosperous village otherwise. Good business, usually.~ []
@1032651 = ~Varia is dead. There is nothing to do but move on.~ []
@1032654 = ~Good to see you again, <SIRMAAM>. Since you saved this village, things have returned to normal, which is a mighty good thing. I'm grateful, for one... as is my company.~ []
@1032657 = ~Especially considering the fact that I know you engineered that deal with Madulf and his fellows. Never would o' thought to sell goods to an ogre, but there it is... and he's a fair bargainer, too.~ []
@1032661 = ~Yes, please... let me see what you have in stock.~ []
@1032671 = ~She should find these conditions relatively easy to meet. I am sure everything will turn out for the best.~ []
@1032672 = ~She should find these conditions relatively easy to meet. I am sure everything will turn out for the best.~ []
@1032673 = ~This will be a relatively difficult set of circumstances for her to overcome. I'm sure she'll be up to the task though.~ []
@1032674 = ~This will be a relatively difficult set of circumstances for her to overcome. I'm sure she'll be up to the task though.~ []
@1032684 = ~Bah! Get out of my face, you moronic <RACE>... I could care less for yer wounded feelings.~ []
@1032687 = ~I have nothing to report on the status of your rogues just yet. We must wait until 5 days has elapsed.~ []
@1032689 = ~(sigh)  I just know that one of these days, one of those ogres is going to come down and massacre me, just like those other villagers. I... I never thought of something like this when I became a merchant!~ []
@1032695 = ~Hanz has returned with a nice profit. His task was dangerous, but his skill has brought him through unscathed.~ []
@1032698 = ~Very well, I will have him released as soon as possible. You will have to reassign him his tasks when I am done reporting on the others.~ []
@1032700 = ~Oh, I suppose so... but there isn't much. Caravans just won't come here unless they're stocked with guards... and that doesn't make it very profitable, now, does it?~ []
@1032701 = ~Ohhh, it's a terrible thing, isn't it? People dying left and right... you can hardly find a customer anymore, and that's probably okay because nobody will restock me, now, anyway.~ []
@1032706 = ~Somebody should do something about those ogres, though. Ever since they came, it all started. One of my caravans once got attacked by ogres... they're evil and brutal!~ []
@1032708 = ~Let's check on how Goshan did under your instruction.~ []
@1032711 = ~Al-alright... just... just be careful of those hungry ogres!~ []
@1032712 = ~I... I can't tell you how relieved I am that you've stopped all the killings! I was sure I was a goner! Maybe now people will start coming back to the village.~ []
@1032713 = ~And... and I met my first ogre face-to-face. He... he wanted to buy some apples that I had shipped up from my orchard outside Athkatla. I was sure he was going to eat me, instead, but he didn't.~ []
@1032714 = ~Well, anyway... did you wish to buy something?~ []
@1032722 = ~Goshan has survived all you have put before him and returned with a tidy sum, though I am sure he is not grateful for the risk of his tasks.~ []
@1032724 = ~Very well, I will have him released as soon as possible. You will have to reassign him his tasks when I am done reporting on the others.~ []
@1032725 = ~Then Goshan will stay locked up until you say and pay otherwise.~ []
@1032733 = ~Well, me name's Dale... I do some herdin' out in the fields with the cows and such with me wife, here, and me kids. Came into the village... just ain't safe anymore out there.~ []
@1032735 = ~I knows two other herders who vanished. An' the farmers ain't safe, neither. Farmer Jacob an' his wife were both slaughtered... and then their bodies disappeared. Turrible things, all.~ []
@1032741 = ~Kretor has proven quite resourceful. Your conditions were difficult, but he has met them and returned with a fair amount of gold.~ []
@1032744 = ~Very well, I will have him released as soon as possible. You will have to reassign him his tasks when I am done reporting on the others.~ []
@1032745 = ~Kretor will rot with the other guttertrash in a pauper's prison until you say otherwise.~ []
@1032746 = ~Kretor has been killed. Nothing more to be said about it.~ []
@1032749 = ~People gets hysterical, they does. Groos, there, babbles on about that witch... and me daughter, Kaatje, is no better with her stories. Ye should hear her, heh.~ []
@1032750 = ~It's the ogres... and they'll come an' finish us all off once 'ey've picked us clean to small enough numbers. We should be fleein' as soon as we can, true enough.~ []
@1032751 = ~You just watch yerself around here... them ogres'll be the death of us all, they will.~ []
@1032757 = ~I think I remember someone mentionin' an old cabin in the hills not far from here, but I don't know anythin' more about it. Ask Groos, maybe... he goes that way more'n I do.~ []
@1032760 = ~Morsa kept her activities to a minimum, transporting only small amounts of contraband. Her return is accordingly small.~ []
@1032762 = ~Morsa responded well to this level of challenge, and has returned with a tidy sum of gold. It was risky, but she came through just fine in the end.~ []
@1032765 = ~Very well, I will have her released before the day is out. You will have to reassign her tasks to her when I am done reporting on the others.~ []
@1032766 = ~Then she will stay locked up until you can put up the gold.~ []
@1032770 = ~Err... hullo. Don't meet a lot o' strangers around here. 'Specially as o' late.~ []
@1032781 = ~Varia has been taken prisoner by the guards. They do not approve of her blackmail tactics, and it will cost a 300 gold bribe to get her out.~ []
@1032783 = ~Then Varia will languish in prison until she is freed.~ []
@1032784 = ~Varia is no longer alive. It is a great loss.~ []
@1032786 = ~Now then, that's all of them. Do not forget to give the quota master his dues, or Renal will close down the guild. He does not wait for long.~ []
@1032787 = ~The mayor sent some people out to find out what's happenin'... but I know what's goin' on. It's Umar... the witch is come back and there ain't no one who goes into the hills going t' come back, now.~ []
@1032796 = ~I knows plenty more than I wants to, believe me. The murders... skin missin', bodies disappearin'... it's the very things that happened when Umar ruled these lands, y'see. She's come back.~ []
@1032798 = ~There's lots of land owned by them old families. They all thought there was mithril, here, long time ago. Half right, I suppose... there was a little, and it ran out right quick.~ []
@1032799 = ~Little mines and temples went an' got swallowed up by the trees... all the families went an' left it all behind. Some kept a little piece o' land here an' there... like the cabin yer talkin' about.~ []
@1032800 = ~It's in the hills, it is... not far but inaccessible. There's a ranger fella that goes out there warned me not to get too close to the cabin. Set out lots of traps, he says.~ []
@1032801 = ~I gets the sense that the fella's hidin' scared there. Shame... seems nice enough. Can't be rich, though... probably just usin' the cabin that was already there.~ []
@1032802 = ~I'd show ya exactly where, but there ain't no way I'm going back into the hills until Umar has had her fill. Which may be never... so there it is.~ []
@1032803 = ~Okay. Don't go into the hills, though... just a friendly warnin'.~ []
@1032804 = ~She's a powerful old witch... ruled these hills over five hundred years ago. Disappeared... no one knows where to, but she's come back, that's for sure.~ []
@1032805 = ~People 'round here... they don't believe me, I know. But they don't go deep into the hills where I go. Late at night... ye hears things not o' this world, and it makes ye believe anythin' is possible.~ []
@1032807 = ~Um... hello, my <LADYLORD>. 'Tis a bad time you picked to visit our fair village.~ []
@1032811 = ~My... my name is Margie. Short for Margaret. My husband is Dale... one of the herders. We fled from the outskirts of the village lands because of the wolves.~ []
@1032814 = ~The wolves have picked this year to start in on us people... mauling and stealing corpses. It has... it has been just ghastly. They've been around for several years, but they've never been this bad.~ []
@1032815 = ~Everyone gets so upset and frightened... and they start thinking things are happening that aren't. Some people are blaming the ogre and his band... but they haven't done anything to harm us.~ []
@1032817 = ~The wolves around here have always been a danger... they're large and they're smart. And they're just a danger once again... that's all there is to it. People should know better.~ []
@1032820 = ~This is not excited. I am merely eager to receive your guild quota. Renal awaits it. He wishes to see if you are a profitable guild master. If not, someone else will be appointed.~ []
@1032824 = ~I am afraid that I must ask for a total of 1,000 gold this time. Renal demands hard sacrifices from all his guild underlings and you are no different.~ []
@1032825 = ~Once again we must all tighten our belts and pay what we can. Renal asks for a quota of 1,000 gold. It is hard, but fair.~ []
@1032830 = ~Ahh, unfortunately I must ask you for 1,000 gold this week. I know it is a lot, but Renal demands that his guilds all pitch in when the need is great.~ []
@1032845 = ~It is a small amount to pay to support the greater guild as a whole.~ []
@1032847 = ~That is quite a lot, but I will pay it cheerfully.~ []
@1032849 = ~A pleasure doing business with you. Renal will be most pleased with your performance. I wish you well.~ []
@1032856 = ~What if I am unable to get back to the guild?~ []
@1032857 = ~I will pay you as soon as I can.~ []
@1032876 = ~You cannot cast multiple instances of the same contingency spell on yourself.~ []
@1032881 = ~Ahh, you return. Obviously you have come to your senses and will pay the quota that Renal is due.~ []
@1032882 = ~I think 5,000 gold will suffice, don't you? It will more than make up for the payments you have missed.~ []
@1032883 = ~Perhaps 4,000 gold will suffice. It will revitalize my faith in you as a provider for your guild.~ []
@1032888 = ~Well, it's good to have you back with us. Consider your guild resanctioned. Go take good care of it this time.~ []
@1032892 = ~So, you be me new boss then? Fair enough. We ain't had time to talk yet, so let me tells ya something. You be square with me and I'll be square with you.~ []
@1032893 = ~I'm not stressing one bit with the current way things are handled. I think it's a bit of a waste of me talents, but who am I to say.~ []
@1032898 = ~I gotta say, <CHARNAME>, I really appreciates you bribing me back onna street. Don't like them closed-in places one bit. You're okay in my books, you are. Keep the work up good.~ []
@1032901 = ~How did you get into this business of yours, Hanz?~ []
@1032914 = ~Things are currently very easy for me, and I would not mind a quickening of the pace. Of course I would be worried about risk, but I think I can bring success to any mission.~ []
@1032919 = ~Your assistance in freeing me was most appreciated. Be assured that I will work all the harder for the guild. I will serve loyally and without fail. There is no other guild that compares.~ []
@1032925 = ~A pleasure as always, <CHARNAME>. Is there anything I can do to service the guild in any way?~ []
@1032928 = ~And how did you come by the Shadow Thieves?~ []
@1032930 = ~It is only as bloody as you let it get. If I must wash my hands after a kill, I have been less effective than I could have.~ []
@1032947 = ~I knows my place, and I'll do my job as you say. Nothing says I gotta like it. Get on, you've got some guildmaster business or somesuch to do. Don't waste your time talking to me.~ []
@1032953 = ~Things are a little slow right now, but if you think it's best for us to conserve our skill, that's okay by me. It's all up to you.~ []
@1032957 = ~It's pretty boring just sitting around, but if you don't want me out and about, that's okay too. I've been catching up on my reading. Did you know that bats see with sound? Neat.~ []
@1032969 = ~I think my talents are currently wasted here. Playing it safe all around is pointless. The profits are small, and the thrills are nonexistent. Get things moving around here.~ []
@1032971 = ~Now we're up to some fun, though there's more coin out there, I can smell it. We should be risking it all, instead of holding back like some common gutter trash.~ []
@1032976 = ~Just give me a report on how things are going.~ []
@1032994 = ~Ahh, the new guild leader. I trust you will find the facilities to your liking.~ [LATHAN02]
@1032998 = ~You are new, so there is little on the agenda just yet. I will try to inform you when something comes up.~ []
@1032999 = ~Nothing to report just yet.~ []
@1033001 = ~My name is Ama, and I am Shadowmaster of eastern Esmeltaran. Here is my signet, I think you'll find it authentic. Now stand aside!~ []
@1033002 = ~What? Ah... yes, m'lady Ama. I meant no offense. Ah, <CHARNAME>, I would suggest you obey proper protocol and present your dagger before your better.~ []
@1033005 = ~Why are you so far afield of your home city?~ []
@1033010 = ~I have come here with a promise of granting his wishes, but I only want to lure him away from his palisade defenses. This is where you come in.~ []
@1033011 = ~I have come to try and end the meddling of a politician that has grown too big for himself.~ []
@1033023 = ~It will be any evening that is best for you. I will await you in Waukeen's Promenade after dark, and then dispense a runner to get Sir Greshal. The suddenness will seem dramatic to him.~ []
@1033033 = ~Just wait a little longer. I'm sure he'll be here soon. He'll want us in full view and unarmed.~ []
@1033034 = ~Ahh, here he comes now.~ []
@1033039 = ~You have fallen for the trap, taken the bait. Now you are vulnerable, and my assassins are in place! Let the Night Masks take you!~ []
@1033041 = ~Er, hello. I... I had you followed and... and I'm awfully sorry about the mess with that Ama person. My informant tells me her cohorts wore the insignia of the Night Masks.~ []
@1033049 = ~We are the knights of honor and good upon Ansalon, a world so far removed from this one.~ []
@1033059 = ~Traps? No, but in the dark rooms of this place I have witnessed horrors. These terrors I am loath to discuss but if it helps your cause then I shall.~ []
@1033061 = ~To the west we were ambushed by small creatures, children in size but not in appetite. We were hard pressed to battle our way out of the trap.~ []
@1033064 = ~Halflings? If halflings seek to rip and rend the flesh from your body, to swallow your flesh and suck the marrow from your bones, then halflings they may be.~ []
@1033073 = ~Past the bone room you will find a chamber full of magical equipment. There is one large tube holding a damaged golem that is missing its head and arm. Whoever sought to repair it was interrupted in his work.~ []
@1033074 = ~That magician's study reminds me of my brother Elic's room, back when he studied to become a wizard. That room, so alien yet so familiar, stirs me the most. That said, there was a presence there that... that worried me. I did not scout further than that room.~ []
@1033112 = ~I'm sorry, I didn't mean to intrude. I'll just be leaving now. Bye.~ []
@1033114 = ~Maybe it'll be me who's eating you.~ []
@1033115 = ~There is nowhere to run to now, my prey.~ []
@1033117 = ~Think again. I'll have digested your heart by day's end.~ []
@1033189 = ~Don't listen to Kaatje... she's always full of stories, she is.~ []
@1033190 = ~I heard that the ranger woman, Merella, is a vampire. She's gone an' started prowlin' the night, stealin' bodies!~ []
@1033197 = ~My name's Kaatje... I came here with me ma and pa to flee the bad people who are killing everybody. When I grow up, though, I'm gonna be a mighty warrior an' leave this place for good.~ []
@1033201 = ~I was bringing the cows home a couple o' weeks ago, but I was bringin' them through the path in the woods because it's faster... even though ma doesn't like it when I goes through there.~ []
@1033202 = ~But I passes by the ranger's cabin... Merella's always been real nice to me. She gives me candies that she says she makes out of tree sap, and she took me fishing once, too.~ []
@1033204 = ~It was so big an' scary... it looked like a wolf-monster. I was so scared for Merella, so I went an' told me ma and pa... but they didn't believe me an' told me to stop tellin' stories.~ []
@1033205 = ~But it really is true, <SIRMAAM>... honest. If you went to the cabin I bet you'd find something.~ []
@1033212 = ~Haaaaaa... it... it cannot be! Have... the cowled ones... come for me...? Have I been... found out... after so long?~ []
@1033216 = ~Hmm... excuse me, maybe I should be going, now.~ []
@1033219 = ~I... I escaped to this place... fled with my pupils... before the Cowled Ones could take me... prisoner. We... we took what books we could.~ []
@1033220 = ~It was... it was so long ago. How... long now? I... I cannot remember. Are you... hunting for the Cowled Ones? Have you... come to... destroy me?~ []
@1033228 = ~You... you are not of the Cowled Ones? That is... that is good. They... found me out... my pupils and I... practicing the arts... without their permission. We... we fled... so long ago...~ []
@1033231 = ~Noooo! NOOOO!! Not... not after so long!! I... I will fight you!!~ []
@1033234 = ~Do... do not disturb me, then... and... and tell my... pupils... that I must... must speak to them, now. They... I... have not spoken to them... it seems like it has been... so looonnnng...~ []
@1033237 = ~Lich? Lich? Is... is this what I am? No... no... was I dying? I was... dying so long ago... I used the... magic to save myself. Just as... as I have used it... to save my pupils...~ []
@1033241 = ~How... how long have my pupils... and I... been below? Do the... wizards still... hunt me? Is the... name of... Nevaziah still spoken in the world above?~ []
@1033245 = ~I... I do not believe you! You... you lie! You... you hunt me... and I must defend myself! After... after all this time... nooooo!!~ []
@1033249 = ~I... I have been forgotten? The name of... Nevaziah... Keeper of Wisdom... has been lost to the sands of time? It... it is as if I have been... in a dream...~ []
@1033250 = ~My... my duty... is long gone. I... I am dead, am I not? And... and all my pupils... as well. Oh... how long has it been? Hiding... hiding... in fear... for centuries!~ []
@1033251 = ~Thank you... for opening my eyes. The Keepers never came... to collect the wisdom... my pupils and I... have saved. They... they are long dead.~ []
@1033254 = ~And... so, too... must the wisdom be destroyed. Tell me, then... why have you come? What... what is it that... you have come to this place for?~ []
@1033255 = ~The memories... of the Cowled Ones... has always been long. But... but how long? I have... hidden in darkness... for years upon countless years, I think. And... and no one has come...~ []
@1033257 = ~The... Nether Scroll? I... I have this... most sacred scroll... here with me. It is... most dangerous wisdom. Others must be... protected from it... lest they be destroyed.~ []
@1033258 = ~I... I have used its power... sparingly... but... perhaps not sparingly enough. What... what makes you think... wizard... that you are strong enough for it? It... it must be destroyed... with the other knowledge...~ []
@1033260 = ~It is... it is you who... are the fool... wizard! I... I am the Keeper of Wisdom... and I say... you shall not have it!!~ []
@1033262 = ~The Book of... Kaza? Yes... yes, I remember... this wisdom. One of... my pupils... has it, nearby.~ []
@1033263 = ~Is... is he dead? I... remember an accident... with fire. I... remember wrapping him in many... bandages... and I used power to... to restore him. I... I believe so...~ []
@1033264 = ~Go... go to my pupil... in the chamber nearby. He... he has your Book of Kaza. Take... take the wisdom from this place... and the rest... the rest shall be destroyed...~ []
@1033265 = ~If it is... treasure... that you seek... then do so quickly. My pupils... and I... will leave this world... a final time... very shortly. Treat what... wisdom... remains behind... with great care.~ []
@1033266 = ~My... my thanks... to you. My... long... long... wait is... over...~ []
@1033267 = ~Haaaa... are you... are you one of my pupils? Come to... speak to me... after so long? No... no... I see that you... are not.~ []
@1033268 = ~Are you... the Cowled Ones, then? Have you... finally found me... after so many long, long... years... centuries... of hunting? Have you... come to destroy me?~ []
@1033269 = ~The Cowled Ones? What are you talking about?~ []
@1033273 = ~Um... perhaps I'll just be going again.~ []
@1033279 = ~Me Madulf... lead fellows from great army of Sythsill in the south. No want to kill races no more. Lead fellows in desertion. We just wants be left alone.~ []
@1033281 = ~You're deserters from the Sythillisian Empire? How do expect to live up here?~ []
@1033282 = ~Well, that's tough... because I'm going to put an end to your evil existence!~ []
@1033284 = ~Nothing... I'll be on my way, I suppose.~ []
@1033286 = ~Wait... you not attack us. We needs you bring word to human village... humans run when Madulf goes, so me needs you'se to do it for me. You'se bring word, yes?~ []
@1033297 = ~Soon after we come, fellows begin to vanish. One, two, they go. Some turn up killed... skin missing. Some bodies vanish, too. Madulf no know who killing us.~ []
@1033298 = ~Madulf worried... numbers get smaller. We like here, but something bad is here, too, killing us fellows. Very bad.~ []
@1033299 = ~I don't believe you! Time to face your punishment!~ []
@1033302 = ~Is very hard. Humans hates us, and we just wants to be left alone. Some humans call knights, who chase us... it not bad here, but Madulf thinks village will call knights soon. Humans very mad.~ []
@1033305 = ~Well, I may not be a knight... but I'll end your evil existence just as quickly!~ []
@1033306 = ~I see... well, I'll be going, then.~ []
@1033307 = ~Madulf no want death... Madulf no want fight. Just want peace. You tell villagers, maybe, that Madulf and fellows will protect village... protect from orcs in mountains, yes?~ []
@1033308 = ~Humans let us stay, then, and no call knights. Maybe let us come, once in a moon, to trade for food and goods. Madulf make deal with village, if you'se tell them... we no want trouble.~ []
@1033311 = ~Is too bad, then. Soon, humans will call knights and Madulf be forced to go elsewhere. You'se change mind, you'se come back to Madulf, okay?~ []
@1033312 = ~But you'se can go... Madulf and fellows no want trouble. No fighting you'se.~ []
@1033313 = ~Madulf no knows. Maybe wolves. Maybe bad magics. Nobody see what kills fellows. Comes at night, though... maybe is the shadows.~ []
@1033315 = ~I see. So your band is no better off than the village. I'll be going, then.~ []
@1033316 = ~Madulf and fellows like here. But something bad killing fellows. Lose one, two maybe, at a time. Disappear, bodies too. Very bad... Madulf very worried.~ []
@1033317 = ~Madulf happy. Maybe fellows can live alone and eat good, be happy here. You do good thing... maybe humans agree. Madulf keep deal, you tell them.~ []
@1033322 = ~Very well, Madulf... I will bring your proposal to the mayor.~ []
@1033323 = ~Forget it... I haven't changed my mind.~ []
@1033330 = ~Actually, I have decided to end your sorry existence... humans will never live with your kind!~ []
@1033331 = ~Is good. Madulf thinks maybe he and fellows can stay... live in peace, maybe. If humans not hunt us down, that is. We protect... we keep word.~ []
@1033332 = ~Madulf not happy. We keep word, <RACE>, why you decide not to tell village? Madulf cannot tell village, himself... they run away in fear. Will just bring knights soon.~ []
@1033333 = ~You change mind, come speak to Madulf again. Madulf and fellows willing to protect village from orcs in mountains, if they want. We do that, and trade. You come again.~ []
@1033340 = ~Madulf and fellows owe you much... we can stay and be left alone, here. Is good. Here... have shield to give you... is magic, from Sythsill army... we no use. Maybe you like.~ []
@1033346 = ~Why you do this?! Untrustworthy <RACE>!! Kill <RACE>... KIIILLL!!~ []
@1033362 = ~We likes you'se... you'se done good for us fellows!~ []
@1033364 = ~Grrrr... we no harm... grrrrrrr... no want trouble... grrrrr... you speak Madulf... grrrrr grrrrrowl!~ []
@1033366 = ~Grrrr grrrrr... you help us... grrrowl! Welcome here... grrrrr~ []
@1033374 = ~This is the second half of the Rift Device Rod. The completed Rod may be used for the destruction of the Unseeing Eye.~ []
@1033375 = ~This is half of a page of parchment, yellowed with age. Its ink is faded but still legible, and reads:

"This land near the Umar Hills is rich with mithril deposits, and I notice many other prospectors have joined me here to plunder its riches. So, too, have scoundrels and bandits been attracted to the area, and they prey mercilessly upon us. I have found an excellent hiding place for my mithril cache, one which even those thieves will never be able to locate. It is far to the northwest of the Imnesvale village, in a forest --"

Beneath this section, the page is torn and jagged as if it has been ripped from its other half.~
@1033392 = ~Er...<PRO_SIRMAAM>? My name is Dirbert and me an' my friends here want to be adventurers like you. Real strong an' powerful, like.~ []
@1033395 = ~I knows we can! But... everyone says we're all too young an' all.~ []
@1033397 = ~Since... since you're already an adventurer an' all, <PRO_SIRMAAM>, I was hopin'... I was hopin' you might maybe... maybe buy some swords for us? Some bastard swords?~ []
@1033400 = ~Er... swords and some ale, then. If... if we give you th' money, <PRO_SIRMAAM>, would you buy us some?~ []
@1033404 = ~I'll buy you ale, boys... but you'd just cut yourselves with a sword in your hands.~ []
@1033406 = ~Merciful beings of light! I offer you a simple exchange. Information on what you seek in exchange for my freedom.~ []
@1033407 = ~Great! Gee, thanks, <PRO_SIRMAAM>! You're the greatest! Here... here's the gold we've saved. Get us three bastard swords, I guess, and a keg of Baalor's ale from Min Minling.~ []
@1033409 = ~O-okay... with three bastard swords, we could at least become adventurers! Here's some of the gold we've saved up. Thanks, <PRO_SIRMAAM>! You're the greatest!~ []
@1033415 = ~No, we wouldn't! We know how to use swords! But... but if you'd buy us some ale, that'd be super. Here's some gold we've saved up for it...~ []
@1033422 = ~Awww... please? Please? Pretty please?~ []
@1033439 = ~I said no... and I still mean it!~ []
@1033457 = ~So... have you got our stuff?~ []
@1033463 = ~Yeah, I got your swords... and some ale for you, too.~ []
@1033464 = ~Well, I didn't get your swords... but I did buy you some ale.~ []
@1033466 = ~Yes, I got your ale... and I got you some bastard swords, as well.~ []
@1033469 = ~Well, I didn't get your ale... but I did get you some swords.~ []
@1033504 = ~Alright... I guess we'll wait a bit longer for it. We're mighty anxious to start our adventurin', though.~ []
@1033510 = ~My wolves? Hah! No longer, fool. The pack has fallen under the fell magicks of the Shade Lord. Your hunting has gone awry.~ []
@1033511 = ~We find Mister Ployer distasteful, even in comparison to others of his ilk. It would not disturb us to... make other arrangements around that task in the future.~ []
@1033518 = ~This place was not always like this... floating in a false and unholy darkness. It began only a short time ago.~ []
@1033528 = ~I... I don't (hic!) feeelll welll...~ []
@1033531 = ~... Ize being (hic!) sooooo glahd ti seeze ye... (hic!) yooze soooo neyce ti usssz beyssz... (hic!)~ [DRUNK01]
@1033540 = ~Only those that are distasteful. For not participating in Ployer's little exercise we might charge... oh... one thousand gold pieces.~ []
@1033541 = ~For not participating in Ployer's little exercise we might charge... oh... one thousand gold pieces. This is a much lower figure than the original service cost.~ []
@1033542 = ~Pleeze, mercy on us! Me sorry. Don't kill. Me just following orders. Didn't want to eat children or kick old people. Just job!~ []
@1033543 = ~Foul orc! You will suffer the same fate as all your kind!~ []
@1033545 = ~Tank yous tank yous. I promising, no more killings here. Not as job, anyway. Maybe hobby. That okay, I think.~ []
@1033548 = ~Oh, don't beg. Begging just makes me ill.~ []
@1033558 = ~You have nothing I wish to know! Die as you should!~ []
@1033562 = ~Falik at your service. My companion Grancor needs help with finding a... a I can't remember what, but if you talk to him he'll tell you.~ []
@1033572 = ~The grill. That big metal thing. Jump on. Be careful, it's hot!~ []
@1033586 = ~What is this place?~ []
@1033594 = ~What is this place that you have built?~ []
@1033599 = ~Beneath the grime you can make out the words 'Copper Coronet'.~ []
@1033603 = ~I hear you might have a sword I seek. It should have spider-like patterns on it.~ []
@1033605 = ~Ain't excited. I just wants ya to leave. Bossmen won't take kindly to us speaking to strangers while we's supposed to be working.~ []
@1033606 = ~Yeah, so get going before we have to call the guards.~ []
@1033607 = ~Now, just a minute there. Ain't no call for that. I mean, be awfully hard for you to stay all nice and pretty if we let the city's blasted sewers back up. You should thank us.~ []
@1033608 = ~Yeah, we do good work, so you take your high n' mighty and get packin'. Get outta here.~ []
@1033616 = ~I'll pay you 1,000 gold, no questions asked.~ []
@1033625 = ~No, I'll stick with the 50 gold I offered.~ []
@1033627 = ~200! Cripes a'mighty, you got a deal!~ []
@1033629 = ~You right, it's not ours. It's mine! I gots it, I'm packing it around, I gotta scare the spiders, so I'm sellin' it and you get squat. 200 is more than I make in years! Here! Take it!~ []
@1033630 = ~Yeah, right. You just happen to have 1,000 gold layin' about. I ain't that stupid. Get lost.~ []
@1033631 = ~Yeah, you have a pretty weird sense of humor. 1,000 gold is more than I ever seen. Get lost, funny<MANWOMAN>.~ []
@1033632 = ~That works too. Here you go.~ []
@1033635 = ~Sorry, but it's city property and I can't give it up.~ []
@1033643 = ~I was wondering if you had found a sword with spider-like etchings on it?~ []
@1033649 = ~There have always been losses, but now there are even more. The workers of the city have found some fell weapon that smites the spiders most unfairly.~ []
@1033651 = ~We must help her. Spiders are the most perfect creatures.~ []
@1033656 = ~We will not help.~ []
@1033659 = ~Good. Then go, and find the accursed blade that kills my charges. I would go myself, but my half-drow blood would be my death if I were seen.~ []
@1033660 = ~The blade is called Spider's Bane, and it is in the hands of the workers that clean the ducts and sewers. They lodge next to the prison, on its north side. Go.~ []
@1033669 = ~Filthy... bugs... filthy... chhhhclclclcl...~ []
@1033673 = ~Oh... greetings to you, stranger. (sigh)~ []
@1033678 = ~My name is Daar and I... I am no one of importance, I suppose. At least, nobody important enough that my love's father might vaguely consider allowing me to court her. (sigh)~ []
@1033682 = ~My love is Colette, and her father is a wizard of no small power... and possessed of considerable bias against me.~ []
@1033683 = ~His name is Jermien... and I understand he intends to use Colette as a bargaining tool for some wizardly endeavour of his own. Against her will, I imagine... although I've had no chance to ask her opinion.~ []
@1033686 = ~I could remove her father from the equation... for a price.~ []
@1033693 = ~It would be of no use, I am sure. And I do not wish to use violence in such an endeavour... I do not appreciate its taste, and no doubt Jermien would crush me with magic.~ []
@1033695 = ~I... I have no wish to use violence, my <LADYLORD>. Jermien loves his daughter, in his own way, and I've no right. But less harsh methods are not likely to work, either.~ []
@1033699 = ~I am <GABBER>... who are you?~ []
@1033701 = ~Forget it... I'll be on my way.~ []
@1033707 = ~And I, since you ask, am none other than Jermien... licensed Cowled Wizard for this region. So you needn't run off and attempt to report me, <GIRLBOY>.~ []
@1033710 = ~What is this... thing... you're making?~ []
@1033711 = ~Er... Daar didn't send me, but I did talk to him. Why don't you give him a break?~ []
@1033715 = ~I don't do anything about it because I don't want to do anything about it. I have more important things to do... and until the Cowled Wizards tell me otherwise, I'll not involve myself.~ []
@1033717 = ~What is this... thing... you're making?~ []
@1033718 = ~Er... Daar didn't send me, but I did talk to him. Why don't you give him a break?~ []
@1033724 = ~It's likely wolves or ogres or some other mundane nonsense... I've no interest in the matter. Why don't you ask some of the yokels, if you're so concerned?~ []
@1033728 = ~What is this... thing... you're making?~ []
@1033729 = ~Er... Daar didn't send me, but I did talk to him. Why don't you give him a break?~ []
@1033733 = ~Few other mages have made the attempt, you see. This type of golem is quite powerful and dangerous... but I am more than skilled enough to control it.~ []
@1033734 = ~Once it's complete, I'll have an excellent servant... and something to keep an eye on my daughter and that foolhardy beau of hers while I am away.~ []
@1033737 = ~Trouble is, I'm missing one of the crucial ingredients... the blood of a mimic. I'd pay handsomely for some, in fact. Hmmmn... you look like the adventurous type... care to find me some?~ []
@1033742 = ~Hmph! I've far more important things in mind for Colette than that fool, Daar. She'll get over her childish infatuation, I assure you... and Daar will be long gone.~ []
@1033746 = ~What is this... thing... you're making?~ []
@1033752 = ~What is this... thing... you're making?~ []
@1033755 = ~A mimic is a vicious little creature... shapechanger... that likes to attract and kill adventurers by looking like a treasure chest or similar objects.~ []
@1033758 = ~Very well... I'll make the attempt.~ []
@1033762 = ~Alright... I'll make the attempt.~ []
@1033763 = ~Forget it... I'm not interested in your task.~ []
@1033770 = ~I've spoken to Daar... why don't you give him a break?~ []
@1033774 = ~No, I don't... but I intend to find some.~ []
@1033775 = ~No, I don't... and I don't intend on looking for it, anymore, either.~ []
@1033776 = ~Eh? Let me have a look at what you have, there. Yes... yes... I see. Well done, <GIRLBOY>, well done! I don't know how you found it, but here it is!~ []
@1033777 = ~I took the liberty of digging out that sword, earlier, just in case. Rather prophetic of me, don't you think? It was just collecting dust, anyway... so here you go and well earned, I might add.~ []
@1033778 = ~Now... all I need to do is add this to the golem and he will be complete! Finally, I will be able to leave in peace and be assured that Colette will not be molested while I am gone!~ []
@1033780 = ~Well, it's no less than I expected. Perhaps you should go find some simpler pursuits for yourself, <GIRLBOY>... like, say, farming or something similar.~ []
@1033781 = ~... Mmm... mmmMMMWWaarrRR?~ []
@1033788 = ~Y-yes... I am alive, my daughter. Thanks to our kind stranger, here...~ []
@1033791 = ~One of my own creations turned on me, boy. It... it seems I am not so wise and powerful as I had first thought.~ []
@1033792 = ~And... perhaps I have been foolish in some of my other decisions, as well. Daar... boy... if you promise to take care of my daughter, and protect her... if you still want her... I'll not stand in the way.~ []
@1033794 = ~Indeed. Thank you, Jermien. I shall take excellent care of Colette, you can be sure. Come, my love... let's not waste this chance.~ []
@1033795 = ~My thanks to you, <PRO_GIRLBOY>, for saving a foolish wizard's life. (sigh)  My daughter is now gone... I think I will leave, myself, for a while and consider what I have done.~ []
@1033798 = ~Daar! Daar, it was terrible! One... one of father's creations... it turned on him! And... and now he's dead!~ []
@1033799 = ~I never meant your father any harm, my love. But his pride killed him in the end. Come... let us away from here, and I will protect you in his stead.~ []
@1033800 = ~A-alright... I just... I just wish father had...~ []
@1033804 = ~My thanks to you, my <PRO_LADYLORD>... whoever you are. Without your aid, the creature would have certainly killed Colette, as well. I wish you well.~ []
@1033806 = ~(sigh)  Father will never let me marry Daar. That is all I wish to do... I don't know why he won't change his mind!~ []
@1033808 = ~I love Daar... but father will have none of it! Now he's making this... thing... to watch over me when he leaves! This is just terrible!~ []
@1033814 = ~There're a lot o' things t' be said about yer inn, Vince... but 'humble' ain't the one I would be pickin', aye?~ []
@1033821 = ~Ah, Vincenzo knows the truth! My family has been in this here area for a long, long time... an' the tales of the witch, Umar, have been passed down, they have!~ []
@1033825 = ~I thought that'd shut yer trap. Now, then, me <LADYLORD>... I can tell ye all about th' witch, Umar... a tale sure to curl yer ears, if ye'd care to hear it.~ []
@1033826 = ~Go ahead... I've got the time.~ []
@1033828 = ~Of course, of course! I've not many rooms, mind you... all th' frightened folk who've fled into the village have near filled me up. Only a room or two left.~ []
@1033830 = ~Silence, boy! There are no foulsome rodents here other than you! (ahem)  Ah... now, my <LADYLORD>...~ []
@1033832 = ~... That's if ye can stand th' stench...~ []
@1033834 = ~I jus' took one this morning, Vince... but yer a peach fer offerin'.~ []
@1033837 = ~Umar was a wicked one. No one e'er saw her except when she came down from the hills to steal some unfortunate soul. Shepherds, babes... anyone who weren't careful.~ []
@1033838 = ~She'd torture 'em, ye could hear their cries durin' the night. People tried to find her, but only the victims' bodies would turn up... mutilated an' dead.~ []
@1033843 = ~I'm warning ye, boy... ye'll be out on yer arse faster than ye can blink, if ye keeps this up!~ []
@1033847 = ~Well, there was a group o' mages some years back who came. Young ones... apprentices, I gathered. Two fellas and a young lass, sure enough.~ []
@1033849 = ~Well... thanks for the story, I suppose.~ []
@1033852 = ~Aye, true enough. Them three went into th' Hills... an' they was ne'er found again. 'Cept for the lass' journals... I found those meself, out in the woods.~ []
@1033856 = ~Aye, ye can... I had a copy or two done up by a scribe friend o' mine some months back. Ye can have one, if ye likes.~ []
@1033858 = ~Well, so what if I have? 'Tis a good story, more or less! Make me bloody rich one day... an' then where will ye be, ye little rugrat?~ []
@1033860 = ~I did nay such thing! Here ye go, me <LADYLORD>... use it as ye will. But beware the witch if ye goes into the hills. She's not sated yet... not by a longshot...~ []
@1033865 = ~Not at all, not at all... glad to see that there's people willin' to listen to it.~ []
@1033867 = ~Watch it, ye little bugbear, or I'll dunk ye in a trough an leave ye to rot in the sun! Now... me <LADYLORD>... was there somethin' else ye wanted?~ []
@1033875 = ~Egad! Somebody actually wants t' hear his cockamamie tripe?~ []
@1033890 = ~Of course, me <LADYLORD>... more'n happy t' offer ye anything under me roof. Things are kind o' quiet, now that the murders have ended... not that I'm complainin'.~ []
@1033893 = ~Magical currents are embedded inside this bullet so that it seems a little more balanced and lighter as it flies towards an opponent. When the bullet strikes an opponent, it explodes in a flash of fire.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1D4 + 2, +2 fire damage
THAC0: +1 bonus
Damage type: missile (piercing)
Weight: 0
Launcher: Sling
~ []
@1033897 = ~Awww... poor Vince has a room full o' them 'Umar Witch Project' journals an' no more killin' an' misery t' sell 'em with. Tsk.~ []
@1033898 = ~Shut yer yip, boy... or I'll offer ye to yon visitin' ogre as a noon-time snack, I will. Now... me <LADYLORD>...~ []
@1033899 = ~Keep it up, boy, and ye'll be eatin' them journals fer lunch, ye will. Hmph. Oh... oh, yes, me <LADYLORD>...~ []
@1033918 = ~One should beware of walking in the Slums and the Bridge District late at night... footpads and muggers openly attack you, amongst other forms of trouble.~ []
@1033921 = ~The Churches of Lathander and Talos are in a constant fight for dominance in the city... many believe this will soon lead to open war.~ []
@1033925 = ~Clerics throughout the city are disappearing... only to be reappear with their eyes plucked out, claiming to have joined a new religion devoted to 'the Unseeing Eye'.~ []
@1033926 = ~The Shadow Thieves run the Docks District... anyone who goes there should pay heed to them or suffer the consequences.~ []
@1033929 = ~The Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart is an order of lawful warriors that serves all of Amn. They can be called to duty anywhere evil threatens.~ []
@1033933 = ~There have been a series of murders in the Bridge District. Victims have been found with the flesh flayed from their bodies... the murderer is still at large.~ []
@1033934 = ~One should be wary of going into the Graveyard District at night... it is said that the dead, and worse things, can come out of the older and deeper tombs.~ []
@1033935 = ~I offer a grand sum, worthy of a <PRO_MANWOMAN> of your stature. I offer 10,000 gold if you can free my land of this scourge. It is a fortune, you will agree.~ []
@1033936 = ~Ten thousand? That is an astounding sum for simple monster hunting.~ []
@1033939 = ~Athkatla is ruled by the Council of Six... their identities are secret so no-one knows who to bribe. The Council is currently not in session, so the Vice-Consul rules.~ []
@1033940 = ~The colony of New Amn in Maztica is growing dangerous. The natives are rebelling against their masters... the Council might send in reinforcements.~ []
@1033948 = ~The rival guild is rumored to have been wiped out by the Shadow Thieves. The Shadow Thieves were far more numerous... and brook no competition.~ []
@1033950 = ~The Shadow Thieves' victory over its rival guild is rumored to be due to the aid of several independent master thieves in the city... something the Shadow Thieves hotly deny.~ []
@1033955 = ~The leaders of the Shadow Thieves have been assassinated... but the victorious rival guild has vanished, cutting off reprisal from the larger Shadow guild.~ []
@1033957 = ~The Council of Six is reeling since the Shadow Thieves were destroyed by rivals in the city... the guild had secretly ruled Athkatla for decades and the Council is now at a loss.~ []
@1033959 = ~The murders in Imnesvale have been caused by a group of monsters that have camped in the regions, deserters from the Sythillisian Empire led by an ogre named Madulf.~ []
@1033961 = ~Many blame the murders in the village on the band of wolves that have been active in the region for the last several years... supposedly led by an actual werewolf.~ []
@1033963 = ~Shepherds and farmers from outlying areas are relieved that the wolf pack has been disbanded and the werewolf destroyed... flocks will be safe once again.~ []
@1033964 = ~Some say the witch Umar has surfaced again. She vanished seven hundred years ago, but legend holds that every century or so her reign of murder and torture begins again.~ []
@1033966 = ~A few centuries ago bands of mithril were discovered and mined. Temples sprung up and wealthy Amnish families bought land... it was all abandoned when the mithril ran out.~ []
@1033967 = ~You are the choice I make, and the offer stands whether you go now or not. There is no other decision that makes sense.~ []
@1033968 = ~Imnesvale's mayor, Lloyd Wainwright, needs more adventurers to seek the source of the village's problems. A group led by the knight Mazzy Fentan disappeared several weeks ago.~ []
@1033971 = ~A month ago, Lady Lilith Lurraxol convinced the Athkatlan Council to sell her sole license for fur sales in Trademeet. Lord Skarmaen Alibakkar was reportedly incensed!~ []
@1033976 = ~The monsters of the Sythillisian army are destroying everything in their path.  Everyone fears they'll march through Imnescar and Trademeet next summer.~ []
@1033977 = ~There's always been talk about a link between this isle and some dark underground city, but then, what do you expect on an isle of braggarts and madmen?~ []
@1033984 = ~Spellhold weren't first built as a jail, but that ain't stopped them locking people up in it. Enchanted through and through... it takes mages to hold mages.~ []
@1033986 = ~So be it. It has been amusing to travel with you. If you have further need of me, you can find me in the graveyard district of Athkatla... away from murderous rivvil eyes.~ []
@1033995 = ~Only that whatever evil lurks about, it does so far below these simple sewers. I have not yet found a downward exit to this place, but I am sure that is where the evil sleeps.~ []
@1033997 = ~I am Keldorn, servant of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart. I have been sent here to root out an evil that has preyed twice on my brothers in faith.~ []
@1034005 = ~Beasts! Curs! Your terror ends here!~ []
@1034014 = ~Here in this note I beseech the noble knights of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart to answer my call of desperation. There are, at this moment, beasts of huge size and ferocity rampaging on my lands. Ogres and their fell kin have killed my peoples and tenants, and I have not the means to rout them. For all that is good, will you descend upon them with your righteousness? I await your response.

Lord Jierdan Firkraag~ []
@1034017 = ~You skip many of the entries of times and places far removed from your current worries.

Flamerule 7
Kaatje came to visit again. A sweet child, eager to learn my ways with the wild creatures.

Flamerule 12
Dark creatures roam the forests. Several townspeople have been slain by some unknown predator. Everyone seems to have their own opinion of what is doing the killing. The strangest thing is that the bodies are disappearing in the morning. This leaves me baffled, for most signs point to a pack of wolves that have been in the area for a long time. Wolves don't steal bodies.

Flamerule 13
Or perhaps I should say wolf-like creatures. At night while I've been patrolling I've often caught shadowy glimpses of these 'wolves' running alongside me. I've tried to attract their attention but they ignore me. I find this most strange, as if the pack is being controlled by someone else. Years ago I spoke with the pack leaders and they were cordial. Now they either flee from me, or, and I fear to say this, they stalk me.

Flamerule 21
It is near noon and still the wood outside my cabin seems full of shadows. I've been hard pressed to hear birds and most of the larger animals have long fled. I plan to find the wolf's den (this afternoon). I've drawn a map to it. All signs point to them as being the culprits, but what wolves act like these? They are wolves with the cunning of men.
And there is something else, a whispering in my mind. It is faint now, in the waking hours, but while I sleep I dream only of this voice and the face behind it. Whether it is connected to the voices, I do not know. I suspect by the time that the sun sets tonight I'll have answers to my questions.~ []
@1034047 = ~I knew you would not let me down. The compound is not far from here... a dry-docked boat just across the way on the east side of the slums.~ []
@1034049 = ~The compound is not far from here... a dry-docked boat just across the way to the east side of the slums.~ []
@1034068 = ~I do not know. Perhaps you slighted him in some way, without even knowing. He seems quite singleminded in his purposes.~ []
@1034070 = ~Lilarcor +3~
@1034071 = ~What I do know is that he is not the worst of your worries. The Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart will seek your death if something is not done quickly.~ []
@1034072 = ~I have friends among the Order. I will speak with them as quickly as possible. Perhaps I can persuade them to look on you with mercy. I can but try.~ []
@1034080 = ~Father has much faith in you, that you are genuinely pained at what has happened. Faith is very important to him. Please do not disappoint him.~ []
@1034085 = ~That is how my father felt. He claims he has found his way again, but I know he doubts. If you can, give the doubt back to Jierdan. Father would not ask, but I will.~ []
@1034090 = ~Lawrence Lilarcor was well known, not for being brave, but as an idiot. As the tale goes, the boastful Lilarcor left his village at the urging of his friends so that the "great hero" could do battle with a devious Treant. He walked for days in the dead of winter until, feverish, he found his target and began an epic wrestling match. Unfortunately (or perhaps luckily), the "Treant" was nothing more than a craggy old normal oak. His friends had been jesting, not actually expecting that Lilarcor would go fight the fictitiously dangerous tree. That might have been the end of it, but Lilarcor, not really knowing what a Treant was, didn't realize the truth. He eventually uprooted the oak and, marching proudly home, he declared himself a hero. Thus was born a laughing stock of epic proportions, and over time Lilarcor became the sacrificial fool in many tales of "less than brilliance."
It is not known whether this enchanted weapon is Lilarcor himself, perhaps imprisoned by an evil mage or some other odd coincidence of fate, but it certainly acts in a manner consistent with his level of competence. If it is he, he has never bemoaned his captivity. He might not realize, or care, that he is no longer a human.
As a weapon, Lilarcor has its uses, but many a warrior has eventually given it away. Banter such as "Ouch, that musta hurt," "Oh yeah! Got 'im good," and "Beware my bite for it might... might... might really hurt or something" is a constant barrage on a warrior's psyche.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1D10 + 3
THAC0: +3 bonus
Damage type: slashing
Equipped Abilities:
    Immunity to Charm
    Immunity to Confusion
Weight: 10
Speed Factor: 7
Proficiency Type: Two Handed Sword
Type: 2-handed
Requires: 14 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Cleric
 Mage 
 Thief
 Monk
 Beast Master~ []
@1034099 = ~Freeing the djinn.

To retrieve what is in possession of the djinn Malaaq, I must first secure his release by obtaining the twin to the flask he is bound to. He informed me that the flask is kept close to his master... either in his chambers or in the possession of some dryads or golems.~ []
@1034101 = ~I do not feel impressive. I have lost my honor to a lie.~ []
@1034102 = ~Your words flatter, but I am undeserving.~ []
@1034106 = ~Find a way to release Minsc from his cell.

Minsc, too, is kept captive in the same room I was. Obviously our captors fear his strength, as his cell is welded shut; there is no lock to pick and no key to find. I don't know how I will get him out.~ []
@1034107 = ~Get the golem to open the dungeon doors.

It appears the sewage golem will open the doors in the dungeon if I find an activation stone... it is on a table near someone named Rielev.~ []
@1034111 = ~Investigate the circus tent.

I have agreed to acquire a sword... from dangerous illusionary peasants... in order to free a winged elf from the illusion that binds her.~ []
@1034113 = ~Find the boy's mother inside the circus tent.

I have found the mother of the boy outside the tent. Now I must see if I can restore her to her original form... along with the rest of this mad circus.~ []
@1034117 = ~You know nothing of me. You base your assumptions on storybooks and legend.~ []
@1034118 = ~Free Hendak and the slaves.

It appears that the Copper Coronet is keeping slaves to perform its entertainments... I have talked to a slave by the name of Hendak and agreed to free his people. I will need a key that is currently held by the beastmaster located across the arena.~ []
@1034119 = ~Free Hendak and the slaves.

I have freed the slaves of the Copper Coronet... only to find that there are yet more slaves being held in a dry-docked ship on the east side of the slums. Hendak mentioned there was a tunnel in the sewers that leads from the inn to the ship, but he didn't know exactly where it was.~ []
@1034129 = ~Er, not as such.~ []
