@1034733 = ~A letter from Mae'Var to the Night Masks assassins requesting the death of Renal Bloodscalp. This is just the kind of proof that Renal requires.~ []
@1034738 = ~These documents were obtained from a merchant called Marcus at the request of Edwin. Edwin has made it clear that the contents are none of your business.~ []
@1034739 = ~The assembled rod would surely destroy the beast. You must use the item upon the beast, and then return it to me. Use it but once, or you will perish under its power.~ [RIFTG10]
@1034744 = ~~ []
@1034794 = ~I assure you that I shall be ever vigilant with guild concerns. I shall bring them to your attention as soon as I have them.~ []
@1034795 = ~Perhaps, but I shall be ever vigilant in keeping you apprised of any shady goings on here in your guild.~ []
@1034799 = ~Goodbye then.~ []
@1034802 = ~Kretor claims that the thieves know which one it is, though they will not say. He has asked me to deal with this since you are new and he does not quite trust you yet. These matters are your responsibility though.~ []
@1034806 = ~The first is Darronal Gwin II, a spoiled child of a noble family. I think he works for Kretor out of boredom, or perhaps he's slumming. He doesn't really need the money, but he is pretty obstinate.~ []
@1034815 = ~A motley lot. Each could be the one.~ []
@1034872 = ~Well, it has been 5 days or so since your order to kill one of the thieves under Kretor for their suspected stealing from the guild coffers, and I must say that perhaps the results could have been better.~ []
@1034874 = ~The stealing of our funds has indeed stopped, but it is because Kretor has quit and closed down that section of your operations. He could not afford to continue funding the quota out of his own purse.~ []
@1034876 = ~Why did you not warn me this would happen?~ []
@1034879 = ~You may have stopped the stealing, but Kretor could not afford to fill the quota on his own, so he has quit. It is a shame, really.~ []
@1034895 = ~Darronal Gwin II has turned up dead. It would seem that the others did not appreciate him hurting their wages for his gain. Excellent decision, I should say.~ []
@1034898 = ~I'm sure that all concerned have learned from this. I will apprise you when another matter requires your attention.~ []
@1034899 = ~The events were perfectly predictable, <PRO_SIRMAAM>. I am your mouthpiece, not your mentor. You will have to make these decisions as you see fit.~ []
@1034900 = ~As you see fit, <PRO_SIRMAAM>. A strange end to an unfortunate bit of business, then.~ []
@1034902 = ~You handled that there business with them thieving underlings like a pro. You keep up the good work and we'll get on fine.~ []
@1034904 = ~I prithee, my lady... it fills me with no small amount of wonder that you have not asked me of my journeys ere we met? We have traveled a short while, and yet we know next to nothing of each other.~ [ANOMEN67]
@1034907 = ~Alright, then... tell me of your journeys, if you wish.~ []
@1034914 = ~There is precious little to tell, although my few adventures have been glorious, indeed. The path to knighthood is a long one, however... hence the need for my travels.~ []
@1034916 = ~Most recently, however... let me think... I was with our men when the orcs came down into the Ommlur Hills once again.~ []
@1034919 = ~In great numbers, they are a force to fear... but individually, they are no match for a warrior. I, myself, was able to fight through many of them alone and take the head of one of their foul chieftains.~ []
@1034936 = ~Actually, I did stop a war with Amn several months ago... but I didn't do it on my own, of course.~ []
@1034939 = ~You find it hard to believe that I have done such things... or is it solely because I am a woman?~ []
@1034941 = ~Perhaps you're right... the tales have probably grown larger as time has passed.~ []
@1034955 = ~I apologize if I am not as charming as Keldorn, here. I had to fight for my place as a squire, without the benefit of a patron father and the privilege that goes with it.~ []
@1034968 = ~A wondrous thing, indeed. Perhaps you will tell me more, <CHARNAME>, as we walk... I would hear more of these former companions of yours and your valiant tales of the Sword Coast.~ []
@1034971 = ~I suspect a taint of sarcasm in your voice, my lady. I do not discount your deeds entirely... I have seen you in action and you are quite impressive, do not misunderstand me.~ []
@1034984 = ~And what person might that be, 'friend?'~ []
@1035004 = ~Alright, everyone just calm down!~ []
@1035033 = ~You have been given <number> proficiencies to give to your character's INACTIVE class. Choose from the above list any of the highlighted proficiencies. Depending on your class, your character may be able to choose the same proficiency twice. This will grant specialization with the weapons listed. Keep in mind that a character can use any weapon available to their race and class whether proficient with it or not. However, there will be a minus to the attack roll if the character attacks with a non-proficient weapon.~ []
@1035064 = ~What do you want? This is important work you're interrupting.~ []
@1035073 = ~I was just wondering what you thought was in the shipment.~ []
@1035076 = ~Don't know. Weapons maybe, or jewels. Doesn't matter 'cause I'll never see it. Just guard it and go, that's what I do.~ []
@1035088 = ~Wh-what? But... my guards! They will stop you!~ []
@1035089 = ~Impaler +3~
@1035093 = ~Halcyon +1~
@1035096 = ~What? What are you talking about? Guards! Expel this fool!~ []
@1035100 = ~Duskblade +2~
@1035101 = ~My... options... ? Please! Please don't kill me! I have a wife and two...~ []
@1035106 = ~Then you should be made aware of it, certainly. It is the greatest force for righteousness in Faerun... an army of knights and paladins ready to combat evil wherever it may be found.~ []
@1035111 = ~I mean... think of all the suffering your average commoner must endure. The hunger, the inequity and injustices... the rebellions in the south. All things of chaos.~ []
@1035112 = ~Surely these things would not occur with the Order placed in command... a force of true goodness and honest brotherhood? It baffles me why more people don't see it.~ []
@1035113 = ~You have heard of it? That is good. I have always been in awe of the Order, ever since I was a child... a force of righteous knights and paladins in a brotherhood of arms.~ []
@1035114 = ~I... I apologize most humbly, my lady, if I have given offense. I did not mean to come across as such an overbearing lout. I shall refrain from bothering you further.~ []
@1035119 = ~There is far too much inequity and injustice for the common man... the Order could do much to eradicate such hopeless existences. What do you think, my lady?~ []
@1035120 = ~I agree with Keldorn. Your Order must remain separate to maintain its purity.~ []
@1035121 = ~I think you're right... there's a lot more the Order could do.~ []
@1035122 = ~Calm down. I won't kill you. You hide for awhile, perhaps in some other town.~ []
@1035123 = ~Pathetic. No, I'm sorry, but I've no other choice.~ []
@1035130 = ~I agree... there is a lot more that the Order could do.~ []
@1035131 = ~I disagree... the Order should remain separate from such things.~ []
@1035135 = ~Aye, you see the right of it, I think. It is something I shall keep in mind once I pass the Test... the Order must become more active beyond simply combating the most obvious evils.~ []
@1035137 = ~Get going, you're free now.~ []
@1035139 = ~Hmph. You're entitled to your opinion, my lady, but I think there is more that can be done to fight chaos than simply combating the most obvious evils with a sword.~ []
@1035141 = ~You are a foreigner and a wanderer, true... but surely, my lady, you must think that evil can be fought with more than just a sword.~ []
@1035143 = ~An idiot, am I? If you've such a low opinion of me, than I shall simply remain silent... and watch you most carefully.~ []
@1035145 = ~The Order has its place, Anomen... and government is not it. Your vision is flawed, and you would do well to think most carefully before you do anything rash.~ []
@1035152 = ~You are on the defensive and yet you taunt! Such gall!~ []
@1035157 = ~The gall is yours to think I am on the defensive when I have led you as a mantis does her prey! You will fall here, and you death shall be... delicious!~ []
@1035164 = ~If Lord Cor was not deep into his cups, he was demanding that I uphold the family honor... or telling me what a worthless son I had become.~ []
@1035166 = ~He was derisive of my choice to join the Order. He wanted me to take over his mercantile business... something I truly had no stomach for.~ []
@1035167 = ~GgrrrrlglAAAAARRRRGHGHGHG!!~ []
@1035169 = ~I would have given much for my father to be my mentor... but, instead, I endured his abuse until I was able to squire for the Order. I fled as quickly as I was able to.~ []
@1035176 = ~I... I suppose I am telling you this because you remind me a little of my sister, Moira. She is young and determined... I miss her... perhaps the only thing of my family I miss.~ []
@1035177 = ~I regret abandoning her to her fate, alone with Lord Cor... but there was... little I could do. She... I am sure she...~ []
@1035178 = ~No. Never mind. I do not wish to speak further about this, <CHARNAME>... excuse me.~ []
@1035180 = ~Whining, is it? I simply mean to talk and you wound me so casually? Very well, then... I shall henceforth keep my thoughts to myself and away from your barbed tongue.~ []
@1035181 = ~I think you might have at that. I could not... I just never could stand up to him. He raises his voice and suddenly I am a little boy hiding in the pantry once again.~ []
@1035183 = ~I... I do wish to apologize for so abruptly ending our conversation yesterday. I meant no offense by it.~ [ANOMEN70]
@1035185 = ~Watch yourself, then, Anomen.~ []
@1035186 = ~This is not a good time to speak of such things... let us just continue on.~ []
@1035188 = ~I am glad to hear of it. I... I think of my sister, sometimes, alone in the manor with my father. From the last letter I received, it seemed as if she was bearing up well.~ []
@1035193 = ~I wonder, sometimes, what has become of her... alone in that mansion with my father. From the last letters I have received, she seems to be bearing up fairly well.~ []
@1035194 = ~Yes... yes, of course, my lady. It pains me that you are always so silent, but I will abide by your wishes.~ []
@1035196 = ~I tire of your constant whining... let's just continue on.~ []
@1035201 = ~If I am such a burden and a caustic presence to you, my lady, perhaps you would prefer it if I sought my adventures elsewhere. I've no wish to disturb you... nor to be insulted.~ []
@1035204 = ~I'm sorry, Anomen... I didn't mean to insult you. Please forgive me.~ []
@1035208 = ~We grew up together and I've tolerated her presence... beyond that, she's proven herself useful occasionally.~ []
@1035211 = ~Ah. If Moira were to be placed in the same situation as your Imoen, I... I am not sure what lengths I would go to free her. I would give my own soul, if need be.~ []
@1035212 = ~I'm sure you have your reasons for seeking Imoen's rescue... even if it is just to find this wizard. I, myself, shall devote myself to seeking her freedom.~ []
@1035213 = ~Of course, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1035222 = ~I remember when I first achieved the rank of squire. It had been a difficult task... my father had refused to be my patron, so I was no better off than a commoner would be.~ []
@1035224 = ~I was proud during the ceremony, and happy... but it was not to last. My father, Lord Cor, stumbled into the Order's headquarters... he was filthy drunk and full of rage.~ []
@1035225 = ~He began shouting at the knights... at Sir Ryan Trawl, no less... that I had been stolen from him. That I was a worthless and weak son who should not be in the Order.~ []
@1035226 = ~Sir Ryan Trawl told him that I had proven myself... but the old bastard would hear none of it. They were finally forced to drag him out of the headquarters, kicking and screaming.~ []
@1035234 = ~No, I'm sorry, Anomen. I meant nothing by it. Please... tell me what you were thinking of, if you still wish to.~ []
@1035235 = ~(sigh)  As... as you wish, my lady. I was hoping to speak to another for a moment, but I've no desire to burden you.~ []
@1035237 = ~You've left me little choice, my lady. So be it... so long as you remain a force for righteousness, I shall remain by your side, silent. For now.~ []
@1035238 = ~Well... as you wish. I have often been accused of a worrisome tongue and a quick temper, myself. I accept your apology, my lady.~ []
@1035239 = ~'Tis difficult, my lady. Since the death of my mother, my father has been a cancer in my soul... a force against which I have struggled for years to prove myself.~ []
@1035240 = ~As am I. Since my mother's death, my father has been the force against which I have always struggled to prove myself... an invisible cancer which I cannot vanquish.~ []
@1035242 = ~I... yes, I am finished my whining, my lady. My... apologies... for burdening you with my dark thoughts. I shall refrain in the future.~ []
@1035244 = ~Don't be ridiculous, Anomen. You've overcome many obstacles... you should be proud of your accomplishments.~ []
@1035248 = ~Yes... I should harden myself. I suppose you are correct. Let us... continue on our journey, here, my lady.~ []
@1035261 = ~My mother, however, was a follower of Helm and known to Sir Ryan Trawl. She... petitioned the Knight-Commander on my behalf, begging him not to turn me away.~ []
@1035262 = ~So Sir Ryan Trawl allowed me to enter as a novitiate to Helm. I trained as a cleric and learned my sword arts from the guardians of the temple... and was able to eventually squire.~ []
@1035263 = ~A long road it has been for me, <CHARNAME>... but I am pleased to serve in the Order under Helm's name. And I trust that Helm is pleased with me, as well.~ []
@1035265 = ~I am. But that is not the way it has always been, my lady. One does not show up young and penniless and begin a career to knighthood straight away... not within the Order.~ []
@1035266 = ~What of you, then, <CHARNAME>? You are a force for righteousness and honor... why do you not join the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart and achieve glory, as well?~ []
@1035267 = ~What of you, then, <CHARNAME>? You told me once that you were a force for righteousness... does that still hold true? Do you still seek to defend the lands against evil?~ []
@1035270 = ~I doubt they would have me, Anomen... besides that, I am hardly interested.~ []
@1035273 = ~I'll do whatever I need to... I hold myself to no tenets, Anomen.~ []
@1035287 = ~Bah! I tire of all this talk... let us just continue your quest, here, in silence for a while.~ []
@1035311 = ~My lady... I feel most terrible about my burst of temper the previous day. Would... would you allow me the opportunity to apologize and try to explain?~ [ANOMEN73]
@1035312 = ~Very well... I will listen to what you have to say.~ []
@1035319 = ~I am most thankful, <CHARNAME>. Sometimes, you see... my zeal for justice and valour can become too much. There is an anger in my heart that I... cannot seem to control.~ []
@1035321 = ~I see injustices everywhere, my lady, and... and I wish to do nothing but strike out against them. But even when I do... I keep on striking out... the hate and anger only grows...~ []
@1035322 = ~When I spoke to you of fighting against evil... I became angry, but it... it was more anger at my own inability to... to be as good and lawful as I might wish to be.~ []
@1035325 = ~Everyone feels at least a little as you do, Anomen... I am sure even the most noble paladin feels anger and hate.~ []
@1035326 = ~You are not unworthy... you just need to strive harder to achieve self-control, Anomen.~ []
@1035328 = ~But I must. An apology alone is not enough... this harsh zeal overtakes me at times. There... there is an anger inside me that I cannot seem to control, <CHARNAME>...~ []
@1035335 = ~Please, my lady... you must hear me through. Allow me to explain my actions or you shall leave me to feel truly unworthy!~ []
@1035340 = ~I... I see. Please... accept my most humble apology, then, and we can... continue on, and I shall remain silent.~ []
@1035342 = ~Again you remind me of my sister, Moira. She, too, has a decent soul and a benevolent heart. You should meet her sometime, <CHARNAME>... I truly think you would like each other.~ []
@1035343 = ~I... do not think that is true. The paladins in the Order speak only of contentment... and I have none of that. But I thank you for your kind words, regardless.~ []
@1035346 = ~I suppose you are correct, my lady. I must... struggle... to continue my battle against evil. And I must struggle to achieve this contentment that others speak of.~ []
@1035348 = ~You... you wound me, my lady. I had thought to find a sympathetic soul to confess my sin... you are far less like my dear Moira then I thought.~ []
@1035351 = ~You are correct, of course. I was a fool to let my anger overtake me... but I had hoped you might be able to discern my true intentions. I shall leave you be, then, my lady.~ []
@1035352 = ~Sorcerous Amin~ []
@1035355 = ~I... I have done something most heinous. This killing of Saerk and his... his daughter... I am not sure that I have done the right thing.~ [ANOMEN74]
@1035360 = ~You... you suggested that I take this course of action, my lady. I need your reassurance that there was nothing else that could be done... please.~ []
@1035363 = ~You had to uphold your family's honor, Anomen... nothing is more important than that.~ []
@1035371 = ~Yes... yes, you speak the truth, and I am glad to hear it. That monster would never have paid as he should have for Moira's death!~ []
@1035373 = ~But... still, my lady... it does not sit well with me that I gave into my great hate so easily. Nor that I enjoyed it so much. I thank you for speaking with me of it, though.~ []
@1035374 = ~Yes, I suppose you are correct. I know not how much honor my father has, but I have a duty to my family that I cannot ignore. I... had to do it for Moira, if nothing else.~ []
@1035375 = ~Yes, Saerk had to be destroyed. I am... uncomfortable with the thought of having killed his daughter, but it was his actions that forced me to those extremes.~ []
@1035376 = ~Too far? I did only what I had to... and what you suggested! If I... if I killed the girl, it was only because Saerk forced my hand. It was his fault!~ []
@1035377 = ~I... had a duty to protect my family... to avenge my sister's death. Saerk... had to understand what he had done. I... did my best, <CHARNAME>... and now you abandon me...~ []
@1035378 = ~I no longer know what I should do. I... shall have to think on this. Let us... walk on, for now.~ []
@1035379 = ~I shall try, my lady. I had hoped to receive your good council again as I did to resolve my conflict, before. Perhaps... perhaps another time.~ []
@1035380 = ~My anger has built to the point when I am shaking with pure rage! I... I must speak to you. I must gain some reassurance!~ [ANOMEN75]
@1035383 = ~My father... that rude, drunken bastard! He has cast me out of the family when I was only doing what I must! I cannot take vengeance when there is no proof, and he knows it!~ []
@1035384 = ~And yet... my heart cries out for vengeance! That my sister should lie murdered and the murderer laughs, untouched...! I am so full of hate I can barely control it!~ []
@1035385 = ~Please, my lady... you are the one I turned to for guidance when I was torn. Did I do the right thing? Should the dictates of honor truly overcome duty and justice?!~ []
@1035386 = ~Of course, Anomen... how would you feel if you killed Saerk and found him to be innocent after the fact?~ []
@1035387 = ~It is not your place to seek justice... that is the duty of the law. You did all you could.~ []
@1035388 = ~You must learn to control this anger, Anomen. You knew this was the right path... and it is the way of the Order, as well.~ []
@1035391 = ~Aye... aye, that would be a stain to my honor I surely could not bear. But I still feel so helpless. Surely... surely Saerk will pay, eventually for what he has done.~ []
@1035392 = ~I feel a little better, now, my lady. My thanks for your consolation. Nothing, however, will take away this burning pain in my heart. (sigh)  Let us just move on.~ []
@1035394 = ~I know what you say is true, my lady. But my sister lies cold and unavenged, and the murderer laughs free. Surely the gods will... make him pay. (sigh)  I know I cannot.~ []
@1035395 = ~But you were the one who advised me! How can I rest when I know that there was no other course than for me to avenge my sister! The murderer is free, and my heart cries out for his blood!~ []
@1035397 = ~I... I will have to think on this. It was... the path of honor, and I should be content. But... but... (sigh)  No. I will not speak to you of this. Let us move on, now.~ []
@1035403 = ~It is everything I have strived for... after years spent proving myself. I... don't know what I would do if I failed the Test...~ []
@1035404 = ~And, yet, suddenly I am quite sure that I will fail it. It is my heart that will betray me. I feel faithless and worthless in my soul... and they will know of it.~ []
@1035405 = ~What do you think, my lady? Am I really so terrible? I have tried so hard, and yet it all seems to come to naught. Do you... do you think I will fail the Test, as well?~ []
@1035407 = ~You may... and you should be prepared for such an eventuality.~ []
@1035408 = ~You must be confident that you follow the right path, Anomen. If you follow your conscience, how can they refuse you?~ []
@1035412 = ~You... you truly think so, my lady? It is a pleasure to hear you say such, but I somehow doubt it will be so simple. Even if you are just reassuring me, I do thank you for it.~ []
@1035414 = ~Aaahh... the Test will come for me soon enough, I suppose. And I doubt there is much more I can do between now and then to rectify my failings. What will come will come.~ []
@1035415 = ~Because I do not know my own conscience, my lady. I would not turn to others for guidance if I did... but I do thank you humbly for your council. You are most kind.~ []
@1035416 = ~I suppose that is expected... You cannot counsel my heart, can you? I simply wish that I knew what my own conscience dictated. A worthy knight would know, yes?~ []
@1035418 = ~You have made it plain for me, my lady. As plain as your thinly-disguised contempt for my heart. I will pass or fail the Test, I suppose... but it will be no thanks to you.~ []
@1035424 = ~I have been told a few things of your travels in the north and in Baldur's Gate in particular. Your adventures are... impressive, my lady. The equal of any great heroine.~ []
@1035426 = ~This man, Sarevok... I am told he was your brother. Is this true?~ []
@1035428 = ~Well... he was my half-brother, more or less. We... had the same father.~ []
@1035429 = ~He was my brother in that I am a child of the god, Bhaal, and so was he... if that's what you mean.~ []
@1035433 = ~You... speak so carefully, my lady, because you have been accused of some manner of relation with the dead god of murder, yes? He who was named Bhaal?~ []
@1035434 = ~You need not deny it. I was surprised, however, since you have maintained an honorable existence. I... I cannot imagine what impulses your heritage must fill you with..~ []
@1035435 = ~You need not deny it... I see evidence of this from some of your more base impulses. I do not judge you, however. I, myself, can lay claim to no pure heart.~ []
@1035436 = ~This Sarevok was a man of great power and of similar godly heritage... and yet you maintained the higher road and saved the north from great chaos and destruction.~ []
@1035438 = ~Yes, I know of this. And I can see the signs. I cannot imagine what it must be like... and I can claim no purity, myself, so I can only judge your actions.~ []
@1035443 = ~I am not discussing Sarevok with you, Anomen... nor my activities in the Sword Coast.~ []
@1035446 = ~Aye... and were that I could be so calm about my own. I do wish you would trust me with more details, but I have no need to pry. Forgive me, my lady.~ []
@1035448 = ~Come... let us continue on your journey so that I may think.~ []
@1035449 = ~But you have not always succeeded, yes? I suppose calls of the blood do not need to rule one. Your actions belie whatever motivations you might have... something to ponder.~ []
@1035452 = ~My lady, I have been pondering your situation for some time... this matter of your peculiar heritage... and I find myself filled with admiration and wonder for you, truly.~ [ANOMEN78]
@1035453 = ~The blood of the former god of murder flows through your veins... and yet you are an honorable woman. You have done many great things and have earned respect.~ []
@1035455 = ~My path is quite clear, Anomen. There is no internal struggle... I am not controlled by my blood.~ []
@1035462 = ~Just... just stand away from me, woman! I stand on the precipice of a test that will decide whether my dream dies, and you are not helping! Away from me, so that I might think!~ []
@1035463 = ~Yes... always a struggle. And, yet, you always manage to come out on top, do you not?~ []
@1035464 = ~It must be so easy for you, my lady... you are a force for good and this blood seems to have no powerful influence over you. 'Always a struggle'? Bah!~ []
@1035465 = ~If I had such evil blood in me, I would be writhing on the ground! I... I could not do what you do! Why must I constantly endure this?!~ []
@1035467 = ~I am full of an anger that I cannot quench, yet one that places my soul in peril... and this is something that I should get over? You are a cruel woman, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1035469 = ~I thought we had become better confidantes than this. I stand on the precipice of a test that will decide whether my dream dies, and you are hesitant to even help me?~ []
@1035470 = ~My lady, I have been pondering your situation for some time... this matter of your peculiar heritage... and I find myself filled with questions that I am almost loath to ask.~ [ANOMEN79]
@1035471 = ~War Hammer +2, +1 electrical: 'Borok's Fist'
Borok Thundercracker was a dwarven hero who led several campaigns against giants and other "tall vermin" that had plagued his people in a number of their communities. This hammer was his blessed weapon, which his elven allies called his "little iron fist," though not to his face.

STATISTICS:

Combat Abilities:
THAC0: +2 bonus
Damage: 1D4 + 3, +1 electrical
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 5
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 9 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Mage
 Thief
 Monk
 Beast Master
~ []
@1035473 = ~Is there a struggle inside you, my lady? Do you have your rage bottled up inside you, as I do? Is there... is there a fight against evil in your heart?~ []
@1035488 = ~My wife and I... were always close, but lately my business has taken much of my time. It has been difficult, and I knew she was unhappy but... I...~ []
@1035490 = ~I... I am truly sorry, my lady. I asked a question of you, and my response to your answer was nothing short of reprehensible. Please... please forgive me.~ [ANOMEN80]
@1035492 = ~Of course... it is no trouble.~ []
@1035493 = ~Forget it, Anomen. I've received enough abuse from you... and more than enough apologies.~ []
@1035494 = ~Fine, fine... but let's get moving. We haven't time for chit-chat right now.~ []
@1035496 = ~The answer is obvious. Your honor has been maligned. Kill them both for their trespass!~ []
@1035497 = ~She will realize where she belongs, I am sure. Do not make a crisis of this.~ []
@1035513 = ~Joining the Order is important to you, Anomen... you should remain vigilant and steel yourself.~ []
@1035515 = ~Joining the Order is important to you, Anomen... you should remain vigilant and steel yourself.~ []
@1035524 = ~I had simply thought that you were a kindred sort, <CHARNAME>. I see a similar struggle in you... and thought that, as a friend, you might understand me a little.~ []
@1035527 = ~Fine, fine. Let's just continue on... we've no time for this chit-chat.~ []
@1035528 = ~Y-yes... thank you for your understanding, I suppose. I simply wish we had more time to speak. More important matters press, however... let us continue your journey.~ []
@1035530 = ~I appreciate your assistance, but it is most confusing. I shall... try to remain vigilant, as you suggest, but I think I will need to work it out for myself.~ []
@1035532 = ~I am not to worry over joining the Order? Fine advice, now that I sit and regret not paying my duty to my family. Saerk sits alive... on your advice, I might add.~ []
@1035533 = ~I appreciate your assistance, <CHARNAME>, but it is most confusing. Perhaps the Order is not worth such agony... it is something I must devote some thought to on my own.~ []
@1035534 = ~Aye. Your advice has always been constant, pointing me back towards the good. Saerk is alive, which is sad but is the lawful course. And... and the Order is my dream.~ []
@1035536 = ~Thank you, <CHARNAME>... your kind words gladden me more than I can say. Your advice means much... you are a... a dark flame, my lady, that I am drawn to almost against my will.~ []
@1035537 = ~But 'tis a most pleasurable experience. You have been kind despite my own boorishness. Perhaps one day... we will speak of other things. I... I think I would like that.~ []
@1035538 = ~Mmm. Your view of the Order's tenets are obvious. You advised me to do my duty by my family... and justice was brought to Saerk and his family, as it should have been.~ []
@1035540 = ~Perhaps the Order is not all I have always thought it to be. Perhaps you are right to advise me to worry less... no doubt I would be happier.~ []
@1035545 = ~It seems that you know little of me, after all. I had thought you a kindred spirit. Perhaps... perhaps I was wrong. (sigh)  Let us just... continue and I shall handle my problems myself.~ []
@1035546 = ~Aye, which is no less than I expected. Always I must struggle on my own. You are wise, my lady... as always. I had simply hoped for... for more.~ []
@1035547 = ~Let us just... move on, then, and continue your quest. It will not be long now, anyway, before my Test comes and my questions will be answered for myself.~ []
@1035548 = ~I am glad to hear that, my lady. I see within you one who goes through a similar struggle as I do... although you do not complain about it half as much as I.~ []
@1035555 = ~Freedom (Abjuration) 
Level: 9
Range: Special 
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None 

NOTE: Cast this spell in an area where you know someone is imprisoned and they will be released.
This spell is the reverse of the ninth level wizard spell Imprisonment. When a creature is imprisoned, he or she is trapped in a sphere far beneath the surface of the earth. If this spell is cast in the area where the imprisonment took place, it will instantly free the victim, who will reappear exactly where he or she was standing prior to being imprisoned. This spell will also cancel the effects of the spell Maze.~ []
@1035558 = ~My Test is coming very soon, my lady. I will need to go to the headquarters of the Order and speak to Ryan Trawl. I... I am not looking forward to the judgement I shall receive there.~ []
@1035563 = ~They are fair, my lady. I am not unsettled by the chance they will make the wrong decision... I am unsettled by the chance that they will make the right one.~ []
@1035564 = ~I... have been thinking on what we have spoken of. I have studied to join the Order as long as I can remember, and suddenly I am unsure if I should even want to.~ []
@1035565 = ~I have done as you said, and my wife and I are together once more. She was shamed by her breach of our vows, so we are united in our duty to the sanctity of our commitment again.~ []
@1035566 = ~What if I am accepted into the Order and I find I have no true place in it? And what if I am refused... and I discover the future has no place for me?~ []
@1035568 = ~There is not the spark we once had, but this is a more realistic pairing now. We have put out the fires of our youth. Thank you again.~ []
@1035569 = ~I know, deep down inside, that I have maintained good faith. But... perhaps I am wrong. Perhaps I will only discover too late where my heart truly lies.~ []
@1035570 = ~I... I have done nothing and... and the situation with my wife is unchanged. She grows ever distant. I... thought you should know.~ []
@1035576 = ~I'm sure it won't be that bad... everything will work out as it should.~ []
@1035584 = ~None of us do, of course! These worms are barely worthy of stepping upon the floor of the house of the Storm Lord! Nevertheless, you will hear them!~ []
@1035589 = ~You will not think so after a few whining fools try to beg for gold or some other paltry service.~ []
@1035594 = ~You jest with me, my lady. I think you would do far better in my position. You are a strong woman. I, on the other hand, am too susceptible to my own desires.~ []
@1035596 = ~I have been thinking about Sir Cadril and the Order, and I have decided I am well rid of them! I cannot believe I wasted so much of my life on such ignorant fools!~ [ANOMEN82]
@1035601 = ~That's good to see... you could use a little freedom, I think.~ []
@1035604 = ~Greater Restoration (Necromancy) 
Level: 7
Sphere: Necromantic
Range: Touch
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: Target Creature
Saving Throw: None 

When this spell is cast, the life energy level of the target is raised, reversing any previous level drain which may have occurred. A restoration spell will also restore the intelligence of a creature affected by a Feeblemind spell. It also negates the negative mental influence of Confusion or being berserk, fully heals the target, and cures any disease or poisons. The casting of this spell is very draining on the priest, who likely will require rest immediately afterwards.~ []
@1035614 = ~No, I really don't think you understand. My name is Inspector Ardis, and I work for the city guard. Vilon and I have had an... understanding in the past.~ []
@1035618 = ~Aye, I could at that! Too long has this poor knight frowned and growled... I've enough of it, to tell the truth. I long to laugh and do as I like... and, by Helm, I shall!~ []
@1035620 = ~Well... perhaps a little. I have been part of the Order too long to shrug it off. But I know what is better for my heart. I feel lighter than I have since... since ever, I suppose.~ []
@1035622 = ~But I won't keep a beautiful woman waiting for me to quit my childish gazing about. I've no need to linger and look at pretty things so long as I am traveling with you, my lady.~ []
@1035625 = ~I've come to this point partly from your own advice, <CHARNAME>. You do not like it? Fair enough... I do, and 'tis more than enough for me.~ []
@1035626 = ~Well said and much appreciated by this formerly dour knight, my lady! 'Tis a grand thing to be complimented by a beautiful lady, especially one with your grace.~ []
@1035627 = ~There's much I'd like to see and do... but for now, it will suffice to keep the company of such a grand woman as yourself. Come, let us complete your quest post-haste.~ []
@1035630 = ~My lady... I have been watching you most intently these past few hours and I have come to a conclusion about you. Would you like to hear my thoughts?~ [ANOMEN83]
@1035641 = ~I refrained from telling you how I felt, of course... it is not proper for a knight of the Order to be so unbecoming. But I am under no such restrictions, now.~ []
@1035643 = ~You are a beautiful woman, <CHARNAME>... full of a life that I have always desired. I wish to experience new things, now that I am free... and I wish to be closer to you.~ []
@1035648 = ~A kiss? I... I suppose so...~ []
@1035655 = ~Yes, that was a desirable choice. Their petty problems are hardly worth the ear of the church. Still, I'm sure there could have been greater destruction in the result. Keep this in mind in future.~ []
@1035657 = ~Ha HA! Marvelous! Death, destruction of vows, and coin for the church coffers on top! A fine coup against the forces of order. You will make a fine Stormlord. Here is your share of the reward.~ []
@1035660 = ~I advised a merchant to forgive his wife her transgressions. They are happy now.~ []
@1035665 = ~Then close your eyes, and I shall do the same... we shall meet for a moment as if we were two innocents coming together in the dark. A single brush of our lips, a kiss...~ []
@1035666 = ~... and there... I shall savor this, my dear, this most sweet favor of yours. I know many pretty lines of poetry from my teachings, but I have never known the favor of a woman.~ []
@1035667 = ~Of all the things I might wish to experience, this is the one I most longed for. A promise for what is to come. Let us... continue on, now, lest the others begin to stare.~ []
@1035669 = ~You could turn the world aside with your power and skill as easily as you brush aside my advances... I follow you willingly and with vigor, and I shall continue to do so.~ []
@1035670 = ~You've refused me, of course... no less than I expected. I am a poor excuse for a courtier and a poorer excuse for a lover, but I shall not give up so easily, my lady.~ []
@1035671 = ~You may have captured me, but I am not so helpless... one day, I shall capture you, too. Either that or I am the simple fool that I appear to be, hm? We shall see.~ []
@1035672 = ~Now... let us catch up with our companions before their stares grow more curious.~ []
@1035675 = ~Nowhere did Talos mention this 'They are Happy Now!!' No, I really do not think you understand the edicts of the Talassan faith!~ []
@1035678 = ~As you wish... but no funny business.~ []
@1035679 = ~I am tired, Anomen... I wish only to sleep.~ []
@1035683 = ~Come aside, then, and let us talk in earnest. I... I spoke to you earlier of my feelings for you, <CHARNAME>. If you thought that I was being facetious, then I apologize.~ []
@1035684 = ~Still, I would have you remember that you are a servant of Talos, and his will must be demonstrated in yours. Do try harder.~ []
@1035685 = ~Nothing would make me happier than to please you... and to lay with you tonight. I have dreamt about this moment, my lady, and I believe the moment is right.~ []
@1035687 = ~Here... in this place. Let me remove my tunic and you may gaze upon my body, honed through years of exertion... and you may decide for yourself if I am worthy of you.~ []
@1035692 = ~Come with me, then, for I consider nothing I have to say or offer to be funny. If you consider me flippant, then I apologize... my yearning for you is both true and honest.~ []
@1035694 = ~I had arranged for Inspector Ardis to meet with you. He has in the past been most cooperative, especially in dealing with those that confess to certain acts.~ []
@1035695 = ~Please reconsider, <CHARNAME>. I cannot stand alone a moment longer, looking upon you without touching... come aside with me and let me speak plainly of these things.~ []
@1035697 = ~Fine... but no funny business.~ []
@1035698 = ~Forget it... I said I wasn't interested and I meant it.~ []
@1035700 = ~I do not wish to be alone, my lady... I wish to be with you! For ones such as we, the time for solitude and love comes so seldom... do not turn me aside, <CHARNAME>, I beg of you.~ []
@1035701 = ~Very well... I will go with you.~ []
@1035702 = ~Fine... but no funny business.~ []
@1035703 = ~No, Anomen... and I mean it.~ []
@1035705 = ~This is talk, my lady... this is me telling you both of my desire and my love for you... I want to enfold you with my strength and feel yours. I want to listen to your heartbeat and feel it.~ []
@1035706 = ~This is talk, my lady... this is me telling you of my desire and my love. I want to listen to your heartbeat and I want you to feel mine.~ []
@1035707 = ~I want to experience passion, <CHARNAME>, and I want to experience it with you. Please do not deny me this... I do not think I could stand it.~ []
@1035709 = ~Very well, then, Anomen... you've won me over.~ []
@1035711 = ~I shall find another, <CHARNAME>. One day, perhaps... and I hope she will be as beautiful and alluring as you.~ []
@1035714 = ~Hmmm. I have been thinking. I am still a bit bitter at being rejected by the Order, but... in many ways, I have never felt so... happy. Is that not odd?~ [ANOMEN85]
@1035724 = ~But it is not just that. Not a month ago, I never would have foreseen this. Rejected by the Order, I would have thought my life over. But the freedom... it is most intoxicating.~ []
@1035725 = ~I killed a man. It wasn't... it wasn't self-defense. Others have said it was, but I know better. He... he did issue a challenge, and we did fight, but he said such things...~ []
@1035726 = ~I need no longer restrict myself to dusty codes of conduct and goodness. No more worrying about honor... I may do as I please and live life as I wish. And I have found you.~ []
@1035728 = ~And I know that I have not done anything untoward. Helm has not been offended... he accepts my worship, still. The Order has turned me aside, but my God knows better.~ []
@1035729 = ~Things have gone well, I think. Helm has worked a mysterious trick on my destiny. We are meant to be together, you and I... I am interested to see what will come of it.~ []
@1035730 = ~I agree... we are meant to be together.~ []
@1035731 = ~I do not think you should talk so flippantly of what Helm is thinking... overconfidence can be dangerous.~ []
@1035734 = ~Don't go making plans... you may not be around to see them through.~ []
@1035736 = ~Simple. Kill all the witnesses. It was an innocent duel if no one is left to say different.~ []
@1035753 = ~Hmm. Do you suspect me of still being bitter against the Order, then, my lady? Perhaps a little, I am... but moreover I am glad to be rid of the yoke of that sad group of men.~ []
@1035756 = ~Well, I'm pleased to hear you say that, my lady. I've become quite used to your company over our time together... and I have no wish to see us part ways.~ []
@1035757 = ~I think I know what Helm approves or disapproves of better than some, my lady. He has not abandoned me... at least not yet.~ []
@1035758 = ~Deny it if you wish, my lady, 'tis destiny and there is no denying it. But... you are likely correct. Fate likely has a few surprises in store for us, yet.~ []
@1035759 = ~Aye. Death may come at any time for either of us, 'tis true. No one may know what fate has up its sleeve... but I'll make a wager on it, regardless, my lady.~ []
@1035760 = ~We are to rest, now, are we? That is good. Come, my lady... I wish to speak with you for a moment away from the ears of others.~ [ANOMEN86]
@1035761 = ~I... have something I must say to you, <CHARNAME>. I do not wish you to think me flippant or lacking in sincerity... I mean this most honestly, what I will say.~ []
@1035763 = ~My... my life is full of chaos, now, and I wish for there to be one thing that is permanent. So I offer my heart to you, along with my service and my companionship.~ []
@1035766 = ~Mounted knights cannot effectively use long pole weapons while on horseback, and as a result, many weapons have been fitted with shorter shafts so they may be wielded with just one hand. Maces and flails are two previous examples of this -- the war hammer is another. The horseman's war hammer is a descendent of the Lucerne hammer. It is made entirely of steel, with rondels protecting and strengthening the grip. Rondels are small disks of metal, often shaped into decorative designs. The shaft is about 18 inches long. Powerful magical energy flows through this weapon, though its origins are unknown.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2 bonus
Damage: 1D4 + 3
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 5
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 9 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Mage 
 Thief
 Monk
 Beast Master~ []
@1035770 = ~No, Anomen... I do not love you.~ []
@1035772 = ~Most wondrous occasion! I will shout my love to the heavens themselves! I shall be your faithful servant and your lover... let nothing else come between us.~ []
@1035773 = ~I... I hope that means that I have some measure of affection from you, as well. If that is so, then I agree to your acceptance. I shall be your faithful servant for as long as fate allows.~ []
@1035774 = ~Yes. Yes, you tell the truth of it. It matters not, my love... I shall remain at your side until this quest of yours is completed. And... perhaps then your mind will have changed its course.~ []
@1035775 = ~Ahhhh... the truth burns my soul, to hear such words from your lips!~ []
@1035776 = ~But... better to have it said, now, than to suffer at length. Turned away from the Order and my love, both...'tis my fate, it seems.~ []
@1035777 = ~I shall say it only one more time, then... I love you, <CHARNAME>. I love you faithfully and truly, and that shall never end. And... and I shall bother you no more.~ []
@1035778 = ~I am out of my mind, yes. Out of my mind with love and adoration. And, yet, to be scorned so by you... it burns my soul to hear such.~ []
@1035779 = ~I... I thought that there was more between us. Or perhaps you mean to drive me away, I am unsure. If so... you are successful in your plan.~ []
@1035780 = ~I... I cannot stay, for I love you still and cannot remain in your sight knowing that you scorn me so. Farewell, then, my love... you will see me not again.~ []
@1035781 = ~A glorious day it is, my lady! I have achieved my dream, and I owe much of that to your assistance and counsel. I... I am most grateful to you for it.~ [ANOMEN87]
@1035782 = ~Thank you... I was happy to help.~ []
@1035785 = ~Good for you... now we need to get moving.~ []
@1035786 = ~And help you did. Meeting your group of fellows has affected me in the most fortunate way. To think I had such grave doubts... that seems like another time for me, now.~ []
@1035787 = ~I spoke to Sir Ryan Trawl before I left the headquarters... he wishes me to lead an expedition to the far south. I will have my own soldiers under my command, <CHARNAME>!~ []
@1035790 = ~Sir Ryan Trawl also mentioned that my duties with the Order could be put aside for the moment so that I might continue my travels with you.~ []
@1035791 = ~Short Sword +2
The short sword is the first type of sword to come into existence. In the simplest of terms, a short sword can be considered a dagger with a blade so long that it can no longer be called a dagger. The term 'short sword' does not exist in sword classifications. However, it has come to be used to describe a double-edged blade about two feet in length. The sword tip is usually pointed, ideal for thrusting. There are etched runes on the surface of this weapon that glow during combat, indicating it has undergone some form of enchantment, but no identifying marks can be found.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2 bonus
Damage: 1D6 + 2
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 2
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: Short Sword
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 5 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Cleric 
 Mage
 Beast Master~ []
@1035792 = ~Very few novices are given such permission after they achieve the rank of knight. I feel quite privileged. Come... let us continue your journey and save your sister, yes?~ []
@1035797 = ~You see this flower I have picked, here? 'Tis a rare find... a crimson rhodelia, if I am not mistaken.~ [ANOMEN88]
@1035809 = ~I... I warned you not to open the sarcophagus! Run, my friends, run!!~ [SASSAR07]
@1035817 = ~I have said many times how grateful I am, but I have never told you that I was attracted to you from the start... your heart and your bright soul, not to mention your beauty.~ []
@1035818 = ~Do... do my words offend you, my lady? Have I overstepped myself?~ []
@1035819 = ~And rightly you should be. It is but a pale comparison to your true beauty, and possesses not a tenth of your merits... but it is the closest to you that I have found.~ []
@1035820 = ~I... I was not trying to be an idiot, as you say, my lady. I was seeking to speak pretty words to you, as pretty words I know well.~ []
@1035821 = ~But if I am... if I am being foolish, then I shall desist. Please forgive me for overstepping my bounds, my lady. I... I meant no harm.~ []
@1035827 = ~Come, then, good lady. Let us continue on your quest... we can talk more at a later time and I shall be free to complement you at your leisure.~ []
@1035829 = ~Do not tease me, though... I mean well and am honest when I speak of you, my lady. But I shall push no more... let us continue our travels... we can speak more later of it.~ []
@1035830 = ~I... I see. It was not my intent to offend you, my lady. I shall bother you no more with my sorry courting, then. Please... please forgive me.~ []
@1035834 = ~I'll go with you, Anomen... so long as there's no funny business.~ []
@1035835 = ~Forget it, Anomen... I just want to sleep.~ []
@1035840 = ~You are on the defensive and yet you taunt! Such gall!~ []
@1035843 = ~The gall is yours to think I am on the defensive when I have led you as a mantis does her prey! You will fall here, and you death shall be... delicious!~ []
@1035847 = ~You pound the stake through the vampire's foul heart. The creature shall prey no more on the blood of others.~ []
@1035850 = ~You have become the captain of my soul, and have kept me on the path of righteousness and good... and aided me in achieving a dream I had nearly thought to be impossible.~ []
@1035851 = ~I... I wish to become closer to you, <CHARNAME>. I wish to feel you in my arms, to caress your skin and lay with you in the night.~ []
@1035852 = ~Am I being too forward with you, my lady? Would you find a poor knight such as I an acceptable lover? I... would not be offended if you did not, I yearn only to be with you.~ []
@1035853 = ~You are not being too forward, Anomen... I wish to be with you, as well.~ []
@1035856 = ~Forget it, Anomen... I've no interest in this.~ []
@1035859 = ~The stench of death assaults your nostrils as the lid slides back. A feeling of raw evil power emanates from four golden limbs of bones that lie within: two complete arms and two complete legs of a golden skeleton. Magical energy swirls in the air around you and a creature appears.~ []
@1035860 = ~There is time enough for sleep, is there not? We have little enough time in our dangerous lives to steal a moment for ourselves... can I not persuade you to consider what I say?~ []
@1035863 = ~No, Anomen... I said no and I meant it.~ []
@1035865 = ~I am glad to hear it, my love. Come to me, then... I shall remove my too-worn armor and we can lay together for the eve... and I shall show you the love that I hold for you...~ []
@1035866 = ~I would yearn to hear words of reciprocation... but I shall accept your agreement, for now. I hope, in time, you will feel the same passion for me that I do for you.~ []
@1035867 = ~For now, however, I shall be content to show you passion... let me remove my worn armor and we may lay together, and I will be content for a time, with you...~ []
@1035868 = ~This is talk, my lady... this is me telling you of my desire and my love. I want to listen to your heartbeat and I want you to feel mine.~ []
@1035870 = ~I want to show you the depth of the passion I feel for you, my lady. If you... if you truly do not wish it, however, I will understand.~ []
@1035871 = ~Very well, Anomen... show me your passion, if you wish.~ []
@1035874 = ~Don't be a fool, Anomen. I said no, and I meant it... and I resent having to tell you twice!~ []
@1035876 = ~As you wish, my lady. Perhaps the time is not right or... perhaps you do not feel the same as I. I wish no answer, just yet. I am content to remain at your side, a follower and companion.~ []
@1035879 = ~I... I meant no offense. I only wished to express myself, and I seem to have done a poor job of it. I shall bother you no further, then, with my clumsy and inexperienced efforts.~ []
@1035880 = ~I have been thinking of many things, now, as we travel. I must admit that I never have felt happier and more content... and yet a week ago I would not have thought this even possible.~ [ANOMEN90]
@1035888 = ~Good for you... now let's keep moving.~ []
@1035907 = ~I have also been thinking of Saerk... and I am glad that you pushed me to refrain from taking vengeance on the man. There was no real evidence of his involvement, was there?~ []
@1035908 = ~It would have been wrong of me to listen to my father's ravings. Moira... she would not have wanted me to take bloody vengeance for her, not if it wasn't true.~ []
@1035909 = ~And, if... if Saerk did those things... well. Well, he will pay for them. Someday... I suppose. The gods will see to that.~ []
@1035912 = ~Aye, perhaps now is not the best time to talk. I only wished to thank you, my lady... for pushing me towards keeping the righteous path during that business.~ []
@1035913 = ~It... it would not have been right for me to take vengeance. And I achieved my dream in the Order, after all that. Father... will just have to be satisfied with things as they are... yes.~ []
@1035914 = ~Ah, but yet I ramble on, don't I? Come, impatient woman... let us keep moving, then.~ []
@1035916 = ~I hope that he will find it in himself to forget about Saerk and rebuild what he has lost. Perhaps he can find a new wife... lose the hatred that festers in his heart as I have.~ []
@1035917 = ~Ahhhh, it is a simple hope, is all. But not likely. Perhaps father will speak to me again when I next return to him. Moira... Moira would want me to, I think.~ []
@1035918 = ~(sigh)  But the thought saddens me, now, when I wanted to think of glad things. Such as you. Come, my love... let us move on, now.~ []
@1035928 = ~I just came back to thank you, <PRO_SIRMAAM>. You have saved my honor and my soul. I have made partial restitution to the family of the man I dueled, and they have forgiven me.~ []
@1035931 = ~I have returned to evaluate your performance with those that seek the advice of our lord Talos. What have you to tell me about Ti'Vael the dwarf? How did his problem work out?~ []
@1035939 = ~Be quick about it. I have to report on your value as a 'servant' of the people.~ []
@1035940 = ~Well done! Death and destruction all around, a man's life ruined, and profit for the church as well. That he lives to suffer is even more fitting.~ []
@1035941 = ~Excellent! Destruction, death, and the damning of a soul to torment. Talos surely approves.~ []
@1035953 = ~I advised him to forgive his wife her transgressions. They are happy now.~ []
@1035962 = ~I have returned to evaluate your performance of your duty to Helm. What have you to tell me about Ti'Vael the dwarf? How did you advise him to deal with his problem?~ []
@1035963 = ~Katana
The katana is a single-edged, slightly curved sword which ends in a chisel point. The katana is perhaps one of the finest swords ever made, the steps to its creation both complex and secret, and more an art form than anything else. This blade is an important facet of Kara-Tur culture. To touch or wield a samurai's katana is to insult the samurai and to incite his wrath. For a gaijin, or foreigner, to own such a blade is rare. Either the gaijin is a greatly honored friend of an important minister, or the gaijin has murdered a samurai.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1D10
Damage type: slashing
Weight: 6
Speed Factor: 4
Proficiency Type: Katana
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 6 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Cleric
 Mage
 Beast Master~ []
@1035970 = ~This is not the way of Helm! There were innocent souls requiring help, and you led them down the path of chaos! You have failed in your duty! This is inexcusable!~ []
@1035971 = ~You have misrepresented the Watcher and made a mockery of your role as a protector! I have no choice but to recommend you be stripped of the honor of specialty priest!~ []
@1035986 = ~I advised him to forgive his wife her transgressions. They are happy now.~ []
@1035994 = ~By the Morninglord! In whose estimation did you think this best?! I cannot imagine a greater lapse in judgement! You are not fit to guide people in the ways of Lathander!~ []
@1036007 = ~You make me sick! Many witnessed your little display with that dwarven fool! This is not the way of Talos! Where is the destruction? Where is the mayhem?~ []
@1036008 = ~You may think you have nothing to report to me about your advice to the dwarf Ti'Vael, but I know better. A friend in the guard has informed me that he is dead.~ []
@1036010 = ~So your benign advice put him off his guard and got him killed. I question the method, but the results please the church. In future, try to expand upon the chaos caused.~ []
@1036012 = ~You have done exceptionally well. By taking responsibility he has spared his soul a most dreadful anguish. This adherence to a higher law is very agreeable to Helm's teachings.~ []
@1036016 = ~A friend in the city guard has informed me about a sad occurrence. The dwarf you were to have given guidance has turned up dead. It would seem that he thought his crime would go unpunished.~ []
@1036019 = ~I have been speaking with some followers that belong to the guard, and they tell me that the dwarf Ti'Vael turned himself in on your advice.~ []
@1036020 = ~While the law is served in this case, I cannot help but wonder if the actual victims could not have been better provided for. Still, Ti'Vael will pay what penalty he thinks he must.~ []
@1036022 = ~When I first met you, my lady... there are many things that went through my head. The possibility that you were not what you seemed, for instance.~ []
@1036023 = ~But what was most striking was the immediacy with which you afflicted my heart. I ignored it, denied it... until recently. And now it consumes my every waking moment.~ []
@1036026 = ~There is so much chaos in your... in our... life, I find myself yearning for something that is permanent. I... would not ask you to promise anything you could not give, my lady.~ []
@1036028 = ~There is death waiting around every corner for us, I know. All I ask, then, is that you accept me as your servant... that, in the days to come, we shall struggle to remain together...~ []
@1036029 = ~That we shall not abandon each other. If I continue to remain with you, my love... I could not bear our parting. If... you cannot see that for us... please... tell me now...~ []
@1036031 = ~Really, <CHARNAME>, the advice you gave him could have been a little more proactive, and could have avoided this. If he had taken responsibility... well, what is done is done.~ []
@1036032 = ~I love you, too, Anomen... and I do not want us to part, either.~ []
@1036033 = ~I do not know what the future will bring, Anomen... but I do not want you to leave me.~ []
@1036037 = ~That you say this... pleases me more than I can express. Suddenly I have the desire to shout my love to the heavens, themselves. But I shall refrain... for now, at least.~ []
@1036038 = ~Let us return to the others, then, and spend the night together... and when we awake we shall continue on your quest.~ []
@1036039 = ~I had hoped that your affection would rival mine, but it would be too much. I am glad to remain... and I will bear up under the possibility that you may grow to love me, yet.~ []
@1036040 = ~I will prove myself worthy to you, my love. Let us... let us return to the others so that we may continue on your quest tomorrow.~ []
@1036041 = ~Aye, you speak the truth of it. This knight shall remain at your side, regardless, because he loves you yet... I shall protect you regardless of your desire.~ []
@1036044 = ~But you are a merciful lady, 'tis true. Better to tell me now and be quick with it. I shall tell you only once more then, and I shall be silent afterwards... I love you.~ []
@1036045 = ~And now I shall bother you no more. Let us... let us return to the others so that we might get our rest.~ []
@1036046 = ~I... I am out of my mind. I am out of my mind with love and with passion. You occupy it completely, and to hear you scorn me so hurts... hurts me more than I can bear.~ []
@1036047 = ~That you have led me this far saddens me... I trusted you, my lady. I trusted you and I gave you my heart, and you have abused it. Was I... was I so unworthy?~ []
@1036048 = ~But you have spoken your will and I shall not disregard it. But... nor can I stay. I shall say this only once more, then, and then I shall be on my way... I love you.~ []
@1036049 = ~And now I shall bother you no more. I... I am sorry, my love, that... that this did not work out between us. Fare you well...~ []
@1036050 = ~Wait, now... who approaches, here?~ [ANOMEN92]
@1036051 = ~Anomen Delryn, son of Lord Cor... I have found you, at last. I have been looking for you for quite some time.~ []
@1036053 = ~I have a letter for you... it is from your father, Lord Cor.~ []
@1036055 = ~Aye... your father bade me to track you down wherever you might be. With good gold, as well. Here is the letter... and I shall leave you, then, my commission done.~ []
@1036059 = ~... no... no, Helm's mercy, no!~ []
@1036061 = ~My... my father writes, here: "... the authorities have found Moira's murderers... a pair of disgruntled workers who were once under my employ..."~ []
@1036062 = ~"... not finding anything of worth, they demanded valuables from your sister and killed her when she could produce nothing. The men have been caught and confessed all..."~ []
@1036063 = ~"... I hear that you have failed the Order, so this should come as no burden to you. Your assistance with Saerk has restored my business, regardless, so I suppose I should thank you..."~ []
@1036064 = ~"... but, my fortunes restored, I cannot afford to have a scandalous son hanging about. A murderer and a failure... so I have declared that you are no longer my son..."~ []
@1036065 = ~"... it is not that I am ungrateful, but it just will not do to have myself associated with such a pathetic personage. Bad for business, you see. Regards... Lord Cor Delryn..."~ []
@1036066 = ~I... I lost everything I worked towards to perform my duty for my family... at his insistence... and he disowns me! He disowns me!!~ []
@1036070 = ~You... feel awful...~ []
@1036071 = ~Not... not worth my anger...~ []
@1036072 = ~... vengeance...~ []
@1036073 = ~NO!! I am not about to listen to you! Ahhh, foulsome wench! I... I have murdered an innocent man and his daughter!! I lost the Order!! And ALL OF IT AT YOUR URGING!!~ []
@1036074 = ~You are the one that has pushed me down this path! I... I cannot believe I have done all of this!! For you!! For my father!!~ []
@1036079 = ~I... I am doing what I must, <CHARNAME>. I love you... and I have lost everything. You... you did what you thought right... I forgive you, my love. But... but my father...~ []
@1036080 = ~... my father and I have a reckoning that will not be stopped. Him I do not forgive, nor will I ever. I am sorry, <CHARNAME>, but I must go to Athkatla, now...~ []
@1036081 = ~... I must go and atone for what I have done. And my father will atone with me. Fare... fare you well...~ []
@1036082 = ~Aye, but it is happening anyway. As it must, for I have lost everything. You... you I forgive, for you meant well. But my father...~ []
@1036083 = ~Aye... aye, you are right in that. You meant well, and are not responsible for my heart. I cannot blame you, my love. But... my father...~ []
@1036084 = ~Aye... you do not deserve my anger. What you did... you meant well by me, at least. I cannot blame you, my love. But... my father...~ []
@1036085 = ~This is the end, Father. Your thoughtless cruelty destroyed Mother... it destroyed Moira... and it destroyed me. I shall atone for my evil acts, and so shall you!~ [ANOMEN93]
@1036086 = ~I am no priest, my former son... you'll not see me bowing before any altars! Best be on your way before I get angry!~ [COR09]
@1036087 = ~You'll atone, father, whether you like it or not. I shall kill you... we shall die together and end this madness as it should be ended!~ []
@1036088 = ~You... you would kill me?! Bah! You're too weak to go through with such an act!~ []
@1036089 = ~It is no act. Prepare yourself, father, for I... what?! <CHARNAME>? What are you doing here?!~ []
@1036095 = ~This will take you further down the path toward evil, Anomen... do not do it.~ []
@1036096 = ~It's time for all this hate to end, Anomen... and you have to be the one to stop it!~ []
@1036102 = ~I intend to do this myself. I do not want you to dirty your hands, my love... but I will not stop whatever you intend. As I said before, then, father... prepare yourself!~ []
@1036103 = ~Very well, then. I... I had no wish for you to see this, but it matters not. I am atoning for what I have done... and father... as I said before... prepare yourself!~ []
@1036104 = ~Aye... aye, you speak the right of it. Father is not responsible solely for what I have done... it has always been I...~ []
@1036105 = ~There is an evil in my heart, I have always known this and I spoke of it to you. Hate and anger, twisted and black... and I... I cannot control it. But... nor can I live with it...~ []
@1036108 = ~Because you will be stronger, then... because we will be together.~ []
@1036110 = ~Aye. Aye, you speak the right of it. I do not wish to go down this path, no matter what my father has done to me. But... I may have no choice, my love.~ []
@1036111 = ~I... I cannot, my love. My heart overflows with rage, and it always has. I cannot live with this... and there is only one way to quench it, one way to atone. I am sorry...~ []
@1036112 = ~Aye... I love you, too. But it is already done. There is a hate in my heart, and only one way to quench it, to atone for what I have done. I... I am sorry, my love...~ []
@1036113 = ~Then... then that is enough for me. I will live on the hope that your love... will one day quench my hate. I thank you, <CHARNAME>, for... for stopping me.~ []
@1036114 = ~Bah! I always knew you were too much of a pansy to go through with it! I was right to disown you as I did... weak and pathetic, you are, since a boy, even!~ []
@1036115 = ~I could have been more, father, had you cared. I... I always loved you. And I still do.~ []
@1036117 = ~Aye. And still I do. We are so much alike, you and I. More than you will ever know. We... could have been so much more.~ []
@1036118 = ~Go, then. Go and tend to your petty schemes, I'll have no more of it. Perhaps one day, if you find some shred of enlightenment... perhaps, then, we'll speak again.~ []
@1036119 = ~... Aye... perhaps...~ []
@1036120 = ~I am sorry, my love, for all of this disturbance. You have a quest to attend to... and I intend to be there to assist you. Now... and forever more...~ []
@1036123 = ~<CHARNAME>,

Goodbye. No sappy farewells or crying over how things must be; I do neither of these things well, nor would I wish to. I have made a decision; one that is not ideal, but it is necessary. I can go nowhere without this shadow, and I wish to leave it behind. I am returning to the Harper Hold that I might face judgement there. I will plead the case as we saw it for whatever they accuse, and if they do not see reason then I will suffer what I must. Galvarey had detractors as well as allies, so I believe I can end this in my favor. If not, at least it will be an end.
 
I do not ask you to follow. I do this for myself, and there will be little or no gain for you. You may still be a target of violence, but perhaps their interest in you will wither beside the capture of a 'traitor.' 

For better or worse, I am taking control once more. I hope to see you again in better times. 

With Nature's love and mine,
Jaheira~ []
@1036124 = ~Together. Together, yes... but do you love me, <CHARNAME>? Am I only your companion, or will I have your strength to draw on?~ []
@1036126 = ~No... I do not love you in that way.~ []
@1036127 = ~Then what is done is done. I have always loved you, <CHARNAME>, but it ends here. I... I am sorry...~ []
@1036128 = ~Well, I'm not accustomed to getting such presents like this. I will have it looked into, and should a reward be appropriate, I will have it delivered to the temple.~ []
@1036131 = ~<CHARNAME>. I... I do love you, as I have said so many times. It is true. But... it is not enough. Not enough to assuage my dark soul.~ []
@1036132 = ~I cannot stay here, after what I have done. And I cannot stay with you. 
I... must go elsewhere. I am sorry... truly sorry.~ []
@1036135 = ~There... the fool is dead, and good riddance. I always knew he was weak, and now I've proved it.~ []
@1036136 = ~You, there... you are the harlot that Anomen adventured with, I see. What are your intentions, then?~ []
@1036138 = ~I will leave you, Lord Cor... but I want you to know that you destroyed a good man. I hope you can live with that.~ []
@1036168 = ~If I must. Speak, and spare no tawdry detail of your confession.~ []
@1036169 = ~I have been slaving away here for some years, and I find it a great insult that you have been promoted above me. It is inexcusable, and also quite perplexing.~ []
@1036176 = ~I demand satisfaction, and I demand it now. You have made offense, albeit indirectly, and now you will duel me, and you will die.~ []
@1036181 = ~Wakizashi
The wakizashi, or companion sword, is extremely important to samurai. It is worn at all times, even indoors, and is near the samurai when he sleeps at night. As finely made as the katana, the wakizashi is a shorter sword with a length between 12 and 24 inches, and is a dangerous weapon in the hands of a skilled user.

STATISTICS

Damage: 1D8
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Scimitar/Wakizashi/Ninja-To
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 5 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Cleric
 Mage
 Beast Master
~ []
@1036188 = ~You were too harsh on her. Though a lack of faith is a dangerous thing for a member of the church, it does not warrant banishment. She could have been made to see reason.~ []
@1036195 = ~Fine work! We will not tolerate any display of questioning! If a follower of Talos appears weak, they are to be culled from the herd.~ []
@1036207 = ~An undead thing pulls itself from the sarcophagus, mumbling angry words in some alien tongue. The thing turns its dead eyes towards you as you recoil in horror.~ []
@1036250 = ~Things stay as they are. Go home, Cotirso.~ []
@1036257 = ~I see. This follower didn't happen to wrong you in some way, did he? Have you been 'encouraged' to report him? Should I gag him on arrest to avoid hearing what he might say?~ []
@1036258 = ~No matter. I will get the praises of my superiors for bringing him in, and you will be heralded at your temple for sowing chaos and securing profit from it. I told you our relationship would be beneficial.~ []
@1036260 = ~Well, <CHARNAME>, haven't you been busy. Quite the bit of skullduggery you have perpetrated. Talos cannot help but chuckle at the lengths you are willing to go for him and the spirit of destruction.~ []
@1036263 = ~This has been a regrettable series of events, hasn't it? Poor Cotirso. He could not understand the will of Helm in this matter. Still, he chose his own fate, and that is empowering.~ []
@1036267 = ~Still, a life was saved, though I don't hold much hope for what he will do with it. For now, all is well again.~ []
@1036269 = ~Now there is a more serious matter to attend to. There is trouble ahead for the entire temple if we do not act. I'm sure you will agree when you hear what I have to say.~ []
@1036283 = ~Tonight, <CHARNAME>, You must enter the Talos temple and... and remove the threat to the coming of dawn. Kill Weathermistress Ada. She longs for our destruction, and she has given the order. You have little time, and the odds are great. Perhaps if Ada is struck down in the middle of their temple, they will think twice before attacking us. Be careful.~ []
@1036301 = ~You must protect the temple of Lathander, repelling all that try to kill those within. Failing that, you must convince the Lathanderites not to launch a revenge attack. Righteous fury can be as deadly as villainy.~ []
@1036304 = ~Your harsh duty is fulfilled, <CHARNAME>. There are casualties, but at least there are some participants left to mourn them. It is not easy to stand in the path of anger, but you have stood tall.~ []
@1036307 = ~I should not wish to experience such again.~ []
@1036315 = ~Among mankind's earliest weapons, dating back to the most primitive of times, the first spears were simply wooden poles or sticks that had been sharpened at one end. Upon mastering the use of metals, weaponsmiths forged spear heads from iron and steel, and began experimenting with different types of spear heads, thus leading to the development of certain types of polearms. Another line of tinkering led to the use of magic in spear construction. Tribal shamans would enchant a spear so that it would hit more often, and do greater damage to its wielder's opponents.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +2 bonus
Damage: 1D6 + 2
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 4
Proficiency Type: Spear 
Type: 2-handed
Requires: 5 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Cleric
 Mage
 Thief
 Monk
 Beast Master~ []
@1036336 = ~Go with Talos, and let your footfalls crush the hopes of the peaceful everywhere!~ []
@1036338 = ~The two-handed sword is a derivative of the long sword. Weaponsmiths have always looked for ways to improve existing weapons, and in an effort to improve the long sword, the blade was lengthened. Eventually, the handle had to be extended and two hands became necessary to properly swing the sword. The primary function of two-handed swords is cleaving mounted knights and breaking up pike formations. This particular sword is even more capable of such functions, serving as a fearful reminder of what comes of the union between weaponsmithing and sorcery.

