@1036339 = ~Wait... one approaches, and his appearance seems familiar to me...~ [ANOMEN95]
@1036340 = ~Sir Anomen, the former son of Lord Cor... I have found you, at last. I have been looking for you for quite some time.~ []
@1036341 = ~Ah, yes... you are the messenger who brought me tidings of my sister. 'Tis not more grim news you bear, is it?~ []
@1036345 = ~Very well... give me your missive then, and be gone with my thanks.~ []
@1036348 = ~... no... no, Helm's mercy, no!~ []
@1036350 = ~The... the Magistrate... she writes: "... It is my regret to inform you that your father, Lord Cor, was killed in an attempt to take vengeance of the merchant, Saerk, on his own..."~ []
@1036352 = ~"... Your father was reacting to recent evidence uncovered proving that Saerk Farrahd was, indeed, responsible for the hiring of the men that killed your sister, Moira..."~ []
@1036353 = ~"... As a member of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart, I trust that you will not take vengeance into your own hands. The law will deal with Saerk Farrahd..."~ []
@1036354 = ~"... I grieve for the loss of your family, and will do everything in my power to see that justice is done. I hope this letter finds you before rumor does. Sincerely, Bylanna Ianulin."~ []
@1036355 = ~That... that merchant was responsible for Moira's death, after all... and father... he took it upon himself to take vengeance. And... he is dead... all because of Saerk...~ []
@1036359 = ~... You... you feel sorry...~ []
@1036360 = ~... Forget... about Saerk...~ []
@1036361 = ~... Justice... be done...~ []
@1036362 = ~... Nay! I speak of Saerk's involvement in this disaster, and yet I forget about yours! It was you who pushed me not to avenge my sister when I had the chance!~ []
@1036364 = ~I TOLD you that Saerk was responsible, <CHARNAME>! And... and you had me turn it over to the law! The law! Saerk has so much gold that the law will never touch him!~ []
@1036365 = ~Aaaah, I cannot believe I have done this! For the Order, for you! I turned my back on my family, on my duty... and look what has happened!~ []
@1036370 = ~I... I am doing what I must. Of all the vows I spoke, none of them can compare to the twisting in my heart, now. My father... dead... doing what I should have done...~ []
@1036371 = ~You... you I can forgive, at least, my love. What you did... you meant well by me. But Saerk... Saerk I cannot forgive. The law will not provide justice on one as rich as he.~ []
@1036372 = ~We have a confrontation that is inevitable, he and I. I shirked my duty once, and I will not do it again. I... I must leave you, <CHARNAME>, and do what I should have long ago.~ []
@1036373 = ~The Order and everything else be damned, Saerk will die when I find him. Fare... fare you well, then, my love. I... I am sorry to do this to you...~ []
@1036374 = ~Aye, but it is happening anyway. I spoke vows to the Order, but they mean nothing, now, to the twisting of my heart. My drunken father... dead for doing what was my duty...~ []
@1036376 = ~I regret much, and now I must act on it no matter my vows. My father is dead because I did not do my duty... dead because of an evil man's desire for wealth.~ []
@1036380 = ~Among mankind's earliest weapons, dating back to the most primitive of times, the first spears were simply wooden poles or sticks that had been sharpened at one end. Upon mastering the use of metals, weaponsmiths forged spear heads from iron and steel, and began experimenting with different types of spear heads, thus leading to the development of certain types of polearms. This spear trembles from the powerful magic used in its creation.

