@1036749 = ~His wished you to be recognized for your heroics. You truly exemplify the paladin spirit, and I would have you demonstrate it further.~ []
@1036756 = ~It would be an honor to serve in any way that I can.~ []
@1036759 = ~Then you shall continue under the guidance of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart. You could ask for no better a patron.~ []
@1036765 = ~The cause shall be just if you perform as you should. Do not neglect your own quests, but treat your assignments with urgency. Go to William Reirrac now.~ []
@1036766 = ~I am not asking you to forever forgo your own agenda, just set it aside for a short time. This offer will not be made again. Decide well and forever.~ []
@1036770 = ~I look forward to the reports of your achievements. I'm sure you will not betray our faith in your ability.~ []
@1036778 = ~It is a great shame that you did not wish to join the Order. You would have been a great asset, though I am sure you still serve the cause of righteousness.~ []
@1036779 = ~You have disgraced the Order and all that it stands for. Find your way as you will, but you will get no help from here.~ []
@1036780 = ~You have done much for the cause of good, even while mistakenly under the guise of a villain. Speak with the Prelate, for he would have the Order make amends.~ []
@1036782 = ~Your refusal is mystifying. Go with our good graces, but remember what you have lost here today.~ []
@1036784 = ~Your name is spoken well of by those that matter most. Go to the Prelate, for he has much to say.~ []
@1036787 = ~You have proven unworthy of the Order. Go and seek your fortune elsewhere, for you will find no sanctuary here.~ []
@1036788 = ~Tyr does live in your actions. Go to the Prelate, that your peers might honor you.~ []
@1036790 = ~I heard of your service to the cause of goodness, but you will not be taking orders from me on this matter. Go to the Prelate, I will speak of other things later.~ []
@1036798 = ~I hope the Order agrees with me. My beliefs are very strict.~ []
@1036810 = ~I will go this instant! Others of the Order will not fall while I stand idle!~ []
@1036812 = ~I will leave as soon as I restock and rest up.~ []
@1036816 = ~You have returned, as have our observing runners. The battle was bloody and fierce, and the outcome all but certain.~ []
@1036822 = ~Only one of our order fell once you joined the fray, though it is a sad loss. She was a squire, the future of the Order, and barely knew life's fleeting wonder.~ []
@1036826 = ~You have betrayed us with your slothfulness. Did you think me not serious when I said that time was of the essence? You are hereby expelled from the Order.~ []
@1036827 = ~Is there nothing I can do? I am sincere in my apology.~ []
@1036846 = ~But we cannot rest upon our laurels for long. There is still much for our kind to do, as the villainous do not rest while we do.~ []
@1036852 = ~Listen, you little maggot! I want to know how you got your collar off, right now... or you'll find there are far worse things than being a slave!~ []
@1036859 = ~What? Others? Ah... the primes. How foolish of you to have followed your actor friends here. Von'ith, close the portal, please.~ []
@1036865 = ~It doesn't matter... I'm here to rescue my friends.~ []
@1036868 = ~Not really... just came through for a bit of sight-seeing, really.~ []
@1036870 = ~This place is one of the finest prisons in the planes. There is no way out of here... except at the whim of the cambion. What fools you must be to come here of your own volition.~ []
@1036871 = ~I am new to the Order. My name is <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1036874 = ~No matter. I expect you'll bring a grand price from the cambion as new thralls. Hunters... take <PRO_HIMHER>!~ []
@1036875 = ~Oh, you are a sharp one, prime. I'm afraid it's much, much worse than that.~ []
@1036877 = ~Hah! Witless and full of bravado, as well. You've experience in your bearing, of that I have no doubt... but if you think your arrival will help your friends, you are quite wrong.~ []
@1036878 = ~Then you are more witless than I mistook you for. This is a poor choice for a sight-seeing trip, prime... as it will likely be your last.~ []
@1036879 = ~I am new to the Order. My name is <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1036882 = ~<CHARNAME>... I do not know it, but I am just a squire. You must have impressed the Prelate if you are a full member. I... I should go. There is much to report...~ []
@1036883 = ~Ah, of course. I am but a squire and still unsure as to how far I might take liberties talking. I will go report these horrible circumstances. Thank you again.~ []
@1036886 = ~Thank the Wounded One for saving Shamus today,  I feared his wounds too grave. Elotte however... I will weep for her. She would have made a fine knight.~ []
@1036888 = ~I must take solace in the teachings of the Maimed God, for I share his pain. Elotte and Shamus... They shall be missed by all that knew them.~ []
@1036890 = ~I am <CHARNAME>, and I am new to the Order. I wish I could have helped more.~ []
@1036894 = ~We must reflect on what we have done. Action without thought is mere instinct, and there is no righteousness in that. You will learn this in the Order. Go if you must.~ []
@1036896 = ~I must speak of these villainous events to the Order... to mourn the losses and exalt the successes. This is the hardest part of the journey. Fear it, young one.~ []
@1036905 = ~'Tis a case of the pot calling the kettle black, I would think. Suit yourself. I must pick up the pieces and go on, to honor the fallen.~ []
@1036906 = ~Of course you did. I always dread the walk home. The glory of the fight is more fulfilling than picking up the pieces afterwards. Farewell.~ []
@1036909 = ~I... I thank you, my <PRO_LADYLORD>, for your timely rescue. I am afraid I did not give much thought as to what I would do after I removed my collar.~ []
@1036917 = ~The warden keeps a large number of slaves here... prisoners that have been turned into thralls by a magical collar that they wear that controls them. They are next to impossible to remove.~ []
@1036918 = ~Mine had a small flaw in it, and I was able to squirm out of it not long ago... only to find that there was almost nowhere for me to go, here, and danger down every corridor.~ []
@1036930 = ~There be no physical exit that I know of. The portals lead only to other rooms within the prison, and there are no doors or windows... if, indeed, there is even an outside to speak of, here.~ []
@1036931 = ~No... the only way one can leave is through the use of magic. Powerful magic that only a few might have, to attract a conduit to this dim and forsaken place.~ []
@1036933 = ~You mentioned a collar... what did you mean by that?~ []
@1036943 = ~Hello, father. Are you... are you coming home for a while?~ []
@1036946 = ~You are friends of the actors? Ahhh... then you may as well begin mourning them, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. They are in the warden's cells, awaiting transport to Duke Rowan's tower, I am told.~ []
@1036947 = ~The warden is directly north of here, through the hallway... but I would advise against going down that path.~ []
@1036948 = ~You will see on the floor markings that the tanar'ri have left with their magic... portals that transport you to the other rooms of this prison.~ []
@1036950 = ~There is another way to reach the warden... a safer way, perhaps, that may serve your purpose and perhaps mine, as well. Might I tell you of it?~ []
@1036954 = ~Er... if you could but tarry a moment, my <PRO_LADYLORD>, I could perhaps offer you some small assistance... something that would aid me, as well.~ []
@1036959 = ~The passage to the east leads to the chambers of the Master of Thralls... a lesser tanar'ri who holds a device that I know allows him to control the collars.~ []
@1036960 = ~Destroy that device and the thralls are freed. The warden is vulnerable... and I will be able to contact my newly freed friends. Some of them are mages who will teleport us away.~ []
@1036961 = ~As well, the portals on the floors to the east may be avoided... they lead only to other cells, I understand, and are full of naught but violent and dangerous creatures.~ []
@1036962 = ~I... I would not offer this chance, my <PRO_LADYLORD>, if I did not think you might have a chance against the warden, himself. I can think of no other way for either of us to escape this place, truly.~ []
@1036965 = ~There are many old and powerful magics in this prison, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. We might get away briefly, but the prison's magic would track us... and the warden would send powerful hunters very quickly.~ []
@1036968 = ~Forget it... I will try to find my own way out of here.~ []
@1036970 = ~Then... then I wish you well, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. I, myself, shall remain here where it is safe... for now.~ []
@1036972 = ~Then all hope is lost. I... I hope you find some way out, my <PRO_LADYLORD>, I truly do.~ []
@1036977 = ~I care not for bureaucratic types, but I serve the will of the Order.~ []
@1036979 = ~Be most careful, my <PRO_LADYLORD>! I understand the Master of Thralls to be a fearsome opponent! But... but you must destroy his device! The thralls must be free!~ []
@1036980 = ~You have destroyed the orb, my <PRO_LADYLORD>? I... I almost did not believe it possible! How wondrous!~ []
@1036984 = ~Is... is there something that I can do for you, my <LADYLORD>? I shall do anything I can, in return for the kindness you have paid me.~ []
@1036988 = ~The Baron waits in a neutral meeting place. He is in a tavern in the Umar Hills, in the village of Imnesvale. Go now.~ []
@1036994 = ~You mentioned a plan you had to get us out of here... tell me about it, please.~ []
@1037000 = ~I see. Well... I shall wish you luck, regardless, in escaping this place.~ []
@1037005 = ~Ah... I see you have the orb with you, my <LADYLORD>. I think the brazier in the room just east of here might serve to destroy it... if anything can.~ []
@1037012 = ~We... we... attack them! Attack them and kill them all!!~ []
@1037030 = ~Hmmmn... vermin, I see. Come, my pretty thralls. These are no escaped prisoners... these are invaders! We must destroy them for my master!~ []
@1037036 = ~You... you have killed the master! You have killed him!! By Clangeddin's Axe, I thought such a thing not even possible!~ []
@1037043 = ~Y-yes... the Warden is in the great chamber just west of here, down the hall. B-but... do you not want to destroy the orb, first?~ []
@1037048 = ~Y-yes... it is the orb he carries... the orb of mastery! I... I cannot touch it so long as I wear this collar. But if you wish to destroy it, you can...~ []
@1037049 = ~You must take the orb to the room south of here with the magical brazier in the center... the flames will surely destroy the orb and free all the thralls, here, in the process!~ []
@1037050 = ~I... I must flee before the Warden discovers that the Master of Thralls is dead! Please... destroy the orb if you are able! I beg you!!~ []
@1037051 = ~There... there is no way out! No way at all! Unless... unless you destroy the orb, I suppose. That... that would free all the thralls...~ []
@1037056 = ~The thralls could... we could remove our collars... and the Warden would be unprotected. Killing the Warden is... is the only way out, I think. I... I don't know...~ []
@1037061 = ~I cannot touch the orb so long as I wear the collar... and I cannot remove the collar without the orb's destruction...~ []
@1037066 = ~There... there is a room to the south... you can reach it through the chambers of the Warden's pet. Although... although I suppose you already came through that way...~ []
@1037067 = ~But... beyond it is a chamber with a brazier in the center. The magical flames might... might serve to destroy the orb. It is the only way I can think to do this...~ []
@1037072 = ~Y-yes... that is the only way. I wish you well... if you take on the warden...~ []
@1037073 = ~Ah... you are the pitiful group of fools from the prime material plane, I see. Well, you will disturb my prison no further. No one escapes this place... no one.~ []
@1037075 = ~Call on the Master of Thralls... I wish to know what is occurring, here. I will tear this plane apart to have those filthy slaves returned! I will flay the skin from their...~ []
@1037076 = ~... what is this? You are not my guards! It... it is you!! You are causing these problems!! I shall take the rest of eternity to make you suffer!!~ []
@1037080 = ~You... you have defeated the Warden and freed us all. I wish I had some better way to thank you, my <PRO_LADYLORD>, but I have little doubt you will find a way home on your own.~ []
@1037082 = ~Please... accept my most heart-felt thanks. The thralls who were once imprisoned here shall always remember you.~ []
@1037085 = ~I am of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart, and I will support the side of right.~ []
@1037086 = ~Order! Is that what the Baron Metrich calls it? I suppose he would think so, but he wasn't here first. His order is a lot different than this place used to be.~ []
@1037089 = ~Are you now? Then maybe you'll be a voice of reason. Not like anyone has cared up until now. Brush the squatters away, even if they were here before.~ []
@1037090 = ~You want the whole story, you ask around. Go to your meeting with all sides known and make your mind up then. Do that, and maybe we'll get what we deserve.~ []
@1037093 = ~I am well worried by what has gone on in this place. Though the choice seems clear and right I am hesitant to take it.~ [ANOMENA7]
@1037105 = ~Baron Metrich took over just recently. He's been trying to run us out, preferring private hunting grounds to our farms. He's taxed, burned, and raided!~ []
@1037113 = ~It's not surprising. You are probably lying to protect yourself and I will believe no more.~ []
@1037114 = ~And, here... I have procured a key for the place from one of his servants. Take it, Anomen. Go... go and avenge our Moira. Let justice be done.~ []
@1037121 = ~Then I shall go there. The Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart would not wish I miss it.~ []
@1037126 = ~You do not love me anymore? ... I... I have always loved you and I always shall. However well I hide it, every day I spend without you is a day that's lost forever.~ []
@1037130 = ~ I am not comfortable wandering about in the dark. The shadows could hold anyone... anything.~ [NALIA20]
@1037145 = ~I will not harm you without cause. I am from the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart.~ []
@1037147 = ~But that is how I was in the circus when I was kept in a--a cage. It was horrible, Valygar, but Quayle came and healed me... healed my sores where...~ []
@1037151 = ~The arms and legs seem melded with the sarcophagus. You may not remove them while their guardian still lives.~ []
@1037152 = ~Psychic Drain~ []
@1037153 = ~When you touch the bones, a wave of nausea and fear washes over you. Covering your hands, you carefully place the arms and legs in your pack.~ []
@1037172 = ~Who are you? Oh, whoever you are, you must flee this place at once! He... he's killed everyone else who has come into this place, almost! Oh, please run!~ [AERIE01]
@1037177 = ~Kalah! Oh, I don't know what he's done, exactly, or how... but everything here is an illusion! But it's magic that can hurt you, if you believe in it...~ []
@1037178 = ~Oh, you probably don't understand, do you? I... I don't know what he's done to the tent or with the others who have come in, but their deaths are real! You must run!~ []
@1037184 = ~I... I'm not a monster! I'm an elf, a winged elf... or at least I was...~ []
@1037185 = ~This... this covering you see is some kind of illusion, but if you believe in it then it becomes real! P-please believe me! Now go before something happens to you, I beg of you!~ []
@1037189 = ~Perhaps you're right, then... I should go.~ []
@1037190 = ~Oh, I hope you don't end up like... like the others! But, alright... m-my name is Aerie. I... work in the circus with my uncle, Quayle...~ []
@1037191 = ~I don't know exactly what happened, but everything changed a few days ago... everything became chaos and turned into what you see here. Although it all isn't real, it's an illusion...~ []
@1037192 = ~The minions... they all say they serve Kalah, so I know he's behind all of this... he's an illusionist in the circus, but I don't understand how he was able to do all of this!~ []
@1037193 = ~He must be stopped! Before he hurts any more people! Please... if... if you release me from my chains, I can help you stop him!~ []
@1037200 = ~No! No, you don't underst... RrrrRRAARGH! I WILL KILL YOU ALL!!~ []
@1037201 = ~Yes! Go, if you can! I... I don't want to see any more people hurt!~ []
@1037202 = ~I... I come from a race of winged elves... although there aren't many of us left. From the Sundabar Mountains in the far North. My wings were cut off a long time ago, though...~ []
@1037203 = ~But... but that isn't important! This place is too dangerous! Go back to the city and warn everyone what is happening here! You must flee!~ []
@1037208 = ~The chains are invisible... covered by the illusion. And... and they are magical... they prevent me from casting my own spells and they maintain the illusion which is placed on me...~ []
@1037213 = ~You... you need the key to these chains. But... but it won't look like a key! There are a couple of... commoners... in the north side of this chamber...~ []
@1037214 = ~Don't be fooled by the illusion, though... they are monsters! They have a sword which is actually my key... if you get it from them, I can remove the chain and regain my normal form!~ []
@1037215 = ~But please be careful! You... you can't trust anything you see, here!~ []
@1037216 = ~I don't know... I tried, earlier, when this first happened. Kalah's spells are too powerful, somehow. He's... he's never been that good, though, so I don't know what he's done...~ []
@1037217 = ~If you free me, though, together we can find out and stop him! And... and hopefully rescue my Uncle, Quayle...~ []
@1037222 = ~Alright, then... but be careful! And don't trust anything that you see! And... and please save my Uncle, Quayle! Please!~ []
@1037223 = ~You... you aren't going to help anyone? But... well, if you must... if that's safest...~ []
@1037224 = ~If... if you're not going to flee, then maybe you can help free me from the chains that keep me bound in this form... and then maybe I can help you!~ [AERIED1]
@1037225 = ~I will do what is just. I am from the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart.~ []
@1037226 = ~Perhaps. Perhaps I am here to do the job.~ []
@1037228 = ~I don't see any chains... what are you referring to?~ []
@1037232 = ~I'm sorry, but I have no time to help you... I must confront this Kalah quickly!~ []
@1037234 = ~You... you haven't found the sword? Oh, please hurry! The... the peasants who have it are on the north side of the chamber... but they aren't what they seem!~ [AERIED2]
@1037244 = ~Have... have you found Quayle?~ [AERIEC9]
@1037247 = ~Not yet... and I would appreciate your help. Please join me and we will look together.~ []
@1037249 = ~Yes... this is it, this is the planar sphere here in the slums. We should... climb the stairs and find some manner of entrance. If I am right, my blood, my presence should open the sphere...~ [VALYGA70]
@1037251 = ~I am dying... and I wish to die there. Under my own sun.~ []
@1037252 = ~In return... in return I shall tell you how to return the sphere to our own plane. I... I am glad that you entered the sphere when you did.~ []
@1037253 = ~I was able to keep from the force... the fact that the sphere had a defense against intrusion. It would automatically travel to another plane...~ []
@1037254 = ~A trap... that would allow me to deal with the intruders... at will. But... that was another time. Bring me home, Valygar Corthala, and I will tell you how...~ []
@1037255 = ~Very well. The sphere... the sphere is powered by the heart of a powerful demon. Our last trip, now, would have depleted the power source of the last heart the sphere had...~ []
@1037257 = ~Bring the heart to the engine room of the sphere and place it inside the engine golem at the center there... and I will pre-set the controls while you are gone.~ []
@1037258 = ~But go quickly, Valygar... there are things that will stir in the planes and take notice of the sphere now that it is here! Go! And I... will try to hang on long enough...~ []
@1037259 = ~We have returned to our home plane, have we? Then I... then I shall complete Lavok's request. Excuse me, <CHARNAME>... I will go outside with my ancestor...~ []
@1037264 = ~I have had an age and more to consider my sins. If I could call it all back... if I could call back my brother and my son... my granddaughter and grandsons... I...~ []
@1037266 = ~The... the sphere has been moved. I can sense this. It was... an automatic defense against intrusion that I kept hidden from the presence...~ []
@1037269 = ~But now that the presence is gone, you need to return to your home plane. I... I shall tell you how, in return for one thing... one small thing...~ []
@1037270 = ~I have been traveling for so long... I wish to see my home one last time. When... we return to the Prime, take me outside, and let me die under the sky of the place I was born...~ []
@1037271 = ~Very good. The... the sphere is powered by the heart of a powerful demon. Or... or at least it was. You must go outside of the sphere... and get another heart.~ []
@1037272 = ~I know this will be difficult, but you defeated the presence... so I hope that you will have strength enough for this last task. Get a heart... and return...~ []
@1037274 = ~But go... go quickly. I do not know how much longer I can maintain my existence...~ []
@1037275 = ~Then... then you will be stuck here on this plane. As am I. I... I hope you will think about this, <PRO_RACE>, and think quickly. I have as little wish to die here as you do...~ []
@1037276 = ~But you are... no longer... on your home plane. Bargain with me, stranger... and I shall tell you how to return...~ []
@1037278 = ~Very well... let me hear what you wish.~ []
@1037280 = ~So... have you decided differently? Have you... seen that there is no other way home?~ [LAVOK11]
@1037284 = ~As... as you wish. But I would not wait much... longer...~ []
@1037285 = ~You must find the heart of a demon, you must!! It... it must be strong enough to power the sphere! Go, <RACE>!~ [LAVOK12]
@1037286 = ~Yes... yes! That heart will do! Go to the engine room... and place it within the golem! Go, quickly!~ [LAVOK13]
@1037287 = ~We... we are returned to our own plane. Please... please, stranger. As per our bargain... let me see my sun one last time...~ [LAVOK14]
@1037289 = ~No, I do not trust you... you may yet pull some trick!~ []
@1037290 = ~I... am most grateful. If... you could but carry me, my strength has all but fled... my last moments... are upon me...~ [LAVOK15]
@1037291 = ~Aye... it is nothing less than I expected. I deserve nothing more, I suppose, after all my evil...~ [LAVOK16]
@1037292 = ~... I... I wish I had... had... ah...~ []
@1037293 = ~... I... I sense within you... a kindred power. You... you are a mage, yes?~ []
@1037294 = ~Yes... I see that you are. I... I grant you the sphere, mage. Do... do with it far... far better than I ever did. It is yours... to use wisely...~ []
@1037297 = ~Why not? We can't leave th' farm to rot completely... we have t' eat, aye, me <LADYLORD>?~ []
@1037302 = ~Er... talk to Erlin if you wish t' discuss the chickens, me <LADYLORD>. I'll have nothin' t' do with it.~ []
@1037308 = ~I know your secret, old man... give me the chicken or there's going to be trouble.~ []
@1037314 = ~I'm only interested in one chicken, truly... a chicken that swallowed something quite valuable...~ []
@1037317 = ~I... you're a terrible, evil <MANWOMAN>, you are! 'Tis all I have left of my daughter! All we have in the world, dead! Dead!~ []
@1037319 = ~I'll pay you fairly for it... then you don't have to hide it anymore.~ []
@1037324 = ~Give up the ruse, old man... I know your secret. Hand over the chicken!~ []
@1037326 = ~(sigh)  I s'pose it's best not t' be hangin' onto it any longer. Eventually someone will come an' take it from us. What... what can ye pay me for it, me <LADYLORD>?~ []
@1037330 = ~100 gold pieces... more than fair, I am sure.~ []
@1037331 = ~Forget it... I've changed my mind.~ []
@1037334 = ~Nay, Enna, there be no sense in causin' trouble over it. Here you go, stranger... I hope it makes you happy wi' yourself.~ []
@1037335 = ~'Tis a terrible price, seein' as me daughter paid for it with her life. But if it must be, it must be. Here... an' I hope it makes ye happy with yerself.~ []
@1037337 = ~Aye... aye, 'tis more than fair. This will pay for a fine headstone for our daughter an' more. A better tribute than a hidden gem in a chicken. Take it, then... you've been more an' kind.~ []
@1037340 = ~My daughter, she is gone! She was home when I left and now she is gone! There is debris about my home and this note was there... and there is blood!~ []
@1037341 = ~My son, he is gone! He was there when I left, but now... This note was at the scene and there is debris about my home and... and there is blood!~ []
@1037350 = ~I will take vengeance for you as well, no matter where he hides!~ []
@1037352 = ~You charge ahead, of valor born, the best of your parental blood commingled here within you, their very destinies made true by your every righteous act!~ []
@1037353 = ~I delight so at the sparrows twittering above and look... there passes a prancing squirrel, all delighted by the softness of our approach!~ []
@1037354 = ~That fortune... brought us no end of grief, however. My family eventually took up his past-time, as well, to my sorrow.~ []
@1037358 = ~... and a body built for untold pleasures that I would fall for such an old ploy? Blow a little sunshine and I will fall all over myself to gain your favor? Best think again, dark one.~ []
@1037360 = ~You're a dreamer, bard. I'm sure you can imagine lots of wonderful scenes... but they would not exceed the truth in intensity, depravity or tenure, I assure you.~ []
@1037372 = ~Yes you do. You should follow in here. It is safe. The orcs let us be safe in there. You should come in.~ []
@1037382 = ~Gosh... you're an adventurer, aren't you? Hey, Derbert... this <MANWOMAN>'s an adventurer! Wow!!~ []
@1037394 = ~You have met my father, <CHARNAME>... surely you have some inkling, from his manner alone if nothing else.~ []
@1037400 = ~You needn't be so impudent, child. The woman is pleasing to the eye and doth stir the loins and I was merely complimenting upon her comeliness.~ []
@1037404 = ~Ho, Haer'Dalis, your poetry ennobles me far beyond my worth. I am a simple man and by simple decisions, I have made my way about this earth.~ []
@1037407 = ~Ha. There are countless books within our holy libraries where bored and dreamy scribes have penned petty blasphemies into the margins.~ [KELDOR65]
@1037408 = ~"I knew a girl from a distant world,
across the planar deep,
and to her place, to see her face,
across the void, I'd creep.
Though time... though time...~ []
@1037409 = ~Oh dear, I hope I didn't write that one down for posterity! Heh... you should be proud of yourself, Yoshimo: you've just made an old knight blush.~ []
@1037410 = ~The very gods granted us dominion here and Ao placed the races that they might flourish and be fruitful. It is a destiny made manifest, druid.~ []
@1037416 = ~I am old but, in what time I have left to me, I shall do all in my power to maintain the sanctity of your soul...~ []
@1037417 = ~I know that you bring with you a troubled past and a painful heritage but, for all the friendship that has formed between us, I cannot turn from such transgressions forever...~ [KELDOR82]
@1037432 = ~Dig...? You torment wit' funny words and projecting voice. You gonna kill, just says so. I scream now. Gaaaahh!~ []
@1037436 = ~More! I would know more of this place! Tell me what defenses Lord Jierdan has!~ []
@1037437 = ~Defenses? Lord Firkraag no need defenses. You silly to think so. We hunt the feed and guard the home, but he not need us protect him.~ []
@1037444 = ~Your pity and endowments only serve to perpetuate their condition and diminish their motivation to improve their lot.~ []
@1037446 = ~Your joviality is a clever cloak to hide agenda and ambitions... but I'll be sure to armor my back to deflect the blade you'll surely aim there.~ []
@1037447 = ~The mandate of your loyal order is deception and ruse, so misery is just another disguise for your gang of holy thugs' agenda is my guess. Yes?~ []
@1037457 = ~You... you really wish to know? Then listen carefully. I know we have not been behaving well, and we have, in fact, k-killed a number of the Baron's guards, but it has not been unprovoked!~ []
@1037472 = ~Oh. Me sad. But fingers happy! If DigDag is dead, I free free free! Been nice cookin' you!~ []
@1037474 = ~Pleased that ye think so, dog-flogger. I had t' act on a couple occasions... out o' necessity, like when we happened upon a hive of giants.~ []
@1037484 = ~It is too bad that you won't take Aerie with you. She should see the world. Think about it, my good <PRO_MANWOMAN>... talk to her when you get the chance.~ []
@1037486 = ~I ask that you take Aerie with you again, to see the world... but it is your affair, after all. It does my heart ill to see her cooped up here, though.~ []
@1037489 = ~This is the way, I just knows it. A southern tomb within the opened cavern. Bloody old, it be.~ [KORGAN82]
@1037490 = ~That's one fine mess that I done cleaned up. They did the killin', but I ends up with the gold, the book, and the satisfaction o' kickin' their tails. Ah... a good day.~ [KORGAN83]
@1037495 = ~I thought you might want to talk to me. Travin said you have something I want.~ []
@1037500 = ~W-what of it? You... you from them Talassans? I gots what you be looking for, but only for a price.~ []
@1037516 = ~There is no place for friendship or compassion in the theater of gods, <CHARNAME>... as I am sure you are beginning to learn, if not understand.~ []
@1037518 = ~My own thoughts, my own shoes, my own BODY! These are all that matter!~ []
@1037522 = ~Y-yes, of course. I am very, very sorry. Very sorry.~ []
@1037534 = ~If you have the need of me again, you'll find me at the Five Flagons inn, where the playhouse once was... or not, as the whim takes me. Farewell, my wandering raven!~ []
@1037535 = ~Treat our kinship as if it never were... for we'll not see one another again. This sparrow flies... farewell or not, I do not care.~ []
@1037536 = ~Aye, I expected this... and verily I am half-glad that the time has come for our parting, my sour raven. I tire of your antics and would be done with them.~ []
@1037541 = ~I'm sorry for what happened before... will you join me again, Haer'Dalis?~ []
@1037544 = ~Aye... the raven and the sparrow, together! It will be good to voyage with you, <CHARNAME>!~ []
@1037545 = ~Aye, but 'tis always such. Nay, I have other things more pleasant than traveling with one such as yourself. Find another, my raven.~ []
@1037546 = ~Mmmm... very well, <CHARNAME>. Let in not be said that this actor has no heart. I can forgive... and besides, it is exciting to voyage with you. Let us go, then, my raven!~ []
@1037547 = ~Aye, and greetings to you, too. I have business to attend to, however... and I suspect so do you. 'Til we meet again, my raven.~ []
@1037550 = ~So... the rescuers of our beloved Haer'Dalis have come to us, at last. Haer'Dalis has preceded you and spoken of you well. Here is a reward for his return.~ [RAELIS13]
@1037551 = ~Now... do you have the gem he spoke of, child? The portal gem that Mekrath had in his keeping?~ []
@1037552 = ~No, I don't... but I intend on getting it.~ []
@1037553 = ~Perhaps... how much is the stone worth to you?~ []
@1037558 = ~Yes, well, regrets to be dealt with another day. You say you have come to take delivery of something?~ []
@1037570 = ~We... we still do not have it, Miss Raelis, try though I might to convince my raven of its import. I shall endeavour to speed the process, if you will it.~ []
@1037574 = ~Dagger of <CHARNAME> +1~
@1037575 = ~So I ask you. Are you currently in service to Talos? Are you loyal to him and him alone? And may he strike you down if you are lying.~ []
@1037581 = ~Then you will not have the item. Leave me.~ []
@1037592 = ~I am only Lanka's assistant. If you wish something, best you speak to her or the Baron directly.~ []
@1037603 = ~Yes, it is a simple matter now that you are here. I require some squatters removed from my lands. They will respect the word of the Order and go.~ []
@1037606 = ~The Order was insistent that I support you, and that is what I intend to do, whatever the details.~ []
@1037607 = ~I have a small problem. One of the farmers claimed the land was theirs, not yours.~ []
@1037610 = ~You would not wish to disappoint a potential friend of the Order, would you? These louts have assaulted my men. Deal with them in the proper fashion.~ []
@1037614 = ~Ahh, but you have proven reasonable yourself in responding to my concerns. I am content to aid you in this.~ []
@1037619 = ~You have spoken with everyone that you need to.  I would have you state your intent with no more delays!~ []
@1037624 = ~I will have my men continue without your aid. Your authority could have made the expulsion more diplomatic, but my men will do what they must. Leave here!~ []
@1037625 = ~I'm sure that, as we speak, the nobles argue over the relative benefits of white and red Evermeet wine, merely a thousand gold pieces per glass.~ [NALIA52]
@1037634 = ~Of course you will. Since you have declared it here, the farmers will not oppose a member of the Order as they have opposed me.~ []
@1037635 = ~Lanka? Have they assembled outside? I was told they might.~ []
@1037636 = ~It would appear so, though they are more armed for battle than debate.~ []
@1037638 = ~Your help has been appreciated, but I no longer have cause to speak with you. Lanka and I must set about building my regulated hunting range.~ []
@1037640 = ~Stop your feeding, my spiders! New victims await! Protect your home!~ []
@1037641 = ~But why do we need to continue this discussion? You have already begun cleansing the area. One dead? Two? No matter. It will put fear into them.~ []
@1037642 = ~Regardless, you have earned my gratitude. With this simple, brutal act you have solved my problem. Go now, and tell your masters that I am pleased.~ []
@1037643 = ~It was a regrettable thing, but I had a duty to fulfill.~ []
@1037644 = ~I had little choice in the matter, though I will take pleasure in a job well done.~ []
@1037646 = ~Do not quibble over details. All is well.~ []
@1037649 = ~Moreno... no. Would you have us fight agents of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart? Matrich's men are one thing, but knights of the Order? No.~ []
@1037650 = ~It is over, Moreno, just as the Baron hoped it would be. We cannot fight such a group as the Order. The word of law has been passed here, and we are on the losing side.~ []
@1037652 = ~We'll fight you! Here and now if we have to!~ []
@1037657 = ~Lanka? Is this true?~ []
@1037659 = ~What would be your concern? Your hands are far from clean in this matter, my dear. Your precious animals and environment have made you a turncoat.~ []
@1037660 = ~The state of the land is important, but I did not agree to this.~ []
@1037662 = ~This is not open for discussion! What matters is the land I want and the people that must get off it!~ []
@1037665 = ~You are not here to think! Leave the thinking to your betters!~ []
@1037669 = ~Now just calm down and we'll straighten this all out.~ []
@1037672 = ~Well, the side you have chosen to support is now quite obvious, I think. I would have preferred a peaceful solution, but if this is the way it must be, I do appreciate being on the winning side.~ []
@1037675 = ~Regardless, this matter is resolved. We will try to bring our lives back to some semblance of normality. We will also try to resolve what guilt we feel for what we did during this incident.~ []
@1037682 = ~You have returned, though not quite as I expected. I must say that your visit to the Metrich Barony has yielded some surprising results.~ []
@1037696 = ~There was evidence of that, but my duty was to the task I was sent to achieve.~ []
@1037698 = ~I... knew of no such evidence. The squatters were quite clearly belligerent.~ []
@1037709 = ~There was evidence of that, but my duty was to the task I was sent to achieve.~ []
@1037710 = ~I... knew of no such evidence. The squatters were quite clearly belligerent.~ []
@1037722 = ~Such a crime is unforgivable! I will lead an army down the throats of those responsible!~ []
@1037730 = ~You will go to a safe-house we have set up, and you will make sure she remains secure. It is as secret as we could make it, though nothing is ever absolute.~ []
@1037738 = ~It... it is true, I can sense it! Oh, by the mercy of the Gods... you must use the artifact to destroy the beholder! You must!~ []
@1037741 = ~You... must retrieve the second half of the rod. It was split apart long ago, by the gods... in order to keep the world safe from its power.~ []
@1037742 = ~I will tell you how to gain the second half... if you agree to use it to destroy the beholder. The device cannot be taken from here, lest its curse strike you down.~ []
@1037745 = ~You... you have killed the creature who has enslaved so many. Of that, I am thankful. But... I see you still hold the rod... the rift device... yet unused.~ [SASSAR09]
@1037746 = ~Be warned, my <LADYLORD>... the device cannot be taken above the ground. My findings here have taught me that. It will surely destroy you if you do...~ []
@1037748 = ~You have destroyed the creature who has enslaved so many... and for that, I am more grateful than I can say.~ [SASSAR10]
@1037749 = ~I sense you have the rift device... the rod. You have used it? I must caution you not to take it to the lands above... its power would consume you.~ []
@1037751 = ~You have freed our brother! For that, I would lay roses at thy feet, my <LADYLORD>! But... there is still the matter of the... ah... gem, is there not?~ []
@1037752 = ~I thank you, my <LADYLORD>... you have done much for us all.~ []
@1037755 = ~Our poor sparrow lies broken. All is darkness, now, for us all... regardless of what occurs...~ []
@1037756 = ~Ahhh... our brother is dead. Poor Haer'Dalis, truly he had little in the way of luck. Leave us be, Prime... we must mourn for our fallen comrade...~ []
@1037757 = ~He... he's free, is he? That's good... Raelis says I still have a long time before I am ready to be a full actor. But I don't mind... it's my dream and I'll work hard!~ []
@1037758 = ~Raelis has asked me to come along and join the troupe! Imagine that... me, a Prime, traveling the planes! And acting! Truly acting!!~ []
@1037759 = ~Haer'Dalis is dead... that means... that means I have to continue acting. Ooooh, I feel ill...~ []
@1037761 = ~There's a tanner, Rejiek Hidesman, who has his shop near here... he might have some tannin, I'm not sure. Might be worth it to ask him.~ []
@1037763 = ~Halt! This place is under the protection of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart. You will leave immediately or suffer the consequences!~ []
@1037768 = ~Halt! You will go no further while I am... Oh, forgive my outburst, <CHARNAME>. I was told you were coming to relieve me but I have been getting rather edgy. It has been a long day.~ []
@1037772 = ~I have... planned this for... too long only to have my plans shattered by some inbred, northern adventurers! I... I just wanted to be respected...~ [KALAH12]
@1037777 = ~This... this is Aegisfield, all right. (sigh)  It is too bad... he was a fine and just man. Here... give his body to me.~ []
@1037778 = ~Your story seems odd... but I can tell if someone's lying. I will check your story... but for now you have the city's thanks for the service you have done us.~ []
@1037780 = ~It is good the tanner is dead... though I would have liked to speak to him first. No matter. I trust this reward will compensate you... thank you again, citizens.~ []
@1037783 = ~I have solved the murders that were occurring in the bridge district... but the murderer killed Inspector Aegisfield. I have his body with me, here.~ []
@1037784 = ~I have solved the murders that were occurring in the Bridge District... but the murderer killed Inspector Aegisfield.~ []
@1037785 = ~Oh... by the gods, that IS the Inspector! Quickly, my good <LADYLORD>, bring the body to Chief Inspector Brega immediately!~ []
@1037786 = ~Oh... oh, my. I think you should speak to Chief Inspector Brega, however... he is here in this building, and I think he should know of this immediately!~ []
@1037787 = ~I have solved the murders that were occurring in the bridge district... but the murderer killed Inspector Aegisfield. I have his body with me, here.~ []
@1037788 = ~I have solved the murders that were occurring in the Bridge District... but the murderer killed Inspector Aegisfield.~ []
@1037789 = ~Damn and done, this crypt looks to be well looted already! The rank, stinking bastards beat us here! Those scoundrels'll dine on me sup of cold steel 'afore I'm through with 'em!~ []
@1037791 = ~Nalia... no offense, but you are not poor; your children will not starve. You empathize, but you may be blinded by the romance of saving the impoverished.~ []
@1037804 = ~Surely such a thing would not be allowed if I were following the wrong path? This shall be my rebirth... after I rest for a bit.~ []
@1037810 = ~I will decide what course is best. I have already seen to your cage.~ []
@1037819 = ~Let us just say that he is less than pleased by the loudness of your voice and the fact that you are currently standing on his cache of nuts.~ []
@1037821 = ~And to answer your question, yes... we do care.~ []
@1037826 = ~Many would still starve in the wood though surrounded by food. We must tell of the wonder, but also of what she requires.~ []
@1037827 = ~Urrr... you... you <PRO_RACE> no attack?~ []
@1037828 = ~We... we go, now. We no work for fat human. Gurgh be sick... me go get him better, now.~ []
@1037829 = ~Greetings to you, my <LADYLORD>. I am afraid that I am waiting for another at the moment... perhaps some other time?~ []
@1037832 = ~Because of you, we have lost the greatest social coup this city has yet seen! Sir Sarles is gone before we could show him off! Get out of here!~ []
@1037834 = ~You have my apologies. I tried to please him, but to no avail.~ []
@1037839 = ~And I curse you for trying! How could guttertrash such as yourself hope to please a man of his caliber? Get out, and leave me be!~ []
@1037840 = ~Here... I'll mark the location on your map. We should head there immediately. Be careful not to be spotted. I hope everything is all right!~ []
@1037841 = ~Well... I've been thinking, and I'm pretty sure they would have left someone alive. Daleson... he would be tending the stable. You should try to reach him.~ []
@1037842 = ~Then I wish you luck finding it. I will go on my own.~ []
@1037855 = ~We've no more time for your morbid fascinations. Let's get moving.~ []
@1037859 = ~What are you doing here, you drunken lout?! I thought you were well-enough banned from this place!~ [LOUTCA01]
@1037862 = ~Aye, then... I shall go. But the gem I mentioned still needs taking from Mekrath's lair. I shall await your arrival at the playhouse beneath the Five Flagons Inn... bring the gem there, I beg of you.~ [HAERDA94]
@1037868 = ~I have heard of your activities. Your disservice to the faithful means I must tell you that any task we may have asked of you is now null and void.~ []
@1037870 = ~Your service is no longer required here. Such as you are not worthy of serving in the name of Helm. All church tasks you have been involved in are considered finished.~ [TELWYN08]
@1037875 = ~Ah, but it is not merely that. You shall understand, I am sure. I formally transfer responsibility for the situation to you, <CHARNAME>. May Helm watch over you in this.~ []
@1037877 = ~Franco, what was that... oh, he has been relieved. Good, I found his manner insulting. Be a dear and fetch me some ale.~ []
@1037879 = ~He shall not be disappointed with my service. She will be safe.~ []
@1037880 = ~I will see to his needs as an ambassador of the Order.~ []
@1037890 = ~Stuffy old paladins are all alike. Same as father, and my uptight godparent, Hurgis. I am not looking forward to living with him. Stupid 'champions of morality.'~ []
@1037891 = ~All you people got my 'best interests' at heart, but I don't want to be a symbol... I just want to get on with my life! Whatever. Stay doggie. Guard. Heel.~ []
@1037896 = ~It's bad enough I have to suffer those paladins without their hired help bugging me too. Go back to guarding, doggie.~ []
@1037901 = ~Stow it, bucket-helm.~ []
@1037905 = ~You are no longer required. There's torches outside... my godparent is here. As bad as living with him will be, it's better than this!~ []
@1037907 = ~Your friend... our former ranger... is no longer welcome here, I can assure you. I think it would be best if you all left.~ []
@1037910 = ~I... despite all you have done for us, you are no longer worthy of being the village's ranger. I find it very... very sad, what you have done. You should be ashamed of yourself, my <PRO_LADYLORD>.~ []
@1037914 = ~In an instant, for you. Quick, boy, stand alert... we gots our best guests present an' in the house!~ []
@1037915 = ~Aww... yer not gonna make me work, are ye?~ []
@1037924 = ~Well, if it ain't our own ranger an' protector, like! Pleased am I t' see ye, me <PRO_LADYLORD> <CHARNAME>! Things have... been going well, I assume?~ []
@1037927 = ~Right. Like ye didn't knows about 'em orogs... or whatever they were. They would o' liked this inn, I'm sure of that!~ []
@1037928 = ~Killed yer precious Umar, too. Hehehe... an here you were screamin' like a banshee, sure as sin that she'd come back, now, t' kill ye!~ []
@1037929 = ~When did Merella ever save us? 'Sides from those orcs that time. An' that black wolf feller. An'... oh, mind yer business, boy! May I help ye, me <PRO_LADYLORD>?~ []
@1037931 = ~Well, they wouldn't 'ave been welcome, I assure ye. They would have eaten ye, boy... yer gettin' mighty portly. Er... something I can get ye, me <PRO_LADYLORD>?~ []
@1037932 = ~Ye'll be minding yer tongue, boy, lest somethin' other than th' witch decides to part ye from it! Ah... er... somethin' I can get for ye, me <PRO_LADYLORD>?~ []
@1037941 = ~Ah... it is ye, me <PRO_LADYLORD>. Is there... does ye wish to rent a room... perhaps?~ []
@1037944 = ~I see. Um... as ye wish...~ []
@1037946 = ~Some... somethin's got t' be done! Somethin' does! She's comin' t' kill us all! Oooh, I knew this would happen! I shouldn't have stayed here!!~ []
@1037947 = ~Relax, there, Vinny... she ain't gonna come an' kill ye personally just 'cause yer selling those books.~ []
@1037948 = ~Yes... yes... that's right... she won't come just after me. Er... did you... did you wish somethin', me <LADYLORD>?~ []
@1037950 = ~What can you tell me about this Umar... do you know anything specific? Weaknesses? Magical powers?~ []
@1037952 = ~Oh... ah... certainly! Right away!~ []
@1037953 = ~Well... ah... there is... there is certain legends that say that... ah...~ []
@1037955 = ~It HAS been over seven centuries since she existed in the valley, me <LADYLORD>! The legends... they don't even agree on what she looks like!~ []
@1037956 = ~As... as you wish... oooh... maybe I should think about settin' up a caravan now. How long t' Athkatla? ... hmmm...~ []
@1037959 = ~Greetings to you, my <LADYLORD>... I must tell you how grateful I am that you saved us all from those awful... shadows... or whatever they were.~ []
@1037960 = ~I suppose I was wrong about that... that Madulf fellow... and those other creatures, as well. They saved Atta from those ogrons! And... and so did you, as well, of course!~ []
@1037961 = ~And... and now you've saved us from that person who pretended to be Umar, of all things. You truly are a marvel!~ []
@1037962 = ~Good day, my <LADYLORD>. I... I don't care what other people say... you saved us all, once, no matter what your friend did. You have my blessing.~ []
@1037963 = ~Greetings to you, ranger. I hope you find yourself warmly welcome in our village... especially after all you have done for us.~ []
@1037965 = ~Something has to be done about that... that witch, Umar! She's threatened to kill us all unless we leave... we cannot abandon our village! Please, you must do something about her!~ []
@1037966 = ~There are a bunch of... of creatures trying to attack the village, my <LADYLORD>... but that ogre, Madulf, has been holding them off! Please protect us, please!!~ []
@1037967 = ~There are a bunch of... of creatures threatening to attack the village! That... that ogre has held them off... or tried to eat them, I don't know! Oh, help us, please!!~ []
@1037969 = ~Yer friend is no longer deservin' of the position he had... wouldn't it be best if ye all just left, now? Imnesvale is not such a place fer folks like you an' that ranger.~ []
@1037970 = ~Mighty pleased t' see ye, ranger... hope yer findin' our village to yer likin'. We all appreciate havin' someone like you t' replace Merella, an' all. Such a tragic thing, her dyin'.~ []
@1037971 = ~Greetings to ye, ranger. Might I say we're mighty pleased to have a fine <PRO_MANWOMAN> like yerself helpin' us all. Ye've proven yerself... I hope the gods continue t' smile on ye, truly.~ []
@1037973 = ~That foul witch, Umar... or whoever it might be... has cast her shadow over us all. It's up to you... an yer friends... t' save us all. Go an' speak to the Minister, if ye haven't already.~ []
@1037974 = ~I wouldn'a believed it if I hadn't seen it myself... that ogre's lived up to his word and saved us all from the initial attack. It's up t' you, though, now... ye has to go to the cave near here and save him.~ []
@1037975 = ~I can't believe it... that ogre an' his creatures... they went an' protected us from those ogrons come from th' hills. But now they're in trouble... you plannin' on helpin' him out o' this trouble?~ []
@1037976 = ~Ogrons have come down from th' hills an' are plannin' to attack us... you must help the village, ranger! Go, quickly!~ []
@1037977 = ~There are a group of those... those creatures preparing to attack the village! The herders say they are near the caves! Oh, you must help us, please!!~ []
@1037981 = ~Maybe ye all should just go... an' take yer former ranger friend, there, with ye. Our village... we'll find our way just fine without the likes o' <PRO_HIMHER>.~ []
@1037982 = ~Yer doin' a fine job, there, my <PRO_LADYLORD> ranger... Merella would o' been proud, in fact. Is there anythin' yer needin' help with?~ []
@1037992 = ~You know quite a bit about the area's history, Nelleck... what can you tell me about it?~ []
@1037994 = ~Not much, my <PRO_LADYLORD> ranger... that noble came an' didn't even talk to the Minister. Just marched on over there with 'is men, easy as ye please.~ []
@1037995 = ~There was lots o' relics and such left from th' days when mithril was mined in th' hills... but most of it's long gone. I don't think he'll find none.~ []
@1037996 = ~'At don't mean he won't disturb the forest, or burn it down while he's goin' about 'is business. Tsk... a real shame. Me pa said that area's all holy ground.~ []
@1037997 = ~None. Like I've said before... Madulf an 'em are pretty quiet an' keep t' themselves, mostly. I don't think they wants any trouble.~ []
@1037998 = ~Better than ye'd think, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. Madulf and a couple o' others have been in an' out a few times... buyin' food an' usin' the inn.~ []
@1037999 = ~Folks were scared at first, but they've been real polite. Keepin' a low profile, too... as low as 'em big 'uns can get, anyway. The merchants like it, anyhow.~ []
@1038000 = ~Nay. They're long gone... an' good riddance. Got what they came for, didn't they? Heh...~ []
@1038001 = ~Nay... no one's come. Nasty bugger wasn't liked much even by them other nobles, I guess. The sacred ground will stay as it is, more or less undisturbed.~ []
@1038002 = ~Aye. Even Johanna went an' thanked Madulf, personally. And now Imnesvale's got defenders like no one else. Who'd 'ave thought, aye, m'<PRO_LADYLORD>?~ []
@1038005 = ~Aye. No one expected Madulf and his followers t' actually help anyone. They been by t' trade things, an' such... real polite. People are mighty thankful.~ []
@1038006 = ~Nay, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. No sightings. Been a long time since them orcs attacked... an' I think they'll think twice, now, 'fore they try it again.~ []
@1038009 = ~Aye, things have been going very well an' smoothly, like. We're all mighty grateful to have ye here, my <PRO_LADYLORD> ranger.~ []
@1038011 = ~Well... the village has been here for centuries, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. Even during Umar's rule... although it was a darker place, then, an' mostly just farms an' such.~ []
@1038012 = ~There was a rush a few centuries back... found mithril in th' hills. Temples and such were built all o'er the place, then abandoned when the mines ran dry.~ []
@1038016 = ~As ye wish, my <PRO_LADYLORD>... anythin' ye wish, I'll always be glad t' help ye.~ []
@1038017 = ~Despite all ye've done fer us, yer no longer welcome here, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. Yer type... well, maybe ye'd better just be on yer way.~ []
@1038018 = ~There's ogrons come from the hills, my <LADYLORD>... orcs with ogre blood in 'em. They're gathered near the cave north o' the river, plannin' to attack the village.~ []
@1038023 = ~There's ogrons come from th' hills, my <LADYLORD>... orcs mixed with ogre blood. That ogre, Madulf, an' his followers... they've been fightin' them for the village.~ []
@1038026 = ~Madulf's given us some time, but the ogrons have him holed up in the cave north o' the river. He needs help... talk to the Minister, if ye haven't already.~ []
@1038030 = ~There's ogrons come from th' hills, my <LADYLORD> ranger... orcs mixed with ogre blood. Madulf an' his followers, they've kept their word and fought against 'em.~ []
@1038031 = ~They've bought us some time... but the ogrons cornered 'em in a cave north o' the river. They need help. Best go an' see the Minister, if ye haven't already.~ []
@1038033 = ~My <LADYLORD>! The... the witch, Umar, has returned an' warns us all to leave 'fore she murders us all! I can hardly believe it t' be true!~ []
@1038034 = ~The Minister has asked for ye... go an' speak to him, if ye haven't already. He knows where the witch to be... ye must protect us, my <LADYLORD>!~ []
@1038045 = ~Ahhh... good day to you, then. Is there something that you need?~ []
@1038056 = ~(sigh)  Well... ye are the local ranger, here. Very well, I'll keep me brusqueness to meself, if it offends ye. Now... did ye want t' buy somethin' or nay?~ []
@1038059 = ~As ye wish, then. But you'll get no discount, here... I nay be givin' me shelves o' goods away.~ []
@1038064 = ~Is there... is there something that you need?~ []
@1038078 = ~Actually... this is a matter I really must talk to our <PRO_LADYLORD> ranger about, my <LADYLORD>. No offense...~ []
@1038079 = ~Actually... the matter of the ogrons is something I really must talk to our <PRO_LADYLORD> ranger about, my <LADYLORD>. No offense...~ []
@1038099 = ~Greetings, my <PRO_LADYLORD> ranger... I trust you have already been approached by the forest spirit? I am afraid there is little that I can do.~ []
@1038106 = ~That is good... I am very relieved. Lord Igen is currently in the same area as those... that Shadow Lord was, earlier. I suggest you go quickly.~ []
@1038107 = ~That is... a little more than I expected, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. But, I suppose you are correct... Lord Igen must be stopped, no matter what occurs.~ []
@1038109 = ~Go swiftly, then, and be safe... Lord Igen is in the land that the Shadow Lord was, until recently... to the west.~ []
@1038112 = ~Very well... I will keep my word. This time.~ []
@1038113 = ~Of course you are right, Minister... please forgive me.~ []
@1038114 = ~As... as you say, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. The Lord Igen is in the lands to the west of here... in the area once occupied by that Shadow Lord. Be... be careful.~ []
@1038115 = ~Then... then you are unworthy to be the ranger of our village! By Mielikki, I've never seen a ranger of your sort! How you are not Fallen is beyond me!~ []
@1038123 = ~The ogron band is collected outside of the cave... on the north shore of the river. I beg of you, <CHARNAME>... please deal with this menace!~ []
@1038124 = ~... he is trapped in a cave with one of our shepherd boys, Atta, who wandered into the area. Madulf scooped the boy up and took refuge in the cave.~ []
@1038125 = ~The boy must be saved, <CHARNAME>... and Madulf must not die in vain! Please... deal with this menace, I beg you! Or we will all be forced to flee our village!~ []
@1038126 = ~... the fighting has driven him back into a cave. Rescue him, <CHARNAME>, and deal with this menace... or the whole village must flee for our lives!~ []
@1038127 = ~Yes he is, but this is too convenient for my tastes. Something could be wrong.~ []
@1038128 = ~I have no desire to fight ogrons... deal with this yourselves.~ []
@1038129 = ~Very well, Minister... I will do what I can.~ []
@1038130 = ~No, I killed the bastard. This was too easy, so I figured he was lying.~ []
@1038131 = ~But... but, <CHARNAME>! You are our ranger! You... you must help us out, we are in desperate need!~ []
@1038134 = ~Very well... I'll see what I can do.~ []
@1038135 = ~Farsight (Divination)
Level: 4
Sphere: Divination
Range: Special
Duration: 3 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 4 
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None 

When Farsight is cast, the caster is able to view an area of an unexplored map. After casting the spell, simply click on a section of the map that you want to view. For the duration of the spell, the caster can spy on that area, noting creatures and fortifications.~
@1038138 = ~The village would be grateful, <CHARNAME>... go, then... the cave is on the north shore of the river. I... I do not know how many ogrons there are... good luck.~ []
@1038140 = ~I am most relieved! Go, <CHARNAME>... the cave is on the north shore of the river! I do not know how many ogrons there are, but I wish you well.~ []
@1038144 = ~Very well, Minister... I will help, if I can.~ []
@1038145 = ~But... but <CHARNAME>, there is a boy whose life is in danger! And you are a ranger, are you not? How can you abandon us like this?~ []
@1038147 = ~(sigh)  Very well, then... I'll see what I can do.~ []
@1038149 = ~I... I do not believe he can, <CHARNAME>. Please... a boy is in danger, and the ogre must not die for helping us. You are a ranger... will you not aid us?~ []
@1038154 = ~Very well... I will help, if I can.~ []
@1038155 = ~But the ogre is in danger, <CHARNAME>... and he fought valiantly to aid us! You... you are a ranger? Have you less honor than an ogre? Will you not help us?~ []
@1038160 = ~Very well, Minister... I will see what I can do.~ []
@1038161 = ~Of course you are right, Minister... I apologize. I will help, if I can.~ []
@1038166 = ~The cave is on the north side of the river, <CHARNAME>, not far to the northwest of here... you will find the ogrons there. Go quickly!~ []
@1038173 = ~<CHARNAME>, we are in dire straits. Umar, or someone claiming to be her, has returned. She came several days ago, ordering all the villagers to leave at once.~ []
@1038175 = ~What? That was your solution? You had better hope you are right, because if you aren't, you are going to be in sooo much trouble.~ []
@1038176 = ~Everyone was so frightened... this Umar then shouted with a great, booming voice, saying she was reclaiming her land and that we were trespassers...~ []
@1038177 = ~She has given us only a few days, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. A few days to leave forever, or she will kill us. You... you will help us, yes?~ []
@1038182 = ~(sigh)  I wonder how long I'll have to live like this? Well... all the assassins are dead, now, no matter what you've done. I know how they work. You should probably go back to the Order and report this... I'd rather be alone.~ []
@1038183 = ~I'll do what I can... where can this supposed 'Umar' be found?~ []
@1038184 = ~But you are a ranger, <CHARNAME>... you are our protector. How can you abandon us now? We cannot fight a force such as this!~ []
@1038188 = ~A... a reward? Did you become a ranger to become rich, <CHARNAME>? You have a duty! Will abandon us now, and leave us to face this witch?~ []
@1038190 = ~I suppose you're right... I'll see what I can do. Where is this 'Umar'?~ []
@1038191 = ~Of course not... I'm sorry, Minister. Where can I find this sorceress?~ []
@1038192 = ~Shepherds followed her to the lands in the west. She... went into the dungeon where you found the Shadow Lord. That is where you should start.~ []
@1038193 = ~I am grateful for your aid, <CHARNAME>... I trust the gods will look out for you... and Imnesvale... once again.~ []
@1038194 = ~Sure, sure. My father was certain, too, that his enemies wouldn't stoop to this. Well, whatever. I know how these assassins work... they're not coming back. Go back to the Order and report whatever you have to. I will be fine.~ []
@1038199 = ~Are you certain you have no proof of your identity?~ []
@1038203 = ~Are you certain you have no proof of your identity?~ []
@1038215 = ~I will go and get her directly. Forgive my obstinate nature, but I had to be sure.~ []
@1038218 = ~I will go and get her directly. Forgive my obstinate nature, but I had to be sure.~ []
@1038223 = ~You, there... you are the <PRO_RACE> who has become the ranger for this place? My name is Mairyn... I am a spirit of this forest, and I am in desperate need of your aid!~ []
@1038225 = ~There are... other humans... in my sacred lands to the north of this place where the temple of the sun god once stood. They have come recently,  digging and tearing down the trees...~ []
@1038226 = ~I have begged them to stop, good ranger... I have pleaded with them that they are destroying not only I, but many of the other forest spirits as well. The humans have refused.~ []
@1038227 = ~I implore you... go to the forest in the north and do whatever you can to stop these humans from further desecrating my forest!~ []
@1038230 = ~And we are baffled as to how you could have made such a mistake! You have killed one of the most respected servants of Torm in the realms!~ []
@1038235 = ~What has happened. <CHARNAME>? I am told that the child is dead and that an imposter of Hurgis Baltezan was also found killed.~ []
@1038239 = ~Very well, Mairyn... I will do what I can to help.~ []
@1038242 = ~No interest? You are a ranger, are you not? You are a defender of the wild... and I am in desperate need of your assistance. Will you turn your back on me, ranger?~ []
@1038244 = ~You are right... I will help you, if I can.~ []
@1038246 = ~I know not who these humans are... they claim, however, to be searching for something. Something I do not know the location of. They... threatened me, ranger. I was forced to flee.~ []
@1038250 = ~Very well... I will go and help you, if I can.~ []
@1038251 = ~Reward? You are the first ranger I have heard of who has desired something in compensation for his duty. I... I have nothing to offer you, ranger, other than my gratitude.~ []
@1038253 = ~Very well... I will see what I can do.~ []
@1038256 = ~I will tell them of their mistake... and I will deal with the humans in the west as best I can. Go, unworthy ranger... go and be a simple warrior or mercenary, if you must. The forest needs not one such as you.~ []
@1038258 = ~I... I sense that the humans yet continue their desecration of my sacred forest. What is it, good ranger? Is there a problem?~ []
@1038260 = ~I have agreed to find what the noble, Lord Igen, was looking for... but I cannot seem to find it.~ []
@1038261 = ~There is no problem, Mairyn... I will continue trying.~ []
@1038262 = ~Yes, there is. I cannot make the Lord stop his search... I can do nothing more to help you.~ []
@1038263 = ~Yes, there is. I have changed my mind... I do not have the time to help you.~ []
@1038268 = ~But how is this possible? You said he would arrive!~ []
@1038275 = ~But you must find a way to stop him, ranger... you must! He cannot continue his actions! He gives no thought to the consequence of what he does!~ []
@1038277 = ~I will not harm him, Mairyn... and I cannot help you.~ []
@1038278 = ~Very well... I will keep on trying.~ []
@1038280 = ~He seeks a cache of mithril hidden by an ancestor... but he has only half of the directions to where it lays.~ []
@1038281 = ~I do not know where this human might find this mithril. I truly do not. I might suggest that you look to the human temple beneath the ground... the place where you, yourself, banished the shadows.~ []
@1038284 = ~Perhaps you might find what you seek there... I cannot say, for certain.~ []
@1038285 = ~Mielikki bless you, good ranger... I will continue to wait here.~ []
@1038288 = ~Very well... I will try again.~ []
@1038291 = ~I already sense that the violation of my forest has ceased, good ranger. I... I am sorry that it had to come to violence. You have protected your charge, nevertheless, and I am grateful.~ []
@1038292 = ~I will return to my home, now, and thank Mielikki that one who is true to her service has taken up a station here... that justice is upheld in this woodland. Bless you, good ranger.~ []
@1038294 = ~You successfully detected the evil they were trying to perpetrate, and for that you have earned the respect of your peers and the community.~ []
@1038299 = ~Good ranger... it is I, Mairyn, and once again I must ask you for help. The witch who has threatened your village... her dark and foul magics have also begun to poison the woodland! You must do something!~ []
@1038305 = ~Very well... I will seek her out and stop her.~ []
@1038309 = ~Yes, I already know of her... I will do what I can, Mairyn.~ []
@1038316 = ~You do not know? A witch has come into the area very recently... a human witch... and she has threatened your village with her magic. Either they leave... or she will kill them.~ []
@1038317 = ~Already she gathers her dark powers in the buried human temple... that place where you destroyed the Shadow Lord. Her magic seeps into the earth and poisons it with evil.~ []
@1038323 = ~Yes, as I said... I have more important things to do.~ []
@1038324 = ~Very well... I will see what I can do. But I must go to Imnesvale, first.~ []
@1038327 = ~She lies below, good ranger, and the need is most urgent... but if you must go to your village, first, then do so quickly. I will wait here for you.~ []
@1038329 = ~I sense that the sorceress is dead... the foul presences she has conjured have ceased. You have done well, good ranger.~ []
@1038330 = ~You have served the natural order with honor and strength, good ranger. I... I have something to give you. It is a present from Mielikki, a most rare thing...~ []
@1038331 = ~... an idol of the Moon Dog to help when you struggle. Take it, <PRO_RACE>, and be thankful that a goddess smiles upon you.~ []
@1038332 = ~Oh! There you are, my <PRO_LADYLORD> ranger! I... I've been looking all over the place for you! You... you've got to come to Imnesvale!~ []
@1038335 = ~There's orcs... big ones! Nelleck says he saw them coming down from the hills. Soon they'll attack! The Minister sent me to find you, my <PRO_LADYLORD>!~ []
@1038338 = ~Tell them to find someone else to deal with it... it's not my problem.~ []
@1038339 = ~But... but you're a ranger! You're the protector that replaced Merella, aren't you? You've got to come! We've got nobody else to turn to!~ []
@1038340 = ~Oh, please, my <PRO_LADYLORD>! Please! Everyone's so scared that they're going to have to flee the village! I... I thought rangers were supposed to help people...~ []
@1038341 = ~Madulf... he said he would do what he can, but Nelleck says there's too many! Oh, please, my <PRO_LADYLORD>! Please! I... I thought rangers were supposed to help people...~ []
@1038342 = ~Nelleck says that they'll be at the village soon... no later than three or four days from now. You've got to hurry!~ []
@1038352 = ~What... what could be more important than this?! Oooh... Nelleck says that the orcs will be on us within four days at the most... maybe less...~ []
@1038353 = ~... I... I'll go an' tell Minister Lloyd that you may not be coming. I do so hope you change your mind, my <PRO_LADYLORD>! I was sure you would help us...~ []
@1038354 = ~If you... if you change your mind... please hurry...~ []
@1038355 = ~I... I thought rangers were good people... that they protected people. I... I can't believe you won't help us anymore...~ []
@1038356 = ~Orcs... big ones... are comin' down from the hills. Nelleck saw 'em, and the Minister sent me to find you. They'll be at the village in four days... maybe less!~ []
@1038357 = ~Madulf says he'll help, but Nelleck says there's too many... even for him and those other creatures of his. The Minister says you should come quickly, my <PRO_LADYLORD>.~ []
@1038358 = ~We haven't got anyone t' turn to, except you. And... and you replaced Merella, right? You'll come, then, right?~ []
@1038359 = ~I... I've found you again, my <PRO_LADYLORD>! It's... it's always so hard to find you, sometimes! The... the village is in danger again! The Minister has asked for you!~ []
@1038363 = ~It's Umar! The witch! She's come back, and she's threatened to kill everyone if they don't go an' leave right now! The... the Minister says he will tell you everything!~ []
@1038367 = ~Don't have time? But... but you helped us fight those orcs... and you saved us all before that. Why... why would you abandon us now? I thought you were a ranger...~ []
@1038369 = ~Perhaps you are right... what is happening in the village?~ []
@1038371 = ~I... I can't believe you won't help us. If you... if you change your mind, please come and help! I don't think we can fight this...~ []
@1038372 = ~It's Umar! The witch! She's come back, and she's threatened to kill everyone if they don't go an' leave right now! The... the Minister says he will tell you everything!~ []
@1038380 = ~Well, what you're doing is destroying the forest... you have to stop.~ []
@1038393 = ~Very well, then... off you go, peasant.~ []
@1038402 = ~I am warning you... your life is forfeit if you continue this desecration.~ []
@1038408 = ~You're not going to continue what you're doing... I'm here to see to that.~ []
@1038412 = ~Hmmmn. I might, at that. It would certainly save me a great deal of trouble... and spare me the danger of facing the monsters, here. Are you serious about this, woods<PRO_MANWOMAN>?~ []
@1038415 = ~No... I doubt you would keep your deal, anyway. It would be far better to kill you now.~ []
@1038417 = ~I am willing to put off the search... at least for a while, to give you time to look for it. I'm sure my men will be glad of the break, at any rate... and it really costs me nothing.~ []
@1038418 = ~You are a ranger, aren't you? I should have guessed from the attitude and the clothing. Very well, then, ranger. I will leave here forever, if you find what I am looking for. You have my word.~ []
@1038421 = ~He was not alone, back then. Many nobles came... and there was not enough for all, certainly. I had always assumed that Idras had found nothing, but his journal suggests otherwise.~ []
@1038423 = ~The part of the journal I have only mentions this area in general... nothing specific. Hence the large search I have undertaken. Here... I have a copy that was printed out. You may need it.~ []
@1038424 = ~The other half of his journal may be around here... I certainly couldn't say where it might be, though, and I'm not about to waste effort looking for it.~ []
@1038425 = ~So... there you have it, ranger. My men will set up camp, here, and we will give you some time to search. It means little to me, but for your sake I wish you well.~ []
@1038430 = ~... I see. So this medallion is the sum of all he found? The fool!   Ahhh, then this whole expedition has been a waste. It cannot be that valuable that all this effort has been worth it.~ []
@1038434 = ~Very well... a thousand gold and your departure is enough for me.~ []
@1038436 = ~I would prefer to hang onto it, actually... it might be worth more than you say.~ []
@1038439 = ~I suppose I do not need your coin... it is yours by right, as you say. Take it and leave, then.~ []
@1038440 = ~Sorry... two thousand or you don't get it.~ []
@1038441 = ~Do not test my patience, peasant. It is mine by right, and I will not be trifled with. I will give you five hundred gold... and do not presume to bargain with me further.~ []
@1038443 = ~Perhaps you are right. Five hundred it is... so long as you leave, as well.~ []
@1038445 = ~Aye. I am a man of my word, ranger. I have found what I desired... such as it is... and I shall go. Come, men... we are returning to the city.~ []
@1038446 = ~You are generous, then. I see the rangers are as noble as their reputation. Very well, then... I am also a man of my word. Come, men... we return to the city.~ []
@1038447 = ~I warn you, peasant. That is my property... and I shall use force, if necessary, to take it from you. I offer five hundred gold... accept or face the consequences.~ []
@1038449 = ~I've no desire for trouble... five hundred it is.~ []
@1038450 = ~Never mind, Lord Igen... I've no need for your coin. It's yours, as you said. Take it and go.~ []
@1038453 = ~Hmmmn... a commoner <MANWOMAN>. Away with you... I doubt we have any business, the two of us.~ []
@1038458 = ~That's too bad... you will not continue this desecration so long as I am here.~ []
@1038460 = ~Nothing... I'll be on my way.~ []
@1038466 = ~I found this medallion, along with a note from Idras. Apparently, he didn't have much luck... he used all his mithril to make this.~ []
@1038467 = ~I haven't... but I have found the other half of Idras' journal, here. Will you accept that, instead?~ []
@1038469 = ~No... and I have decided not to continue looking.~ []
@1038470 = ~It doesn't matter... I doubt you can be trusted, anyway. It is better to kill you now.~ []
@1038471 = ~Certainly not. I do not know where you got those writings, ranger... they might not even be authentic. And even if they are... use them to find the cache yourself.~ []
@1038473 = ~After all... it is you who is so concerned about my men leaving tracks in your precious landscape, not I.~ []
@1038474 = ~Oh all right, but then we have to get going. It isn't safe here.~ []
@1038477 = ~Forget it, then... I am not about to continue this fool's errand.~ []
@1038478 = ~I have my doubts as to whether you would even keep your word... forget your task, noble. Killing you is the only option.~ []
@1038479 = ~As you wish. You can look no better than I, I suppose... I shall continue to bide my time, here. I'll even keep my men off the grass.~ []
@1038480 = ~I think they let us stay because Gorion had powerful friends. I wish he had said where I was before that, but he thought it wasn't important, so I didn't worry too much.~ []
@1038481 = ~That is not good enough. You know too much about what I look for. In fact... you could already have found the cache and intend to keep it for yourself. Continue the search... or face the consequence.~ []
@1038482 = ~Very well... I'll keep looking.~ []
@1038484 = ~Do so... and return once you have it. And do not force me to come looking for you, either, peasant...~ []
@1038486 = ~We left when Sarevok killed Gorion. I was sorry I couldn't help, but we got him in the end. Remember that? That Sarevok turned out to be a child of Bhaal, like you?~ []
@1038488 = ~I am no one you need to concern yourself with, traveler. I am here to ensure the safety of Lord Igen, and that is all.~ []
@1038490 = ~You have agreed to undertake Lord Igen's search for him? Then you are foolish, indeed. He will not stray from his quarry... and I doubt you have the ability to complete the task.~ []
@1038495 = ~Don't mind the break, here, at all. You all just watch yourselves... any funny business with Lord Tombelthen and that'll be the end of you.~ []
@1038496 = ~You'se must kill the ogrons, <RACE>! Li'l human must be protected! Go an' kill ogrons... Madulf wounded. Madulf stay and protect li'l human...~ []
@1038497 = ~You'se must kill ogrons! Madulf try, but Madulf wounded... Madulf hold off ogrons from here. Go, <RACE>... kill ogrons! Protect human village!!~ []
@1038501 = ~Ogrons dead? You'se done good, <RACE>. You'se kill all 'em ogrons good... Madulf try, but Madulf's friends get hurt and run. Then li'l human came, and Madulf had to protect li'l human.~ []
@1038502 = ~Madulf pick up li'l human and run for cave. Ogrons shoot arrows... hurt Madulf. You'se okay, though, li'l human? You'se not hurt?~ []
@1038504 = ~I... my name's Atta... and I'm fine, mister Ogre, sir...~ []
@1038507 = ~... Okay... um, thank you, mister Ogre...~ []
@1038510 = ~Madulf say he protect village, so he try kill ogrons. Ogrons very strong, though. Madulf kept word, though... Madulf hold ogrons back so ogrons no attack too soon. You'se get here just in time.~ []
@1038511 = ~Madulf go, now... Madulf must find his friends, see if friends dead or wounded, maybe. Madulf see, now, if humans in village be nicer to Madulf and friends.~ []
@1038512 = ~You'se a good <RACE>... Madulf thanks you for saving Madulf.~ []
@1038513 = ~Madulf knows Madulf never promise to protect village... but Madulf not watch village humans be hurt. Madulf and friends... we hold ogrons back. You'se get here just in time.~ []
@1038514 = ~Ogrons dead? You'se done good, <RACE>. You'se kill all 'em ogrons good... Madulf try, but Madulf's friends get hurt and run into hills.~ []
@1038515 = ~Madulf fight ogrons on own, but ogrons shoots arrows... arrows hurt Madulf, so Madulf run for cave.~ []
@1038516 = ~Are... are all those bad monsters gone, <SIRMAAM>? I... I'm so scared...~ []
@1038521 = ~Thank you again, <CHARNAME>... the gods have smiled on us, indeed, to allow us you as our ranger.~ []
@1038525 = ~Well... this changes my mind about him, and I hope others in the village will feel the same. We are blessed, truly, to have him... and you... as our protectors.~ []
@1038527 = ~We had to call the Knights of the Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart to help... but they arrived too late to save many. You could have done much to prevent it.~ []
@1038538 = ~Of course, but if <CHARNAME> is here as well I should speak with <PRO_HIMHER>.~ []
@1038539 = ~Minsc, that is horrible! I am so sorry for you.~ []
@1038543 = ~Eww, I... really don't want to think about that too much.~ []
@1038544 = ~I... I know this room. I've been in here... we both have. He... There are things in these tanks. They used to be people...~ [IMOENJ52]
@1038546 = ~You must invade their lair for one last time. You must kill Aran Linvail, the Shadow Master. Do this for me and our arrangement will be fulfilled.~ []
@1038563 = ~I don't know about that, Minsc, but he sure is a cute little fuzzy wuzzy. Aren't you, Boo?~ []
@1038567 = ~Cloak of Fear (Conjuration)
Level: 4
Sphere: Charm
Range: Touch
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: Self
Saving Throw: Neg.

Cloak of fear empowers the caster to radiate a personal aura of fear out to a 3-foot radius. All other characters and creatures within this aura must roll successful saving throws vs. spell or run away in panic for 4 rounds. Affected individuals may even drop items. Party members are immune to the effects, although the aura of fear may still disturb them.~
@1038570 = ~False Dawn (Evocation)
Level: 6
Sphere: Sun
Range: 0
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None

False dawn calls into existence a bright reddish light, as if a sunrise were occurring, within the area of effect. All undead creatures within a false dawn suffer 6d6 points of damage. There is no saving throw against this damage. Affected undead also act confused on the round after the false dawn appears.~
@1038572 = ~Dolorous Decay (Alteration, Necromancy)
Level: 6
Sphere: Combat, Necromantic
Range: 10 yards
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: One creature
Saving Throw: Special

This spell affects a single living creature. Dolorous Decay is a rotting and withering of the body that spreads throughout the afflicted creature quickly. The target creature will automatically be slowed for two rounds. Furthermore, if the target fails a saving throw vs. poison at a -2 penalty, he or she will receive 1 point of damage per second until a total of 50 points of damage have been inflicted.~ []
@1038574 = ~Wondrous Recall (Alteration)
Level: 6
Sphere: Charm, Creation
Range: 0
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This enables the caster to bring back into memory two spells that have been previously cast. If no spells have been cast yet, then nothing happens. Wondrous recall cannot recall 6th-level or greater spells.~
@1038576 = ~Bolt of Glory (Invocation/Evocation)
Level: 6
Sphere: Combat, Summoning
Range: 20 yards
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Target Creature
Saving Throw: None

By casting this spell, the priest channels a bolt of divine energy against one creature. No attack roll is needed. Creatures struck suffer varying damage, depending on their plane of existence.

Creature Type                       Damage
 Prime Material Plane            6d6
 Elemental                             3d4
 Undead                                8d6
 Demon                                 10d6~
@1038580 = ~Sol's Searing Orb (Invocation)
Level: 6
Sphere: Sun
Range: 30 yards
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: Target
Saving Throw: Special

When the spell is completed, it creates a glowing stone. This gem must be immediately thrown at an opponent, for it quickly becomes too hot to hold. It is not possible for the priest to give the stone to another character to throw. The priest must roll normally to hit; he gains a +3 bonus to his attack roll and suffers no penalty for nonweapon proficiency. In addition, the glowing gem can be used to strike any creature, even those hit only by magical weapons. There is no damage bonus, however.
When it hits, the gem bursts with a brilliant, searing flash that causes 6d6 points of fire damage to the target and blinds her for 1d6 rounds. The victim is allowed a saving throw vs. spell. If successful, only half damage is sustained and the target is not blinded. Undead creatures suffer 12d6 points of fire damage and are blinded for twelve rounds (if applicable) assuming their save is failed. They receive 9d6 points of damage and are blinded for six rounds if the save is successful.~
@1038582 = ~Zone of Sweet Air (Abjuration)
Level: 3
Sphere: Wards
Range: 30 yards
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

Zone of Sweet Air repels all noxious elements from poisonous vapors (including magically created vapors such as Cloudkill). This spell will dismiss all clouds within its area of effect.~ []
@1038585 = ~Alarm 

(Abjuration, Evocation)


Range: 10 yds.'Components: V, S, M
Duration: 4 hrs. + ' hr./level'Casting Time: 1 rd.
Area of Effect: Up to 20-ft. cube'Saving Throw: None

When an alarm spell is cast, the wizard causes a selected area to react to the presence of any creature larger than a normal rat--anything larger than about 1 cubic foot in volume or more than about three pounds in weight. The area of effect can be a portal, a section of floor, stairs, etc. As soon as any creature enters the warded area, touches it, or otherwise contacts it without speaking a password established by the caster, the alarm spell lets out a loud ringing that can be heard clearly within a 60-foot radius. (Reduce the radius by 10 feet for each interposing door and by 20 feet for each substantial interposing wall.)  The sound lasts for one round and then ceases. Ethereal or astrally projected creatures do not trigger an alarm, but flying or levitating creatures, invisible creatures, or incorporeal or gaseous creatures do. The caster can dismiss the alarm with a single word.~ []
@1038589 = ~Melf's Minute Meteors (Evocation/Alteration)
Level: 3
Range: 70 yds
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 1 target/meteor
Saving Throw: None

This spell enables the wizard to summon small globes of fire (one for each level of experience of the caster), which, when thrown, burst upon impact and inflict 1d4 + 3 points of damage, +3 additional fire damage, to the creature struck. The meteors are treated as missiles hurled by the wizard with a +5 bonus to the attack roll and with no penalty for range. Each meteor has a +6 level of enchantment. The wizard may discharge up to five missiles per round.~ []
@1038597 = ~Wizard Eye (Divination/Alteration)
Level: 4
Range: 0
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is employed, the wizard creates an invisible sensory organ capable of sending him visual information. The Wizard Eye can see with normal vision up to 60 feet away, and can travel in any direction as long as the spell lasts. It has substance and a form that can be detected (by a Detect Invisibility spell, for instance). Solid barriers prevent the passage of a Wizard Eye. The powers of the eye cannot be enhanced by other spells or items. A successful dispel cast on the wizard or eye ends the spell.~ []
@1038600 = ~Limited Wish 
(Conjuration/Summoning, Invocation/Evocation)
Level: 7
Range: Unlimited
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Special

The Limited Wish is a very potent but difficult spell. It will fulfill literally, but only partially or for a limited duration, the utterance of the spellcaster. The use of a Limited Wish will not substantially change major realities (the spell can, for example, restore some hit points lost by the wizard). Greedy desires usually end in disaster for the wisher. Finally, the wiser the wizard, the better the chance that he or she will choose the right wording. Wizards with low wisdom will more often than not meet with disaster when asking for a wish.~ []
@1038605 = ~I shall send a mage to meet you there and arrange for the doors to be opened. Here, you shall need these stakes if you are to truly finish these creatures.~ []
@1038608 = ~This flail has been in the care of Lord de'Arnise for some time, a relic of his adventuring youth. It has been kept disassembled, the individual pieces stored in separate locations, and only used in the direst of emergencies. Lord de'Arnise was likely concerned about the powerful magic that the weapon radiates when assembled, and rightfully so. A trail of destruction has followed it through history, leading straight back to the original owners. The flail was the creation of the warlike Rakshasa, a race of vengeful spirits that crave human meat, and used as an adaptable weapon that could suit any battle. During a particularly violent hunt the flail was lost, only to be returned when they used their affinity with magic to locate its powerful aura. They discovered that the weapon had found its way into the hands of a great human warrior, and the battle that followed was truly splendid. They have since used the item as bait countless times, 'losing' it again and again. Powerful items gravitate towards powerful people, and powerful people yield the most glorious battles.

STATISTICS:

Combat Abilities: Target will be slowed on each hit (no saving throw)
THAC0: +3 bonus
Damage: 1D6 + 4, +1 acid damage, +1 fire damage, +1 cold damage
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 10
Speed Factor: 4
Proficiency Type: Flail/Morningstar
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 13 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Mage 
 Thief
 Monk
 Beast Master~ []
@1038609 = ~Flail of Ages +1~
@1038611 = ~They only do exactly what they are directed to; they don't really think. If it hasn't been told to keep quiet we might get some information out of it.~ []
@1038612 = ~What... what is this place? It's beautiful. Oh, there is simply no way that this space belongs to the same person that owns those horrible glass containers.~ [IMOENJ53]
@1038618 = ~Perhaps it is simply a side of him we have not seen.~ []
@1038625 = ~This room: if he could care for anything he would care for this room. Above the lives of all of us. It makes me sick. I feel... I feel... so much hate.~ []
@1038633 = ~Jaheira... I want to say how sorry I am about Khalid. I... I know this is hard...~ [IMOENJ54]
@1038634 = ~No! You do not know. This is not the time for this conversation, child.~ [JAHEIRE1]
@1038637 = ~I'm not babbling! I saw him do this! Khalid was dead when our captor started... doing those things to him!~ []
@1038647 = ~So beautiful! I used to dream of dryads and their beautiful trees.~ [IMOENJ55]
@1038657 = ~The name of our captor, but we are no closer to his motive.~ []
@1038670 = ~Verily... of that, I have no doubt, Minsc. But the question is hypothetical and requires an answer born of the wisdom of <CHARNAME>, not your impatience.~ []
@1038673 = ~But we have done nothing to you, lady. We have only just come upon you... perhaps if you calm yourself, we could--~ []
@1038675 = ~We have done nothing to you. I see that you are an elf... we are prisoners here, as are you, perhaps if we could--~ []
@1038684 = ~There wasn't much to go back to with Gorion gone.~ []
@1038692 = ~So... I see we have a name for our captor at last. Irenicus, is it? Tell me, dryads, why this Irenicus would go to such lengths to keep you three here.~ []
@1038695 = ~That's your preference. I prefer to lead. Speaking of which, we should get going.~ []
@1038700 = ~While your cursor is over a monster, you can press the Tab key to look at the monster's general hit point status.~ []
@1038706 = ~Not that I'm much help right now. My head still aches and I keep seeing things. Too much death around here, everywhere. It's in everything, even me.~ []
@1038709 = ~This hidden forge seems to work by the mind's will alone. Its magic is such that it will fix the Flail of Ages merely by your wishing it to do so. The forge has a handle with several chains attached. You shall have to find the heads of the flail and bring them to this forge.~ []
@1038727 = ~Glaicus~
@1038728 = ~Glaicus~
@1038736 = ~Well, I'm not about to refuse you a coin or two, you poor soul. We have plenty, I think... and a few gold can do them a lot more good than it does you, <CHARNAME>!~ []
@1038738 = ~Silence, child. Allow the fool to make his judgement.~ [DPJON146]
@1038740 = ~That was a nice thing to do, <CHARNAME>. Although I'm sure you could spare a lot more... what are you saving up for? A golden sword?~ []
@1038743 = ~Now, now, Nalia. A golden sword wouldn't be so bad... except maybe for the weight. And the softness. Pretty much only good for one swing, actually. Hmmm... tell me, <CHARNAME>, just why are you planning on buying a golden sword, anyway? Sounds pretty useless to me.~ []
@1038745 = ~Oh, don't go and tell me you don't want one. I've heard you mumbling in your sleep, you chatty little <PRO_MANWOMAN>. But never mind... I'd like to see you try and fight with one.~ []
@1038751 = ~"The measure of our hearts is taken by the kindness we show to the least of our brethren."  Aye, 'tis truly so.~ []
@1038752 = ~We dared not approach.~ [CSCOW707]
@1038760 = ~Money has far more uses than to simply be given away, Nalia... I'm sure that is exactly what <CHARNAME> has in mind.~ []
@1038765 = ~It might not hurt to see where the child's mother is... if it's on our way, that is. But it's your call, <CHARNAME>.~ []
@1038769 = ~And the fight between the wizard and those men... you saw the whole thing?~ []
@1038775 = ~No, tall one. The Cowled Wizards. They are permitted by the Council to use their foul arts... they watch for any signs of sorcery here in the city.~ []
@1038780 = ~We should be careful, <CHARNAME>... there's no telling what is going on within if the city guard can't handle it. Be prepared for anything, is what I always say.~ []
@1038795 = ~<GABBER>, welcome! You have escaped somewhat later than I had hoped. I am Aataqah.~ [OGREM01]
@1038819 = ~Thrall Fighter~ []
@1038845 = ~Who... me? N-no... I've never done much in the way of shopping. I'm not even sure I would know, exactly, if someone was trying to cheat me, sir.~ []
@1038854 = ~You can press the Tab key while on the main screen and your party members' hit points will appear above their heads.~ []
@1038856 = ~Ribald? Ribald... is that really you?~ []
@1038865 = ~With your kin there always be a need to worry... but I should mind me manners. Please excuse me.~ []
@1038870 = ~I'm sure it's not so... so terrible... as you describe. If you dislike it so much, what are you doing here?~ []
@1038871 = ~Rod of Smiting +3~
@1038875 = ~What... what a pitiful little man. Everyone did laugh at him... but they didn't deserve to die. I... I just can't hate him, despite all he's done.~ []
@1038879 = ~Is... is that you, Jansen?~ []
@1038882 = ~It was well earned. Have you ever told <CHARNAME> how you acquired it? No? Well, let me start by saying that the cockatrice is a rather pernicious breed of chicken, and not one that takes lightly to being plucked. And I suppose I should mention that you actually can make a pretty decent glue out of a bit of spit and goblin droppings, no matter what the old wives tell you. Well, anyway, Queasy here decides to --~ []
@1038883 = ~Come, now, Jan... we're in mixed company here, and I'm sure that's not a tale for certain ears, if you take my meaning.~ []
@1038884 = ~Well, now, I suppose you're right, Queasy. They got the stain out, anyway, so no permanent damage was done. So... joined the circus, eh? Good choice. Thought of it, myself.~ []
@1038885 = ~Ah, but a life of thievery and barter was too appealing, I see. Heh heh... it is good to see you, too, Jansen.~ []
@1038887 = ~Wouldn't think of it. Although I've always had a fondness for those spinning wheels of yours... I've always thought they would make excellent dinner tables. Especially when Aunt Beatrice is cooking... just give 'er a spin and hope for the best, if you take my meaning.~ []
@1038904 = ~I am seeing a lot, Uncle Quayle... and I want you to meet Minsc, as well. He's my protector, I suppose... he says I'm his 'witch'.~ []
@1038912 = ~Ahh, yes... that's what I meant, I suppose.~ []
@1038913 = ~Perhaps you should work a little on your approach, my dear lady. Perhaps a bit of a limp in your step, hunch down a bit more... there, now you have it. Nothing wrong with improving your display, see?~ []
@1038914 = ~I can't believe the conditions here. The nobility allows the poor to live like this just so long as they are out of their sight... it... it makes me furious!~ []
@1038919 = ~I agree. Only with self-determination will such rabble amount to anything, rivvil or no. It makes my stomach reel to see anything relying on the limited pity of others.~ []
@1038921 = ~I've heard of the place. It is the large central building here in the slums. Best be careful inside... although if you are looking for other adventurers, no place is better.~ []
@1038927 = ~Ye can go ahead an' search Shagbag's corpse... the blasted fool. Th' bleedin' book might still be worth something if it's intact.~ []
@1038928 = ~I don't think I've seen... so many destitute people. Can... can we just leave here, <CHARNAME>? It makes me cold all over to think that people live like this...~ []
@1038930 = ~I... I have a coin for you, beggar. Praise be to Ilmater, may the gods look kindly on you, human.~ []
@1038933 = ~The fact that the city barely patrols this area is offensive enough, but the lack of honor in the guards that do... accepting money to overlook offenses... is completely reprehensible!~ []
@1038934 = ~Oh, yes... these are the guards I remember. Blind as a bat once a few coins get placed over their eyes. Tsk.~ []
@1038939 = ~Oh, no! We must do something to help that poor man! I... I can't just stand here and watch this!~ []
@1038942 = ~Such dealings will not go on without response! And you... you vile excuse for a guard... your blind eyes shall be the first put out! <CHARNAME>! Take the others!~ []
@1038945 = ~I don't know if you want to get involved in this, <CHARNAME>... from what I've heard, the slavers in the slums, here, are not to be trifled with. But it could be fun, I suppose...~ []
@1038951 = ~I'd say that, technically, I already own the damnable sphere... and if you continue your irritating attempt to con passers-by, you'll find yourself on the end of my blade. Got it?~ []
@1038953 = ~Er... ah... got it, ah, yes I sure do...~ []
@1038959 = ~I'd say you're a pathetic man who should seriously consider finding some honest work, for once. Honestly... who do you expect to fall for that line?~ []
@1038962 = ~You know, I always wanted a sphere like that. Something the gods might play marbles with... it would make a good conversation piece sitting out on the lawn. Hmmmn. I would hate it if it rolled over the house, though...~ []
@1038964 = ~Oh... (erp) ... you really must excuse me. I just... (erf) ... don't have the stomach for this, much...~ []
@1038965 = ~I... I'm supposed to be Booter's apprentice, but I'm beginning to have second thoughts...~ []
@1038966 = ~Come on back t' the table, boy! Looks like I got another one for ye t' clean up after. And... oh, yeah... bring th' saw.~ []
@1038967 = ~Oh... oh, no... I... (erp) ... I can't...!!~ []
@1038969 = ~Heh... I lose more good apprentices that way, it seems. Ah, well. There was always that fella wi' the pug nose. He jus' vomited at th' screamin.~ []
@1038970 = ~Y-you... you should have heard 'im screamin' earlier... and there was all th' blood... and then there was the hooks... and... and... (erp) ... excuse me... I think I'm going t' be sick...~ []
@1038971 = ~Eh? I kin hardly remember the last time someone actually came in an' talked t' me... must 'a bin, what? Six years ago?~ []
@1038979 = ~Ahhhh, leave me alone. Aran ain't e'en thought o' me in years, he ain't about t' let me outta here. Unless ye gots some good bread, there... does ye gots good bread?~ []
@1038981 = ~Come on, mate... does <HESHE> look like Bingham? You think <HESHE>'s bringin' ye food?~ []
@1038984 = ~Yeah... he were a good fella. Slipped us extra bread, now an' again.~ []
@1038986 = ~'Til Aran locked 'im in here, with us. Fat boy, I 'member... looked mighty tasty. Er... if'n you're into that sorta thing...~ []
@1038989 = ~Yeah... but ye sure <HESHE> ain't here wi' food?~ []
@1038997 = ~(grumble)  Is it night or day, yet? I wouldn't mind seein' th' sun, or somethin'. Mebbe a picture o' th' sun. Or some heat... yeah... like a blanket...~ []
@1038999 = ~Heh... welcome to the guild, friend. We haven't met, yet... me name's Cuchul. Burglar extraordinaire. Best rooftop crawler this side o' Waterdeep, aye.~ []
@1039003 = ~I remember when I wandered into what looked like a mighty temptin' house... large, with lots o' windows. Turned out it were a house o' ill repute, if ye catch me drift.~ []
@1039004 = ~Caught one o' the girls changin'... she didn't mind, none. Yup... 'twas a good night. Came out even, too, helpin' the girls throw out the drunks. Some of 'em was rich drunks.~ []
@1039005 = ~You just mind yer manners when yer around Aran. He's had more than a few close scrapes, as o' late. Assassination attempts... foolish ones, too.~ []
@1039008 = ~This here's the lounge, in case ye were wonderin'. Ain't much in the way of service, but it's a place t' sit when ye ain't training. Ye gotta watch out fer that Pelanna... she'll work ye t' the bone, if she cares to.~ []
@1039010 = ~Yer plannin' on usin' the courses, maybe? Huntin' someone in the crawl or tryin' out the rafters? Watch out fer the trap room, though... the guildmaster there is a bit o' a sadist, if ye asks me.~ []
@1039011 = ~Don't know why Aran bothers with that Tassa... now Pelanna... there's a gal with th' business goin' on, if ye knows what I mean. She can whip me inta shape any time!~ []
@1039012 = ~Heh... ye should'a seen the face on the mark I had last night. Big, round fella, right? Snorin' like there's no tomorrow, an' I sees he's got all this food on 'is belly. Fell asleep eatin' in bed, I guess.~ []
@1039019 = ~You think he says he's welcome or anythin'? Nope. But that's people for ya... it's all goin' downhill, if ye asks me.~ []
@1039042 = ~I'm sure yer wondering just what Mitsu is doing amongst the Shadow Thieves. They don't have many halflings here, right? Well, that's true... but not many halflings take their thievery so seriously.~ []
@1039043 = ~Me, I do. And the fact that I can pass fer a human child... a helpless, cute human child... gives me the edge when I want to rob a mark.~ []
@1039044 = ~All I have t' do is bat me eyes, see? And I make a moue and say, "Please, sir... I can't find my way home? Can you help me?"  Ha! Works like a charm!~ []
@1039046 = ~Heh... of course I shall, if ye wish. I jus' can't help starin' at the wee curves of yer leather, is all. Stirs the heart, it does.~ []
@1039048 = ~Ya know... I was just in the graveyard district the other day, leanin' against a tombstone an' counting coins from a mark I'd hit in the promenade, right?~ []
@1039049 = ~An' this nobleman walks up to me... I'm in me little girl dress, mind... an' he asks if I'm lost. So I goes with it, cryin' and shiverin' and actin' all helpless, like.~ []
@1039051 = ~I gave 'im a kiss on the forehead, too, 'cause he's such a gentleman. 'Course... that's when I had him tied up in his chair and robbed his safe an' all. Good haul. Nice man.~ []
@1039052 = ~Don't let that Tassa order ya around, none. She's just Aran's mistress... and while that means ya don't touch her and don't piss 'er off too much, it doesn't mean ya has to listen to her, s'right?~ []
@1039055 = ~Hmmmn... must be nigh on three months, now. But I've been avoidin' Pelanna like the plague. She won't be convinced me trainin's done 'til I'm on me deathbed.~ []
@1039069 = ~Aye... I suppose nothing that occurs in the guild is any of my business. At least, not any longer. Not once Aran got through with me.~ []
@1039073 = ~I am Achon... I was once Aran's lieutenant, his chief assistant and right-hand man. I was loyal to the guild above all, and that was my greatest fault. I thought I was doing the guild a favor by trying to assassinate Aran.~ []
@1039074 = ~Perhaps I was right, perhaps I was wrong. Perhaps Aran will not destroy our guild. Perhaps the other guild run by that... that woman... will be eliminated. I suppose I shall never know.~ []
@1039083 = ~'Twould be a relief, I think. Aran's had me here for over a month. At least... I think it's been a month. I'd hate to think I'd just be left here to rot, forever...~ []
@1039085 = ~Aran sent me to sneak into a fort in Murann... bring someone who was there back out. I was the best, and he told me the mission was important. Just... just not how important, though.~ []
@1039086 = ~I made it to the fort and even snuck inside under cover of midnight. I got fumbled in a gas trap, though. Didn't even see it coming. My lungs burned as a fought to stay conscious... but I lost.~ []
@1039088 = ~You see... the one I was sent to retrieve was Aran's nephew. They had him prisoner there. And... and he was executed the next morning, by the time I stumbled back to the guild.~ []
@1039090 = ~It's so... so cold down here. And the other prisoners are bleaker than a dark pit in the Abyss. I just... I just wish Aran would take pity on me and have it over with.~ []
@1039094 = ~You'd best be careful not to cross Aran, if you ever work for him. The Shadow Thieves are deadly assassins... and they're completely at his beck and call.~ []
@1039096 = ~There's that other guild, now, isn't there? One run by some woman. I wonder... I wonder if she would get me out of here. I'd work for her, for sure... and I bet there's others that would be willing too, as well.~ []
@1039098 = ~But who am I kidding? There's no hope for me... or any of us, here. Just... go away, whoever you are.~ []
@1039099 = ~... uhhhh... UHHH... n-n-noOOOO, PLEASE!!...~ []
@1039103 = ~(gasp!)  N-nooOOOO... Gggh... ngh... uuuhhhHHHAAAIIIIIEEE!!~ []
@1039105 = ~Do you know how hard that is? Ahhhh... the lack of appreciation, sometimes.~ []
@1039106 = ~Hmmmn. Douglas... find me th' pliers. Time our guest, here, found some respect for the craft.~ []
@1039109 = ~Oh... oh, oh... <erf> ... I... I don't think I can...~ []
@1039110 = ~... uhhhhn... hnghhh... <erf>~ []
@1039112 = ~AYYYYYAHHHHHHhhhh... hhnh...  nn...~ []
@1039116 = ~... s-sorry, Master Booter...~ []
@1039122 = ~Hmmn... I've heard about you. You've done a lot of fighting... deadly, they say, and powerful. Lots of talk. Care to... listen to an offer, hmmmm?~ []
@1039125 = ~Good, good. Now... as I figure it, you can't be too loyal to Aran Linvail just yet, right? You must realize that his position is ripe for the plucking! Anyone with guts could take it, now!~ []
@1039126 = ~The whole guild could be ours! Ours! Just think of it! I... I think...~ []
@1039128 = ~Oooo... I didn't see him, there...~ []
@1039129 = ~Fool! Face your death! And you, there... unless you wish the same, you'll assist me!~ []
@1039136 = ~The Shadowmaster's position hangs by a thread! A thread, I tell you! The slightest touch could topple him! And... and you could do it! I've heard about you!~ []
@1039137 = ~We could... you could rule the entire guild! You could do it! And I could tell... I could... er...~ []
@1039142 = ~Oh... oh no! What have I done! I... I've got to flee! Flee!!~ []
@1039144 = ~Now... where did he go? I could have sworn I saw him come through this part of the crawl only a second ago!~ []
@1039149 = ~Don't make me laugh, Krin. I practically snuck up behind you twice in there and breathed on your ear.~ []
@1039151 = ~(pant)  Alright... alright then. Are you ready for another match?~ []
@1039154 = ~S-stop! Stop! I... I concede. <pant!>  Whew... you really got me, there.~ []
@1039158 = ~Heh... well, you never know. She could be listening from the shadows, right? Nothing wrong with a few extra brownie points, if you know what I mean.~ []
@1039163 = ~Sorry, my friend... Pelanna has us training together, at the moment. She'd murder us if she saw us chatting. Perhaps another time?~ []
@1039166 = ~Combat between men, is it? Such a practice is vile, <CHARNAME>... surely we will not stand idly and allow such practices to continue?~ []
@1039167 = ~They watch people fight each other, here? For pleasure? Why would they do that? Those men... they don't do that willingly, do they?~ []
@1039172 = ~Ah, I see. We've interrupted something, I see. Hmmmn... why, aren't you Lord Havrelock? I believe I've seen you somewhere... with Lady Havrelock, I do believe...~ []
@1039173 = ~Ah! Er... no, no, no... that's not me... or him... or... er...~ []
@1039174 = ~<CHARNAME>! Don't be so cruel... he... he is just a little human boy! What has he done that you should treat him so?~ []
@1039179 = ~A medium shield is carried in the same manner as a small shield. Unlike the small shield, however, a medium shield's weight prevents the bearer from using his or her shield hand for anything other than carrying the medium shield. Medium shields are usually made of metal, range from 3 to 4 feet in diameter, and can be of any shape, from round to square to resembling a dragon's spread wings. A typical medieval shield resembles a triangle with one point facing downward. This is a magical shield.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class Bonus: 3
Weight: 5
Not Usable By:
 Bard
 Druid
 Mage
 Thief
 Monk
 Kensai~ []
@1039183 = ~Greetings to you! I hope you have enjoyed your stay at the Duchal Palace.~ [TTBELT01]
@1039185 = ~But before you leave, it is my duty to make sure you are prepared for what awaits you in the world of Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn.~ []
@1039187 = ~We'll begin with the PAUSE feature. Pause the game at any time with the SPACE BAR or by Left-Clicking on the Clock at the lower left of the screen.~ []
@1039189 = ~Pausing is most useful during combat where it gives you the time to carefully orchestrate your party's attack. While paused, issue your commands.~ []
@1039192 = ~My next topic is on how to differentiate enemies from people you want to talk to. Enemies have red circles, people you want to talk to have blue circles.~ [TTBELT05]
@1039196 = ~Hey there! Wasn't that easy? What I'm going to do now is Turn Hostile. My circle will turn red, and then you can Left-Click on me to attack.~ [TTSER101]
@1039199 = ~All right then! Let's go... hit me if you can!~ []
@1039202 = ~You can look at your Inventory Page by Right-Clicking on your Character Portrait, or be pressing the backpack icon on the left side of the screen (hotkey 'I').~ []
@1039203 = ~Take a quick look at your Inventory Page. To get out of your inventory page, simply press the return to game button at the top left of your screen (hotkey 'G').~ []
@1039204 = ~Equip items by placing them in the appropriate slots around your character on the Inventory Page.~ [TTBELT07]
@1039207 = ~You haven't equipped your weapon yet. Remember, just Right-Click on your Character Portrait and you will find your weapon at the bottom of your screen in your Inventory.~ [TTBELT08]
@1039212 = ~Left-Click on the weapon and you will GRAB the weapon with your cursor. Drag it over to the Character Doll and Left-Click again.~ []
@1039213 = ~Good job! It's time for us to go upstairs now. If you move your cursor over to the stairs, you'll notice that your cursor becomes a stair cursor.~ [TTBELT09]
@1039216 = ~What's taking you so long? Go up the stairs.~ [TTBELT10]
@1039219 = ~Entries are catalogued according to the story chapter in which you encountered them. They are also divided up into quests and main story entries.~ []
@1039220 = ~Main story entries will remain in your journal forever, and they are a reminder of all of the major events in your character's life so far.~ []
@1039221 = ~Quest entries are entered in your journal when a quest begins, and removed when the quest ends. The entry then appears in the Completed Quests section.~ []
@1039223 = ~All right then. Now your first combat lesson. My combat teacher, Brevin, is going to be coming right up the stairs. I want you to hit him with your weapon,  and then check your journal.~ [TTBELT12]
@1039225 = ~Now I want you to check your Map Screen. To access it, just click the Map icon on the left side of your screen (second icon from the top, or press the hotkey 'M'). This will show a view of the area you are currently in.~ [TTBELT14]
@1039232 = ~Another page you might be interested in is the Character sheet. This can be accessed by clicking on the head icon on the left side of the screen (or by pressing the hotkey 'R').~ [TTBELT02]
@1039242 = ~Hello. I am Xan, a mage from Evereska in the north. I am going to join your party and show you how to cast and memorize spells.~ [TTXAN01]
@1039245 = ~You can also configure Quick Spells by Right-Clicking on a Quick Spell slot. This summons a list of memorized spells to choose. If no spells are listed, the character either does not have any spells memorized or cannot cast until higher levels.~ []
@1039254 = ~Any mage (or other spellcaster) must memorize spells using the Rest button on the Left Panel, Mage Book or Priest Scroll pages. Select the Wizard Book (hotkey 'W') or Priest Scroll (hotkey 'P') icon that appears on the left.~ []
@1039257 = ~You haven't slept yet. You can access your Rest button from either your Memorization screen, or your Inventory screen (or the main screen.)~ [TTXAN05]
@1039262 = ~Right click on the scroll and it will bring you to the Item History screen. On the bottom of the screen you will find a button that says 'Write Magic'. Press this and your mage (me) will now be able to cast Flame Arrow (once I memorize it that is.)~ []
@1039264 = ~You haven't had me learn the spell yet. Remember; just Right-Click on the scroll, then on the learn spell ('Write Magic') button on the bottom of the Item History page.~ [TTXAN07]
@1039266 = ~They're going to... they're going to make him fight a wild animal! Oh no! I d-don't think I can watch this... it's horrible!~ []
@1039268 = ~Good job. Now I'm going to teach you how to Identify items. When you find a magical item, you won't automatically know what it does. To find out, you must first Right-Click on the item.~ [TTXAN08]
@1039273 = ~The button can be found somewhere to the north, at the end of a heavily trapped hallway.~ []
@1039278 = ~Have you no compassion for the weak, Anomen? I find this course of action most dishonorable... it leaves a dark taste in my mouth.~ []
@1039284 = ~Aye... giving these destitute men their freedom is only the right thing to do. Are you sure we should not trust them?~ []
@1039287 = ~I think it's the right thing to do, to free these people. I was... once something of a slave, myself, locked away in a tiny cage. It... it isn't right.~ []
@1039292 = ~I want you to cast a spell on Belt now. He is slightly wounded from the other spell you cast on him, so you should use one of my healing spells. Go ahead, cast a healing spell on Belt, or anyone else for that matter. (You can rest to restore a healing spell if necessary).~ []
@1039298 = ~You haven't slept yet. You can access your Sleep button from either your Memorization screen, or your Inventory screen.~ [TTBRAN05]
@1039300 = ~Paladins also have the ability to Turn Undead. Activating this icon will cause many undead creatures to flee or even be destroyed. Evil-aligned clerics will dominate rather than terrify or destroy undead creatures, turning them from enemies into allies.~ []
@1039301 = ~When in this mode, the character can move wherever they wish. Any other action, such as attacking or casting a spell, will deactivate the ability.~ []
@1039302 = ~I am now going to teleport in a skeleton. Try to destroy it using my Turn Undead ability.~ []
@1039303 = ~You haven't destroyed the skeleton yet. What's wrong? My Turn Undead button is the skull on the bottom of your screen (if you have me selected.)~ [TTBRAN07]
@1039307 = ~Anyway, I'm supposed to teach you about how to use thief skills; but only after I join your party.~ []
@1039310 = ~Once you've selected the Thieving button, Left-Click on the person whose pocket you want to pick.~ []
@1039312 = ~You haven't got the gem yet. What's taking you so long? To use this ability you must press the Thieving button on the bottom of the screen. Once you've selected the Thieving button, Left-Click on the person you want to Pick Pocket.~ [TTIMOE92]
@1039313 = ~Very good! Now I'm going to teach you how to Detect and Disarm traps.~ [TTIMOE93]
@1039317 = ~When in this mode, the character can move wherever they wish. Any other action, such as attacking or casting a spell, will deactivate the ability.~ []
@1039320 = ~What's taking you so long to Disarm the trap? Hurry up! Remember, to Disarm a trap, you must press the Thieving button. You must then Left-Click on the red highlighted trap. ~ [TTIMOE94]
@1039321 = ~Good job! You should also know that when you're in Detect Traps mode, you'll also be able to detect Secret Doors AND Illusions.~ [TTIMOE95]
@1039322 = ~The next ability you need to learn is the ability to Pick Locks. To pick a lock you must select the Thieving button and then Left-Click on whatever locked container you want to open.~ []
@1039324 = ~What's taking you so long? To Pick a Lock you must select the Thieving button and then Left-Click on whatever locked container you want to open.~ [TTIMOE96]
@1039327 = ~You will notice that at the bottom of the screen is a Stealth button. Simply press the button and your character will attempt to 'go into shadows.'~ []
@1039328 = ~When in this mode, the character can move wherever they wish. Any other action, such as attacking or casting a spell, will deactivate the ability.~ []
@1039334 = ~You've been doing very well. Now I'm going to introduce you to two more party members:  Minsc and Jaheira.~ [TTBELT18]
@1039339 = ~Ummm... yes Minsc, I forgot Boo. Okay then, Minsc, BOO and I are going to join your party and tell you about your remaining skills.~ []
@1039341 = ~You will notice that there is a Special Abilities button on the bottom right of your screen. If you press this, the selected character's special skills will come up.~ [JAHEIRG3]
@1039343 = ~The Bard also has an extra ability, but you do not have to access the special abilities to use it.~ []
@1039345 = ~Bards can inspire their comrades in combat by use of the Battle Song. They are able to move when singing but any other action will end the song.~ []
@1039346 = ~Why don't you take a few moments to experiment with our abilities.~ []
@1039354 = ~I've... heard rumors about the owner of this place, before, but I never thought that the truth went to this extent. This place... is repulsive. We must do something!~ []
@1039358 = ~Aye... and naturally he shall not put the profits of the inn into depraved entertainments similar to the current ones. Aye, surely we can believe a filthy barbarian.~ []
@1039366 = ~Take on the slavers themselves? On their home ground? I don't know... do it if you must, <CHARNAME>, but don't think it will be easy.~ []
@1039367 = ~The man's not simply going to confess his crimes. Perhaps there might be some way to get him to allow us access to the entertainments without seeming too... obvious.~ []
@1039371 = ~
As always <CHARNAME> I am here to serve you, if but only for a short time.~ []
@1039372 = ~A thoroughly despicable man... and an equally despicable place. This is the sort of thing that comes naturally with civilization, it seems.~ []
@1039373 = ~Hah! I would enjoy partaking, as he puts it. I have heard of th' pleasures to be found here... but ye seem nay the type for it, <CHARNAME>, being yellow and such.~ []
@1039374 = ~Oh! You... you are such a disgusting man!~ []
@1039375 = ~Your base appetite will be your downfall, dwarf. You have no honor, for one of your kind... I am surprised and dismayed.~ []
@1039378 = ~Isn't there always? My cousin Urnist... bad speller, by the way, always been the curse of that particular branch of the family... once owned a tavern that opened up into a pancake factory in the back. Best pancakes this side of the vales, too, and you wouldn't know it if you drank there. Mind you, after the Pancake Famine things were never quite the same at the factory again. I'll have to tell you about it, sometime.~ []
@1039380 = ~<CHARNAME>, my <PRO_LADYLORD>! You cannot be seriously considering such a depraved practice! You are... just looking for information... correct?~ []
@1039390 = ~Um... perhaps I had best be on my way. Please excuse me.~ []
@1039396 = ~I see. Perhaps you should reconsider where you are then... and remember not to bother other customers with your puerile attitude.~ []
@1039399 = ~N-no! No, he isn't! <CHARNAME> has more than enough company, and no need for your... your... filth!~ []
@1039406 = ~Well, nothing... unless you happen to be attempting to sneak through a dungeon filled with hobgoblins and you have a few dozen cats noisily following the smell of sour milk and meowing all the time. Tsk. Well, at least the smell prevented them from eating him. The hobgoblins, I mean, not the cats.~ []
@1039407 = ~Hmph. Well, the pay best be bloody well worth it, if I'm to be wandering through the wilderness, hacking away at bears and squirrels and other such beasties.~ []
@1039413 = ~You will not, Korgan. There is a disturbance in nature that we are to restore... I will not have you swinging about, heedless of the consequences.~ []
@1039417 = ~I almost hate to ask this... what, exactly, is wrong with milk baths?~ []
@1039421 = ~Oh, <CHARNAME>, is... is this really necessary? Can't you just ignore him?~ []
@1039432 = ~Hmmm... actually, dear woman, your husband is fondling another of your kind in the back rooms. A much younger member of your kind, rather...~ []
@1039436 = ~This ancient tome creaks as you open it. Each page of the Book of Infinite Spells contains a spell described in layman's terms, easy enough for a thief, a cleric or even a fighter to understand and cast. Each spell on a page can be cast once per day. A second function of the book is to turn to a different page of the book. This allows for the possibility of getting a better spell. However, once the page has been turned the previous spell is lost forever, unless it happens to appear again.

Be warned. Once you turn to the last page of the book, you are stuck with that spell.

The spell on this page is:

Stinking Cloud (Evocation) 
Level: 2
Range: 30 yards 
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 2 
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: Special 

When a Stinking Cloud is cast, the wizard creates a billowing mass of nauseous vapors up to 30 yards away from his or her position. Any creature caught within the cloud must roll a successful saving throw vs. poison or be sent reeling and fall down for 1-2 rounds. Those who make successful saving throws can leave the cloud without suffering any ill effects, although those remaining in the cloud must continue to save each round. A dispel magic will remove the nausea on a particular character, but if they remain in the cloud then they are still subject to its effects.~ []
@1039438 = ~This ancient tome creaks as you open it. Each page of the Book of Infinite Spells contains a spell described in layman's terms, easy enough for a thief, a cleric or even a fighter to understand and cast. Each spell on a page can be cast once per day. A second function of the book is to turn to a different page of the book. This allows for the possibility of getting a better spell. However, once the page has been turned the previous spell is lost forever, unless it happens to appear again.

This is the last page of the book.

The spell on this page is:

Burning Hands (Alteration) 
Level: 1
Range: 5 feet 
Duration: Instantaneous 
Casting Time: 1 
Area of Effect: 60 degree arc
Saving Throw: 1/2

When the wizard casts this spell, a jet of searing flame shoots from his or her fingertips. The wizard's hands must be held so as to send forth a fanlike sheet of flames: the thumbs must touch each other and the fingers must be spread. The burning hands send out flame jets five feet in length, in a horizontal arc of about 60 degrees. Any creature in the area of the flames suffers 1d3 hit points of damage, plus 2 points for each level of the spellcaster, to a maximum of 1d3 + 20 points of fire damage. Those successfully saving vs. spells receive half damage.~ []
@1039443 = ~Dwarven Thrower, War Hammer +3
This hammer -- not to be confused with the elven made Dwarf Thrower -- is only usable by dwarves. In the capable hands of a dwarven warrior, the hammer may be thrown at an opponent. The magic in the hammer draws it back to the hand of its wielder. If it hits an opponent, it does double the damage that a thrown hammer would normally do. Against giants and ogres the hammer does an additional +8 damage, due to the special hatred that dwarves hold for these races.

STATISTICS:

Combat Abilities: Returns to thrower
THAC0: +3 bonus
Damage: 2D4 + 3, +8 extra damage to giants and ogres
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 4
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 9 Strength
Not Usable By:
Non-dwarves
 Thief
 Kensai~ []
@1039444 = ~Hammer of Thunderbolts

A dwarven smith, Silverblade, forged this hammer and two other items: a girdle of giant strength and gauntlets of ogre power. His intention was to gift them to his son, who was then a high officer in the dwarven armies, fighting the giant and ogre tribes of the area. Unfortunately Silverblade's son died just after the completion of the three items, and before they could be gifted to him. In his grief Silverblade himself donned the girdle and the gauntlets. Taking up the Hammer of Thunderbolts, he went to battle against the giant folk, and died valiantly. 
Alone, the Hammer of Thunderbolts is a powerful magical weapon, but when merged with the gauntlets of ogre power and a girdle of giant strength the hammer is transformed. This transformation requires magical assistance. The Hammer of Thunderbolts is then capable of doing an additional +8 damage as well as instantly killing any golem, ettin or troll that it strikes.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +3 bonus
Damage: 2D4 + 3
Damage type: crushing
Weight: 4
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 18 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Mage 
 Thief
 Monk
 Beast Master~ []
@1039449 = ~Ilbratha, Short Sword +1

This ancient bronze sword is set with six matching bloodstones, and was apparently forged for Azoun the First, a long dead king of Cormyr. It saw little use, and eventually found its way to a favored of the king's guards. Despite the aid of its illusionary magic, that unnamed soldier fell in a later battle, and the sword was lost to brigands or scavengers.

