@1039770 = ~It is done... isn't it? But what is left for... My father, dead. My home, in shambles. Someone put these creatures up to this... but... but who...~ [NALIA78]
@1039771 = ~Aye, now... so you're the <MANWOMAN> whom Mistress Nalia has brought to help us, eh? Well, you've got your work cut out for you, sure enough.~ []
@1039786 = ~The trolls and those yuan-ti have shut the keep up tight. I'm hoping they will merely demand ransom for our Lord... but my hope has been quickly dwindling.~ []
@1039787 = ~If you can do as Mistress Nalia asks and rid the castle of the vermin, we'd be mighty grateful. As would Lord de'Arnise... if he still lives, within.~ []
@1039791 = ~Nalia has told you of the secret entrance, has she not? 'Tis to the north of the palisade, here, hidden in the wall of the keep behind some bushes.~ []
@1039792 = ~I should have told you previously, but others abandoned me when they found out. We are beset by trolls. The main assault began just a few nights ago.~ []
@1039793 = ~Lord de'Arnise knows of it... I've been watching to see if he escapes and uses it to flee. But I've not enough men, here, to attempt any kind of rescue.~ []
@1039804 = ~Hmph. So you be the vagabonds Mistress Nalia has brought to aid us. Hehhh... I suppose we cannot be choosy now. I hope the young lass knows you better than I.~ []
@1039807 = ~There's a way into the keep... where is it?~ []
@1039818 = ~Very well... but raising her from the dead isn't cheap.~ []
@1039822 = ~As you say, then. Had she told you of the way into the keep?  The secret entrance lies in the wall north of the palisade here, hidden behind some bushes.~ []
@1039823 = ~If you could do what you can, then do so... we would all appreciate such assistance. But return quickly, good <MANWOMAN>, for much is at stake.~ []
@1039826 = ~Then I shall complete these business with the keep... and raise her afterwards.~ []
@1039830 = ~ I will not see it used as such again. There is no excuse. How did they... Daleson, did you tell these beasts of the cellar?~ []
@1039831 = ~Despite her wishes, Nalia be betrothed to the Roenall family... a wealthy house renowned for their cruelty. I've no desire to work for such as them.~ []
@1039839 = ~If you've no wish to aid her, nor us, then begone... there be too much at stake here to deal further with the likes of you.~ []
@1039843 = ~I am relieved... perhaps the lass was right to go to you. Go, then... the secret entrance lies to the north of the palisade, here, hidden behind some bushes.~ []
@1039846 = ~You have not finished the task, as of yet, I see... is there something more that you need of me, good <MANWOMAN>?~ []
@1039851 = ~A terrible business, this, my lady Nalia. I... I did all I could to find your father. I hope he remains well, within.~ []
@1039854 = ~I am worried about your father, not regaining my post... but I hope you are correct. Take care within, Miss Nalia. Trolls can only be dispatched with fire or acid.~ []
@1039855 = ~It is... it is very sad that this has happened to your father. I... I shall serve wherever I am required, my Lady.~ []
@1039856 = ~You have destroyed the soldiers and performed your task... but with the Lady Nalia dead, you have only delivered us to the Roenall family who will take this keep.~ []
@1039857 = ~I... I hope that the Lord died well. And that he shall rest in peace with his daughter and wife at his side. Fare you well, good <MANWOMAN>.~ []
@1039860 = ~Very well... I will do so immediately.~ []
@1039862 = ~Forget it... I've done what I came here to do. You raise her.~ []
@1039864 = ~My Lord... betrothed her to the youngest of the Roenall family. The Mistress Nalia did not approve, but the betrothal exists, yet.~ []
@1039865 = ~If the Lady is not restored, the Roenall will use the betrothal to take the keep away. They are... a cruel family. I would not wish to serve under such people.~ []
@1039866 = ~Perhaps Lady Nalia has different ideas, I know not... but she will have to be raised for us to find out.~ []
@1039868 = ~Very well... I will go and do this now.~ []
@1039869 = ~Forget it... I've no need to involve myself in any more of this matter. Raise her yourself.~ []
@1039872 = ~Very well... I'll go and get her raised.~ []
@1039873 = ~Forget it... raise her yourself, I've other things to do, now.~ []
@1039874 = ~You've a heart of stone, then. I'll take her 'troublesome' body from you, then, and... somehow... we shall raise the money to restore her.~ []
@1039877 = ~You have my sincere thanks for all you have done. The Lady Nalia shall reward you suitably. It is... sad, however, that my poor Lord died during this attack.~ []
@1039879 = ~I can barely believe that we got out of the keep alive! So... so many of my fellow guardsmen were killed... slaughtered...~ []
@1039880 = ~The trolls were so strong! And more often than not, even after we would strike one down, they would get back up again! You... you have to use fire... or acid... to kill them once and for all...~ []
@1039881 = ~I cannot believe that the lord and his sister still live within... they must be dead, they must! And... perhaps that would be a mercy...~ []
@1039882 = ~Why have the trolls chosen to attack us? Why here? It makes no sense... what do they want?!~ []
@1039883 = ~We are grateful for all that you have done... you have destroyed the beasts that have murdered our Lord.~ []
@1039887 = ~I am <CHARNAME>... I have been hired by Nalia to clear out this keep of its invaders.~ []
@1039889 = ~I... I have remained to guard the Lady Delcia. We... we have been barricaded here for days!~ []
@1039890 = ~But I will listen to no more until I know... are you friend or foe?!~ []
@1039891 = ~I am a friend... I have been brought here by Nalia to save this keep.~ []
@1039893 = ~I'm not about to trust anyone I see in this castle... foe it is!~ []
@1039894 = ~Oh! Thank the gods! You... you cannot believe how relieved I am to see you, then. Not only have I been barricaded in here, fighting against trolls...~ []
@1039895 = ~(... but you cannot BELIEVE the audacity of this woman! The Lady Delcia is the Lord's sister... and she is a... a trial, to say the least! I have been tempted to strangle her myself more than a dozen times!...)~ []
@1039896 = ~... er... I suggest you speak to the Lady Delcia, further. She will decide what to do, I suppose. (... and it will be the first break I've had from her in days...)~ []
@1039898 = ~I will stay with the Lady Delcia, where she decides to go. This is my duty, and I can help you no more beyond this. (... despite what a pain in the behind the hag has turned out to be...)~ []
@1039899 = ~Hold! How did you -- Mistress Nalia! Is it... is it really you?!~ []
@1039900 = ~I barricaded us in here to protect your Aunt, my lady. I have fought few trolls... I think they are not interested in either of us. What they are doing, I cannot say.~ []
@1039901 = ~I will go where your Aunt goes. I have sworn to protect her, and I have maintained my oath thus far. It is... it is just...~ []
@1039902 = ~... well... yes...~ []
@1039904 = ~We are here to deal with the invaders, Hendron, and save whomever remains. I... am glad Auntie is still safe. Will you go to the palisade with her, Hendron?~ []
@1039908 = ~G-glaicus? Is that you? Oh, no, <CHARNAME>... he must be charmed! He's one of my father's most loyal guards, he would never do this otherwise!!~ []
@1039909 = ~(uhhh...)  Wh... what's going on? What's happening here?~ []
@1039913 = ~Yes... yes, I remember now. It was... it was horrible! Oh, thank you so much for freeing me from that enchantment!~ []
@1039914 = ~You... you must find the leader of the trolls... TorGal, I believe his name is. You must find him and kill him! If he falls, the rest of his minions will flee.~ []
@1039915 = ~I am afraid that I do not know where he is, though... or where Lord de'Arnise is, exactly. I... I wish I did. But I think I do know something that might help you...~ []
@1039917 = ~Lord de'Arnise was looking for a flail that belongs to him... it was disassembled long ago and the heads spread throughout the keep. I was helping him search when we were captured.~ []
@1039918 = ~He said it had powers of flame and acid and the like... things that would have aided us greatly against the trolls, had we found them in time. I... have the first of the heads with me, still... you may have it.~ []
@1039919 = ~I cannot thank you enough for releasing me. I... I would help you, more, but I simply cannot face them again. I... I wish you well...~ []
@1039921 = ~The troll leader is dead? That is... that is good. I must find Captain Arat... and see if anyone else is alive, here. P-please... excuse me...~ []
@1039923 = ~Accept? No, they could not do much. It is not uncommon for a fighting <PRO_MANWOMAN> to take possession of a keep once the lord of the manor is... is dead.~ []
@1039926 = ~This will benefit us both! You gain status while my home is maintained as befits my father. It is not uncommon to take over a keep when the lord is... is dead.~ []
@1039939 = ~So you obviously want me to assume the role. A marriage of convenience perhaps?~ []
@1039955 = ~Ring of Spell Turning
