@1041633 = ~You do not understand, my dear. I have watched centuries... ages... unfold. You are but a passing flame, soon extinguished... and one day just a name.~ []
@1041655 = ~Grow up, Ketrick! This is the theater... it never goes quite how you'd expect it to and you can NEVER prepare enough.~ []
@1041666 = ~Ahhhh! Patron, patron! <pant!>  I found you! <pant!>  Master Higgold... he says... come quick! Quick! It's... <pant!> ... some opening night emergency! <pant!>~ []
@1041680 = ~We open our play in the Turmish land, in the highest peaks of the Aphrunn, the nearest town away by weeks...~ []
@1041717 = ~I... ah, you... you are married, my master?!~ []
@1041731 = ~Little useless trinket enchantment.~ []
@1041733 = ~Stop it! We have to start somewhere. <CHARNAME>, if you would direct us in what our next assignment should be then we can begin.~ []
@1041740 = ~Stow it, Nara. I say we try our hand at making wands of death! ZeeOWWW!! That'll show 'em.~ []
@1041741 = ~Is that before or after you fix the hole you burned in Teos' roof?~ []
@1041754 = ~Or maybe a little basic levitation?~ []
@1041756 = ~QUIET DOWN! *ahem* I'm sorry Nara, but I think Larz is right.~ []
@1041763 = ~Thank you, <CHARNAME>, we won't bother you again.~ []
@1041768 = ~There's a little something I like to call 'The Wand of the Apprenti!'   When used it randomly shoots fire, ice, or lightning. Very nasty. Materials will cost 1,000 gold.~ []
@1041770 = ~Very good, though I would prefer something a little more practical still. A ring of Protection is a standard test in this discipline. It is... a little risky though. What say you, <CHARNAME>? It would cost 2,000 gold.~ []
@1041789 = ~Yes <PRO_SIRMAAM>, one Wand of the Apprenti coming right up. Simple, easy, and I really hope it works.~ []
@1041799 = ~What? Oh sure, it will do something. I think.~ []
@1041807 = ~Well, that was an interesting lesson.~ []
@1041814 = ~We completely kicked that wand's a...~ []
@1041815 = ~... and this one's for grandma, who said I'd never amount to anything more than a butterknife!!~ [SSWORD49]
@1041829 = ~Look, magic is dangerous! He knew it! You know it! I... I know it too. Let's... I'm sorry. There's nothing I can do.~ []
@1041844 = ~There is a Mislead scroll which will cost 250 gold in supplies, Abi Dalzim's Horrid Wilting at 1,000 gold, and Meteor Swarm at 2,500 gold. That is also the order of difficulty.~ []
@1041848 = ~Very well. We'll start working on the Mislead scroll.~ []
@1041854 = ~Yes, we'll be done before we know it. A few days I think.~ []
@1041855 = ~Yes, we'll be done before we know it. Another four days I think.~ []
@1041856 = ~We'll be okay. We've got to learn this stuff sooner or later. Four or five days from now and we'll be laughing about how hard we thought it was.~ []
@1041857 = ~We'll be okay. We've got to learn this stuff sooner or later. A few days from now and we'll be laughing about how hard we thought it was.~ []
@1041862 = ~This really makes me nervous, but if you want to be a powerful mage I guess you have to work with powerful magic.~ []
@1041864 = ~I hope this works. I know you'll put our efforts to good use.~ []
@1041868 = ~I love this. I feel like Elminster when the magic arcs through my hands. Sure they are numb for a few hours, but it's still great.~ []
@1041870 = ~We did pretty good, if I might say so.~ []
@1041872 = ~We did quite well!~ []
@1041874 = ~I'm afraid... I'm afraid that Nara...~ []
@1041882 = ~And I'm amazed at how we manage to stand ourselves, what with us being cowards.~ []
@1041884 = ~Quit making excuses. What it boils down to is that we stink.~ []
@1041887 = ~We made the spell. It worked. It all seemed good, and then a slip of the tongue... a twitch in a casting finger...~ []
@1041892 = ~Now comes serious enchantment. These items are powerful, and also potentially deadly if not constructed properly. They show the true benefits of magical infusion.~ []
@1041894 = ~The second is the Ring of Wizardry. Such rings are legendary in their usefulness. Usually only masters make them, but I would like to try. It will cost 3,000 gold to make.~ []
@1041895 = ~The third is... is from the advanced class. I borrowed a tome from a friend of mine who said no one has attempted it in years. It is armor for a mage. It is a Staff of Power, and will cost... 10,000 gold.~ []
@1041896 = ~There is risk in all of these, particularly the last one. I think they are doable, but the making will be difficult, almost assuredly deadly.~ []
@1041904 = ~Are you sure of this? I imagine this will not be viewed as a failure, but it is certainly an anticlimactic way to end an apprenticeship.~ []
@1041909 = ~Then the apprenticeship is over. I... I thank you for the opportunity to study under you.~ []
@1041910 = ~Yeah, I guess it was a fun time. I... aw shucks, I don't do goodbyes well.~ []
@1041911 = ~Farewell <CHARNAME>. I thank you for this. All of it.~ []
@1041913 = ~Then the Robe of the Apprenti is what it shall be. This may take another tenday to figure out, but I'm sure you will be pleased in the end.~ []
@1041918 = ~Ready to direct our lessons, <CHARNAME>? The choices available were the Wand of the Apprenti for 1,000, the Dagger of <CHARNAME> for 250, and the Ring of Protection for 2,000.~ []
@1041928 = ~There is Mislead which will cost 250 gold in supplies, Horrid Wilting at 1,000 gold, and Meteor Swarm at 2,500 gold. That is also the order of difficulty.~ []
@1041933 = ~Wait, wait! I must raise the gold for these things.~ []
@1041934 = ~Very well. Please, return before I regain my senses and decide these things are better left to archmagi.~ []
@1041935 = ~Well, <CHARNAME>? Are you able to supply the needed gold? 250 for the Robe of the Apprenti, 3,000 for the Ring of Wizardry, or... or 10,000 for the Staff of Power.~ []
@1041940 = ~Wait, wait! I must still raise the gold for these things.~ []
@1041948 = ~This tomb has been cracked open and anything of value has been removed. Looters have broken the fingers of the corpse, no doubt to take something it was holding.~ []
@1041950 = ~Amulet of Power
This amulet bears the signature enchantments of Conster Damon, an archmage that fell in the Year of the Dracorage (1018DR). The crispness of its etchings may have faded with fire and time, but it still echoes his famous defiant cries: "Your magic denied!"  "I will be heard!"  "Defeat comes swiftly!"  "Take nothing from me!"  It has seen much use, and changed hands many times through blood and battle.

STATISTICS

While Equipped:
 Magic Resistance: +5%
 Vocalize
 Decrease Spell Casting Speed by 1
 Immunity to Level Drain

Not Usable By:
 Thief
 Fighter
 Barbarian
 Monk~ []
@1041964 = ~This is a fine task for a final project. I certainly hope the ring functions properly.~ []
@1041965 = ~This is stretching our luck, even for me. I really don't even understand half of the conjuring I'm doing. Perhaps this was a mistake.~ []
@1041966 = ~I hope you enjoy the robe when it is done. I put much of myself into it. I hope it will be worth it.~ []
@1041972 = ~Nara and Larz are both dead, leaving me alone. Head of the class now, I guess... I... guess.~ []
@1041985 = ~At least their deaths have been for something. The Ring of Wizardry turned out wonderful. It cost... 3,000 gold... and two lives. I suppose that is a bargain.~ []
@1041986 = ~Their deaths... their deaths were for nothing. The ring fouled when I lost their voices from the incantations. 3,000 gold and... and two lives. Gone.~ []
@1041994 = ~I am sure you are, as will be their parents. I'm not sure what my superiors were expecting, though. I told them this was a bad idea.~ []
@1041997 = ~I will report the fates of these youths to the proper people, and you will see no more of me for a time.~ []
@1042013 = ~Well quit stalling and get her over here then.~ []
@1042015 = ~That was a single creature, and you say you have multiple ones? I think the enterprise will cost you... oh... 9,000 gold.~ []
@1042016 = ~9,000 gold! That is outrageous!~ []
@1042020 = ~Fine, I'll take it.~ []
@1042025 = ~A pleasure doing business with you. You are in that wondrously odd sphere, are you not? I'll have my friend come by there tomorrow.~ []
@1042068 = ~(sniff!)  I wish I could have been there... bloody sickness just... (sniff!) ... washed over me. It has to be the curse! (sniff!)  Oh, well... at least I'll get to play Velden, still.~ []
@1042075 = ~A pleasure, as always. Ahh, but such a waste to watch your blood drain to the sewers. Can you hear them? The rats are singing.~ []
@1042078 = ~Hello, <CHARNAME>, I heard you approach. Did you appreciate the performance? Was it to your liking? I should hope so. You will see it again in future.~ []
@1042120 = ~Sssssthhh... Mazzy... you left us here... no matter... join the delightful darknesss...

(The shadow chitters in a most disturbing manner)~ []
@1042124 = ~Ha! Excellent, my servant! Hahah! Our Lady Knight shall embrace the darkness and give the gift of flesh that I might keep my hold on this mortal plane.~ [SHADEL08]
@1042136 = ~Bravado, of course. Your kind grows tiresome and predictable yet you may be of some use to me.~ [SHADEL12]
@1042139 = ~Oh, but you shall, mortal. This body that I inhabit grows tired. You shall make an excellent replacement. Come my shades! Open the portal! This brash fool has some strength.~ [SHADEL13]
@1042160 = ~Oh, I would be glad to help you, truly I would... but we simply must help Uncle Quayle, first! We must!~ []
@1042206 = ~I know little of wizards except that they meddle in the affairs of others far too often. Aid me first in this cause, my friend, and I will then strive to aid you in yours. Let us be off.~ []
@1042212 = ~Where are the mirrors... the switches to pull to show where he is hidden... Khalid!~ [JAHEIRC5]
@1042217 = ~Looks like the fool finally got himself killed.~ []
@1042220 = ~I knew him not, but I mourn for your loss.~ []
@1042221 = ~Stranger! Nobody! I will not hear your words! Leave me!~ []
@1042224 = ~Imbecile! Affront to nature! What do you and your rodent know?! What can you know?!?!~ []
@1042226 = ~Khalid of my heart, let my love... my love guide the way...~ []
@1042237 = ~I regret that I do not know how they could be sent home, but if what you say is true they would be honored guests here.~ []
@1042238 = ~Have them come and I shall give them lodgings. There is always evil to strive against, even if they are not in their home plane. They can do their work here.~ []
@1042240 = ~I thank you, though they would rather go home.~ []
@1042255 = ~We are ready, of course. Our home beckons from beyond the walls of dimensions.~ []
@1042258 = ~And with that, we are gone.~ []
@1042266 = ~I see. You are suggesting that we make what lives we can within this paladins' order. Perhaps... perhaps we should.~ []
@1042269 = ~You there! You are <CHARNAME>, are you not? I have a message, a message from the Cowled Wizards.~ []
@1042276 = ~But, seeing as how they all survived, you are cordially invited to their graduation, which we will be holding right here.~ []
@1042277 = ~They are a small class, and renting a hall would be excessive. I hope you are dressed for it, you are the only guest. It starts in... oh, about 5 minutes.~ []
@1042278 = ~But, seeing as how at least some of them survived your tutelage, you are cordially invited to the graduation ceremony, which will be held right here.~ []
@1042284 = ~Wait, I need to know if you can help me send these Solamnic Knights home.~ []
@1042291 = ~And before you ask, no, I have no information about Imoen. I will ask again, because I know you will pester me.~ []
@1042304 = ~Well, that was certainly unpleasant. Sorry I... sorry I wasn't much help, but I... I... sprained a... casting finger. Heh heh...~ [TEOSXX07]
@1042308 = ~You are not the only one with enemies. The Cowled Wizards have many. Some are incredibly fanatical as well.~ []
@1042323 = ~That is unfortunate. Such an abrupt end to this long relationship. I will almost miss you. Almost. Farewell then.~ []
@1042325 = ~All right, I will help.~ []
@1042326 = ~You are now barred from entering the sphere. It's a little spell we've been working on. So sorry.~ []
@1042327 = ~Good and good. Here is the rune. Be careful; it will only work on Lord Argrim and it has a frightfully long casting time.~ []
@1042337 = ~Whatever, just do it. If he continues magic use will be grounds for torture and executions, not imprisonment. He is the greater of two evils.~ []
@1042346 = ~A noble cause that I shall be glad to help you with.~ []
@1042510 = ~So ends the Morning Ritual.~ []
@1042515 = ~Do not get presumptuous with me, <GIRLBOY>... you do not want to provoke the wrath of the Cowled Wizards. But I have heard a little of what you speak.~ []
@1042519 = ~Now... I have told you all I know. Do not bother any of my order further with your ignorant questions, for you shall learn no more than I have given you.~ []
@1042529 = ~Hail, good people, I welcome you to Trademeet. Mind not the worried stares of our citizens while you are here. Strangers are not easily trusted these days.~ []
@1042534 = ~Hail, I welcome you to Trademeet. I trust you will not earn the worried stares you have received so far?~ [CELOGA02]
@1042568 = ~Until recently we did not know where to place blame, but now the people have found a target. The last group attacked saw several figures directing the chaos.~ []
@1042575 = ~Hardly. Tensions have just made people quick to judge. If you had appeared a tenday ago you would have found your welcome colder still.~ []
@1042595 = ~I am anxious about this new group. It is rumored that it is led by a woman, but we know nothing of her, not even her name.~ []
@1042623 = ~So ends the Noontide Ritual.~ []
@1042628 = ~I will recite the Tenets of the Faith.~ []
@1042629 = ~I will recite the Tenets of the Faith.~ []
@1042668 = ~I should have crept quietly as the vine instead of blustering as the wind. On occasion I forget the subtleties that allow nature to progress.~ []
@1042688 = ~Very well, though I would have preferred to accompany you. Sometimes Nature needs her servants to act as one.~ []
@1042711 = ~No one is safe in Trademeet, many are panicking. They blame the druids, and no druid -- or any outsider-- is welcome within the town at the moment.~ []
@1042713 = ~Your ruin continues with the devastation of Garren Windspear in your name. Away goes his child from under your nose, and I wonder who shall bear the blame!~ []
@1042738 = ~I'm sure there is a reason... but it isn't anything we've done. Trademeet is a peaceful town where business is conducted fairly... blessed by Waukeen herself!~ []
@1042756 = ~I don't know what kind of reward the mayor is offering, but that's a possibility. The town would be grateful to be rid of this menace, that much I know.~ []
@1042763 = ~You seek Imoen, your lost comrade. I am prepared to give you her location, and the means with which to reach her.~ [BODHIX30]
@1042773 = ~I know much and will share it. You do not know the full picture of the man, and I cannot blame you for your cautiousness.~ []
@1042777 = ~It is true that Irenicus was your captor, and indeed, your stay in his care was not the most comfortable, but there were circumstance that you are not aware of.~ []
@1042779 = ~Irenicus requested a service of the Shadow Thieves, for which they demanded your capture as payment. You are of great interest to them, as you probably know.~ []
@1042788 = ~I will get to that in a moment. While you were in Jon's... 'care' he discovered the potential you have, and resolved to aid your development.~ []
@1042794 = ~Trademeet is a peaceful town... we haven't even had the Sythillisian Empire to worry about, yet. And yet we are attacked by wild animals... it is almost beyond belief!~ []
@1042817 = ~But I do! I do! Listen to me... it won't stop with the animals. Soon, the floods will come... an' the storms! Trademeet will be washed away, you'll see.~ []
@1042831 = ~So you would betray your 'brother' even as you rescue him? He deserves worse.~ []
@1042834 = ~What was the nature of the fight with the Shadow Thieves?~ []
@1042838 = ~That I cannot tell. Likely they wished to observe or interrogate. Either way, they wished you alive. That has probably changed with your recent actions, however.~ []
@1042840 = ~They're jus' waitin' for the big genie to come an' kill us all. The gods are angry. If not the genies, it'll be them Sythillisian ogres. One or the other.~ []
@1042842 = ~You ask too much of me. I have already paid a large amount of gold for your help.~ []
@1042845 = ~Sythillisian ogres?~ []
@1042847 = ~You don't know about th' genies holdin' all o' Trademeet hostage? They owns everythin'... gold, supplies, food. An' they won't give none of it up.~ []
@1042851 = ~Just outside o' Riatavin... thousands of monsters, all under a bunch o' ogres. Taken over half of Amn. Just let 'em all in to deal with the genies, I says.~ []
@1042854 = ~It will not interfere. You will reach Irenicus and Imoen with ease, for they are both in the same place; a horrible place designed to hold the strong-willed.~ []
@1042858 = ~What was the nature of the fight with the Shadow Thieves?~ []
@1042859 = ~You ask too much of me. I have already paid a large amount of gold for your help.~ []
@1042864 = ~So you would betray your 'brother' even as you rescue him? He deserves worse.~ []
@1042866 = ~What was the nature of the fight with the Shadow Thieves?~ []
@1042867 = ~You ask too much of me. I have already paid a large amount of gold for your help.~ []
@1042869 = ~So you would betray your 'brother' even as you rescue him? He deserves worse.~ []
@1042871 = ~What was the nature of the fight with the Shadow Thieves?~ []
@1042874 = ~So you would betray your 'brother' even as you rescue him? He deserves worse.~ []
@1042875 = ~What was the nature of the fight with the Shadow Thieves?~ []
@1042876 = ~You ask too much of me. I have already paid a large amount of gold for your help.~ []
@1042881 = ~So you would betray your 'brother' even as you rescue him? He deserves worse.~ []
@1042883 = ~You ask too much of me. I have already paid a large amount of gold for your help.~ []
@1042888 = ~You! You're the ones that have been behind all o' the towns troubles! I knew you were nothing but trouble th' first time I laid eyes on you!~ []
@1042892 = ~Then it is a simple matter of retrieving Imoen from this place.~ []
@1042897 = ~The island it is located on is under its own rule, and even the Cowled Wizards are not certain what becomes of those sent there.~ []
@1042898 = ~It is considered a necessary evil, and like so many other evils, no one really wanted to deal with it once it began.~ []
@1042899 = ~I have used your gold to secure passage to the isle. You will have to contend with the asylum itself, and with the pirates that run the isle.~ []
@1042915 = ~Anyway, it is with great honor that I welcome our graduates to the... er... stage. Morul, Larz, Nara, you are mages today.~ []
@1042917 = ~Duh. We'd be dead.~ []
@1042918 = ~Oh shush. <CHARNAME>, we certainly appreciate this.~ []
@1042920 = ~But under the benevolent yoke of the Cowled Wizards you will be somewhat protected from arrest. Go forth into that brave new world, quietly and carefully.~ []
@1042925 = ~Hehe, oh those wacky kids. Celebrations all around!~ []
@1042930 = ~Oooh, that burns. Anyway, that's it for our ceremonies. Morul, you can now look forward to a long career under the benevolent yoke of the Cowled Wizards.~ []
@1042931 = ~Go softly and quietly into the real world, and I'm sure you will be mostly safe from arrest and persecution.~ []
@1042933 = ~Graduating class of 1369DR, we salute you.~ []
@1042935 = ~Oooh, that burns.~ []
@1042941 = ~She and the others involved in the disturbance were taken into custody, that much you know. They proved too unruly for simple incarceration.~ []
@1042942 = ~They are no longer in the city. I could get nothing further from my superiors, and I expect that asking for more would yield a harsh response.~ []
@1042947 = ~Hold, traveler. What is your business here in Athkatla?~ []
@1042950 = ~Now really, there is no cause for that.~ []
@1042970 = ~You'll pay you will, or yous get a face full of fist. That's pretty clear, isn't it?~ []
@1042976 = ~Fight! Kill him!~ []
@1042979 = ~I'm not doing a thing. It's amusing, so I'm going to watch.~ []
@1042985 = ~That's it? You're not going to help? What kind of people are you!~ []
@1042991 = ~So you're all bluff and no bite, eh? Get outta here, before I tie your toes in a knot!~ []
@1042993 = ~I knew that fool was all bluster and no muster, but thanks for your help all the same.~ []
@1043005 = ~Such things are not for you to know... yet. When the time comes you will know much, and if the Mistress bids it, you may also live.~ []
@1043008 = ~I know you not, but you are the enemy of those that would help me!~ []
@1043014 = ~No more so than you! Why did you attack Irenicus? His capture deprived me of my revenge!~ []
@1043021 = ~You have done well, and for that I am grateful. We had a deal, and I am certain you are eager to see it fulfilled.~ [ARAN18]
@1043033 = ~Your map has many notes and locations marked on it. If you ever get lost, using it is a sure way to get back on course.~ []
@1043037 = ~Try using different party formations to protect your weaker party members.~ []
@1043040 = ~You can turn down the feedback levels (circles under your character etc.) in the options page to suit your playing style.~ []
@1043052 = ~Like others of its type, this halberd consists of a cleaver-like axe blade mounted on a staff approximately six feet in length. It has also been bestowed with a small number of magical properties, thus making it more effective in combat. Its keen blade, for instance, will shear through your opponent's flesh to find bone, while its barbed tip will seek out gaps in their armor.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +1 bonus
Damage: 1D10 + 1, +1 fire damage
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 14
Speed Factor: 8
Proficiency Type: Halberd
Type: 2-handed
Not Usable By:
 Druid
 Cleric
 Mage
 Thief
 Monk
 Beast Master~ []
@1043055 = ~He must be found, and that is best facilitated by helping you find Imoen. They were taken to the same place, you see.~ []
@1043058 = ~Then it is a simple matter of retrieving Imoen from this place.~ []
@1043062 = ~The island it is located on is under its own rule, and even the Cowled Wizards are not certain what becomes of those sent there.~ []
@1043073 = ~ Nothing like some time ashore... all I needs is some grog an' a good lass on me lap.~ [MALSAL02]
@1043074 = ~We are not sure. Spies within the Cowled Wizards tell us that they have not had direct contact with the isle for some time.~ []
@1043095 = ~Mostly only happens at night though, and the city is so much more impressive during the day anyway.~ []
@1043103 = ~They don't scare me. Look at this bunch. Dead as they can get, and their black little hoods didn't help them one bit.~ []
@1043104 = ~What killed them was a lot more than you could handle. Look... look at the marks on them.~ []
@1043105 = ~If this is a guild war like they say, it's just going to get worse.~ []
@1043109 = ~At ease, soldier! I'll not have you running around accosting people on my watch!~ []
@1043114 = ~These people are not who we are looking for, I am certain. We'll cause panic if we accuse everyone. You! Have you seen anything suspicious or unnatural lately?~ []
@1043119 = ~There have been reports of fighting in the streets at night. Something to do with the supposed Shadow Thief guild and a rival.~ []
@1043134 = ~You should take this to the theater district. They would be a better audience.~ []
@1043141 = ~Join or die! You cannot flee! Watch the death... in front of me... in front of... me...~ []
@1043143 = ~Beware the streets at night, my children. There are strange things taking from the coffers of your lives. Best invest in the day to be certain of many returns.~ []
@1043153 = ~Very well, an in-depth response. Your fathers are my interest. Your lineage crosses the mortal and spiritual, and both concern me somewhat.~ [FIRKRA10]
@1043157 = ~He was also an adventurer in his day, and crossed my path long ago. Him and his Harper friends. I bear the scars of that meeting.~ [FIRKRA12]
@1043161 = ~I had toyed with forgetting the transgression, though it has not been that long in dragon terms. It was your other father that made me curious however.~ []
@1043172 = ~Here, rescue the child from my servant and feel fulfilled. Do not think it will be easy. I test my subjects thusly all the time, and they know that failure is death.~ []
@1043174 = ~Conster! Go to the child! If <CHARNAME> fails to take it from you, kill it.~ []
@1043178 = ~I thank you for this act of charity, disguised though it is.~ []
@1043180 = ~Do I know this? Do I really? Oh, very well. The brat was but a byproduct of my scrutiny of you anyway.~ []
@1043184 = ~What do you know of Irenicus!~ []
@1043188 = ~Now walk away, and see to your little rescue efforts. Take your time. Enjoy life. You have much to face.~ []
@1043189 = ~Do not think me soft because of this. I am capable of far more than you can imagine. Of course you are destined to experience worse.~ []
@1043195 = ~You return? Oh, why do you insist on bothering me? (sigh) You would think that the children of the gods would have something better to do.~ [FIRKRA15]
@1043202 = ~Alas, we must part ways. Until next time then.~ []
@1043208 = ~I wish you safe travels. I am hopeful you can prevail against the odds set before you.~ []
@1043212 = ~Normally we would have addressed this situation, but between the vanishing of Waukeen and the druid problems, we couldn't do anything. Now it is too late.~ []
@1043271 = ~I speak the words of the spirit, in the form that I must. If it does not prove plain enough, the listener must examine their faith.~ []
@1043348 = ~Either you pay their prices or ye has nothin', that's the way it be. Mayhap ye'll speak to Guildmistress Busya if ye wants to do somethin' about that.~ []
@1043350 = ~That said, I don't suppose there is much harm in stating plainly that walking the streets at night are a danger.~ []
@1043358 = ~Hungry wolves, we thought at first. A bear wandering too close to town. My brother-in-law was nearly mauled by a jaguar while traveling through the woods.~ []
@1043379 = ~We don't keep many prisoners here, but the ones we have are usually kept in the High Merchant's manor... until they're sent to Athkatla, that is.~ []
@1043407 = ~I hear they made a demand of the mayor, and they'll keep hold of our trade until the demand is met. You can go buy from them, but their prices are outlandish.~ []
@1043418 = ~What would Calimshite genies be doing here in Trademeet?~ []
@1043424 = ~Suffice it to say that we have come on a service, hunting a criminal of some repute from Calimshan... a rakshasi by the name of Ihtafeer.~ []
@1043425 = ~Rakshasa, of which the rakshasi are females, if you have never encountered them, are devious shapeshifters and thieves. We have followed this particular prey for quite some months now, and she has eluded us at every turn.~ []
@1043427 = ~We Dao buy all that comes here, you see, and charge prices too high for the mortals to afford... and we will not relinquish it until the mortals find this rakshasi for us.~ []
@1043453 = ~Indeed we are! The Dao grew tired of chasing this little rakshasi... one does not always have to do things the difficult way, after all.~ []
@1043459 = ~Hmmmn. I would say, mortal, that I wish the head of this rakshasi returned to me... and once that was done, despite the amusements we have found here, the Dao would return to Calimshan.~ []
@1043471 = ~Very well. I will attempt to find this rakshasa and bring her head back to you... if that means you will leave Trademeet.~ []
@1043477 = ~Very well. I will attempt to find this rakshasa and bring her head back to you... if that means you will leave Trademeet.~ []
@1043480 = ~Ah, it is one of our wayfarers once again! Tell me, what can the Dao do for you this time, my friend?~ [TRGENI07]
@1043511 = ~Hmmm... this is promising news, mortal. Promising, indeed. But if you wish your reward, you must bring the head of the rakshasi to us. We shall await its delivery!~ []
@1043512 = ~Wondrous! Find the dreaded rakshasi, mortal... bring us her head and the Dao shall be pleased!~ []
@1043524 = ~You must be careful, mortal one! Ihtafeer is a ruhk, a knight of the rakshasa... she is a wondrous being of magic and may only be struck by the most powerful magic, herself! Cautious, cautious, little mortal!~ []
@1043525 = ~Oooh, poor mortal you are! Too timid to find the mighty rakshasi ruhk for us! It is a sad, sad thing to see you here.~ []
@1043526 = ~Oh, come now, mortal! It is only a ruhk rakshasi and her companions we seek! You are a strong and powerful being, yourself, are you not?~ []
@1043592 = ~So if you know where the ruhk lies, excellent! I suggest you go forth and retrieve her head for us, yes? We shall await your return!~ []
@1043606 = ~The genies are hoarding all the food! I... I went to them yesterday and they were charging four coppers for a loaf of bread! I'm soooo hungry...~ []
@1043627 = ~If only something could be done now about the founding families. The Lurraxols and the Alibakkars have been feuding for years... and yet the Council does nothing about it!~ []
@1043631 = ~Why, Mistress Bodhi, you speak of our relations as though they have been unkind to you. I sincerely hope that's not the case.~ [PPSAEM09]
@1043634 = ~Flasher Master Bruiser Mate
This is the ammunition for Jan's crossbow (the Flasher Master Bruiser). The skulls are filled with a special powder that does a little bit of damage and has a chance to stun an opponent (save vs. spells or be stunned for 2 rounds).

STATISTICS

Always considered to be of +1 enchantment when determining what they can hit.
Special Ability: Stun opponent for 2 rounds (save vs. spells at a -1 penalty to avoid effect)
THAC0: +1 bonus
Damage: 1D2 + 1~ []
@1043635 = ~Again I sense a hesitation in your voice, Mistress Bodhi, such that I must seriously consider reexamining the way in which I conduct myself.~ []
@1043653 = ~Of course, Mistress Bodhi, of course. <CHARNAME>, being inexperienced with the sea as you are, I suggest you pay careful heed to my words.~ []
@1043657 = ~Bodhi? Am I to be subservient to this foppish milksop?~ []
@1043660 = ~My family is one of the wealthiest in Athkatla... we have interests in the gold mines up north and the shipwrights here in the city. So I will thank you not to stand too close~ []
@1043661 = ~I don't suppose you're from one of the mercantile companies, are you? No... I didn't think so.~ []
@1043667 = ~Hmm... hmmn. Yes, you'll do. You... the pretty elf, there. I need a new mistress, and I think you'll do nicely.~ []
@1043673 = ~Er, of course. A stalwart captain is always prepared for any eventuality.~ []
@1043677 = ~I am not sure I approve of the tone of this discourse. Best that we direct our thoughts to the voyage ahead and set our sails. More shall be said on arrival.~ []
@1043680 = ~With a reminder that any loss of time due to attacks will be exacted off the end of the captain's life.~ []
@1043688 = ~Hear, hear!~ [TRCUT201]
@1043690 = ~Oh, yes... most excellent work, hero!~ [TRCUT301]
@1043700 = ~No doubt Lady Lilith has asked you to perform a service for her... I happen to need the same service done, so I ask that you come to see me in my home so that we may discuss it further.~ [TRCUTX04]
@1043703 = ~Be careful in your dealings with them, that's all I can say. I have here a reward that the town merchants have gathered for you. Don't forget to go and see the statues that have been conjured in your image. They're in the center of town at the fountain.~ [CELOGA18]
@1043714 = ~You are a hero who might enter that tomb and retrieve the circlet for me, if you are willing. In return, I will pay you 1,000 gold. What do you say, my <LADYLORD>?~ []
@1043720 = ~Excellent! Here is the key to the tomb... the fact that we possess it is yet more proof of our legitimacy. Use it to enter and obtain the mantle, and then return to me when you are done.~
@1043740 = ~What?! You are very rude, even for a commoner. Very well, if that is how you wish to be, I cannot stop you. If you change your mind, do come and speak to me again.~ []
@1043746 = ~All that has recently changed. An old tome belonging to my family states that there is proof; that proof can be found right here in Trademeet.~ []
@1043774 = ~I see. How you gained your vaunted reputation, then, is beyond my knowledge. But I can do nothing about it. If your courage changes, however, do come and see me again.~ []
@1043775 = ~Yes, Saemon Havarian, it was particularly wily of you to distract those other ships we saw in the distance. I take it that your signals in the night were some type of warning?~ []
@1043784 = ~Of... of course, Mistress Bodhi, it had merely slipped my mind for the moment.~ []
@1043786 = ~Find out how to safely breach the asylum and rescue your comrade, Imoen. I shall await the inevitable ruckus and meet you afterwards.~ []
@1043794 = ~How do you know of her? You do not seem like her usual lackeys.~ []
@1043827 = ~Mistress Bodhi is a delicious evil, one that I am better for having known. I merely mention her coldness to test your own thoughts.~ []
@1043833 = ~Enough of this for now, I must carry out my duties and see to your entrenchment within the town.~ []
@1043837 = ~Greetings again, <CHARNAME>. Lady Lilith and Lord Skarmaen are not annoying you overmuch, I hope? Again, I urge you to be cautious.~ []
@1043839 = ~Oh Light! Can it be? You come, <MANWOMAN> bearing the bones of the Child Prophetess Amuana! Her defilement is at an end.~ []
@1043854 = ~Oh Light! Can it be? You come, <MANWOMAN> bearing the bones of the Child Prophetess Amuana! Her defilement is at an end.~ []
@1043863 = ~I have a name about this town, that is not spoken in polite company. My presence would prove more hindrance than help.~ []
@1043873 = ~Ah! There you are. I see that you have weathered the storms of this place with reasonable pluck and health. It does me good to see you alive.~ [PPSAEM16]
@1043884 = ~Having trouble? Haha! I should've thought that those in Mistress Bodhi's employ would be more adept at caring for their own needs.~ [PPSAEM13]
@1043888 = ~I intend no other.~ []
@1043895 = ~There is a representative of the Cowled Wizards here as well. I know that he comes and goes whenever he pleases, so he must have a key or some such.~ []
@1043919 = ~Sime shall also advise you, <CHARNAME>. She is acquainted with a few of the inhabitants of the island.~ []
@1043928 = ~I do not trust this pirate, <CHARNAME>. His manner is that of a fool, but his behavior during the voyage betrays a cunning mind beneath.~ []
@1043929 = ~He has delivered us as promised. There are more important things to worry about.~ []
@1043932 = ~Agreed. Be prepared, this place is dangerous enough even without my suspicions of Saemon.~ []
@1043933 = ~We may need his ship for our return. No, just be on your guard. He is probably the least of our worries in this place.~ []
@1043940 = ~I knew he would prove treacherous. Our threats were sufficient to keep us safe while afloat, but there must be someone here that he fears even more.~ []
@1043945 = ~There are more important things to worry about right now, anyway. I must see that you are able to enter the asylum.~ []
@1043949 = ~The search has not gone well. I do not know how to get inside.~ []
@1043952 = ~I have a ward token that will unlock the gates.~ []
@1043956 = ~Always did have a mercenary's heart. I probably helped him cut it out. Nevertheless, here. Take this. It should be enough to pay him off.~ []
@1043962 = ~A loud gong sounds and you fear you may have failed in the task that the drow have given you.~ []
@1044012 = ~Saemon Havarian said I might find what I need here.~ []
@1044014 = ~'One' gets an appointment by being worthy of it! Ain't just anyone that can get in here! Gotta be referred here by someone he knows.~ []
@1044017 = ~And how much would this cost?~ []
@1044021 = ~But Saemon Havarian said I might find what I need here.~ []
@1044026 = ~What? Hey, sure, you bet. Usually people just go find someone to name-drop, but if you want to pay, go right in. Just made my wage for the season!~ []
@1044028 = ~Saemon? Saemon Havarian? Uh, all right, you can go in, if you really want to.~ []
@1044029 = ~You're okay by me, friend. Go where you want.~ []
@1044039 = ~The altar has been cleaned and inscribed by Mazzy. It now stands as a monument to her brave companions who gave their lives in an attempt to defeat the Shade Lord.~ []
@1044050 = ~All you need to know is that I wish to go there. I will pay for your help.~ []
@1044076 = ~Er, why is your friend pointing a hamster at me?~ []
@1044088 = ~Do you now? I am no student of the mind, but perhaps these are just your wishes to become more than you are?~ []
@1044100 = ~It is! It is!~ []
@1044109 = ~...<CHARNAME>? <CHARNAME>?~ []
@1044115 = ~Now settle down. Are you in control of yourself? Perhaps I can help you.~ []
@1044116 = ~Quit speaking in riddles you Cowled bastard! Where is Imoen?!~ []
@1044118 = ~Demand? No, no one demands except the warden. Demands...~ []
@1044119 = ~A moment? No, all the moments are together. All together and with another. I have no moments.~ []
@1044121 = ~Proceed to the recreation area. Enjoy your time out; you go back under key when night comes.~ []
@1044122 = ~What is this place?~ []
@1044125 = ~What is this place? Strange question coming from you. It was my understanding that you wanted to be confined here.~ []
@1044126 = ~But I suppose you ARE out of your mind, so I will explain. This is Spellhold, I am Lonk, you are an inmate, and this is recreation time. Frolic, if you please.~ []
@1044135 = ~And your job here?~ []
@1044145 = ~Imoen? I think so. Hard to say. There is a girl here that used to answer to that. Don't think she remembers it anymore.~ []
@1044147 = ~And your job here?~ []
@1044162 = ~Irenicus? How do you know that name? Hmm, no matter. You'll be seeing him soon enough. He sees everybody.~ []
@1044164 = ~And your job here?~ []
@1044168 = ~Try to stop pestering me. It's hard enough keeping an eye on all of these weaving robes of spellcasters.~ []
@1044169 = ~Oh, please try to stay away from Wanev. He's very excitable. Still sore about losing his position here. I tell him he shouldn't dwell on it, but he's quite inconsolable.~ []
@1044170 = ~Wh-who... who is that? Keep back. Keep back!~ [IMOEN63]
@1044172 = ~Stop fooling around, Imoen, I don't have time for it.~ []
@1044186 = ~Hello. You are new. Those your faces? Funny... ha! Maybe change them.~ [PPDILI02]
@1044193 = ~<GABBER>? Ok, I'll be <GABBER> tomorrow. I've seen you, so now I can take your face. Don't worry, you can keep it too.~ []
@1044194 = ~Nothing. Don't you change your face? That's okay, I'll take it and change it for you. Don't worry, you can keep it too. Who are you today?~ []
@1044197 = ~I like taking puppy's face, but it scares him. He's not here though.~ []
@1044200 = ~You are now beginning the tutorial for Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn. This is a simple walk-through of some of the basic skills you will need to play and enjoy the game. 

Once the tutorial area has loaded, an NPC (non-player character) will guide you through fighting monsters, casting spells, the use of thieving abilities, and some of the more common interactions you will experience in the game world. 

If you have played the original Baldur's Gate you may already be familiar with many of these functions, though the tutorial is still a convenient way to re-familiarize yourself with the interface in a safe environment.~ []
@1044201 = ~Stiletto of Demarchess +2
Most who take up the trade of murder for hire do so for reasons other than personal pleasure, but not so the Lady Demarche. She took special pleasure in the torture of her targets, which is why she made this dagger. With but one touch of its polished blade an opponent was rendered immobile, incapable of so much as screaming, yet the victim could watch and feel all that happened to them. While her opponent was thus held, the Lady would slowly bleed them, sometimes taking several hours before allowing her subject to succumb to the final agony of death. The Lady finally fell victim to her own evil; disarmed by a rival and struck by her own stiletto, her fate was soon sealed.

STATISTICS

Combat Ability: a 20% chance on each hit that the victim must save vs. death or be held for two rounds
THAC0: +2 bonus
Damage: 1D4 + 2
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 1
Speed Factor: 0 
Proficiency Type: Dagger
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 3 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Cleric
 Beast Master~ []
@1044206 = ~Shut up! No questions! Make an appointment! The Coordinator speaks to no one! No one... speaks the Coordinator...~ [ppwane08]
@1044207 = ~He rules all, he does! You?! You are but the left bunion of his wondrous idol! You be grateful for the chance!~ [PPTIAX02]
@1044210 = ~Oh great, I thought I was rid of this ridiculous gnome back in Baldur's Gate.~ []
@1044211 = ~The heavens move because he waves his hand! The waters stir as he twiddles his toes! The wind blows as he passes! And on a whim he can break them all!~ [PPTIAX08]
@1044216 = ~Er...~ [PPTIAX10]
@1044217 = ~... ah...~ [PPTIAX26]
@1044221 = ~You made inquiries in town. I have agents, and eyes. Security is quite important when dealing with an institution such as this.~ [IRENIC11]
@1044224 = ~Then release her to me.~ []
@1044226 = ~She was taken here against her will!~ []
@1044240 = ~At a remarkably young age she learned how to shape magical energy, allowing her to change her form as she wishes.~ [IRENIC16]
@1044241 = ~Have you a new face today? I think you do. I can see the real one. Tomorrow I will be you, okay?~ [PPDILI06]
@1044243 = ~This is Wanev. He used to be the Asylum Coordinator before I took the post. Too much exposure to magical forces, I suspect.~ [IRENIC18]
@1044244 = ~What?! What do you want?! Is this not enough? I want this hall cleaned! Don't you stare at me!~ [PPwane06]
@1044245 = ~His mind could not handle the energies that circulate this place. A bad reaction to a particular spell unhinged him quite dramatically.~ [IRENIC19]
@1044246 = ~No one foresaw it, but with study we can prevent it happening again. His career is over though.~ [IRENIC20]
@1044248 = ~I fear I have had an advantage over you. I have planned your coming from the start. It could be no other way.~ [IRENIC40]
@1044250 = ~But don't worry... you won't have to think about any of this or that. Your life ends today.~ [IRENIC42]
@1044251 = ~What are you doing, Irenicus?! What is all of this?~ []
@1044253 = ~Where is Imoen?! What have you done to her?!~ []
@1044282 = ~Well, it be fine an' well that ye've taken care o' the assault o' nature on this town... but I will nay be joinin' in the celebration. With them genies hoardin' the gold, me trade is a mite constricted, aye?~ []
@1044286 = ~Yes, I believe that you would. I can't blame you, really, not when I wish the death of others for similar reasons. A pity one of us must be denied.~ []
@1044288 = ~That is not for you to know. Suffice to say that I regret what must occur. I know the rage you will feel once I am done. I seek the death of others for similar reasons.~ []
@1044380 = ~What cheek! How dare a disgusting ruffian like yourself make advances on a noblewoman?! Oo!!~ []
@1044382 = ~There was this one time... (hic) ... my party and I were travelin' through the elven woods down in, uh, Tethyr. (hic)  We got drunk with a whole group o' elves... (hic)~ []
@1044383 = ~And... and... my party once fought a powerful lich! (hic)  Yup... boy, he was tough. (hic)  We ran like a flock o' frightened chickens, we did... (hic) ... no, wait, uh, we fought 'im! Yeah, we fought 'im!~ []
@1044385 = ~If I was younger... (hic) ... an' sober... (hic) ... I could kick yer butt...~ []
@1044386 = ~Heeeey, baby... (hic) ... y'know, I was a great adventurer once. Betcha I could give you aaaallll kinds of advice, yup. (hic)~ []
@1044388 = ~Lemme tell you about this time me an' my fellow adventurers... (hic) ... we decapitated an ogre, we did! Yup! We were mighty strong... (hic)~ []
@1044390 = ~Aaahhh... lemme alone... (hic)  ... can't a man drink in peace, aye? (hic)~ []
@1044394 = ~Trademeet will not be safe for long anyway, I think. You have heard of the Sythillisian Empire, yes? My cousin tells me we will be overrun by ogres and orcs within a month or so.~ []
@1044406 = ~I am Alenina, a minstrel from Tethyr. If you are traveling further south, you may wish to reconsider. I had difficulty passing the Sythillisian lines, myself, and now it would be even less likely to do so.~ []
@1044449 = ~Oh, dear... it's a stranger, my darling. Probably come to accost us or rob us or some dreadful thing...~ []
@1044488 = ~This Gorion of yours should have told you about yourselves early on. You might have learned not to fear what you are.~ []
@1044560 = ~Why turn to me? I won't help you.~ []
@1044574 = ~My name is none of your concern, but I may be hunting the same creature you speak of.~ []
@1044594 = ~A noble cause, but not easily accomplished. The Skin Dancer's lair is just north of the East Gate, in a walled-off section of town with an orange pavilion.~ []
@1044597 = ~I have found several clues. I suspect the creature's lair is just north of the East Gate, in a walled off section of town with an orange pavilion.~ []
@1044599 = ~If you are the skilled adventurers that everyone speaks of, I could certainly use your help. The Skin Dancer is a powerful foe.~ []
@1044615 = ~It is dead, as I said! Its... its body has crumbled... that is its nature...~ []
@1044620 = ~You assume you are a volunteer, but I don't need your co-operation. I will take the essence of you regardless.~ []
@1044621 = ~... Uhhh... wh-what? Tiris? Is that... is that you?~ []
@1044623 = ~I am done with her. You should be more concerned about yourself. There is a very good chance you are about to die.~ []
@1044634 = ~I used to have pretties piled high to the sky. Don't remember where they are though... mmm, pretties...~ [PPNALJ06]
@1044645 = ~All around... all around! Behind! Above! ALL AROUND!! Aaah!~ [PPAPHR06]
@1044648 = ~This is Tiax. Not too much is known about him. He was found raving on the side of some road.~ [IRENIC27]
@1044661 = ~She does not seem willing to respond right now. Her consciousness comes and goes. It is fortunate you arrived when you did.~ [IRENIC32]
@1044665 = ~Oh, you misunderstand. It is fortunate for *me* that you arrived when you did. I am quite through with her for the moment. It is you that I am after.~ [IRENIC33]
@1044670 = ~Typical. If I had a sense of humor left I might find that funny. I do not, on both accounts.~ []
@1044674 = ~You are intent on revenge or justice, or whatever. I care not. You can do nothing I do not wish.~ []
@1044675 = ~You will find you are powerless. I have taken precautions that you will not be damaged. Rage would be wasted.~ []
@1044676 = ~There is no battle; no heroics. Only sleep.~ []
@1044681 = ~How do we come to be anywhere? I asked that once. Looked all the way beyond the stars... pretty stars.~ []
@1044686 = ~They take my pretties... and the exams hurt. Questions about the far away... I don't want to go back far away.~ []
@1044694 = ~Everything... everyone! Across the planes! All the time! My eyes do not close when closed!~ []
@1044696 = ~And they are next to you, and me, and everyone! Always! More and more creatures from everywhere and everywhen!~ []
@1044701 = ~Harper's Call (Necromancy) 
Level: 5
Sphere: Necromantic 
Range: Sight of the caster
Duration: Permanent 
Casting Time: 1 round 
Area of Effect: 1 person 
Saving Throw: Special 

This spell is only available to Harpers. The Harper's Call restores a comrade to life, to further serve the cause of the Harpers. This spell functions similarly to Raise Dead, with the following exceptions: the Harper must transfer a small portion of her life essence (10 hit points) to successfully raise the deceased person; the target has but 1 hit point when raised and must regain the rest by natural healing or curative magic; and the raised person suffers a -5 penalty to all ability scores for one minute, making this spell virtually useless in combat.~ []
@1044716 = ~D-death? I suppose it is better than living like this... Oooh, the evil... it's building in me! The urges! Aaah, y-your flesh! I must have your flesh!!~ []
@1044717 = ~Ring of Acuity:
The origins of this ring are unclear, and while its enchantments share similarities with historical examples of Rings of Wizardry, there is something strange in how it feels, either in the weight of the metal or in the aura it projects, and it does not function the same. It was likely found on some distant plane, and as such, its maker will remain a mystery to you.

STATISTICS:

Spells: Gives two extra second level spells, one extra third level spell and one extra fourth level spell

Only usable by:
 Mage~ []
@1044731 = ~Don't be afraid, <CHARNAME>. I suspect this will be mercifully quick.~ []
@1044732 = ~Do... not fight... to fight... is to lose... come to me... find me...~ [IMOEN83]
@1044733 = ~Imoen? Where are you?~ []
@1044734 = ~I do not trust you! This is another trick!~ []
@1044737 = ~Within... find me within. You cannot fight alone... you cannot. Find me within...~ [IMOEN84]
@1044776 = ~The witch in the grove, who sells potions an such... suddenly, she don't know me none! An' she never mentioned no kids, but suddenly she's got sons! Old bat.~ []
@1044791 = ~Little time... you cannot fight alone. To fight is to lose. Find me... within... find me within...~ [IMOEN85]
@1044792 = ~You cannot face this alone. Find me within... find me within...~ [IMOEN86]
@1044801 = ~Ahhhh... (hic!) ... now, I nay be recognizin' ye. Should I be? Are ye kin, mayhap, come t' take me home?~ []
@1044823 = ~So. (hic!)  Ye be the <GIRLBOY> who's replaced Merella, eh? Well, I be the town drunk, Travor... so if I wanders o'er to yer cabin at night fer a place t' sleep, ye won't skewer me, will ye? (hic!)~ []
@1044831 = ~Then you shall go back over territory you have already walked, the experience of the journey relived through loss.~ []
@1044833 = ~Then you shall become less clouded by facts, and be closer to the emotions of your soul.~ []
@1044837 = ~I... I can see you there. Wait... and we can win...~ [PPDRIM01]
@1044841 = ~Shhhh... before the shadows return to me. I have seen what is to come. One alone cannot fight...~ [PPDRIM02]
@1044842 = ~Together we must battle your instinct. Alone you would fall, whether you win or lose, but here, in my sight... we can defeat it...~ [PPDRIM03]
@1044848 = ~What do you want here?~ []
@1044850 = ~You may as well ask to live without blood, or deny you breathe air! I am of you and within you; I am what you should have been!~ [PPBHAA02]
@1044856 = ~I don't know what you faced while mired within the spell, but here in the world of the living my plans have gone just as I wished.~ []
@1044860 = ~I have drained you, drained you of the very thing that made you special. It is the worst of curses, and I should know.~ [IRENIC46]
@1044863 = ~I will not let you harm Imoen further. I will free us both.~ []
@1044865 = ~I have no doubt you would, but you are no longer a living threat. I have taken your very divinity, and drained you of your soul.~ [IRENIC48]
@1044872 = ~And so your life does come to an end. A pity. You have proven resilient beyond all expectation. It is appealing to me.~ [BODHIX34]
@1044874 = ~Appealing enough that you should allow me to live?~ []
@1044875 = ~You waste my time. I am not here for your amusement.~ []
@1044879 = ~Not quite so much as that, though I am quite willing to postpone your death for the sake of my own goals.~ []
@1044883 = ~I will not perform for you!~ []
@1044890 = ~It has been some time since I have given chase to a worthy foe. Enter the maze of this place and seek an exit. I give you time to run, after which I will come to feed.~ []
@1044891 = ~But you are not running solely for my benefit. I give you a reason as well, to make the hunt more desperate. You may yet foil Irenicus, though the chance is small.~ []
@1044895 = ~I am your instinct, yet you deny me! Fight me within your own mind! I should devour you! How do you stand?!~ [PPBHAA06]
@1044896 = ~I sense... your soul... it has taken form to guide from within! You are strange among your kin!~ [PPBHAA07]
@1044897 = ~But it... it is weak and will not help again! You are empty inside! There is nothing within... but the instinct!~ [PPBHAA08]
@1044920 = ~And what do you wish from me?~ []
@1044922 = ~Such hostility, and I wager it is well-earned. It is, however, misdirected. I do not wish to be your enemy here.~ []
@1044923 = ~I wish nothing from you, save the satisfaction that you succeed in your goal. The winds are changing, and I must heed their gentle push.~ []
@1044924 = ~Ahh, but a single moment of hesitation will not alter your course. I wish only that you heed my words, for they are worth the wait that you can spare.~ []
@1044930 = ~The inmates of this place are a resource to be tapped. Release them and their anger and frustrations will strike at Irenicus.~ []
@1044937 = ~This dagger was created for <CHARNAME> by <PRO_HISHER> apprentices.

STATISTICS:

THAC0: +1 bonus
Damage: 1D4 + 1
Damage type: piercing
Weight: 1
Speed Factor: 1 
Proficiency Type: Dagger
Type: 1-handed
Requires: 3 Strength
Not Usable By:
 Cleric
 Beast Master~ []
@1044943 = ~Iron Skins (Alteration)
Level: 5
Sphere: Elemental
Range: 0
Duration: 12 hours
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None 

Upon casting this powerful spell, an outer skin of iron will move up from the ground and completely cover the druid. This skin is magical, will not hinder the movements of the druid, and will protect the druid from physical attacks. For every 2 levels of the caster an additional skin is gained upon casting (a 10th level druid would receive 5 skins, while a 20th level druid would receive 10). Each skin the druid possesses will stop one attack (and be destroyed in the process). The skins will remain on the druid until dispelled, until all of the skins are destroyed from absorbing attacks, or until the spell duration expires.~ []
@1044946 = ~Nature's Beauty (Illusion/Phantasm)
Level: 7
Sphere: Elemental
Range: Caster
Duration: Instant 
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: Neg

When this spell is cast, the caster appears to undergo a remarkable transformation. The caster becomes the very ideal of beauty; for a male, this is usually a nymph, and for a female, the image varies. As with a nymph, anyone viewing the disguised caster must make a saving throw vs. spells with a +3 bonus or die of longing for the denied illusion. Even if the saving throw is successful, hapless viewers of the transformed druid are all instantly smitten with permanent blindness (until dispelled). The transformation is instantaneous and lasts only seconds, affecting all those near the caster (except for fellow party members).~ []
@1044952 = ~Mystra, the goddess of magic and a reputed friend of the Harpers.~ []
@1044989 = ~The mass of black evil forming the body of the engine golem seems weakened and looks ready to dissipate.~ []
@1045007 = ~Pixie Dust (Illusion/Phantasm)
Level: 5
Sphere: Combat
Range: 0
Duration: Special 
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None 

This spell creates a small handful of pixie dust that the caster can use to toss into the air. Anyone hit by the dust becomes invisible (the range of the dust is about 15 feet). Of course, the invisible creature is not magically silenced, and certain other conditions can render the creature detectable. Even allies cannot see the invisible creature or his gear, unless these allies can normally see invisible things or employ magic to do so. Items dropped or put down by the invisible creature become visible, items picked up disappear if tucked into the clothing or pouches worn by the creature. The spell remains in effect until it is magically broken or dispelled, until the wizard or recipient cancels it, until the recipient attacks any creature, or until 24 hours have passed. Thus the invisible being can walk around and cast defensive spells. However, if he attacks, he immediately becomes visible, although the invisibility enables him to attack first.~
@1044990 = ~I am not as distanced from the workings of the city as some nobles might be. I have heard the mutterings of our stableboy and his kin.~ []
@1045018 = ~This is a painting of one of a group of young adventurers from long ago, this one a ranger... all of whom were attempting to return to their homeland far away. Word has it they died horribly at the hand of the dragon, Tiamat.~ []
@1045037 = ~Now just you wait a moment! Do you know what would happen if you released these people all at once?~ []
@1045038 = ~There ain't but one 'key,' and you ain't getting it. Now get to your cell before I get angry. More tests for you if I get angry!~ []
@1045047 = ~Summon Insects (Conjuration/Summoning)
Level: 3
Sphere: Animal
Range: 30 yds.
Duration: 7 rounds
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Special

The summon insects spell attracts a cloud or swarm of normal insects to attack one enemy of the caster. This swarm gathers at a point chosen by the caster, within the spell's range, and attacks any single creature the caster points to.
The victim may make a saving throw vs. breath weapons (with a -4 penalty) to escape the swarm. Otherwise, the victim receives 1 point of damage every two seconds for the duration of the spell.
The victim fights with a -2 penalty to his attack roll and a +2 penalty to his Armor Class. The swarm will repeatedly bite the target, making it very difficult to cast spells (50% spell failure).~
@1045051 = ~Insect Plague (Conjuration/Summoning)
Level: 5
Sphere: Combat
Range: 120 yds.
Duration: 6 rounds
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Enemies within visual range
Saving Throw: Special

When this spell is cast by the priest, a horde of creeping, hopping, and flying insects gather and swarm. This swarm will jump first to the target, then to the nearest allies of the target, until six creatures have been affected. Spellcasting within the swarm is impossible (100% failure rate). Creatures in the insect plague, regardless of Armor Class, sustain 1 point of damage for every two seconds they remain within, due to the bites and stings of the insects. Invisibility is no protection. Due to the suffocating nature of the writhing insect swarm, each victim must make a saving vs. breath weapon or run away in fear for a round.~
@1045055 = ~Earthquake (Alteration)
Sphere: Elemental (Earth)
Level: 7
Range: 120 yds.
Duration: 3 tremors
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: Special

When this spell is cast by a priest, a local tremor of fairly high strength rips the ground. The shock is over in several rounds. The earthquake affects all creatures in its area of effect.

There are three tremors that are caused by the earthquake. The first tremor causes all creatures affected to suffer 6d6 points of damage (save vs. spell at a -6 penalty for half damage). Those who fail their saving throws fall to the ground for four rounds and drop their weapons.

The second tremor is less severe, causing 3d6 points of damage (save for half at a -2 penalty). Those failing the saving throw will also drop their weapons. The final tremor causes 2d6 damage (save for half) and if the saving throw is failed they will drop their weapons.

This spell will affect both enemies and friends of the caster, so care must be taken in its use. Finally, Earth Elementals dislike mere mortals toying with the land and there is a small chance that casting this spell will cause an earth elemental to appear. This elemental will attack the party.~
@1045058 = ~Symbol, Death (Conjuration,Summoning)
Level: 7
Sphere: Guardian
Range: 30 yards
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: 12-foot radius
Saving Throw: Neg.

Symbol, Death is a powerful enchantment that allows the caster to inscribe a symbol of power on the ground or any other surface. The symbol will remain there until someone comes too close, at which point it will explode, causing all those within the area of effect to to make a save vs. death or die. Creatures with more than 60 current hit points are immune to this effect.~ []
@1045059 = ~Symbol, Stun (Conjuration,Summoning)
Level: 7
Sphere: Guardian
Range: 30 yards
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: 12-foot radius
Saving Throw: Neg.

Symbol, Stun is a powerful enchantment that allows the priest to inscribe a symbol on the ground or any other surface. The symbol will remain there until someone comes too close, at which point it will explode, causing all those within the area to make a save vs. spells at a -4 penalty or be stunned for 2 rounds + 1 round for every 3 levels of the caster.~
@1045061 = ~You're looking to be difficult, aren't you? I can accommodate that. I don't watch over this place because I'm helpless.~ []
@1045064 = ~What would it be worth to get you to release them?~ []
@1045068 = ~All right, I'll go.~ []
@1045071 = ~This statue of Tyr towers over a private shrine, with de'Arnise ancestors mounted on the wall behind it.~ []
@1045073 = ~Then die at my hand instead of his!~ []
@1045077 = ~How about 2,000 gold. Is that worth it?~ []
@1045078 = ~10,000 gold will change your tune.~ []
@1045081 = ~You know, I really preferred Wanev as director. It was a shame what Irenicus did to him. I will help you, I think. You may do as you wish with the inmates. I'll be back when this mess is cleared up.~ []
@1045083 = ~2,000! That's... that's a fortune! I could get pretty far on that... yes sir... hmmm.~ []
@1045092 = ~10,000?! You *are* out of your mind. I have never even seen that much gold. Get back to your cell before I get mad.~ []
@1045093 = ~2,000 then! How about that?~ []
@1045094 = ~How about 10,000. A fortune!~ []
@1045095 = ~10,000 then! Think of it!~ []
@1045101 = ~All right, I'll go.~ []
@1045103 = ~Tonight I'm someone free? What face should I wear for this?~ [PPDILI09]
@1045107 = ~Is that the rule of all you survey, or beyond? W-w-what of those that walk inside, and around, and through? That stand where you stand now?~ [PPAPHR09]
@1045108 = ~None stand where Tiax stands, lest he walk atop them... mm-hmm.~ [PPTIAX14]
@1045112 = ~Hehehehehee... he did this... He did this! I will... uh... we must find him! He is the cause! He is the one that brings the tests!~ [ppwane10]
@1045116 = ~Irenicus? Oh... I took his face once. His punishment was...~ [PPDILI10]
@1045118 = ~No... to look at him is to see too far... I cannot look to him...~ [PPNALJ11]
@1045119 = ~He is cold through all the planes... none walk where he does, though they see him not!~ [PPAPHR11]
@1045126 = ~Down to the dogs! Bad dogs!~ [PPDRAD14]
@1045137 = ~Tiax will have the glory of the kill! He shall build his throne with the skulls of his enemies!~ [PPTIAX17]
@1045157 = ~It matters not! All will fall eventually!~ [PPTIAX18]
@1045170 = ~What is this? You have released all of my test subjects? How wonderfully mad of you. I did not expect this in the least, so dangerously risky it is.~ [IRENIC54]
@1045175 = ~Your fate has been sealed with the curse I transferred to you. I have the souls from both you and Imoen, and they have healed Bodhi and myself. You will die in our place, or worse.~ []
@1045177 = ~Hmph. You think you're trustworthy? We have enough problems here in Trademeet, even without those druids.~ []
@1045185 = ~Bodhi tells me you have exhibited a... transformation. With your will slowly fading perhaps the essence of Bhaal will rise to take you. That would be a sight, I am sure.~ []
@1045189 = ~Die! All of you! I have restored my soul and will work my revenge without your interference!~ [IRENIC55]
@1045191 = ~Damn you all, why do I fight over this place when my plans may be laid anywhere! I must start anew!~ [IRENIC56]
@1045203 = ~Some have, indeed, abandoned the Waukeenar faith for Lliira, Shaundakul and Tymora, thinking she will never return. But this town was founded by Waukeen... we cannot abandon her.~
@1045234 = ~The 5th level mage spell Breach can be used to remove combat protections (Stoneskin, etc) from a mage.~ []
@1045240 = ~Spells can be stored in a (Minor) Spell Trigger so that they may be used faster and without interruption during combat.~ []
@1045241 = ~The mage spell (Minor) Spell Turning can be used to reflect spells back on an enemy magic user or priest.~ []
@1045245 = ~The mage spell Limited Wish works much better if you have a high wisdom.~ []
@1045247 = ~The 3rd level priest spell Zone Of Sweet Air will remove all cloud area effect spells such as Stinking Cloud.~ []
@1045248 = ~Why would you encourage me so? You were in his service!~ []
@1045254 = ~So I will offer my service to you, in the hopes that we can benefit one another. I'm sure you can understand the motives of self-preservation.~ []
@1045258 = ~What could you possibly offer me?~ []
@1045282 = ~Step up, step up, and test your luck upon the wheel. A simple game with simple goals!~ []
@1045296 = ~Round and round the spire she goes, and where she stops, Tymora knows.~ []
@1045297 = ~Round and round the spire she goes, and where she stops, Tymora knows.~ []
@1045298 = ~Round and round the spire she goes, and where she stops, Tymora knows.~ []
@1045299 = ~Round and round the spire she goes, and where she stops, Tymora knows.~ []
@1045303 = ~The Lady giveth, and the Lady taketh away. No winner, step back.~ []
@1045306 = ~Sorry, my friend, but you and any you travel with are no longer allowed at the table. Someone wins too much and people start calling foul. No chances taken here.~ []
@1045307 = ~'Ey, step up. Don't be afraid of the table, my friends. Roll your luck and see what comes.~ []
@1045323 = ~The dice are high, the house is low! 1 gold has got you 2! These dice are charmed to win for sure!~ []
@1045339 = ~They were fightin', and we hoped they would split and go the straight an... uh... narrow. No luck though.~ []
@1045340 = ~Been on a spree o' crimes. They dedicated most o' what they've done to the person that got them back together.~ []
@1045341 = ~I'd like to give a kick to that person, I tell you. That... uh... ah, lost my thought. Better relax for a bit, I think...~ []
@1045347 = ~That will be fine if I stay. Let me see what else you've got first.~ []
@1045353 = ~If it's all the same to you, I'll pass on that offer for now.~ []
@1045358 = ~You'll fit right in then. We treat everyone equal in here, mostly because they are. The nobles stay in the city.~ []
@1045365 = ~That won't be me. I don't care at all.~ []
@1045368 = ~I don't care one whit whether you care about what I care... Why am I wasting my time on you? Goodbye.~ []
@1045376 = ~You don't know anything about it, and I suggest you keep it that way. We don't want to draw attention to this.~ []
@1045384 = ~Yeah... I guess.~ []
@1045389 = ~Yeah, I'd hate to have to hurt you or something.~ []
@1045400 = ~Not like they've been help so far. They've just had guards following us, making sure we don't do anything wrong.~ []
@1045410 = ~I know, I know, but are we ready to go it alone? I mean, your father has kept what we do quiet.~ []
@1045415 = ~Yeah. Yeah! The complete and total stranger is right!~ []
@1045419 = ~Thanks <CHARNAME>! We owe this all to you!~ []
@1045422 = ~Is it? Is that all that matters? Even if you do things that others don't approve of?~ []
@1045427 = ~You! You are <CHARNAME> aren't you! I warned you! I told you not to get involved!~ []
@1045439 = ~They certainly aren't shy about saying who got them back together. Your name is mud around here.~ []
@1045442 = ~The most important thing? You don't know them. You don't know their parents. How could you claim to know what was best?~ []
@1045449 = ~I didn't realize the evil you would cause. I have no choice but to end this now.~ []
@1045462 = ~You know, maybe I should give you some more advice. You should really split up.~ []
@1045463 = ~We haven't given a thought to that since we talked with you. We realized that we were the only ones that mattered.~ []
@1045464 = ~The only ones! And if we love each other it doesn't matter what we do.~ []
@1045465 = ~And if we want to go out in a blaze of glory, that's our business!~ []
@1045466 = ~But slandering my name is *my* business. I didn't think you would act like this!~ []
@1045480 = ~I've heard some nonsense about someone challenging them, but I don't put stock in it. The Shadow Thieves have as much power as the Cowled Wizards, you know...~ []
@1045520 = ~Good to see your person well and sound. As you can see, the way is clear and we are free. Now to the business at hand.~ [PPSAEM18]
@1045561 = ~I'm glad to see you, though our meeting is colored by the unfortunate events I must relate. I had hoped them settled, but... I am denied.~ [PPSAEM20]
@1045562 = ~I have no ship with which to offer passage. It has been scuttled in an act of the purest malice. Such villainy I am subjected to!~ [PPSAEM21]
@1045566 = ~But if anyone could be helpin' ye with that, it'd be the Shadow Thieves, themselves. They could pry the secrets from a dead roach, if ye're willin' to pay the price, heh...~ []
@1045584 = ~Then it is back to Spellhold and the magic portal to the Underdark.~ []
@1045605 = ~Back to the magic portal under Spellhold then.~ []
@1045618 = ~Ah! You return! I take it that you have reconsidered your foolish trek beneath the earth? I am still willing to transport you if you help me secure a ship.~ [PPSAEM22]
@1045637 = ~No, my mind is set.~ []
@1045647 = ~Very well, I will set out under cover of night and retrieve the horn.~ []
@1045664 = ~What are you doing here without the horn? The sea gates are steadfastly locked until it is blown.~ []
@1045679 = ~Then you likely can't buy me goods, either. So be it, me poor <MANWOMAN>... we can be talkin' once you've some coin in yer pocket.~ []
@1045691 = ~Ugh, speak not his name.~ []
@1045696 = ~Then go if you are so offended.~ []
@1045697 = ~I am not. I know where I stand.~ []
@1045700 = ~You will anyway. Ah... forgive me, I... I did not mean to offend.~ []
@1045704 = ~Then let us forget I brought it up.~ []
@1045706 = ~His guild be here in the Docks. But ye'll not be able to get in. Either ye meet with one who can arrange an introduction, or ye're lost.~ []
@1045715 = ~An' if ye're thinkin' of contacting this guild, I can't. Me friends say if they wish t' contact ye, someone will appear out o' the mist itself to talk to ye.~ []
@1045725 = ~ZzzZZzzz...~ []
@1045726 = ~(sigh) Message received... sleep then...~ []
@1045729 = ~Who... who is there?! Guards! To my aid! Intruders in my quarters!~ []
@1045751 = ~If there is someone standing against such a group, they must have something to aid them... perhaps powerful magic.~ []
@1045760 = ~They I wish you well, but I won't go with you. I'll stay here and try to complete my plan on my own.~ []
@1045763 = ~I've heard whispers of a thieves' war... I don't know how there could be another guild as powerful as the Shadow Thieves, but maybe it is so.~ []
@1045773 = ~Certainly not. It must be wondrously devious,  to hold those powerful sorcerers... unless the Cowled Wizards do not simply... ah... kill them.~ []
@1045776 = ~I've heard rumors of thieves running the Docks... do you know anything about that?~ []
@1045788 = ~This new guild ain't in it for the gold. They already GOT the gold. Must be in it for the power...~ []
@1045802 = ~You said something about having 'all' types of drinks... that isn't true, is it?~ []
@1045808 = ~You said something about having 'all' types of drinks... that isn't true, is it?~ []
@1045828 = ~Stand fast, I see lights approaching!~ []
@1045829 = ~Saemon Havarian!~ [DESHAR08]
@1045832 = ~Heh. You know, there's all sorts of nasty stories about what the Cowled Wizards do with the mages they imprison.~ []
@1045833 = ~But finding the Cowled Wizards themselves can be a feat, never mind finding their prisoners. They could be atop the Cloudpeaks for all anyone knows.~ []
@1045836 = ~But make no mistake: that other guild won't survive long. The Shadow Thieves aren't about to let themselves be kicked out of another city, not after Waterdeep.~ []
@1045843 = ~Blank stares all around! All right then, I alone get the spoils! You there! Hand over your loot or I split your skulls wide! 1,000 gold will do!~ []
@1045846 = ~All right, here's your damned gold.~ []
@1045850 = ~The answer would be no, and I now demand a yes or no answer from you! 1,000 gold or your lives! Will you pay?~ []
@1045866 = ~SORCERER: Sorcerers are practitioners of magic who were born with the innate ability to cast spells. It is thought that the blood of some powerful creature flows through their veins; perhaps they are the spawn of the gods themselves, or even dragons walking in humanoid form. Regardless, the Sorcerer's magic is intuitive rather than logical. They know fewer spells than wizards, and acquire spells more slowly, but they can cast spells more often and have no need to select and prepare spells ahead of time. Sorcerers cannot specialize in magic the way wizards do. Other than these differences, a Sorcerer is very similar to a wizard.
NOTE:  A sorcerer does NOT learn spells from scrolls, but instead chooses new spells with each level. A sorcerer's prime requisites are INTELLIGENCE and CHARISMA.~ []
@1045867 = ~MONK: Monks are warriors who pursue perfection through contemplation as well as action. They are versatile fighters, especially skilled in combat without weapons or armor. Though monks cannot cast spells, they have a unique magic of their own. They channel a subtle energy, called ki, which allows them to perform amazing feats. The monk's best known feat is their ability to stun an opponent with an unarmed blow.

Monks must be of Lawful alignments.

Advantages:
-  The monk can make 1 unarmed attack per round, and gains 1/2 an additional attack every 3 levels to a maximum of 4 attacks per round at level 18.
-  The damage inflicted by the monk's fists goes up as as the monk increases in levels:
Level 1-2:  1-6
Level 3-5:  1-8
Level 6-8:  1-10
Level 9-14:  1-12
Level 15+: 1-20
-  A monk's natural armor class gets better as the monk goes up in levels. Armor class starts off at 9, and then decreases by 1 for every 2 levels until level 21, then every 3 levels until 30, then every 5 levels until 40.
-  Stunning blow, once per day for every 4 levels. All attacks in the next 6 seconds force the victim to save or be stunned. NOTE:  this special ability automatically modifies a Monk's normal attack, no targeting needs to be done.
-  Monks have the Deflect Missiles ability. This gives them a -1 to their AC vs missiles for every 3 levels.
-  The monk gains a +2 to save vs spells
-  A monk starts off moving at +2 move, then +1 move every 5 levels.
-  5th level:  Immunity to all diseases, and cannot be Slowed or Hasted.
-  7th level:  Lay on Hands to heal 2 hit points per level
-  8th level:  -1 to speed factor
-  9th level:  +1 to all saves. Immune to charm. The monk's fist is considered a +1 weapon (+2 at 12th, +3 at 15th)
-  11th level:  Immune to poison
-  12th level:  Another -1 to speed factor.  Fists are considered +2 weapons. 
-  13th level:  Quivering palm spell once per day. This spell gives one hand attack. If an opponent is struck, the opponent must Save Vs. Death or die. NOTE:  this special ability automatically modifies a Monk's normal attack, no targeting needs to be done.
-  14th level:  The monk gains 3% innate magic resistance per level (starting a 42% at 14th level, and reaching a maximum of 78%)
-  15th level:  Fists are considered +3 weapons
-  20th level:  Immune to non-magical weapons

Disadvantages:
-  Cannot wear any armor
-  May not use the off-hand in combat, so may only use one-handed weapons available to the thief class, may not carry a shield, and may not dual-wield (use a second melee weapon.)~ []
@1045869 = ~BARBARIAN: A barbarian can be an excellent warrior. While not as disciplined or as skilled as a normal fighter, the barbarian can willingly be thrown into a berserker rage, becoming a tougher and stronger opponent.

Advantages:
-  Moves at 2 points faster than the normal character movement rate
-  Immunity to backstab
-  Can rage once per day per every 4 levels (starts at 1st level with one use). Rage gives +4 to constitution and strength for 5 rounds. Gives a 2 point armor class penalty and +2 to saves vs magic (for 5 rounds). Rage also gives immunity to all charm, hold, fear, maze, confusion and level drain spells.
-  At 11th level the barbarian gains 10% resistance to slashing, piercing, crushing and missile damage. He gains +5% to this every 4 levels thereafter.
-  The barbarian rolls d12 for hit points instead of a fighter's d10.

Disadvantages:
-  Cannot wear full plate or plate mail armors.
-  Cannot specialize in weapons past normal specialization (two proficiency points.)~ []
@1045882 = ~The Cowled Wizards keep their own counsel on that matter, I'm afraid. They keep their own prison, I imagine, but its location is kept a secret.~ []
@1045898 = ~Aw hell. Uh... I-I'll be below deck securing the... um... s-something, ah...~ [PPSAEM25]
@1045910 = ~You'll stand where you are, Havarian! You've gone too far this time!~ []
@1045912 = ~Your pretty words are wasted on me, cur, I have seen your like a dozen times over, and buried them all!~ []
@1045915 = ~Your mouth is no better! How else would he have got the gate horn if not by taking your company again?!~ []
@1045925 = ~<CHARNAME>! You have been invaluable in service to me!~ []
@1045927 = ~Stow it, Saemon. You have used me.~ []
@1045932 = ~It is yours. I give it to you without reservation or hesitation.~ []
@1045936 = ~Enjoy it as you will. Now, we are all but away. Gather what loot you can, for the sea will surely wash all bodies overboard once we hit open water.~ []
@1045951 = ~Search away, Captain! You'll not find any such object on me.~ []
@1046016 = ~Do not look so surprised. You must have expected to find me near your Imoen.~ [IRENIC36]
@1046019 = ~You are an afterthought. My concern is Imoen, not your imprisonment.~ []
@1046021 = ~Oh, but I'm not incarcerated here. No, I am the new coordinator, and you are in my care... once again.~ [IRENIC37]
@1046031 = ~You are intent on revenge or justice or whatever, but I don't really care. You can't do anything I don't wish you to.~ []
@1046032 = ~You will find you are powerless. I have taken precautions that you will not be damaged. Your rage is for naught.~ []
@1046033 = ~There is no battle; no heroics. Only sleep.~ []
@1046046 = ~What is this... thing... you're making?~ []
@1046047 = ~Er... Daar didn't send me, but I did talk to him. Why don't you give him a break?~ []
@1046105 = ~Ye've seen your last tea biscuit, dancy-boy.~ []
@1046106 = ~Culture will defeat you loutish brutes each and every time.~ []
@1046107 = ~Well sported, sir. I shall have Desharik apprised of the results.~ []
