@1046118 = ~And that also means, regrettably, that we can do nothing if we oppose their actions. And still the Council deludes itself into thinking the Cowled Wizards obey them.~ []
@1046124 = ~If you are thinking of dealing with either, don't. A number of bodies have turned up... recruits by either side. I am sure you don't want to end up like that.~ []
@1046154 = ~I also have it on authority of Isaea Roenall that Nalia was distraught after the death of her father, and that he has placed her under his care as a protective measure.~ []
@1046155 = ~I am afraid it is his word against yours, and no matter what you think Nalia has said of her motivations, Isaea is the more credible claimant.~ []
@1046158 = ~Remember that nothing is proven. Any number of factors could place his insignia there and not directly involve him. Whatever the truth is, we will be sure to expose it.~ []
@1046160 = ~Nalia, my dear, I must reiterate what a shame it is your father is no longer with us. He was a fine man, despite his eccentricities.~ []
@1046163 = ~Lord de'Arnise certain kept varied company. I recognize very few people, least of all yourself. If you would excuse me...~ []
@1046172 = ~That may well be, but today is not the time for such things. We are celebrating a life in this place, and all grievances should be put aside.~ []
@1046173 = ~I will try, Minister Adelain.~ []
@1046174 = ~Again, your father would have appreciated it. Wander and speak with the others, and talk of how you felt about him.~ []
@1046176 = ~Enjoy the company of others in the remembrance of Lord de'Arnise. He gave much to life while he lived.~ []
@1046177 = ~Welcome to this place for this somber occasion. Mingle and celebrate the life of Lord de'Arnise. He would have everyone speak as equals.~ []
@1046178 = ~Oh, Lord de'Arnise did fraternize with some... colorful company, I must say. Not what I would expect from a gentleman's funeral.~ []
@1046182 = ~Oh he has, has he? He talks far too much for my comfort, Miss Tandolan. If you would excuse me?~ []
@1046189 = ~My pleasure, my dear, though the honor to say such is mine. I hope I can aspire to gauge my integrity by comparison to your father's.~ []
@1046191 = ~I thank you, my dear. Now go, and don't let the dark cloud above this place seep into your heart.~ []
@1046193 = ~Would that Lord de'Arnise were here now. He always brightened a room with his antics.~ []
@1046194 = ~Damn ye for dyin', de'Arnise! Ye still owed me a keg and a hunt since me last visit. To your health, wherever you are!~ []
@1046202 = ~Then my work is done for the tenday. I will leave on this good note, before we start to crying and backslapping.~ []
@1046208 = ~You might also wish to pry into his personal records. They may reveal something of his fondness for gems.~ []
@1046210 = ~<CHARNAME>, I have reviewed this matter extensively.~ []
@1046213 = ~You believe the lies this ditch rat is spewing? Need I remind you how respected I am? I am Isaea Roenall.~ []
@1046217 = ~The matter is closed until further investigated! Nalia, you are free to go. Isaea, you are not to leave Athkatla.~ []
@1046219 = ~Don't whine, Isaea. It makes you seem even less of a man.~ []
@1046225 = ~I will try to be less of a burden on the group in future. I... I trust you still want my company in the party?~ []
@1046226 = ~Yes, join and we shall be on our way again.~ []
@1046234 = ~I did not tell you this... and I certainly did not say his records are in his home northwest of the main government building in the Government District.~ []
@1046237 = ~Then I have little choice but to forcefully show you the error of your ways. Nalia de'Arnise, I place you under arrest by order of the Amnish army.~ []
@1046238 = ~What?!?!~ []
@1046241 = ~I have every right. I am an officer in the army and a liaison to the nobility. It is my function to see that everyone is well in their proper station.~ []
@1046242 = ~You have demonstrated that you are under some strange influence, and I must act to protect you.~ []
@1046250 = ~Don't take it so hard; I am just better than you. Oh, feel free to lodge a complaint to the proper authority. That... would be me.~ [ISAEAX06]
@1046251 = ~There is no risk! It is a certainty! I am the word of law at this moment! You cannot touch me! This is my will and you will obey it!~ []
@1046252 = ~Mourners in search of the Lord de'Arnise ceremony? If you are, please enter the door behind me.~ []
@1046253 = ~Lord de'Arnise was quite important, and his service is to be held on the upper partition of the tombs.~ []
@1046254 = ~Do stand away from me, I find your presence here an insult as it is. Lord de'Arnise slummed around entirely too much, if you ask me.~ []
@1046256 = ~We searched for the three parts of the key to the door that leads to the horror that the Shade Lord commands.~ []
@1046261 = ~Lord Farthington Roenall~ []
@1046262 = ~Lord Farthington Roenall~ []
@1046272 = ~Isaea Roenall~ []
@1046278 = ~My apologies. Captain Feerlattiys performs well as protector of our Shark-Father's Temple, but has little experience with your kind.~ []
@1046293 = ~The most exalted King Ixilthetocal calls for the presence of the prophesied ones, now, but there is time for you to ask questions if you have the desire.~ []
@1046295 = ~This document contains a register of slaves recently sold to this outpost of Slave Lords located in the Temple District. It also bears a signature in wax, pressed by a signet ring. It is the greater crest of the family Roenall, along with the individualized markings of Isaea Roenall. This is damning evidence if it is to be believed.~ []
@1046299 = ~Your kind has many names for us, I believe. We are called the Sea Devils and our eel-kin the Anguiliians, although I believe the merman word is most prevalent: Sahuagin...~ []
@1046317 = ~Ah, yes, the prophecy. Sekolah visited the City-of-Caverns long ago... all raised their arms in rejoicing as the Great Shark's song filled our hearts.~ []
@1046320 = ~We... Sahuagin, as you call us... have watched and waited from our temples here in the City. The signs have come, surface <PRO_MANWOMAN>, and now you are here.~ []
@1046341 = ~And... and these... (heh heh heh!) ... these are the strange creatures from the surface? (heh heh!)  These are the ones you claim... the mighty Sekolah has promised us?~ [SAHKNG07]
@1046363 = ~(Heh heh heh!)~ []
@1046367 = ~This ring bears the greater crest of the family Roenall, along with the individualized markings of Isaea Roenall specifically.~ []
@1046372 = ~Of course the whole matter is not viewed as such by the guards, but it's an honorable trade amidst ourselves.~ []
@1046378 = ~Of course that Isaea is into other things too, but me and the boys don't go in for slavery and such.~ []
@1046379 = ~Me, I've never talked to that slaver contact Dirth. Hey, what do you suppose they pay to get the guard to look the other way?~ []
@1046381 = ~Must be thousands to overlook it. Wow, that's a lot. Anyway, I've never even talked to Dirth (hic) even though I spend hours in the Sea's Bounty. Ain't even far from here. Wanna drink?~ []
@1046383 = ~What does that scoundrel pay you to do?!~ []
@1046391 = ~Don't (hic) go getting mad and all. Never harmed a soul in my life. Relieved a few of their purses, but never harmed 'em.~ []
@1046395 = ~Hey, what? (hic) don't go getting mad! I never hurt a soul! Hon-(hic)-honest!~ []
@1046399 = ~You don't know if you have more worth than a sea crab? It's tempting to taste for myself. But then, a scrumptious <PRO_RACE> might come in handy...~ []
@1046417 = ~Sekolah demands perseverance, strength and self-reliance! But not stupidity... the priestesses shall heal you before you fight, surface <PRO_RACE>.~ []
@1046419 = ~So, then! Do you agree, my tasty <PRO_RACE>... or... (hee hee!) ... do you refuse?~ []
@1046429 = ~For now... (hee hee!) ... kill the surface <PRO_RACE>! Kill them all! I wish their hearts on my dinner platter!!~ []
@1046430 = ~Congratulations, my wondrous little <PRO_RACE>! You are, indeed, a mighty specimen... and the one sent to us by Sekolah, I might add.~ []
@1046440 = ~Ah. Now that that little dispute is over with, perhaps we can get down to real business, eh? (heh heh heh!)  Are you bitter, Thelokassyil?~ [SAHKNG08]
@1046442 = ~N-no, most exalted one. As... as long as the prophesied ones deal with the rebels, they will have served the purpose Sekolah intended...~ []
@1046453 = ~We should have the rebel and his army join us... in principle. The drow and the illithids take more each year. I've no wish to retreat to the depths...~ []
@1046479 = ~Hello there. I've been watching you since you entered... I suspect you may have need of my wares.~ []
@1046529 = ~Spell Cancelled: Cannot target spells on invisible or sanctuaried creatures.~ []
@1046530 = ~Peddler? Bah! I have no need of fools like yourself. Good day.~ []
@1046532 = ~And since I received signs from Sekolah that you were returning, I had three of the guards sacrificed promptly for good measure.~ []
@1046534 = ~There. Now I suppose you want to know how to get to the surface. Well... if you haven't found it already, I'll show you the way. Follow me.~ []
@1046557 = ~Oh, what do you know?! (sigh)  But the <PRO_RACE> IS the chosen of Sekolah, so it should know. Have the treacherous Senityili brought before me.~ []
@1046567 = ~That is most vicious of you, my little <PRO_RACE>. I like this side of you! But it is tiresome, too. Go hunt for the rebel, or I shall become annoyed.~ []
@1046574 = ~So... this is the only way back to your home. You seem to be in good with Sekolah, so you should do well against the Drow and Illithids and such. (hee hee!)~ []
@1046576 = ~You are not the one who was prophesied to save us. Indeed, you have destroyed us! The Prince and the exiles were our last chance to keep our bloodline strong!~ []
@1046580 = ~You are not the one who was prophesied to save us. Indeed, you have destroyed us! The Prince and the exiles were our last chance to keep our bloodline strong!~ []
@1046594 = ~Our numbers are too few, our blood too thin. We must regain what we have lost. Prince Villynaty, the exiles' leader outside the city, is our only hope.~ []
@1046610 = ~You are not of our race... you owe him no allegiance. You have seen Ixilthetocal's state of mind... he may decide to kill you in the end anyway.~ []
